4851 with a forward reference.
4852 If its type defines a new named structure or union
4853 or defines an enum, it is valid but we need not do anything here.
4854 Otherwise, it is an error.
4855
4856 C++: may have to grok the declspecs to learn about static,
4857 complain for anonymous unions.
4858
4859 Returns the TYPE declared -- or NULL_TREE if none. */
4860
4861tree
4862shadow_tag (cp_decl_specifier_seq *declspecs)
4863{
4864 tree t = check_tag_decl (declspecs,
4865 /*explicit_type_instantiation_p=*/false);
4866
4867 if (!t)
4868 return NULL_TREE;
4869
4870 if (maybe_process_partial_specialization (t) == error_mark_node)
4871 return NULL_TREE;
4872
4873 /* This is where the variables in an anonymous union are
4874 declared. An anonymous union declaration looks like:
4875 union { ... } ;
4876 because there is no declarator after the union, the parser
4877 sends that declaration here. */
4878 if (ANON_AGGR_TYPE_P (t))
4879 {
4880 fixup_anonymous_aggr (t);
4881
4882 if (TYPE_FIELDS (t))
4883 {
4884 tree decl = grokdeclarator (/*declarator=*/NULL,
4885 declspecs, NORMAL, 0, NULL);
4886 finish_anon_union (decl);
4887 }
4888 }
4889
4890 return t;
4891}
4892
4893/* Decode a "typename", such as "int **", returning a ..._TYPE node. */
4894
4895tree
4896groktypename (cp_decl_specifier_seq *type_specifiers,
4897 const cp_declarator *declarator,
4898 bool is_template_arg)
4899{
4900 tree attrs;
4901 tree type;
4902 enum decl_context context
4903 = is_template_arg ? TEMPLATE_TYPE_ARG : TYPENAME;
4904 attrs = type_specifiers->attributes;
4905 type_specifiers->attributes = NULL_TREE;
4906 type = grokdeclarator (declarator, type_specifiers, context, 0, &attrs);
4907 if (attrs && type != error_mark_node)
4908 {
4909 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
4910 warning (OPT_Wattributes, "ignoring attributes applied to class type %qT "
4911 "outside of definition", type);
4912 else if (MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
4913 /* A template type parameter or other dependent type. */
4914 warning (OPT_Wattributes, "ignoring attributes applied to dependent "
4915 "type %qT without an associated declaration", type);
4916 else
4917 cplus_decl_attributes (&type, attrs, 0);
4918 }
4919 return type;
4920}
4921
4922/* Process a DECLARATOR for a function-scope variable declaration,
4923 namespace-scope variable declaration, or function declaration.
4924 (Function definitions go through start_function; class member
4925 declarations appearing in the body of the class go through
4926 grokfield.) The DECL corresponding to the DECLARATOR is returned.
4927 If an error occurs, the error_mark_node is returned instead.
4928
4929 DECLSPECS are the decl-specifiers for the declaration. INITIALIZED is
4930 SD_INITIALIZED if an explicit initializer is present, or SD_DEFAULTED
4931 for an explicitly defaulted function, or SD_DELETED for an explicitly
4932 deleted function, but 0 (SD_UNINITIALIZED) if this is a variable
4933 implicitly initialized via a default constructor. ATTRIBUTES and
4934 PREFIX_ATTRIBUTES are GNU attributes associated with this declaration.
4935
4936 The scope represented by the context of the returned DECL is pushed
4937 (if it is not the global namespace) and is assigned to
4938 *PUSHED_SCOPE_P. The caller is then responsible for calling
4939 pop_scope on *PUSHED_SCOPE_P if it is set. */
4940
4941tree
4942start_decl (const cp_declarator *declarator,
4943 cp_decl_specifier_seq *declspecs,
4944 int initialized,
4945 tree attributes,
4946 tree prefix_attributes,
4947 tree *pushed_scope_p)
4948{
4949 tree decl;
4950 tree context;
4951 bool was_public;
4952 int flags;
4953 bool alias;
4954
4955 *pushed_scope_p = NULL_TREE;
4956
4957 /* An object declared as __attribute__((deprecated)) suppresses
4958 warnings of uses of other deprecated items. */
4959 if (lookup_attribute ("deprecated", attributes))
4960 deprecated_state = DEPRECATED_SUPPRESS;
4961
4962 attributes = chainon (attributes, prefix_attributes);
4963
4964 decl = grokdeclarator (declarator, declspecs, NORMAL, initialized,
4965 &attributes);
4966
4967 deprecated_state = DEPRECATED_NORMAL;
4968
4969 if (decl == NULL_TREE || VOID_TYPE_P (decl)
4970 || decl == error_mark_node)
4971 return error_mark_node;
4972
4973 context = CP_DECL_CONTEXT (decl);
4974 if (context != global_namespace)
4975 *pushed_scope_p = push_scope (context);
4976
4977 /* Is it valid for this decl to have an initializer at all?
4978 If not, set INITIALIZED to zero, which will indirectly
4979 tell `cp_finish_decl' to ignore the initializer once it is parsed. */
4980 if (initialized
4981 && TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL)
4982 {
4983 error ("typedef %qD is initialized (use decltype instead)", decl);
4984 return error_mark_node;
4985 }
4986
4987 if (initialized)
4988 {
4989 if (! toplevel_bindings_p ()
4990 && DECL_EXTERNAL (decl))
4991 warning (0, "declaration of %q#D has %<extern%> and is initialized",
4992 decl);
4993 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 0;
4994 if (toplevel_bindings_p ())
4995 TREE_STATIC (decl) = 1;
4996 }
4997 alias = lookup_attribute ("alias", DECL_ATTRIBUTES (decl)) != 0;
4998
4999 if (alias && TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
5000 record_key_method_defined (decl);
5001
5002 /* If this is a typedef that names the class for linkage purposes
5003 (7.1.3p8), apply any attributes directly to the type. */
5004 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL
5005 && OVERLOAD_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (decl))
5006 && decl == TYPE_NAME (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (decl))))
5007 flags = ATTR_FLAG_TYPE_IN_PLACE;
5008 else
5009 flags = 0;
5010
5011 /* Set attributes here so if duplicate decl, will have proper attributes. */
5012 cplus_decl_attributes (&decl, attributes, flags);
5013
5014 /* Dllimported symbols cannot be defined. Static data members (which
5015 can be initialized in-class and dllimported) go through grokfield,
5016 not here, so we don't need to exclude those decls when checking for
5017 a definition. */
5018 if (initialized && DECL_DLLIMPORT_P (decl))
5019 {
5020 error ("definition of %q#D is marked %<dllimport%>", decl);
5021 DECL_DLLIMPORT_P (decl) = 0;
5022 }
5023
5024 /* If #pragma weak was used, mark the decl weak now. */
5025 if (!processing_template_decl && !DECL_DECOMPOSITION_P (decl))
5026 maybe_apply_pragma_weak (decl);
5027
5028 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
5029 && DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl)
5030 && DECL_UNINLINABLE (decl)
5031 && lookup_attribute ("noinline", DECL_ATTRIBUTES (decl)))
5032 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), 0,
5033 "inline function %qD given attribute noinline", decl);
5034
5035 if (TYPE_P (context) && COMPLETE_TYPE_P (complete_type (context)))
5036 {
5037 bool this_tmpl = (processing_template_decl
5038 > template_class_depth (context));
5039 if (VAR_P (decl))
5040 {
5041 tree field = lookup_field (context, DECL_NAME (decl), 0, false);
5042 if (field == NULL_TREE
5043 || !(VAR_P (field) || variable_template_p (field)))
5044 error ("%q+#D is not a static data member of %q#T", decl, context);
5045 else if (variable_template_p (field)
5046 && (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl)
5047 && DECL_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION (decl)))
5048 /* OK, specialization was already checked. */;
5049 else if (variable_template_p (field) && !this_tmpl)
5050 {
5051 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
5052 "non-member-template declaration of %qD", decl);
5053 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (field), "does not match "
5054 "member template declaration here");
5055 return error_mark_node;
5056 }
5057 else
5058 {
5059 if (variable_template_p (field))
5060 field = DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (field);
5061
5062 if (DECL_CONTEXT (field) != context)
5063 {
5064 if (!same_type_p (DECL_CONTEXT (field), context))
5065 permerror (input_location, "ISO C++ does not permit %<%T::%D%> "
5066 "to be defined as %<%T::%D%>",
5067 DECL_CONTEXT (field), DECL_NAME (decl),
5068 context, DECL_NAME (decl));
5069 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = DECL_CONTEXT (field);
5070 }
5071 /* Static data member are tricky; an in-class initialization
5072 still doesn't provide a definition, so the in-class
5073 declaration will have DECL_EXTERNAL set, but will have an
5074 initialization. Thus, duplicate_decls won't warn
5075 about this situation, and so we check here. */
5076 if (initialized && DECL_INITIALIZED_IN_CLASS_P (field))
5077 error ("duplicate initialization of %qD", decl);
5078 if (duplicate_decls (decl, field, /*newdecl_is_friend=*/false))
5079 decl = field;
5080 if (decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_constexpr)
5081 && !DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (field))
5082 error ("%qD declared %<constexpr%> outside its class", field);
5083 }
5084 }
5085 else
5086 {
5087 tree field = check_classfn (context, decl,
5088 this_tmpl
5089 ? current_template_parms
5090 : NULL_TREE);
5091 if (field && field != error_mark_node
5092 && duplicate_decls (decl, field,
5093 /*newdecl_is_friend=*/false))
5094 decl = field;
5095 }
5096
5097 /* cp_finish_decl sets DECL_EXTERNAL if DECL_IN_AGGR_P is set. */
5098 DECL_IN_AGGR_P (decl) = 0;
5099 /* Do not mark DECL as an explicit specialization if it was not
5100 already marked as an instantiation; a declaration should
5101 never be marked as a specialization unless we know what
5102 template is being specialized. */
5103 if (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl) && DECL_USE_TEMPLATE (decl))
5104 {
5105 SET_DECL_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION (decl);
5106 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
5107 DECL_COMDAT (decl) = (TREE_PUBLIC (decl)
5108 && DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl));
5109 else
5110 DECL_COMDAT (decl) = false;
5111
5112 /* [temp.expl.spec] An explicit specialization of a static data
5113 member of a template is a definition if the declaration
5114 includes an initializer; otherwise, it is a declaration.
5115
5116 We check for processing_specialization so this only applies
5117 to the new specialization syntax. */
5118 if (!initialized && processing_specialization)
5119 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 1;
5120 }
5121
5122 if (DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) && ! DECL_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION (decl)
5123 /* Aliases are definitions. */
5124 && !alias)
5125 permerror (input_location, "declaration of %q#D outside of class is not definition",
5126 decl);
5127 }
5128
5129 was_public = TREE_PUBLIC (decl);
5130
5131 /* Enter this declaration into the symbol table. Don't push the plain
5132 VAR_DECL for a variable template. */
5133 if (!template_parm_scope_p ()
5134 || !VAR_P (decl))
5135 decl = maybe_push_decl (decl);
5136
5137 if (processing_template_decl)
5138 decl = push_template_decl (decl);
5139 if (decl == error_mark_node)
5140 return error_mark_node;
5141
5142 if (VAR_P (decl)
5143 && DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (decl) && !TREE_PUBLIC (decl) && !was_public
5144 && !DECL_THIS_STATIC (decl) && !DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl))
5145 {
5146 /* This is a const variable with implicit 'static'. Set
5147 DECL_THIS_STATIC so we can tell it from variables that are
5148 !TREE_PUBLIC because of the anonymous namespace. */
5149 gcc_assert (CP_TYPE_CONST_P (TREE_TYPE (decl)) || errorcount);
5150 DECL_THIS_STATIC (decl) = 1;
5151 }
5152
5153 if (current_function_decl && VAR_P (decl)
5154 && DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (current_function_decl))
5155 {
5156 bool ok = false;
5157 if (CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (decl))
5158 error ("%qD declared %<thread_local%> in %<constexpr%> function",
5159 decl);
5160 else if (TREE_STATIC (decl))
5161 error ("%qD declared %<static%> in %<constexpr%> function", decl);
5162 else
5163 ok = true;
5164 if (!ok)
5165 cp_function_chain->invalid_constexpr = true;
5166 }
5167
5168 if (!processing_template_decl && VAR_P (decl))
5169 start_decl_1 (decl, initialized);
5170
5171 return decl;
5172}
5173
5174/* Process the declaration of a variable DECL. INITIALIZED is true
5175 iff DECL is explicitly initialized. (INITIALIZED is false if the
5176 variable is initialized via an implicitly-called constructor.)
5177 This function must be called for ordinary variables (including, for
5178 example, implicit instantiations of templates), but must not be
5179 called for template declarations. */
5180
5181void
5182start_decl_1 (tree decl, bool initialized)
5183{
5184 tree type;
5185 bool complete_p;
5186 bool aggregate_definition_p;
5187
5188 gcc_assert (!processing_template_decl);
5189
5190 if (error_operand_p (decl))
5191 return;
5192
5193 gcc_assert (VAR_P (decl));
5194
5195 type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
5196 complete_p = COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type);
5197 aggregate_definition_p = MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (type) && !DECL_EXTERNAL (decl);
5198
5199 /* If an explicit initializer is present, or if this is a definition
5200 of an aggregate, then we need a complete type at this point.
5201 (Scalars are always complete types, so there is nothing to
5202 check.) This code just sets COMPLETE_P; errors (if necessary)
5203 are issued below. */
5204 if ((initialized || aggregate_definition_p)
5205 && !complete_p
5206 && COMPLETE_TYPE_P (complete_type (type)))
5207 {
5208 complete_p = true;
5209 /* We will not yet have set TREE_READONLY on DECL if the type
5210 was "const", but incomplete, before this point. But, now, we
5211 have a complete type, so we can try again. */
5212 cp_apply_type_quals_to_decl (cp_type_quals (type), decl);
5213 }
5214
5215 if (initialized)
5216 /* Is it valid for this decl to have an initializer at all? */
5217 {
5218 /* Don't allow initializations for incomplete types except for
5219 arrays which might be completed by the initialization. */
5220 if (complete_p)
5221 ; /* A complete type is ok. */
5222 else if (type_uses_auto (type))
5223 ; /* An auto type is ok. */
5224 else if (TREE_CODE (type) != ARRAY_TYPE)
5225 {
5226 error ("variable %q#D has initializer but incomplete type", decl);
5227 type = TREE_TYPE (decl) = error_mark_node;
5228 }
5229 else if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (complete_type (TREE_TYPE (type))))
5230 {
5231 if (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl) && DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (decl))
5232 error ("elements of array %q#D have incomplete type", decl);
5233 /* else we already gave an error in start_decl. */
5234 }
5235 }
5236 else if (aggregate_definition_p && !complete_p)
5237 {
5238 if (type_uses_auto (type))
5239 gcc_assert (CLASS_PLACEHOLDER_TEMPLATE (type));
5240 else
5241 {
5242 error ("aggregate %q#D has incomplete type and cannot be defined",
5243 decl);
5244 /* Change the type so that assemble_variable will give
5245 DECL an rtl we can live with: (mem (const_int 0)). */
5246 type = TREE_TYPE (decl) = error_mark_node;
5247 }
5248 }
5249
5250 /* Create a new scope to hold this declaration if necessary.
5251 Whether or not a new scope is necessary cannot be determined
5252 until after the type has been completed; if the type is a
5253 specialization of a class template it is not until after
5254 instantiation has occurred that TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR
5255 will be set correctly. */
5256 maybe_push_cleanup_level (type);
5257}
5258
5259/* Handle initialization of references. DECL, TYPE, and INIT have the
5260 same meaning as in cp_finish_decl. *CLEANUP must be NULL on entry,
5261 but will be set to a new CLEANUP_STMT if a temporary is created
5262 that must be destroyed subsequently.
5263
5264 Returns an initializer expression to use to initialize DECL, or
5265 NULL if the initialization can be performed statically.
5266
5267 Quotes on semantics can be found in ARM 8.4.3. */
5268
5269static tree
5270grok_reference_init (tree decl, tree type, tree init, int flags)
5271{
5272 if (init == NULL_TREE)
5273 {
5274 if ((DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl) == 0
5275 || DECL_IN_AGGR_P (decl) == 0)
5276 && ! DECL_THIS_EXTERN (decl))
5277 error ("%qD declared as reference but not initialized", decl);
5278 return NULL_TREE;
5279 }
5280
5281 if (TREE_CODE (init) == TREE_LIST)
5282 init = build_x_compound_expr_from_list (init, ELK_INIT,
5283 tf_warning_or_error);
5284
5285 tree ttype = TREE_TYPE (type);
5286 if (TREE_CODE (ttype) != ARRAY_TYPE
5287 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (init)) == ARRAY_TYPE)
5288 /* Note: default conversion is only called in very special cases. */
5289 init = decay_conversion (init, tf_warning_or_error);
5290
5291 /* check_initializer handles this for non-reference variables, but for
5292 references we need to do it here or the initializer will get the
5293 incomplete array type and confuse later calls to
5294 cp_complete_array_type. */
5295 if (TREE_CODE (ttype) == ARRAY_TYPE
5296 && TYPE_DOMAIN (ttype) == NULL_TREE
5297 && (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init)
5298 || TREE_CODE (init) == STRING_CST))
5299 {
5300 cp_complete_array_type (&ttype, init, false);
5301 if (ttype != TREE_TYPE (type))
5302 type = cp_build_reference_type (ttype, TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (type));
5303 }
5304
5305 /* Convert INIT to the reference type TYPE. This may involve the
5306 creation of a temporary, whose lifetime must be the same as that
5307 of the reference. If so, a DECL_EXPR for the temporary will be
5308 added just after the DECL_EXPR for DECL. That's why we don't set
5309 DECL_INITIAL for local references (instead assigning to them
5310 explicitly); we need to allow the temporary to be initialized
5311 first. */
5312 return initialize_reference (type, init, flags,
5313 tf_warning_or_error);
5314}
5315
5316/* Designated initializers in arrays are not supported in GNU C++.
5317 The parser cannot detect this error since it does not know whether
5318 a given brace-enclosed initializer is for a class type or for an
5319 array. This function checks that CE does not use a designated
5320 initializer. If it does, an error is issued. Returns true if CE
5321 is valid, i.e., does not have a designated initializer. */
5322
5323static bool
5324check_array_designated_initializer (constructor_elt *ce,
5325 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT index)
5326{
5327 /* Designated initializers for array elements are not supported. */
5328 if (ce->index)
5329 {
5330 /* The parser only allows identifiers as designated
5331 initializers. */
5332 if (ce->index == error_mark_node)
5333 {
5334 error ("name used in a GNU-style designated "
5335 "initializer for an array");
5336 return false;
5337 }
5338 else if (identifier_p (ce->index))
5339 {
5340 error ("name %qD used in a GNU-style designated "
5341 "initializer for an array", ce->index);
5342 return false;
5343 }
5344
5345 tree ce_index = build_expr_type_conversion (WANT_INT | WANT_ENUM,
5346 ce->index, true);
5347 if (ce_index
5348 && INTEGRAL_OR_UNSCOPED_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (ce_index))
5349 && (TREE_CODE (ce_index = maybe_constant_value (ce_index))
5350 == INTEGER_CST))
5351 {
5352 /* A C99 designator is OK if it matches the current index. */
5353 if (wi::eq_p (ce_index, index))
5354 return true;
5355 else
5356 sorry ("non-trivial designated initializers not supported");
5357 }
5358 else
5359 error ("C99 designator %qE is not an integral constant-expression",
5360 ce->index);
5361
5362 return false;
5363 }
5364
5365 return true;
5366}
5367
5368/* When parsing `int a[] = {1, 2};' we don't know the size of the
5369 array until we finish parsing the initializer. If that's the
5370 situation we're in, update DECL accordingly. */
5371
5372static void
5373maybe_deduce_size_from_array_init (tree decl, tree init)
5374{
5375 tree type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
5376
5377 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE
5378 && TYPE_DOMAIN (type) == NULL_TREE
5379 && TREE_CODE (decl) != TYPE_DECL)
5380 {
5381 /* do_default is really a C-ism to deal with tentative definitions.
5382 But let's leave it here to ease the eventual merge. */
5383 int do_default = !DECL_EXTERNAL (decl);
5384 tree initializer = init ? init : DECL_INITIAL (decl);
5385 int failure = 0;
5386
5387 /* Check that there are no designated initializers in INIT, as
5388 those are not supported in GNU C++, and as the middle-end
5389 will crash if presented with a non-numeric designated
5390 initializer. */
5391 if (initializer && BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (initializer))
5392 {
5393 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *v = CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (initializer);
5394 constructor_elt *ce;
5395 HOST_WIDE_INT i;
5396 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (v, i, ce)
5397 if (!check_array_designated_initializer (ce, i))
5398 failure = 1;
5399 }
5400
5401 if (!failure)
5402 {
5403 failure = cp_complete_array_type (&TREE_TYPE (decl), initializer,
5404 do_default);
5405 if (failure == 1)
5406 {
5407 error_at (EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (initializer,
5408 DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl)),
5409 "initializer fails to determine size of %qD", decl);
5410 }
5411 else if (failure == 2)
5412 {
5413 if (do_default)
5414 {
5415 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
5416 "array size missing in %qD", decl);
5417 }
5418 /* If a `static' var's size isn't known, make it extern as
5419 well as static, so it does not get allocated. If it's not
5420 `static', then don't mark it extern; finish_incomplete_decl
5421 will give it a default size and it will get allocated. */
5422 else if (!pedantic && TREE_STATIC (decl) && !TREE_PUBLIC (decl))
5423 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 1;
5424 }
5425 else if (failure == 3)
5426 {
5427 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
5428 "zero-size array %qD", decl);
5429 }
5430 }
5431
5432 cp_apply_type_quals_to_decl (cp_type_quals (TREE_TYPE (decl)), decl);
5433
5434 relayout_decl (decl);
5435 }
5436}
5437
5438/* Set DECL_SIZE, DECL_ALIGN, etc. for DECL (a VAR_DECL), and issue
5439 any appropriate error messages regarding the layout. */
5440
5441static void
5442layout_var_decl (tree decl)
5443{
5444 tree type;
5445
5446 type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
5447 if (type == error_mark_node)
5448 return;
5449
5450 /* If we haven't already laid out this declaration, do so now.
5451 Note that we must not call complete type for an external object
5452 because it's type might involve templates that we are not
5453 supposed to instantiate yet. (And it's perfectly valid to say
5454 `extern X x' for some incomplete type `X'.) */
5455 if (!DECL_EXTERNAL (decl))
5456 complete_type (type);
5457 if (!DECL_SIZE (decl)
5458 && TREE_TYPE (decl) != error_mark_node
5459 && complete_or_array_type_p (type))
5460 layout_decl (decl, 0);
5461
5462 if (!DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) && DECL_SIZE (decl) == NULL_TREE)
5463 {
5464 /* An automatic variable with an incomplete type: that is an error.
5465 Don't talk about array types here, since we took care of that
5466 message in grokdeclarator. */
5467 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
5468 "storage size of %qD isn%'t known", decl);
5469 TREE_TYPE (decl) = error_mark_node;
5470 }
5471#if 0
5472 /* Keep this code around in case we later want to control debug info
5473 based on whether a type is "used". (jason 1999-11-11) */
5474
5475 else if (!DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) && MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (ttype))
5476 /* Let debugger know it should output info for this type. */
5477 note_debug_info_needed (ttype);
5478
5479 if (TREE_STATIC (decl) && DECL_CLASS_SCOPE_P (decl))
5480 note_debug_info_needed (DECL_CONTEXT (decl));
5481#endif
5482
5483 if ((DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) || TREE_STATIC (decl))
5484 && DECL_SIZE (decl) != NULL_TREE
5485 && ! TREE_CONSTANT (DECL_SIZE (decl)))
5486 {
5487 if (TREE_CODE (DECL_SIZE (decl)) == INTEGER_CST)
5488 constant_expression_warning (DECL_SIZE (decl));
5489 else
5490 {
5491 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
5492 "storage size of %qD isn%'t constant", decl);
5493 TREE_TYPE (decl) = error_mark_node;
5494 }
5495 }
5496}
5497
5498/* If a local static variable is declared in an inline function, or if
5499 we have a weak definition, we must endeavor to create only one
5500 instance of the variable at link-time. */
5501
5502void
5503maybe_commonize_var (tree decl)
5504{
5505 /* Static data in a function with comdat linkage also has comdat
5506 linkage. */
5507 if ((TREE_STATIC (decl)
5508 /* Don't mess with __FUNCTION__. */
5509 && ! DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl)
5510 && DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (decl)
5511 && vague_linkage_p (DECL_CONTEXT (decl)))
5512 || (TREE_PUBLIC (decl) && DECL_INLINE_VAR_P (decl)))
5513 {
5514 if (flag_weak)
5515 {
5516 /* With weak symbols, we simply make the variable COMDAT;
5517 that will cause copies in multiple translations units to
5518 be merged. */
5519 comdat_linkage (decl);
5520 }
5521 else
5522 {
5523 if (DECL_INITIAL (decl) == NULL_TREE
5524 || DECL_INITIAL (decl) == error_mark_node)
5525 {
5526 /* Without weak symbols, we can use COMMON to merge
5527 uninitialized variables. */
5528 TREE_PUBLIC (decl) = 1;
5529 DECL_COMMON (decl) = 1;
5530 }
5531 else
5532 {
5533 /* While for initialized variables, we must use internal
5534 linkage -- which means that multiple copies will not
5535 be merged. */
5536 TREE_PUBLIC (decl) = 0;
5537 DECL_COMMON (decl) = 0;
5538 const char *msg;
5539 if (DECL_INLINE_VAR_P (decl))
5540 msg = G_("sorry: semantics of inline variable "
5541 "%q#D are wrong (you%'ll wind up with "
5542 "multiple copies)");
5543 else
5544 msg = G_("sorry: semantics of inline function "
5545 "static data %q#D are wrong (you%'ll wind "
5546 "up with multiple copies)");
5547 if (warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), 0,
5548 msg, decl))
5549 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
5550 "you can work around this by removing the initializer");
5551 }
5552 }
5553 }
5554}
5555
5556/* Issue an error message if DECL is an uninitialized const variable. */
5557
5558static void
5559check_for_uninitialized_const_var (tree decl)
5560{
5561 tree type = strip_array_types (TREE_TYPE (decl));
5562
5563 /* ``Unless explicitly declared extern, a const object does not have
5564 external linkage and must be initialized. ($8.4; $12.1)'' ARM
5565 7.1.6 */
5566 if (VAR_P (decl)
5567 && TREE_CODE (type) != REFERENCE_TYPE
5568 && (CP_TYPE_CONST_P (type) || var_in_constexpr_fn (decl))
5569 && !DECL_INITIAL (decl))
5570 {
5571 tree field = default_init_uninitialized_part (type);
5572 if (!field)
5573 return;
5574
5575 if (CP_TYPE_CONST_P (type))
5576 permerror (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
5577 "uninitialized const %qD", decl);
5578 else
5579 {
5580 if (!is_instantiation_of_constexpr (current_function_decl))
5581 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
5582 "uninitialized variable %qD in %<constexpr%> function",
5583 decl);
5584 cp_function_chain->invalid_constexpr = true;
5585 }
5586
5587 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
5588 {
5589 tree defaulted_ctor;
5590
5591 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (type)),
5592 "%q#T has no user-provided default constructor", type);
5593 defaulted_ctor = in_class_defaulted_default_constructor (type);
5594 if (defaulted_ctor)
5595 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (defaulted_ctor),
5596 "constructor is not user-provided because it is "
5597 "explicitly defaulted in the class body");
5598 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (field),
5599 "and the implicitly-defined constructor does not "
5600 "initialize %q#D", field);
5601 }
5602 }
5603}
5604
5605/* Structure holding the current initializer being processed by reshape_init.
5606 CUR is a pointer to the current element being processed, END is a pointer
5607 after the last element present in the initializer. */
5608struct reshape_iter
5609{
5610 constructor_elt *cur;
5611 constructor_elt *end;
5612};
5613
5614static tree reshape_init_r (tree, reshape_iter *, bool, tsubst_flags_t);
5615
5616/* FIELD is a FIELD_DECL or NULL. In the former case, the value
5617 returned is the next FIELD_DECL (possibly FIELD itself) that can be
5618 initialized. If there are no more such fields, the return value
5619 will be NULL. */
5620
5621tree
5622next_initializable_field (tree field)
5623{
5624 while (field
5625 && (TREE_CODE (field) != FIELD_DECL
5626 || (DECL_C_BIT_FIELD (field) && !DECL_NAME (field))
5627 || (DECL_ARTIFICIAL (field)
5628 && !(cxx_dialect >= cxx1z && DECL_FIELD_IS_BASE (field)))))
5629 field = DECL_CHAIN (field);
5630
5631 return field;
5632}
5633
5634/* Return true for [dcl.init.list] direct-list-initialization from
5635 single element of enumeration with a fixed underlying type. */
5636
5637bool
5638is_direct_enum_init (tree type, tree init)
5639{
5640 if (cxx_dialect >= cxx1z
5641 && TREE_CODE (type) == ENUMERAL_TYPE
5642 && ENUM_FIXED_UNDERLYING_TYPE_P (type)
5643 && TREE_CODE (init) == CONSTRUCTOR
5644 && CONSTRUCTOR_IS_DIRECT_INIT (init)
5645 && CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (init) == 1)
5646 return true;
5647 return false;
5648}
5649
5650/* Subroutine of reshape_init_array and reshape_init_vector, which does
5651 the actual work. ELT_TYPE is the element type of the array. MAX_INDEX is an
5652 INTEGER_CST representing the size of the array minus one (the maximum index),
5653 or NULL_TREE if the array was declared without specifying the size. D is
5654 the iterator within the constructor. */
5655
5656static tree
5657reshape_init_array_1 (tree elt_type, tree max_index, reshape_iter *d,
5658 tsubst_flags_t complain)
5659{
5660 tree new_init;
5661 bool sized_array_p = (max_index && TREE_CONSTANT (max_index));
5662 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT max_index_cst = 0;
5663 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT index;
5664
5665 /* The initializer for an array is always a CONSTRUCTOR. */
5666 new_init = build_constructor (init_list_type_node, NULL);
5667
5668 if (sized_array_p)
5669 {
5670 /* Minus 1 is used for zero sized arrays. */
5671 if (integer_all_onesp (max_index))
5672 return new_init;
5673
5674 if (tree_fits_uhwi_p (max_index))
5675 max_index_cst = tree_to_uhwi (max_index);
5676 /* sizetype is sign extended, not zero extended. */
5677 else
5678 max_index_cst = tree_to_uhwi (fold_convert (size_type_node, max_index));
5679 }
5680
5681 /* Loop until there are no more initializers. */
5682 for (index = 0;
5683 d->cur != d->end && (!sized_array_p || index <= max_index_cst);
5684 ++index)
5685 {
5686 tree elt_init;
5687 constructor_elt *old_cur = d->cur;
5688
5689 check_array_designated_initializer (d->cur, index);
5690 elt_init = reshape_init_r (elt_type, d, /*first_initializer_p=*/false,
5691 complain);
5692 if (elt_init == error_mark_node)
5693 return error_mark_node;
5694 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (new_init),
5695 size_int (index), elt_init);
5696 if (!TREE_CONSTANT (elt_init))
5697 TREE_CONSTANT (new_init) = false;
5698
5699 /* This can happen with an invalid initializer (c++/54501). */
5700 if (d->cur == old_cur && !sized_array_p)
5701 break;
5702 }
5703
5704 return new_init;
5705}
5706
5707/* Subroutine of reshape_init_r, processes the initializers for arrays.
5708 Parameters are the same of reshape_init_r. */
5709
5710static tree
5711reshape_init_array (tree type, reshape_iter *d, tsubst_flags_t complain)
5712{
5713 tree max_index = NULL_TREE;
5714
5715 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE);
5716
5717 if (TYPE_DOMAIN (type))
5718 max_index = array_type_nelts (type);
5719
5720 return reshape_init_array_1 (TREE_TYPE (type), max_index, d, complain);
5721}
5722
5723/* Subroutine of reshape_init_r, processes the initializers for vectors.
5724 Parameters are the same of reshape_init_r. */
5725
5726static tree
5727reshape_init_vector (tree type, reshape_iter *d, tsubst_flags_t complain)
5728{
5729 tree max_index = NULL_TREE;
5730
5731 gcc_assert (VECTOR_TYPE_P (type));
5732
5733 if (COMPOUND_LITERAL_P (d->cur->value))
5734 {
5735 tree value = d->cur->value;
5736 if (!same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (value), type))
5737 {
5738 if (complain & tf_error)
5739 error ("invalid type %qT as initializer for a vector of type %qT",
5740 TREE_TYPE (d->cur->value), type);
5741 value = error_mark_node;
5742 }
5743 ++d->cur;
5744 return value;
5745 }
5746
5747 /* For a vector, we initialize it as an array of the appropriate size. */
5748 if (VECTOR_TYPE_P (type))
5749 max_index = size_int (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (type) - 1);
5750
5751 return reshape_init_array_1 (TREE_TYPE (type), max_index, d, complain);
5752}
5753
5754/* Subroutine of reshape_init_r, processes the initializers for classes
5755 or union. Parameters are the same of reshape_init_r. */
5756
5757static tree
5758reshape_init_class (tree type, reshape_iter *d, bool first_initializer_p,
5759 tsubst_flags_t complain)
5760{
5761 tree field;
5762 tree new_init;
5763
5764 gcc_assert (CLASS_TYPE_P (type));
5765
5766 /* The initializer for a class is always a CONSTRUCTOR. */
5767 new_init = build_constructor (init_list_type_node, NULL);
5768 field = next_initializable_field (TYPE_FIELDS (type));
5769
5770 if (!field)
5771 {
5772 /* [dcl.init.aggr]
5773
5774 An initializer for an aggregate member that is an
5775 empty class shall have the form of an empty
5776 initializer-list {}. */
5777 if (!first_initializer_p)
5778 {
5779 if (complain & tf_error)
5780 error ("initializer for %qT must be brace-enclosed", type);
5781 return error_mark_node;
5782 }
5783 return new_init;
5784 }
5785
5786 /* Loop through the initializable fields, gathering initializers. */
5787 while (d->cur != d->end)
5788 {
5789 tree field_init;
5790 constructor_elt *old_cur = d->cur;
5791
5792 /* Handle designated initializers, as an extension. */
5793 if (d->cur->index)
5794 {
5795 if (d->cur->index == error_mark_node)
5796 return error_mark_node;
5797
5798 if (TREE_CODE (d->cur->index) == FIELD_DECL)
5799 {
5800 /* We already reshaped this. */
5801 if (field != d->cur->index)
5802 {
5803 tree id = DECL_NAME (d->cur->index);
5804 gcc_assert (id);
5805 gcc_checking_assert (lookup_field_1 (type, id,
5806 /*want_type=*/false)
5807 == d->cur->index);
5808 field = d->cur->index;
5809 }
5810 }
5811 else if (TREE_CODE (d->cur->index) == IDENTIFIER_NODE)
5812 field = lookup_field_1 (type, d->cur->index, /*want_type=*/false);
5813 else
5814 {
5815 if (complain & tf_error)
5816 error ("%<[%E] =%> used in a GNU-style designated initializer"
5817 " for class %qT", d->cur->index, type);
5818 return error_mark_node;
5819 }
5820
5821 if (!field || TREE_CODE (field) != FIELD_DECL)
5822 {
5823 if (complain & tf_error)
5824 error ("%qT has no non-static data member named %qD", type,
5825 d->cur->index);
5826 return error_mark_node;
5827 }
5828 }
5829
5830 /* If we processed all the member of the class, we are done. */
5831 if (!field)
5832 break;
5833
5834 field_init = reshape_init_r (TREE_TYPE (field), d,
5835 /*first_initializer_p=*/false, complain);
5836 if (field_init == error_mark_node)
5837 return error_mark_node;
5838
5839 if (d->cur == old_cur && d->cur->index)
5840 {
5841 /* This can happen with an invalid initializer for a flexible
5842 array member (c++/54441). */
5843 if (complain & tf_error)
5844 error ("invalid initializer for %q#D", field);
5845 return error_mark_node;
5846 }
5847
5848 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (new_init), field, field_init);
5849
5850 /* [dcl.init.aggr]
5851
5852 When a union is initialized with a brace-enclosed
5853 initializer, the braces shall only contain an
5854 initializer for the first member of the union. */
5855 if (TREE_CODE (type) == UNION_TYPE)
5856 break;
5857
5858 field = next_initializable_field (DECL_CHAIN (field));
5859 }
5860
5861 return new_init;
5862}
5863
5864/* Subroutine of reshape_init_r. We're in a context where C99 initializer
5865 designators are not valid; either complain or return true to indicate
5866 that reshape_init_r should return error_mark_node. */
5867
5868static bool
5869has_designator_problem (reshape_iter *d, tsubst_flags_t complain)
5870{
5871 if (d->cur->index)
5872 {
5873 if (complain & tf_error)
5874 error ("C99 designator %qE outside aggregate initializer",
5875 d->cur->index);
5876 else
5877 return true;
5878 }
5879 return false;
5880}
5881
5882/* Subroutine of reshape_init, which processes a single initializer (part of
5883 a CONSTRUCTOR). TYPE is the type of the variable being initialized, D is the
5884 iterator within the CONSTRUCTOR which points to the initializer to process.
5885 FIRST_INITIALIZER_P is true if this is the first initializer of the
5886 outermost CONSTRUCTOR node. */
5887
5888static tree
5889reshape_init_r (tree type, reshape_iter *d, bool first_initializer_p,
5890 tsubst_flags_t complain)
5891{
5892 tree init = d->cur->value;
5893
5894 if (error_operand_p (init))
5895 return error_mark_node;
5896
5897 if (first_initializer_p && !CP_AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (type)
5898 && has_designator_problem (d, complain))
5899 return error_mark_node;
5900
5901 if (TREE_CODE (type) == COMPLEX_TYPE)
5902 {
5903 /* A complex type can be initialized from one or two initializers,
5904 but braces are not elided. */
5905 d->cur++;
5906 if (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init))
5907 {
5908 if (CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (init) > 2)
5909 {
5910 if (complain & tf_error)
5911 error ("too many initializers for %qT", type);
5912 else
5913 return error_mark_node;
5914 }
5915 }
5916 else if (first_initializer_p && d->cur != d->end)
5917 {
5918 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *v = 0;
5919 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT (v, NULL_TREE, init);
5920 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT (v, NULL_TREE, d->cur->value);
5921 if (has_designator_problem (d, complain))
5922 return error_mark_node;
5923 d->cur++;
5924 init = build_constructor (init_list_type_node, v);
5925 }
5926 return init;
5927 }
5928
5929 /* A non-aggregate type is always initialized with a single
5930 initializer. */
5931 if (!CP_AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (type))
5932 {
5933 /* It is invalid to initialize a non-aggregate type with a
5934 brace-enclosed initializer before C++0x.
5935 We need to check for BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P here because
5936 of g++.old-deja/g++.mike/p7626.C: a pointer-to-member constant is
5937 a CONSTRUCTOR (with a record type). */
5938 if (TREE_CODE (init) == CONSTRUCTOR
5939 /* Don't complain about a capture-init. */
5940 && !CONSTRUCTOR_IS_DIRECT_INIT (init)
5941 && BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init)) /* p7626.C */
5942 {
5943 if (SCALAR_TYPE_P (type))
5944 {
5945 if (cxx_dialect < cxx11
5946 /* Isn't value-initialization. */
5947 || CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (init) > 0)
5948 {
5949 if (complain & tf_error)
5950 error ("braces around scalar initializer for type %qT",
5951 type);
5952 init = error_mark_node;
5953 }
5954 }
5955 else
5956 maybe_warn_cpp0x (CPP0X_INITIALIZER_LISTS);
5957 }
5958
5959 d->cur++;
5960 return init;
5961 }
5962
5963 /* "If T is a class type and the initializer list has a single element of
5964 type cv U, where U is T or a class derived from T, the object is
5965 initialized from that element." Even if T is an aggregate. */
5966 if (cxx_dialect >= cxx11 && (CLASS_TYPE_P (type) || VECTOR_TYPE_P (type))
5967 && first_initializer_p
5968 && d->end - d->cur == 1
5969 && reference_related_p (type, TREE_TYPE (init)))
5970 {
5971 d->cur++;
5972 return init;
5973 }
5974
5975 /* [dcl.init.aggr]
5976
5977 All implicit type conversions (clause _conv_) are considered when
5978 initializing the aggregate member with an initializer from an
5979 initializer-list. If the initializer can initialize a member,
5980 the member is initialized. Otherwise, if the member is itself a
5981 non-empty subaggregate, brace elision is assumed and the
5982 initializer is considered for the initialization of the first
5983 member of the subaggregate. */
5984 if (TREE_CODE (init) != CONSTRUCTOR
5985 /* But don't try this for the first initializer, since that would be
5986 looking through the outermost braces; A a2 = { a1 }; is not a
5987 valid aggregate initialization. */
5988 && !first_initializer_p
5989 && (same_type_ignoring_top_level_qualifiers_p (type, TREE_TYPE (init))
5990 || can_convert_arg (type, TREE_TYPE (init), init, LOOKUP_NORMAL,
5991 complain)))
5992 {
5993 d->cur++;
5994 return init;
5995 }
5996
5997 /* [dcl.init.string]
5998
5999 A char array (whether plain char, signed char, or unsigned char)
6000 can be initialized by a string-literal (optionally enclosed in
6001 braces); a wchar_t array can be initialized by a wide
6002 string-literal (optionally enclosed in braces). */
6003 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE
6004 && char_type_p (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (type))))
6005 {
6006 tree str_init = init;
6007
6008 /* Strip one level of braces if and only if they enclose a single
6009 element (as allowed by [dcl.init.string]). */
6010 if (!first_initializer_p
6011 && TREE_CODE (str_init) == CONSTRUCTOR
6012 && CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (str_init) == 1)
6013 {
6014 str_init = (*CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (str_init))[0].value;
6015 }
6016
6017 /* If it's a string literal, then it's the initializer for the array
6018 as a whole. Otherwise, continue with normal initialization for
6019 array types (one value per array element). */
6020 if (TREE_CODE (str_init) == STRING_CST)
6021 {
6022 if (has_designator_problem (d, complain))
6023 return error_mark_node;
6024 d->cur++;
6025 return str_init;
6026 }
6027 }
6028
6029 /* The following cases are about aggregates. If we are not within a full
6030 initializer already, and there is not a CONSTRUCTOR, it means that there
6031 is a missing set of braces (that is, we are processing the case for
6032 which reshape_init exists). */
6033 if (!first_initializer_p)
6034 {
6035 if (TREE_CODE (init) == CONSTRUCTOR)
6036 {
6037 if (TREE_TYPE (init) && TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (TREE_TYPE (init)))
6038 /* There is no need to reshape pointer-to-member function
6039 initializers, as they are always constructed correctly
6040 by the front end. */
6041 ;
6042 else if (COMPOUND_LITERAL_P (init))
6043 /* For a nested compound literal, there is no need to reshape since
6044 brace elision is not allowed. Even if we decided to allow it,
6045 we should add a call to reshape_init in finish_compound_literal,
6046 before calling digest_init, so changing this code would still
6047 not be necessary. */
6048 gcc_assert (!BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init));
6049 else
6050 {
6051 ++d->cur;
6052 gcc_assert (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init));
6053 return reshape_init (type, init, complain);
6054 }
6055 }
6056
6057 if (complain & tf_warning)
6058 warning (OPT_Wmissing_braces,
6059 "missing braces around initializer for %qT",
6060 type);
6061 }
6062
6063 /* Dispatch to specialized routines. */
6064 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
6065 return reshape_init_class (type, d, first_initializer_p, complain);
6066 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
6067 return reshape_init_array (type, d, complain);
6068 else if (VECTOR_TYPE_P (type))
6069 return reshape_init_vector (type, d, complain);
6070 else
6071 gcc_unreachable();
6072}
6073
6074/* Undo the brace-elision allowed by [dcl.init.aggr] in a
6075 brace-enclosed aggregate initializer.
6076
6077 INIT is the CONSTRUCTOR containing the list of initializers describing
6078 a brace-enclosed initializer for an entity of the indicated aggregate TYPE.
6079 It may not presently match the shape of the TYPE; for example:
6080
6081 struct S { int a; int b; };
6082 struct S a[] = { 1, 2, 3, 4 };
6083
6084 Here INIT will hold a vector of four elements, rather than a
6085 vector of two elements, each itself a vector of two elements. This
6086 routine transforms INIT from the former form into the latter. The
6087 revised CONSTRUCTOR node is returned. */
6088
6089tree
6090reshape_init (tree type, tree init, tsubst_flags_t complain)
6091{
6092 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *v;
6093 reshape_iter d;
6094 tree new_init;
6095
6096 gcc_assert (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init));
6097
6098 v = CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init);
6099
6100 /* An empty constructor does not need reshaping, and it is always a valid
6101 initializer. */
6102 if (vec_safe_is_empty (v))
6103 return init;
6104
6105 /* Handle [dcl.init.list] direct-list-initialization from
6106 single element of enumeration with a fixed underlying type. */
6107 if (is_direct_enum_init (type, init))
6108 {
6109 tree elt = CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (init, 0)->value;
6110 if (check_narrowing (ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (type), elt, complain))
6111 {
6112 warning_sentinel w (warn_useless_cast);
6113 return cp_build_c_cast (type, elt, tf_warning_or_error);
6114 }
6115 else
6116 return error_mark_node;
6117 }
6118
6119 /* Recurse on this CONSTRUCTOR. */
6120 d.cur = &(*v)[0];
6121 d.end = d.cur + v->length ();
6122
6123 new_init = reshape_init_r (type, &d, true, complain);
6124 if (new_init == error_mark_node)
6125 return error_mark_node;
6126
6127 /* Make sure all the element of the constructor were used. Otherwise,
6128 issue an error about exceeding initializers. */
6129 if (d.cur != d.end)
6130 {
6131 if (complain & tf_error)
6132 error ("too many initializers for %qT", type);
6133 else
6134 return error_mark_node;
6135 }
6136
6137 if (CONSTRUCTOR_IS_DIRECT_INIT (init)
6138 && BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (new_init))
6139 CONSTRUCTOR_IS_DIRECT_INIT (new_init) = true;
6140
6141 return new_init;
6142}
6143
6144/* Verify array initializer. Returns true if errors have been reported. */
6145
6146bool
6147check_array_initializer (tree decl, tree type, tree init)
6148{
6149 tree element_type = TREE_TYPE (type);
6150
6151 /* The array type itself need not be complete, because the
6152 initializer may tell us how many elements are in the array.
6153 But, the elements of the array must be complete. */
6154 if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (complete_type (element_type)))
6155 {
6156 if (decl)
6157 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
6158 "elements of array %q#D have incomplete type", decl);
6159 else
6160 error ("elements of array %q#T have incomplete type", type);
6161 return true;
6162 }
6163 /* A compound literal can't have variable size. */
6164 if (init && !decl
6165 && ((COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type) && !TREE_CONSTANT (TYPE_SIZE (type)))
6166 || !TREE_CONSTANT (TYPE_SIZE (element_type))))
6167 {
6168 error ("variable-sized compound literal");
6169 return true;
6170 }
6171 return false;
6172}
6173
6174/* Subroutine of check_initializer; args are passed down from that function.
6175 Set stmts_are_full_exprs_p to 1 across a call to build_aggr_init. */
6176
6177static tree
6178build_aggr_init_full_exprs (tree decl, tree init, int flags)
6179
6180{
6181 gcc_assert (stmts_are_full_exprs_p ());
6182 return build_aggr_init (decl, init, flags, tf_warning_or_error);
6183}
6184
6185/* Verify INIT (the initializer for DECL), and record the
6186 initialization in DECL_INITIAL, if appropriate. CLEANUP is as for
6187 grok_reference_init.
6188
6189 If the return value is non-NULL, it is an expression that must be
6190 evaluated dynamically to initialize DECL. */
6191
6192static tree
6193check_initializer (tree decl, tree init, int flags, vec<tree, va_gc> **cleanups)
6194{
6195 tree type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
6196 tree init_code = NULL;
6197 tree core_type;
6198
6199 /* Things that are going to be initialized need to have complete
6200 type. */
6201 TREE_TYPE (decl) = type = complete_type (TREE_TYPE (decl));
6202
6203 if (DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (decl))
6204 {
6205 /* A variable with DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P set is just a placeholder,
6206 it doesn't have storage to be initialized. */
6207 gcc_assert (init == NULL_TREE);
6208 return NULL_TREE;
6209 }
6210
6211 if (type == error_mark_node)
6212 /* We will have already complained. */
6213 return NULL_TREE;
6214
6215 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
6216 {
6217 if (check_array_initializer (decl, type, init))
6218 return NULL_TREE;
6219 }
6220 else if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type))
6221 {
6222 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
6223 "%q#D has incomplete type", decl);
6224 TREE_TYPE (decl) = error_mark_node;
6225 return NULL_TREE;
6226 }
6227 else
6228 /* There is no way to make a variable-sized class type in GNU C++. */
6229 gcc_assert (TREE_CONSTANT (TYPE_SIZE (type)));
6230
6231 if (init && BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init))
6232 {
6233 int init_len = CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (init);
6234 if (SCALAR_TYPE_P (type))
6235 {
6236 if (init_len == 0)
6237 {
6238 maybe_warn_cpp0x (CPP0X_INITIALIZER_LISTS);
6239 init = build_zero_init (type, NULL_TREE, false);
6240 }
6241 else if (init_len != 1 && TREE_CODE (type) != COMPLEX_TYPE)
6242 {
6243 error_at (EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (init, DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl)),
6244 "scalar object %qD requires one element in "
6245 "initializer", decl);
6246 TREE_TYPE (decl) = error_mark_node;
6247 return NULL_TREE;
6248 }
6249 }
6250 }
6251
6252 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == CONST_DECL)
6253 {
6254 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (type) != REFERENCE_TYPE);
6255
6256 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = init;
6257
6258 gcc_assert (init != NULL_TREE);
6259 init = NULL_TREE;
6260 }
6261 else if (!init && DECL_REALLY_EXTERN (decl))
6262 ;
6263 else if (init || type_build_ctor_call (type)
6264 || TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
6265 {
6266 if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
6267 {
6268 init = grok_reference_init (decl, type, init, flags);
6269 flags |= LOOKUP_ALREADY_DIGESTED;
6270 }
6271 else if (!init)
6272 check_for_uninitialized_const_var (decl);
6273 /* Do not reshape constructors of vectors (they don't need to be
6274 reshaped. */
6275 else if (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init))
6276 {
6277 if (is_std_init_list (type))
6278 {
6279 init = perform_implicit_conversion (type, init,
6280 tf_warning_or_error);
6281 flags |= LOOKUP_ALREADY_DIGESTED;
6282 }
6283 else if (TYPE_NON_AGGREGATE_CLASS (type))
6284 {
6285 /* Don't reshape if the class has constructors. */
6286 if (cxx_dialect == cxx98)
6287 error_at (EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (init, DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl)),
6288 "in C++98 %qD must be initialized by "
6289 "constructor, not by %<{...}%>",
6290 decl);
6291 }
6292 else if (VECTOR_TYPE_P (type) && TYPE_VECTOR_OPAQUE (type))
6293 {
6294 error ("opaque vector types cannot be initialized");
6295 init = error_mark_node;
6296 }
6297 else
6298 {
6299 init = reshape_init (type, init, tf_warning_or_error);
6300 flags |= LOOKUP_NO_NARROWING;
6301 }
6302 }
6303 else if (TREE_CODE (init) == TREE_LIST
6304 && TREE_TYPE (init) != unknown_type_node
6305 && !MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
6306 {
6307 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (decl) != RESULT_DECL);
6308
6309 /* We get here with code like `int a (2);' */
6310 init = build_x_compound_expr_from_list (init, ELK_INIT,
6311 tf_warning_or_error);
6312 }
6313
6314 /* If DECL has an array type without a specific bound, deduce the
6315 array size from the initializer. */
6316 maybe_deduce_size_from_array_init (decl, init);
6317 type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
6318 if (type == error_mark_node)
6319 return NULL_TREE;
6320
6321 if (((type_build_ctor_call (type) || CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
6322 && !(flags & LOOKUP_ALREADY_DIGESTED)
6323 && !(init && BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init)
6324 && CP_AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (type)
6325 && (CLASS_TYPE_P (type)
6326 || !TYPE_NEEDS_CONSTRUCTING (type)
6327 || type_has_extended_temps (type))))
6328 || (DECL_DECOMPOSITION_P (decl) && TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE))
6329 {
6330 init_code = build_aggr_init_full_exprs (decl, init, flags);
6331
6332 /* A constructor call is a non-trivial initializer even if
6333 it isn't explicitly written. */
6334 if (TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (init_code))
6335 DECL_NONTRIVIALLY_INITIALIZED_P (decl) = true;
6336
6337 /* If this is a constexpr initializer, expand_default_init will
6338 have returned an INIT_EXPR rather than a CALL_EXPR. In that
6339 case, pull the initializer back out and pass it down into
6340 store_init_value. */
6341 while (TREE_CODE (init_code) == EXPR_STMT
6342 || TREE_CODE (init_code) == CONVERT_EXPR)
6343 init_code = TREE_OPERAND (init_code, 0);
6344 if (TREE_CODE (init_code) == INIT_EXPR)
6345 {
6346 init = TREE_OPERAND (init_code, 1);
6347 init_code = NULL_TREE;
6348 /* Don't call digest_init; it's unnecessary and will complain
6349 about aggregate initialization of non-aggregate classes. */
6350 flags |= LOOKUP_ALREADY_DIGESTED;
6351 }
6352 else if (DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (decl))
6353 {
6354 /* Declared constexpr, but no suitable initializer; massage
6355 init appropriately so we can pass it into store_init_value
6356 for the error. */
6357 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type)
6358 && (!init || TREE_CODE (init) == TREE_LIST))
6359 {
6360 init = build_functional_cast (type, init, tf_none);
6361 if (TREE_CODE (init) == TARGET_EXPR)
6362 TARGET_EXPR_DIRECT_INIT_P (init) = true;
6363 }
6364 init_code = NULL_TREE;
6365 }
6366 else
6367 init = NULL_TREE;
6368 }
6369
6370 if (init && TREE_CODE (init) != TREE_VEC)
6371 {
6372 /* In aggregate initialization of a variable, each element
6373 initialization is a full-expression because there is no
6374 enclosing expression. */
6375 gcc_assert (stmts_are_full_exprs_p ());
6376
6377 init_code = store_init_value (decl, init, cleanups, flags);
6378
6379 if (pedantic && TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE
6380 && DECL_INITIAL (decl)
6381 && TREE_CODE (DECL_INITIAL (decl)) == STRING_CST
6382 && PAREN_STRING_LITERAL_P (DECL_INITIAL (decl)))
6383 warning_at (EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (DECL_INITIAL (decl),
6384 DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl)),
6385 0, "array %qD initialized by parenthesized "
6386 "string literal %qE",
6387 decl, DECL_INITIAL (decl));
6388 init = NULL;
6389 }
6390 }
6391 else
6392 {
6393 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (core_type = strip_array_types (type))
6394 && (CLASSTYPE_READONLY_FIELDS_NEED_INIT (core_type)
6395 || CLASSTYPE_REF_FIELDS_NEED_INIT (core_type)))
6396 diagnose_uninitialized_cst_or_ref_member (core_type, /*using_new=*/false,
6397 /*complain=*/true);
6398
6399 check_for_uninitialized_const_var (decl);
6400 }
6401
6402 if (init && init != error_mark_node)
6403 init_code = build2 (INIT_EXPR, type, decl, init);
6404
6405 if (init_code)
6406 {
6407 /* We might have set these in cp_finish_decl. */
6408 DECL_INITIALIZED_BY_CONSTANT_EXPRESSION_P (decl) = false;
6409 TREE_CONSTANT (decl) = false;
6410 }
6411
6412 if (init_code
6413 && (DECL_IN_AGGR_P (decl)
6414 && DECL_INITIALIZED_IN_CLASS_P (decl)
6415 && !DECL_VAR_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl)))
6416 {
6417 static int explained = 0;
6418
6419 if (cxx_dialect < cxx11)
6420 error ("initializer invalid for static member with constructor");
6421 else if (cxx_dialect < cxx1z)
6422 error ("non-constant in-class initialization invalid for static "
6423 "member %qD", decl);
6424 else
6425 error ("non-constant in-class initialization invalid for non-inline "
6426 "static member %qD", decl);
6427 if (!explained)
6428 {
6429 inform (input_location,
6430 "(an out of class initialization is required)");
6431 explained = 1;
6432 }
6433 return NULL_TREE;
6434 }
6435
6436 return init_code;
6437}
6438
6439/* If DECL is not a local variable, give it RTL. */
6440
6441static void
6442make_rtl_for_nonlocal_decl (tree decl, tree init, const char* asmspec)
6443{
6444 int toplev = toplevel_bindings_p ();
6445 int defer_p;
6446
6447 /* Set the DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME for the object. */
6448 if (asmspec)
6449 {
6450 /* The `register' keyword, when used together with an
6451 asm-specification, indicates that the variable should be
6452 placed in a particular register. */
6453 if (VAR_P (decl) && DECL_REGISTER (decl))
6454 {
6455 set_user_assembler_name (decl, asmspec);
6456 DECL_HARD_REGISTER (decl) = 1;
6457 }
6458 else
6459 {
6460 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
6461 && DECL_BUILT_IN_CLASS (decl) == BUILT_IN_NORMAL)
6462 set_builtin_user_assembler_name (decl, asmspec);
6463 set_user_assembler_name (decl, asmspec);
6464 }
6465 }
6466
6467 /* Handle non-variables up front. */
6468 if (!VAR_P (decl))
6469 {
6470 rest_of_decl_compilation (decl, toplev, at_eof);
6471 return;
6472 }
6473
6474 /* If we see a class member here, it should be a static data
6475 member. */
6476 if (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl) && DECL_IN_AGGR_P (decl))
6477 {
6478 gcc_assert (TREE_STATIC (decl));
6479 /* An in-class declaration of a static data member should be
6480 external; it is only a declaration, and not a definition. */
6481 if (init == NULL_TREE)
6482 gcc_assert (DECL_EXTERNAL (decl)
6483 || !TREE_PUBLIC (decl)
6484 || DECL_INLINE_VAR_P (decl));
6485 }
6486
6487 /* We don't create any RTL for local variables. */
6488 if (DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (decl) && !TREE_STATIC (decl))
6489 return;
6490
6491 /* We defer emission of local statics until the corresponding
6492 DECL_EXPR is expanded. But with constexpr its function might never
6493 be expanded, so go ahead and tell cgraph about the variable now. */
6494 defer_p = ((DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (decl)
6495 && !var_in_maybe_constexpr_fn (decl))
6496 || DECL_VIRTUAL_P (decl));
6497
6498 /* Defer template instantiations. */
6499 if (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl)
6500 && DECL_IMPLICIT_INSTANTIATION (decl))
6501 defer_p = 1;
6502
6503 /* If we're not deferring, go ahead and assemble the variable. */
6504 if (!defer_p)
6505 rest_of_decl_compilation (decl, toplev, at_eof);
6506}
6507
6508/* walk_tree helper for wrap_temporary_cleanups, below. */
6509
6510static tree
6511wrap_cleanups_r (tree *stmt_p, int *walk_subtrees, void *data)
6512{
6513 /* Stop at types or full-expression boundaries. */
6514 if (TYPE_P (*stmt_p)
6515 || TREE_CODE (*stmt_p) == CLEANUP_POINT_EXPR)
6516 {
6517 *walk_subtrees = 0;
6518 return NULL_TREE;
6519 }
6520
6521 if (TREE_CODE (*stmt_p) == TARGET_EXPR)
6522 {
6523 tree guard = (tree)data;
6524 tree tcleanup = TARGET_EXPR_CLEANUP (*stmt_p);
6525
6526 tcleanup = build2 (TRY_CATCH_EXPR, void_type_node, tcleanup, guard);
6527 /* Tell honor_protect_cleanup_actions to handle this as a separate
6528 cleanup. */
6529 TRY_CATCH_IS_CLEANUP (tcleanup) = 1;
6530
6531 TARGET_EXPR_CLEANUP (*stmt_p) = tcleanup;
6532 }
6533
6534 return NULL_TREE;
6535}
6536
6537/* We're initializing a local variable which has a cleanup GUARD. If there
6538 are any temporaries used in the initializer INIT of this variable, we
6539 need to wrap their cleanups with TRY_CATCH_EXPR (, GUARD) so that the
6540 variable will be cleaned up properly if one of them throws.
6541
6542 Unfortunately, there's no way to express this properly in terms of
6543 nesting, as the regions for the temporaries overlap the region for the
6544 variable itself; if there are two temporaries, the variable needs to be
6545 the first thing destroyed if either of them throws. However, we only
6546 want to run the variable's cleanup if it actually got constructed. So
6547 we need to guard the temporary cleanups with the variable's cleanup if
6548 they are run on the normal path, but not if they are run on the
6549 exceptional path. We implement this by telling
6550 honor_protect_cleanup_actions to strip the variable cleanup from the
6551 exceptional path. */
6552
6553static void
6554wrap_temporary_cleanups (tree init, tree guard)
6555{
6556 cp_walk_tree_without_duplicates (&init, wrap_cleanups_r, (void *)guard);
6557}
6558
6559/* Generate code to initialize DECL (a local variable). */
6560
6561static void
6562initialize_local_var (tree decl, tree init)
6563{
6564 tree type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
6565 tree cleanup;
6566 int already_used;
6567
6568 gcc_assert (VAR_P (decl)
6569 || TREE_CODE (decl) == RESULT_DECL);
6570 gcc_assert (!TREE_STATIC (decl));
6571
6572 if (DECL_SIZE (decl) == NULL_TREE)
6573 {
6574 /* If we used it already as memory, it must stay in memory. */
6575 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = NULL_TREE;
6576 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (decl) = TREE_USED (decl);
6577 return;
6578 }
6579
6580 if (type == error_mark_node)
6581 return;
6582
6583 /* Compute and store the initial value. */
6584 already_used = TREE_USED (decl) || TREE_USED (type);
6585 if (TREE_USED (type))
6586 DECL_READ_P (decl) = 1;
6587
6588 /* Generate a cleanup, if necessary. */
6589 cleanup = cxx_maybe_build_cleanup (decl, tf_warning_or_error);
6590
6591 /* Perform the initialization. */
6592 if (init)
6593 {
6594 tree rinit = (TREE_CODE (init) == INIT_EXPR
6595 ? TREE_OPERAND (init, 1) : NULL_TREE);
6596 if (rinit && !TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (rinit))
6597 {
6598 /* Stick simple initializers in DECL_INITIAL so that
6599 -Wno-init-self works (c++/34772). */
6600 gcc_assert (TREE_OPERAND (init, 0) == decl);
6601 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = rinit;
6602
6603 if (warn_init_self && TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
6604 {
6605 STRIP_NOPS (rinit);
6606 if (rinit == decl)
6607 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
6608 OPT_Winit_self,
6609 "reference %qD is initialized with itself", decl);
6610 }
6611 }
6612 else
6613 {
6614 int saved_stmts_are_full_exprs_p;
6615
6616 /* If we're only initializing a single object, guard the
6617 destructors of any temporaries used in its initializer with
6618 its destructor. This isn't right for arrays because each
6619 element initialization is a full-expression. */
6620 if (cleanup && TREE_CODE (type) != ARRAY_TYPE)
6621 wrap_temporary_cleanups (init, cleanup);
6622
6623 gcc_assert (building_stmt_list_p ());
6624 saved_stmts_are_full_exprs_p = stmts_are_full_exprs_p ();
6625 current_stmt_tree ()->stmts_are_full_exprs_p = 1;
6626 finish_expr_stmt (init);
6627 current_stmt_tree ()->stmts_are_full_exprs_p =
6628 saved_stmts_are_full_exprs_p;
6629 }
6630 }
6631
6632 /* Set this to 0 so we can tell whether an aggregate which was
6633 initialized was ever used. Don't do this if it has a
6634 destructor, so we don't complain about the 'resource
6635 allocation is initialization' idiom. Now set
6636 attribute((unused)) on types so decls of that type will be
6637 marked used. (see TREE_USED, above.) */
6638 if (TYPE_NEEDS_CONSTRUCTING (type)
6639 && ! already_used
6640 && TYPE_HAS_TRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (type)
6641 && DECL_NAME (decl))
6642 TREE_USED (decl) = 0;
6643 else if (already_used)
6644 TREE_USED (decl) = 1;
6645
6646 if (cleanup)
6647 finish_decl_cleanup (decl, cleanup);
6648}
6649
6650/* DECL is a VAR_DECL for a compiler-generated variable with static
6651 storage duration (like a virtual table) whose initializer is a
6652 compile-time constant. Initialize the variable and provide it to the
6653 back end. */
6654
6655void
6656initialize_artificial_var (tree decl, vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *v)
6657{
6658 tree init;
6659 gcc_assert (DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl));
6660 init = build_constructor (TREE_TYPE (decl), v);
6661 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (init) == CONSTRUCTOR);
6662 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = init;
6663 DECL_INITIALIZED_P (decl) = 1;
6664 determine_visibility (decl);
6665 layout_var_decl (decl);
6666 maybe_commonize_var (decl);
6667 make_rtl_for_nonlocal_decl (decl, init, /*asmspec=*/NULL);
6668}
6669
6670/* INIT is the initializer for a variable, as represented by the
6671 parser. Returns true iff INIT is type-dependent. */
6672
6673static bool
6674type_dependent_init_p (tree init)
6675{
6676 if (TREE_CODE (init) == TREE_LIST)
6677 /* A parenthesized initializer, e.g.: int i (3, 2); ? */
6678 return any_type_dependent_elements_p (init);
6679 else if (TREE_CODE (init) == CONSTRUCTOR)
6680 /* A brace-enclosed initializer, e.g.: int i = { 3 }; ? */
6681 {
6682 if (dependent_type_p (TREE_TYPE (init)))
6683 return true;
6684
6685 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *elts;
6686 size_t nelts;
6687 size_t i;
6688
6689 elts = CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init);
6690 nelts = vec_safe_length (elts);
6691 for (i = 0; i < nelts; ++i)
6692 if (type_dependent_init_p ((*elts)[i].value))
6693 return true;
6694 }
6695 else
6696 /* It must be a simple expression, e.g., int i = 3; */
6697 return type_dependent_expression_p (init);
6698
6699 return false;
6700}
6701
6702/* INIT is the initializer for a variable, as represented by the
6703 parser. Returns true iff INIT is value-dependent. */
6704
6705static bool
6706value_dependent_init_p (tree init)
6707{
6708 if (TREE_CODE (init) == TREE_LIST)
6709 /* A parenthesized initializer, e.g.: int i (3, 2); ? */
6710 return any_value_dependent_elements_p (init);
6711 else if (TREE_CODE (init) == CONSTRUCTOR)
6712 /* A brace-enclosed initializer, e.g.: int i = { 3 }; ? */
6713 {
6714 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *elts;
6715 size_t nelts;
6716 size_t i;
6717
6718 elts = CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init);
6719 nelts = vec_safe_length (elts);
6720 for (i = 0; i < nelts; ++i)
6721 if (value_dependent_init_p ((*elts)[i].value))
6722 return true;
6723 }
6724 else
6725 /* It must be a simple expression, e.g., int i = 3; */
6726 return value_dependent_expression_p (init);
6727
6728 return false;
6729}
6730
6731// Returns true if a DECL is VAR_DECL with the concept specifier.
6732static inline bool
6733is_concept_var (tree decl)
6734{
6735 return (VAR_P (decl)
6736 // Not all variables have DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC.
6737 && DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl)
6738 && DECL_DECLARED_CONCEPT_P (decl));
6739}
6740
6741/* A helper function to be called via walk_tree. If any label exists
6742 under *TP, it is (going to be) forced. Set has_forced_label_in_static. */
6743
6744static tree
6745notice_forced_label_r (tree *tp, int *walk_subtrees, void *)
6746{
6747 if (TYPE_P (*tp))
6748 *walk_subtrees = 0;
6749 if (TREE_CODE (*tp) == LABEL_DECL)
6750 cfun->has_forced_label_in_static = 1;
6751 return NULL_TREE;
6752}
6753
6754/* Finish processing of a declaration;
6755 install its line number and initial value.
6756 If the length of an array type is not known before,
6757 it must be determined now, from the initial value, or it is an error.
6758
6759 INIT is the initializer (if any) for DECL. If INIT_CONST_EXPR_P is
6760 true, then INIT is an integral constant expression.
6761
6762 FLAGS is LOOKUP_ONLYCONVERTING if the = init syntax was used, else 0
6763 if the (init) syntax was used. */
6764
6765void
6766cp_finish_decl (tree decl, tree init, bool init_const_expr_p,
6767 tree asmspec_tree, int flags)
6768{
6769 tree type;
6770 vec<tree, va_gc> *cleanups = NULL;
6771 const char *asmspec = NULL;
6772 int was_readonly = 0;
6773 bool var_definition_p = false;
6774 tree auto_node;
6775
6776 if (decl == error_mark_node)
6777 return;
6778 else if (! decl)
6779 {
6780 if (init)
6781 error ("assignment (not initialization) in declaration");
6782 return;
6783 }
6784
6785 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (decl) != RESULT_DECL);
6786 /* Parameters are handled by store_parm_decls, not cp_finish_decl. */
6787 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (decl) != PARM_DECL);
6788
6789 type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
6790 if (type == error_mark_node)
6791 return;
6792
6793 /* Warn about register storage specifiers except when in GNU global
6794 or local register variable extension. */
6795 if (VAR_P (decl) && DECL_REGISTER (decl) && asmspec_tree == NULL_TREE)
6796 {
6797 if (cxx_dialect >= cxx1z)
6798 pedwarn (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), OPT_Wregister,
6799 "ISO C++1z does not allow %<register%> storage "
6800 "class specifier");
6801 else
6802 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), OPT_Wregister,
6803 "%<register%> storage class specifier used");
6804 }
6805
6806 /* If a name was specified, get the string. */
6807 if (at_namespace_scope_p ())
6808 asmspec_tree = maybe_apply_renaming_pragma (decl, asmspec_tree);
6809 if (asmspec_tree && asmspec_tree != error_mark_node)
6810 asmspec = TREE_STRING_POINTER (asmspec_tree);
6811
6812 if (current_class_type
6813 && CP_DECL_CONTEXT (decl) == current_class_type
6814 && TYPE_BEING_DEFINED (current_class_type)
6815 && !CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATION (current_class_type)
6816 && (DECL_INITIAL (decl) || init))
6817 DECL_INITIALIZED_IN_CLASS_P (decl) = 1;
6818
6819 if (TREE_CODE (decl) != FUNCTION_DECL
6820 && (auto_node = type_uses_auto (type)))
6821 {
6822 tree d_init;
6823 if (init == NULL_TREE)
6824 {
6825 if (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl)
6826 && DECL_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATION (decl)
6827 && !DECL_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATED (decl))
6828 {
6829 /* init is null because we're deferring instantiating the
6830 initializer until we need it. Well, we need it now. */
6831 instantiate_decl (decl, /*defer_ok*/true, /*expl*/false);
6832 return;
6833 }
6834
6835 gcc_assert (CLASS_PLACEHOLDER_TEMPLATE (auto_node));
6836 }
6837 d_init = init;
6838 if (d_init)
6839 {
6840 if (TREE_CODE (d_init) == TREE_LIST
6841 && !CLASS_PLACEHOLDER_TEMPLATE (auto_node))
6842 d_init = build_x_compound_expr_from_list (d_init, ELK_INIT,
6843 tf_warning_or_error);
6844 d_init = resolve_nondeduced_context (d_init, tf_warning_or_error);
6845 }
6846 enum auto_deduction_context adc = adc_variable_type;
6847 if (VAR_P (decl) && DECL_DECOMPOSITION_P (decl))
6848 adc = adc_decomp_type;
6849 type = TREE_TYPE (decl) = do_auto_deduction (type, d_init, auto_node,
6850 tf_warning_or_error, adc,
6851 NULL_TREE, flags);
6852 if (type == error_mark_node)
6853 return;
6854 if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
6855 {
6856 error ("initializer for %<decltype(auto) %D%> has function type "
6857 "(did you forget the %<()%> ?)", decl);
6858 TREE_TYPE (decl) = error_mark_node;
6859 return;
6860 }
6861 cp_apply_type_quals_to_decl (cp_type_quals (type), decl);
6862 }
6863
6864 if (!ensure_literal_type_for_constexpr_object (decl))
6865 DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (decl) = 0;
6866
6867 if (VAR_P (decl)
6868 && DECL_CLASS_SCOPE_P (decl)
6869 && DECL_INITIALIZED_IN_CLASS_P (decl))
6870 check_static_variable_definition (decl, type);
6871
6872 if (init && TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
6873 {
6874 tree clone;
6875 if (init == ridpointers[(int)RID_DELETE])
6876 {
6877 /* FIXME check this is 1st decl. */
6878 DECL_DELETED_FN (decl) = 1;
6879 DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl) = 1;
6880 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = error_mark_node;
6881 FOR_EACH_CLONE (clone, decl)
6882 {
6883 DECL_DELETED_FN (clone) = 1;
6884 DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (clone) = 1;
6885 DECL_INITIAL (clone) = error_mark_node;
6886 }
6887 init = NULL_TREE;
6888 }
6889 else if (init == ridpointers[(int)RID_DEFAULT])
6890 {
6891 if (defaultable_fn_check (decl))
6892 DECL_DEFAULTED_FN (decl) = 1;
6893 else
6894 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = NULL_TREE;
6895 }
6896 }
6897
6898 if (init && VAR_P (decl))
6899 {
6900 DECL_NONTRIVIALLY_INITIALIZED_P (decl) = 1;
6901 /* If DECL is a reference, then we want to know whether init is a
6902 reference constant; init_const_expr_p as passed tells us whether
6903 it's an rvalue constant. */
6904 if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
6905 init_const_expr_p = potential_constant_expression (init);
6906 if (init_const_expr_p)
6907 {
6908 /* Set these flags now for templates. We'll update the flags in
6909 store_init_value for instantiations. */
6910 DECL_INITIALIZED_BY_CONSTANT_EXPRESSION_P (decl) = 1;
6911 if (decl_maybe_constant_var_p (decl)
6912 /* FIXME setting TREE_CONSTANT on refs breaks the back end. */
6913 && TREE_CODE (type) != REFERENCE_TYPE)
6914 TREE_CONSTANT (decl) = 1;
6915 }
6916 }
6917
6918 if (processing_template_decl)
6919 {
6920 bool type_dependent_p;
6921
6922 /* Add this declaration to the statement-tree. */
6923 if (at_function_scope_p ())
6924 add_decl_expr (decl);
6925
6926 type_dependent_p = dependent_type_p (type);
6927
6928 if (check_for_bare_parameter_packs (init))
6929 {
6930 init = NULL_TREE;
6931 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = NULL_TREE;
6932 }
6933
6934 /* Generally, initializers in templates are expanded when the
6935 template is instantiated. But, if DECL is a variable constant
6936 then it can be used in future constant expressions, so its value
6937 must be available. */
6938
6939 if (!VAR_P (decl) || type_dependent_p)
6940 /* We can't do anything if the decl has dependent type. */;
6941 else if (init
6942 && init_const_expr_p
6943 && TREE_CODE (type) != REFERENCE_TYPE
6944 && decl_maybe_constant_var_p (decl)
6945 && !type_dependent_init_p (init)
6946 && !value_dependent_init_p (init))
6947 {
6948 /* This variable seems to be a non-dependent constant, so process
6949 its initializer. If check_initializer returns non-null the
6950 initialization wasn't constant after all. */
6951 tree init_code;
6952 cleanups = make_tree_vector ();
6953 init_code = check_initializer (decl, init, flags, &cleanups);
6954 if (init_code == NULL_TREE)
6955 init = NULL_TREE;
6956 release_tree_vector (cleanups);
6957 }
6958 else if (!init && is_concept_var (decl))
6959 error ("variable concept has no initializer");
6960 else if (!DECL_PRETTY_FUNCTION_P (decl))
6961 {
6962 /* Deduce array size even if the initializer is dependent. */
6963 maybe_deduce_size_from_array_init (decl, init);
6964 /* And complain about multiple initializers. */
6965 if (init && TREE_CODE (init) == TREE_LIST && TREE_CHAIN (init)
6966 && !MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
6967 init = build_x_compound_expr_from_list (init, ELK_INIT,
6968 tf_warning_or_error);
6969 }
6970
6971 if (init)
6972 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = init;
6973 return;
6974 }
6975
6976 /* Just store non-static data member initializers for later. */
6977 if (init && TREE_CODE (decl) == FIELD_DECL)
6978 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = init;
6979
6980 /* Take care of TYPE_DECLs up front. */
6981 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL)
6982 {
6983 if (type != error_mark_node
6984 && MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (type) && DECL_NAME (decl))
6985 {
6986 if (TREE_TYPE (DECL_NAME (decl)) && TREE_TYPE (decl) != type)
6987 warning (0, "shadowing previous type declaration of %q#D", decl);
6988 set_identifier_type_value (DECL_NAME (decl), decl);
6989 }
6990
6991 /* If we have installed this as the canonical typedef for this
6992 type, and that type has not been defined yet, delay emitting
6993 the debug information for it, as we will emit it later. */
6994 if (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (TREE_TYPE (decl)) == decl
6995 && !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
6996 TYPE_DECL_SUPPRESS_DEBUG (decl) = 1;
6997
6998 rest_of_decl_compilation (decl, DECL_FILE_SCOPE_P (decl),
6999 at_eof);
7000 return;
7001 }
7002
7003 /* A reference will be modified here, as it is initialized. */
7004 if (! DECL_EXTERNAL (decl)
7005 && TREE_READONLY (decl)
7006 && TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
7007 {
7008 was_readonly = 1;
7009 TREE_READONLY (decl) = 0;
7010 }
7011
7012 if (VAR_P (decl))
7013 {
7014 /* If this is a local variable that will need a mangled name,
7015 register it now. We must do this before processing the
7016 initializer for the variable, since the initialization might
7017 require a guard variable, and since the mangled name of the
7018 guard variable will depend on the mangled name of this
7019 variable. */
7020 if (DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (decl)
7021 && TREE_STATIC (decl)
7022 && !DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl))
7023 {
7024 push_local_name (decl);
7025 /* Normally has_forced_label_in_static is set during GIMPLE
7026 lowering, but [cd]tors are never actually compiled directly.
7027 We need to set this early so we can deal with the label
7028 address extension. */
7029 if ((DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (current_function_decl)
7030 || DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (current_function_decl))
7031 && init)
7032 {
7033 walk_tree (&init, notice_forced_label_r, NULL, NULL);
7034 add_local_decl (cfun, decl);
7035 }
7036 /* And make sure it's in the symbol table for
7037 c_parse_final_cleanups to find. */
7038 varpool_node::get_create (decl);
7039 }
7040
7041 /* Convert the initializer to the type of DECL, if we have not
7042 already initialized DECL. */
7043 if (!DECL_INITIALIZED_P (decl)
7044 /* If !DECL_EXTERNAL then DECL is being defined. In the
7045 case of a static data member initialized inside the
7046 class-specifier, there can be an initializer even if DECL
7047 is *not* defined. */
7048 && (!DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) || init))
7049 {
7050 cleanups = make_tree_vector ();
7051 init = check_initializer (decl, init, flags, &cleanups);
7052
7053 /* Handle:
7054
7055 [dcl.init]
7056
7057 The memory occupied by any object of static storage
7058 duration is zero-initialized at program startup before
7059 any other initialization takes place.
7060
7061 We cannot create an appropriate initializer until after
7062 the type of DECL is finalized. If DECL_INITIAL is set,
7063 then the DECL is statically initialized, and any
7064 necessary zero-initialization has already been performed. */
7065 if (TREE_STATIC (decl) && !DECL_INITIAL (decl))
7066 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = build_zero_init (TREE_TYPE (decl),
7067 /*nelts=*/NULL_TREE,
7068 /*static_storage_p=*/true);
7069 /* Remember that the initialization for this variable has
7070 taken place. */
7071 DECL_INITIALIZED_P (decl) = 1;
7072 /* This declaration is the definition of this variable,
7073 unless we are initializing a static data member within
7074 the class specifier. */
7075 if (!DECL_EXTERNAL (decl))
7076 var_definition_p = true;
7077 }
7078 /* If the variable has an array type, lay out the type, even if
7079 there is no initializer. It is valid to index through the
7080 array, and we must get TYPE_ALIGN set correctly on the array
7081 type. */
7082 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
7083 layout_type (type);
7084
7085 if (TREE_STATIC (decl)
7086 && !at_function_scope_p ()
7087 && current_function_decl == NULL)
7088 /* So decl is a global variable or a static member of a
7089 non local class. Record the types it uses
7090 so that we can decide later to emit debug info for them. */
7091 record_types_used_by_current_var_decl (decl);
7092 }
7093
7094 /* Add this declaration to the statement-tree. This needs to happen
7095 after the call to check_initializer so that the DECL_EXPR for a
7096 reference temp is added before the DECL_EXPR for the reference itself. */
7097 if (DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (decl))
7098 {
7099 /* If we're building a variable sized type, and we might be
7100 reachable other than via the top of the current binding
7101 level, then create a new BIND_EXPR so that we deallocate
7102 the object at the right time. */
7103 if (VAR_P (decl)
7104 && DECL_SIZE (decl)
7105 && !TREE_CONSTANT (DECL_SIZE (decl))
7106 && STATEMENT_LIST_HAS_LABEL (cur_stmt_list))
7107 {
7108 tree bind;
7109 bind = build3 (BIND_EXPR, void_type_node, NULL, NULL, NULL);
7110 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (bind) = 1;
7111 add_stmt (bind);
7112 BIND_EXPR_BODY (bind) = push_stmt_list ();
7113 }
7114 add_decl_expr (decl);
7115 }
7116
7117 /* Let the middle end know about variables and functions -- but not
7118 static data members in uninstantiated class templates. */
7119 if (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (decl))
7120 {
7121 if (VAR_P (decl))
7122 {
7123 layout_var_decl (decl);
7124 maybe_commonize_var (decl);
7125 }
7126
7127 /* This needs to happen after the linkage is set. */
7128 determine_visibility (decl);
7129
7130 if (var_definition_p && TREE_STATIC (decl))
7131 {
7132 /* If a TREE_READONLY variable needs initialization
7133 at runtime, it is no longer readonly and we need to
7134 avoid MEM_READONLY_P being set on RTL created for it. */
7135 if (init)
7136 {
7137 if (TREE_READONLY (decl))
7138 TREE_READONLY (decl) = 0;
7139 was_readonly = 0;
7140 }
7141 else if (was_readonly)
7142 TREE_READONLY (decl) = 1;
7143
7144 /* Likewise if it needs destruction. */
7145 if (TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (type))
7146 TREE_READONLY (decl) = 0;
7147 }
7148
7149 make_rtl_for_nonlocal_decl (decl, init, asmspec);
7150
7151 /* Check for abstractness of the type. Notice that there is no
7152 need to strip array types here since the check for those types
7153 is already done within create_array_type_for_decl. */
7154 abstract_virtuals_error (decl, type);
7155
7156 if (TREE_TYPE (decl) == error_mark_node)
7157 /* No initialization required. */
7158 ;
7159 else if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
7160 {
7161 if (init)
7162 {
7163 if (init == ridpointers[(int)RID_DEFAULT])
7164 {
7165 /* An out-of-class default definition is defined at
7166 the point where it is explicitly defaulted. */
7167 if (DECL_DELETED_FN (decl))
7168 maybe_explain_implicit_delete (decl);
7169 else if (DECL_INITIAL (decl) == error_mark_node)
7170 synthesize_method (decl);
7171 }
7172 else
7173 error ("function %q#D is initialized like a variable", decl);
7174 }
7175 /* else no initialization required. */
7176 }
7177 else if (DECL_EXTERNAL (decl)
7178 && ! (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl)
7179 && DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (decl)))
7180 {
7181 if (init)
7182 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = init;
7183 }
7184 /* A variable definition. */
7185 else if (DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (decl) && !TREE_STATIC (decl))
7186 /* Initialize the local variable. */
7187 initialize_local_var (decl, init);
7188
7189 /* If a variable is defined, and then a subsequent
7190 definition with external linkage is encountered, we will
7191 get here twice for the same variable. We want to avoid
7192 calling expand_static_init more than once. For variables
7193 that are not static data members, we can call
7194 expand_static_init only when we actually process the
7195 initializer. It is not legal to redeclare a static data
7196 member, so this issue does not arise in that case. */
7197 else if (var_definition_p && TREE_STATIC (decl))
7198 expand_static_init (decl, init);
7199 }
7200
7201 /* If a CLEANUP_STMT was created to destroy a temporary bound to a
7202 reference, insert it in the statement-tree now. */
7203 if (cleanups)
7204 {
7205 unsigned i; tree t;
7206 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (*cleanups, i, t)
7207 push_cleanup (decl, t, false);
7208 release_tree_vector (cleanups);
7209 }
7210
7211 if (was_readonly)
7212 TREE_READONLY (decl) = 1;
7213
7214 invoke_plugin_callbacks (PLUGIN_FINISH_DECL, decl);
7215}
7216
7217/* For class TYPE return itself or some its bases that contain
7218 any direct non-static data members. Return error_mark_node if an
