7219 error has been diagnosed. */
7220
7221static tree
7222find_decomp_class_base (location_t loc, tree type, tree ret)
7223{
7224 bool member_seen = false;
7225 for (tree field = TYPE_FIELDS (type); field; field = DECL_CHAIN (field))
7226 if (TREE_CODE (field) != FIELD_DECL
7227 || DECL_ARTIFICIAL (field)
7228 || (DECL_C_BIT_FIELD (field) && !DECL_NAME (field)))
7229 continue;
7230 else if (ret)
7231 return type;
7232 else if (ANON_AGGR_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (field)))
7233 {
7234 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (field)) == RECORD_TYPE)
7235 error_at (loc, "cannot decompose class type %qT because it has an "
7236 "anonymous struct member", type);
7237 else
7238 error_at (loc, "cannot decompose class type %qT because it has an "
7239 "anonymous union member", type);
7240 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (field), "declared here");
7241 return error_mark_node;
7242 }
7243 else if (!accessible_p (type, field, true))
7244 {
7245 error_at (loc, "cannot decompose inaccessible member %qD of %qT",
7246 field, type);
7247 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (field),
7248 TREE_PRIVATE (field)
7249 ? G_("declared private here")
7250 : G_("declared protected here"));
7251 return error_mark_node;
7252 }
7253 else
7254 member_seen = true;
7255
7256 tree base_binfo, binfo;
7257 tree orig_ret = ret;
7258 int i;
7259 if (member_seen)
7260 ret = type;
7261 for (binfo = TYPE_BINFO (type), i = 0;
7262 BINFO_BASE_ITERATE (binfo, i, base_binfo); i++)
7263 {
7264 tree t = find_decomp_class_base (loc, TREE_TYPE (base_binfo), ret);
7265 if (t == error_mark_node)
7266 return error_mark_node;
7267 if (t != NULL_TREE && t != ret)
7268 {
7269 if (ret == type)
7270 {
7271 error_at (loc, "cannot decompose class type %qT: both it and "
7272 "its base class %qT have non-static data members",
7273 type, t);
7274 return error_mark_node;
7275 }
7276 else if (orig_ret != NULL_TREE)
7277 return t;
7278 else if (ret != NULL_TREE)
7279 {
7280 error_at (loc, "cannot decompose class type %qT: its base "
7281 "classes %qT and %qT have non-static data "
7282 "members", type, ret, t);
7283 return error_mark_node;
7284 }
7285 else
7286 ret = t;
7287 }
7288 }
7289 return ret;
7290}
7291
7292/* Return std::tuple_size<TYPE>::value. */
7293
7294static tree
7295get_tuple_size (tree type)
7296{
7297 tree args = make_tree_vec (1);
7298 TREE_VEC_ELT (args, 0) = type;
7299 tree inst = lookup_template_class (get_identifier ("tuple_size"), args,
7300 /*in_decl*/NULL_TREE,
7301 /*context*/std_node,
7302 /*entering_scope*/false, tf_none);
7303 inst = complete_type (inst);
7304 if (inst == error_mark_node || !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (inst))
7305 return NULL_TREE;
7306 tree val = lookup_qualified_name (inst, get_identifier ("value"),
7307 /*type*/false, /*complain*/false);
7308 if (TREE_CODE (val) == VAR_DECL || TREE_CODE (val) == CONST_DECL)
7309 val = maybe_constant_value (val);
7310 if (TREE_CODE (val) == INTEGER_CST)
7311 return val;
7312 else
7313 return error_mark_node;
7314}
7315
7316/* Return std::tuple_element<I,TYPE>::type. */
7317
7318static tree
7319get_tuple_element_type (tree type, unsigned i)
7320{
7321 tree args = make_tree_vec (2);
7322 TREE_VEC_ELT (args, 0) = build_int_cst (integer_type_node, i);
7323 TREE_VEC_ELT (args, 1) = type;
7324 tree inst = lookup_template_class (get_identifier ("tuple_element"), args,
7325 /*in_decl*/NULL_TREE,
7326 /*context*/std_node,
7327 /*entering_scope*/false,
7328 tf_warning_or_error);
7329 return make_typename_type (inst, get_identifier ("type"),
7330 none_type, tf_warning_or_error);
7331}
7332
7333/* Return e.get<i>() or get<i>(e). */
7334
7335static tree
7336get_tuple_decomp_init (tree decl, unsigned i)
7337{
7338 tree get_id = get_identifier ("get");
7339 tree targs = make_tree_vec (1);
7340 TREE_VEC_ELT (targs, 0) = build_int_cst (integer_type_node, i);
7341
7342 tree etype = TREE_TYPE (decl);
7343 tree e = convert_from_reference (decl);
7344
7345 /* [The id-expression] e is an lvalue if the type of the entity e is an
7346 lvalue reference and an xvalue otherwise. */
7347 if (TREE_CODE (etype) != REFERENCE_TYPE
7348 || TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (etype))
7349 e = move (e);
7350
7351 tree fns = lookup_qualified_name (TREE_TYPE (e), get_id,
7352 /*type*/false, /*complain*/false);
7353 bool use_member_get = false;
7354
7355 /* To use a member get, member lookup must find at least one
7356 declaration that is a function template
7357 whose first template parameter is a non-type parameter. */
7358 for (tree iter = BASELINK_P (fns) ? BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (fns) : fns;
7359 iter;
7360 iter = OVL_NEXT (iter))
7361 {
7362 tree fn = OVL_CURRENT (iter);
7363 if (TREE_CODE (fn) == TEMPLATE_DECL)
7364 {
7365 tree tparms = DECL_TEMPLATE_PARMS (fn);
7366 tree parm = TREE_VEC_ELT (INNERMOST_TEMPLATE_PARMS (tparms), 0);
7367 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_VALUE (parm)) == PARM_DECL)
7368 {
7369 use_member_get = true;
7370 break;
7371 }
7372 }
7373 }
7374
7375 if (use_member_get)
7376 {
7377 fns = lookup_template_function (fns, targs);
7378 return build_new_method_call (e, fns, /*args*/NULL,
7379 /*path*/NULL_TREE, LOOKUP_NORMAL,
7380 /*fn_p*/NULL, tf_warning_or_error);
7381 }
7382 else
7383 {
7384 vec<tree,va_gc> *args = make_tree_vector_single (e);
7385 fns = lookup_template_function (get_id, targs);
7386 fns = perform_koenig_lookup (fns, args, tf_warning_or_error);
7387 return finish_call_expr (fns, &args, /*novirt*/false,
7388 /*koenig*/true, tf_warning_or_error);
7389 }
7390}
7391
7392/* It's impossible to recover the decltype of a tuple decomposition variable
7393 based on the actual type of the variable, so store it in a hash table. */
7394static GTY(()) hash_map<tree,tree> *decomp_type_table;
7395static void
7396store_decomp_type (tree v, tree t)
7397{
7398 if (!decomp_type_table)
7399 decomp_type_table = hash_map<tree,tree>::create_ggc (13);
7400 decomp_type_table->put (v, t);
7401}
7402
7403tree
7404lookup_decomp_type (tree v)
7405{
7406 return *decomp_type_table->get (v);
7407}
7408
7409/* Mangle a decomposition declaration if needed. Arguments like
7410 in cp_finish_decomp. */
7411
7412void
7413cp_maybe_mangle_decomp (tree decl, tree first, unsigned int count)
7414{
7415 if (!processing_template_decl
7416 && !error_operand_p (decl)
7417 && DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (decl))
7418 {
7419 auto_vec<tree, 16> v;
7420 v.safe_grow (count);
7421 tree d = first;
7422 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++, d = DECL_CHAIN (d))
7423 v[count - i - 1] = d;
7424 SET_DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (decl, mangle_decomp (decl, v));
7425 maybe_apply_pragma_weak (decl);
7426 }
7427}
7428
7429/* Finish a decomposition declaration. DECL is the underlying declaration
7430 "e", FIRST is the head of a chain of decls for the individual identifiers
7431 chained through DECL_CHAIN in reverse order and COUNT is the number of
7432 those decls. */
7433
7434void
7435cp_finish_decomp (tree decl, tree first, unsigned int count)
7436{
7437 if (error_operand_p (decl))
7438 {
7439 error_out:
7440 while (count--)
7441 {
7442 TREE_TYPE (first) = error_mark_node;
7443 if (DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (first))
7444 {
7445 SET_DECL_VALUE_EXPR (first, NULL_TREE);
7446 DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (first) = 0;
7447 }
7448 first = DECL_CHAIN (first);
7449 }
7450 if (DECL_P (decl) && DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (decl))
7451 SET_DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (decl, get_identifier ("<decomp>"));
7452 return;
7453 }
7454
7455 location_t loc = DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl);
7456 if (type_dependent_expression_p (decl)
7457 /* This happens for range for when not in templates.
7458 Still add the DECL_VALUE_EXPRs for later processing. */
7459 || (!processing_template_decl
7460 && type_uses_auto (TREE_TYPE (decl))))
7461 {
7462 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
7463 {
7464 if (!DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (first))
7465 {
7466 tree v = build_nt (ARRAY_REF, decl,
7467 size_int (count - i - 1),
7468 NULL_TREE, NULL_TREE);
7469 SET_DECL_VALUE_EXPR (first, v);
7470 DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (first) = 1;
7471 }
7472 if (processing_template_decl)
7473 {
7474 retrofit_lang_decl (first);
7475 SET_DECL_DECOMPOSITION_P (first);
7476 }
7477 first = DECL_CHAIN (first);
7478 }
7479 return;
7480 }
7481
7482 auto_vec<tree, 16> v;
7483 v.safe_grow (count);
7484 tree d = first;
7485 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++, d = DECL_CHAIN (d))
7486 {
7487 v[count - i - 1] = d;
7488 retrofit_lang_decl (d);
7489 SET_DECL_DECOMPOSITION_P (d);
7490 }
7491
7492 tree type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
7493 tree dexp = decl;
7494
7495 if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
7496 {
7497 dexp = convert_from_reference (dexp);
7498 type = complete_type (TREE_TYPE (type));
7499 if (type == error_mark_node)
7500 goto error_out;
7501 if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type))
7502 {
7503 error_at (loc, "structured binding refers to incomplete type %qT",
7504 type);
7505 goto error_out;
7506 }
7507 }
7508
7509 tree eltype = NULL_TREE;
7510 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT eltscnt = 0;
7511 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
7512 {
7513 tree nelts;
7514 nelts = array_type_nelts_top (type);
7515 if (nelts == error_mark_node)
7516 goto error_out;
7517 if (!tree_fits_uhwi_p (nelts))
7518 {
7519 error_at (loc, "cannot decompose variable length array %qT", type);
7520 goto error_out;
7521 }
7522 eltscnt = tree_to_uhwi (nelts);
7523 if (count != eltscnt)
7524 {
7525 cnt_mismatch:
7526 if (count > eltscnt)
7527 error_n (loc, count,
7528 "%u name provided for structured binding",
7529 "%u names provided for structured binding", count);
7530 else
7531 error_n (loc, count,
7532 "only %u name provided for structured binding",
7533 "only %u names provided for structured binding", count);
7534 /* Some languages have special plural rules even for large values,
7535 but it is periodic with period of 10, 100, 1000 etc. */
7536 inform_n (loc, eltscnt > INT_MAX
7537 ? (eltscnt % 1000000) + 1000000 : eltscnt,
7538 "while %qT decomposes into %wu element",
7539 "while %qT decomposes into %wu elements",
7540 type, eltscnt);
7541 goto error_out;
7542 }
7543 eltype = TREE_TYPE (type);
7544 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
7545 {
7546 TREE_TYPE (v[i]) = eltype;
7547 layout_decl (v[i], 0);
7548 if (processing_template_decl)
7549 continue;
7550 tree t = unshare_expr (dexp);
7551 t = build4_loc (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (v[i]), ARRAY_REF,
7552 eltype, t, size_int (i), NULL_TREE,
7553 NULL_TREE);
7554 SET_DECL_VALUE_EXPR (v[i], t);
7555 DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (v[i]) = 1;
7556 }
7557 }
7558 /* 2 GNU extensions. */
7559 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == COMPLEX_TYPE)
7560 {
7561 eltscnt = 2;
7562 if (count != eltscnt)
7563 goto cnt_mismatch;
7564 eltype = cp_build_qualified_type (TREE_TYPE (type), TYPE_QUALS (type));
7565 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
7566 {
7567 TREE_TYPE (v[i]) = eltype;
7568 layout_decl (v[i], 0);
7569 if (processing_template_decl)
7570 continue;
7571 tree t = unshare_expr (dexp);
7572 t = build1_loc (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (v[i]),
7573 i ? IMAGPART_EXPR : REALPART_EXPR, eltype,
7574 t);
7575 SET_DECL_VALUE_EXPR (v[i], t);
7576 DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (v[i]) = 1;
7577 }
7578 }
7579 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == VECTOR_TYPE)
7580 {
7581 eltscnt = TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (type);
7582 if (count != eltscnt)
7583 goto cnt_mismatch;
7584 eltype = cp_build_qualified_type (TREE_TYPE (type), TYPE_QUALS (type));
7585 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
7586 {
7587 TREE_TYPE (v[i]) = eltype;
7588 layout_decl (v[i], 0);
7589 if (processing_template_decl)
7590 continue;
7591 tree t = unshare_expr (dexp);
7592 convert_vector_to_array_for_subscript (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (v[i]),
7593 &t, size_int (i));
7594 t = build4_loc (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (v[i]), ARRAY_REF,
7595 eltype, t, size_int (i), NULL_TREE,
7596 NULL_TREE);
7597 SET_DECL_VALUE_EXPR (v[i], t);
7598 DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (v[i]) = 1;
7599 }
7600 }
7601 else if (tree tsize = get_tuple_size (type))
7602 {
7603 if (tsize == error_mark_node)
7604 {
7605 error_at (loc, "%<std::tuple_size<%T>::value%> is not an integral "
7606 "constant expression", type);
7607 goto error_out;
7608 }
7609 if (!tree_fits_uhwi_p (tsize))
7610 {
7611 error_n (loc, count,
7612 "%u name provided for structured binding",
7613 "%u names provided for structured binding", count);
7614 inform (loc, "while %qT decomposes into %E elements",
7615 type, tsize);
7616 goto error_out;
7617 }
7618 eltscnt = tree_to_uhwi (tsize);
7619 if (count != eltscnt)
7620 goto cnt_mismatch;
7621 for (unsigned i = 0; i < count; ++i)
7622 {
7623 location_t sloc = input_location;
7624 location_t dloc = DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (v[i]);
7625
7626 input_location = dloc;
7627 tree init = get_tuple_decomp_init (decl, i);
7628 tree eltype = (init == error_mark_node ? error_mark_node
7629 : get_tuple_element_type (type, i));
7630 input_location = sloc;
7631
7632 if (init == error_mark_node || eltype == error_mark_node)
7633 {
7634 inform (dloc, "in initialization of decomposition variable %qD",
7635 v[i]);
7636 goto error_out;
7637 }
7638 /* Save the decltype away before reference collapse. */
7639 store_decomp_type (v[i], eltype);
7640 eltype = cp_build_reference_type (eltype, !lvalue_p (init));
7641 TREE_TYPE (v[i]) = eltype;
7642 layout_decl (v[i], 0);
7643 if (DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (v[i]))
7644 {
7645 /* In this case the names are variables, not just proxies. */
7646 SET_DECL_VALUE_EXPR (v[i], NULL_TREE);
7647 DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (v[i]) = 0;
7648 }
7649 if (!processing_template_decl)
7650 cp_finish_decl (v[i], init, /*constexpr*/false,
7651 /*asm*/NULL_TREE, LOOKUP_NORMAL);
7652 }
7653 }
7654 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == UNION_TYPE)
7655 {
7656 error_at (loc, "cannot decompose union type %qT", type);
7657 goto error_out;
7658 }
7659 else if (!CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
7660 {
7661 error_at (loc, "cannot decompose non-array non-class type %qT", type);
7662 goto error_out;
7663 }
7664 else if (LAMBDA_TYPE_P (type))
7665 {
7666 error_at (loc, "cannot decompose lambda closure type %qT", type);
7667 goto error_out;
7668 }
7669 else
7670 {
7671 tree btype = find_decomp_class_base (loc, type, NULL_TREE);
7672 if (btype == error_mark_node)
7673 goto error_out;
7674 else if (btype == NULL_TREE)
7675 {
7676 error_at (loc, "cannot decompose class type %qT without non-static "
7677 "data members", type);
7678 goto error_out;
7679 }
7680 for (tree field = TYPE_FIELDS (btype); field; field = TREE_CHAIN (field))
7681 if (TREE_CODE (field) != FIELD_DECL
7682 || DECL_ARTIFICIAL (field)
7683 || (DECL_C_BIT_FIELD (field) && !DECL_NAME (field)))
7684 continue;
7685 else
7686 eltscnt++;
7687 if (count != eltscnt)
7688 goto cnt_mismatch;
7689 tree t = dexp;
7690 if (type != btype)
7691 {
7692 t = convert_to_base (t, btype, /*check_access*/true,
7693 /*nonnull*/false, tf_warning_or_error);
7694 type = btype;
7695 }
7696 unsigned int i = 0;
7697 for (tree field = TYPE_FIELDS (btype); field; field = TREE_CHAIN (field))
7698 if (TREE_CODE (field) != FIELD_DECL
7699 || DECL_ARTIFICIAL (field)
7700 || (DECL_C_BIT_FIELD (field) && !DECL_NAME (field)))
7701 continue;
7702 else
7703 {
7704 tree tt = finish_non_static_data_member (field, unshare_expr (t),
7705 NULL_TREE);
7706 if (REFERENCE_REF_P (tt))
7707 tt = TREE_OPERAND (tt, 0);
7708 TREE_TYPE (v[i]) = TREE_TYPE (tt);
7709 layout_decl (v[i], 0);
7710 if (!processing_template_decl)
7711 {
7712 SET_DECL_VALUE_EXPR (v[i], tt);
7713 DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (v[i]) = 1;
7714 }
7715 i++;
7716 }
7717 }
7718 if (processing_template_decl)
7719 {
7720 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
7721 if (!DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (v[i]))
7722 {
7723 tree a = build_nt (ARRAY_REF, decl, size_int (i),
7724 NULL_TREE, NULL_TREE);
7725 SET_DECL_VALUE_EXPR (v[i], a);
7726 DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (v[i]) = 1;
7727 }
7728 }
7729}
7730
7731/* Returns a declaration for a VAR_DECL as if:
7732
7733 extern "C" TYPE NAME;
7734
7735 had been seen. Used to create compiler-generated global
7736 variables. */
7737
7738static tree
7739declare_global_var (tree name, tree type)
7740{
7741 tree decl;
7742
7743 push_to_top_level ();
7744 decl = build_decl (input_location, VAR_DECL, name, type);
7745 TREE_PUBLIC (decl) = 1;
7746 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 1;
7747 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl) = 1;
7748 /* If the user has explicitly declared this variable (perhaps
7749 because the code we are compiling is part of a low-level runtime
7750 library), then it is possible that our declaration will be merged
7751 with theirs by pushdecl. */
7752 decl = pushdecl (decl);
7753 cp_finish_decl (decl, NULL_TREE, false, NULL_TREE, 0);
7754 pop_from_top_level ();
7755
7756 return decl;
7757}
7758
7759/* Returns the type for the argument to "__cxa_atexit" (or "atexit",
7760 if "__cxa_atexit" is not being used) corresponding to the function
7761 to be called when the program exits. */
7762
7763static tree
7764get_atexit_fn_ptr_type (void)
7765{
7766 tree fn_type;
7767
7768 if (!atexit_fn_ptr_type_node)
7769 {
7770 tree arg_type;
7771 if (flag_use_cxa_atexit
7772 && !targetm.cxx.use_atexit_for_cxa_atexit ())
7773 /* The parameter to "__cxa_atexit" is "void (*)(void *)". */
7774 arg_type = ptr_type_node;
7775 else
7776 /* The parameter to "atexit" is "void (*)(void)". */
7777 arg_type = NULL_TREE;
7778
7779 fn_type = build_function_type_list (void_type_node,
7780 arg_type, NULL_TREE);
7781 atexit_fn_ptr_type_node = build_pointer_type (fn_type);
7782 }
7783
7784 return atexit_fn_ptr_type_node;
7785}
7786
7787/* Returns a pointer to the `atexit' function. Note that if
7788 FLAG_USE_CXA_ATEXIT is nonzero, then this will actually be the new
7789 `__cxa_atexit' function specified in the IA64 C++ ABI. */
7790
7791static tree
7792get_atexit_node (void)
7793{
7794 tree atexit_fndecl;
7795 tree fn_type;
7796 tree fn_ptr_type;
7797 const char *name;
7798 bool use_aeabi_atexit;
7799
7800 if (atexit_node)
7801 return atexit_node;
7802
7803 if (flag_use_cxa_atexit && !targetm.cxx.use_atexit_for_cxa_atexit ())
7804 {
7805 /* The declaration for `__cxa_atexit' is:
7806
7807 int __cxa_atexit (void (*)(void *), void *, void *)
7808
7809 We build up the argument types and then the function type
7810 itself. */
7811 tree argtype0, argtype1, argtype2;
7812
7813 use_aeabi_atexit = targetm.cxx.use_aeabi_atexit ();
7814 /* First, build the pointer-to-function type for the first
7815 argument. */
7816 fn_ptr_type = get_atexit_fn_ptr_type ();
7817 /* Then, build the rest of the argument types. */
7818 argtype2 = ptr_type_node;
7819 if (use_aeabi_atexit)
7820 {
7821 argtype1 = fn_ptr_type;
7822 argtype0 = ptr_type_node;
7823 }
7824 else
7825 {
7826 argtype1 = ptr_type_node;
7827 argtype0 = fn_ptr_type;
7828 }
7829 /* And the final __cxa_atexit type. */
7830 fn_type = build_function_type_list (integer_type_node,
7831 argtype0, argtype1, argtype2,
7832 NULL_TREE);
7833 if (use_aeabi_atexit)
7834 name = "__aeabi_atexit";
7835 else
7836 name = "__cxa_atexit";
7837 }
7838 else
7839 {
7840 /* The declaration for `atexit' is:
7841
7842 int atexit (void (*)());
7843
7844 We build up the argument types and then the function type
7845 itself. */
7846 fn_ptr_type = get_atexit_fn_ptr_type ();
7847 /* Build the final atexit type. */
7848 fn_type = build_function_type_list (integer_type_node,
7849 fn_ptr_type, NULL_TREE);
7850 name = "atexit";
7851 }
7852
7853 /* Now, build the function declaration. */
7854 push_lang_context (lang_name_c);
7855 atexit_fndecl = build_library_fn_ptr (name, fn_type, ECF_LEAF | ECF_NOTHROW);
7856 mark_used (atexit_fndecl);
7857 pop_lang_context ();
7858 atexit_node = decay_conversion (atexit_fndecl, tf_warning_or_error);
7859
7860 return atexit_node;
7861}
7862
7863/* Like get_atexit_node, but for thread-local cleanups. */
7864
7865static tree
7866get_thread_atexit_node (void)
7867{
7868 /* The declaration for `__cxa_thread_atexit' is:
7869
7870 int __cxa_thread_atexit (void (*)(void *), void *, void *) */
7871 tree fn_type = build_function_type_list (integer_type_node,
7872 get_atexit_fn_ptr_type (),
7873 ptr_type_node, ptr_type_node,
7874 NULL_TREE);
7875
7876 /* Now, build the function declaration. */
7877 tree atexit_fndecl = build_library_fn_ptr ("__cxa_thread_atexit", fn_type,
7878 ECF_LEAF | ECF_NOTHROW);
7879 return decay_conversion (atexit_fndecl, tf_warning_or_error);
7880}
7881
7882/* Returns the __dso_handle VAR_DECL. */
7883
7884static tree
7885get_dso_handle_node (void)
7886{
7887 if (dso_handle_node)
7888 return dso_handle_node;
7889
7890 /* Declare the variable. */
7891 dso_handle_node = declare_global_var (get_identifier ("__dso_handle"),
7892 ptr_type_node);
7893
7894#ifdef HAVE_GAS_HIDDEN
7895 if (dso_handle_node != error_mark_node)
7896 {
7897 DECL_VISIBILITY (dso_handle_node) = VISIBILITY_HIDDEN;
7898 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (dso_handle_node) = 1;
7899 }
7900#endif
7901
7902 return dso_handle_node;
7903}
7904
7905/* Begin a new function with internal linkage whose job will be simply
7906 to destroy some particular variable. */
7907
7908static GTY(()) int start_cleanup_cnt;
7909
7910static tree
7911start_cleanup_fn (void)
7912{
7913 char name[32];
7914 tree fntype;
7915 tree fndecl;
7916 bool use_cxa_atexit = flag_use_cxa_atexit
7917 && !targetm.cxx.use_atexit_for_cxa_atexit ();
7918
7919 push_to_top_level ();
7920
7921 /* No need to mangle this. */
7922 push_lang_context (lang_name_c);
7923
7924 /* Build the name of the function. */
7925 sprintf (name, "__tcf_%d", start_cleanup_cnt++);
7926 /* Build the function declaration. */
7927 fntype = TREE_TYPE (get_atexit_fn_ptr_type ());
7928 fndecl = build_lang_decl (FUNCTION_DECL, get_identifier (name), fntype);
7929 /* It's a function with internal linkage, generated by the
7930 compiler. */
7931 TREE_PUBLIC (fndecl) = 0;
7932 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (fndecl) = 1;
7933 /* Make the function `inline' so that it is only emitted if it is
7934 actually needed. It is unlikely that it will be inlined, since
7935 it is only called via a function pointer, but we avoid unnecessary
7936 emissions this way. */
7937 DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (fndecl) = 1;
7938 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (fndecl) = 1;
7939 /* Build the parameter. */
7940 if (use_cxa_atexit)
7941 {
7942 tree parmdecl;
7943
7944 parmdecl = cp_build_parm_decl (NULL_TREE, ptr_type_node);
7945 DECL_CONTEXT (parmdecl) = fndecl;
7946 TREE_USED (parmdecl) = 1;
7947 DECL_READ_P (parmdecl) = 1;
7948 DECL_ARGUMENTS (fndecl) = parmdecl;
7949 }
7950
7951 pushdecl (fndecl);
7952 start_preparsed_function (fndecl, NULL_TREE, SF_PRE_PARSED);
7953
7954 pop_lang_context ();
7955
7956 return current_function_decl;
7957}
7958
7959/* Finish the cleanup function begun by start_cleanup_fn. */
7960
7961static void
7962end_cleanup_fn (void)
7963{
7964 expand_or_defer_fn (finish_function (0));
7965
7966 pop_from_top_level ();
7967}
7968
7969/* Generate code to handle the destruction of DECL, an object with
7970 static storage duration. */
7971
7972tree
7973register_dtor_fn (tree decl)
7974{
7975 tree cleanup;
7976 tree addr;
7977 tree compound_stmt;
7978 tree fcall;
7979 tree type;
7980 bool ob_parm, dso_parm, use_dtor;
7981 tree arg0, arg1, arg2;
7982 tree atex_node;
7983
7984 type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
7985 if (TYPE_HAS_TRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (type))
7986 return void_node;
7987
7988 /* If we're using "__cxa_atexit" (or "__cxa_thread_atexit" or
7989 "__aeabi_atexit"), and DECL is a class object, we can just pass the
7990 destructor to "__cxa_atexit"; we don't have to build a temporary
7991 function to do the cleanup. */
7992 dso_parm = (flag_use_cxa_atexit
7993 && !targetm.cxx.use_atexit_for_cxa_atexit ());
7994 ob_parm = (CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (decl) || dso_parm);
7995 use_dtor = ob_parm && CLASS_TYPE_P (type);
7996 if (use_dtor)
7997 {
7998 int idx;
7999
8000 /* Find the destructor. */
8001 idx = lookup_fnfields_1 (type, complete_dtor_identifier);
8002 gcc_assert (idx >= 0);
8003 cleanup = (*CLASSTYPE_METHOD_VEC (type))[idx];
8004 /* Make sure it is accessible. */
8005 perform_or_defer_access_check (TYPE_BINFO (type), cleanup, cleanup,
8006 tf_warning_or_error);
8007 }
8008 else
8009 {
8010 /* Call build_cleanup before we enter the anonymous function so
8011 that any access checks will be done relative to the current
8012 scope, rather than the scope of the anonymous function. */
8013 build_cleanup (decl);
8014
8015 /* Now start the function. */
8016 cleanup = start_cleanup_fn ();
8017
8018 /* Now, recompute the cleanup. It may contain SAVE_EXPRs that refer
8019 to the original function, rather than the anonymous one. That
8020 will make the back end think that nested functions are in use,
8021 which causes confusion. */
8022 push_deferring_access_checks (dk_no_check);
8023 fcall = build_cleanup (decl);
8024 pop_deferring_access_checks ();
8025
8026 /* Create the body of the anonymous function. */
8027 compound_stmt = begin_compound_stmt (BCS_FN_BODY);
8028 finish_expr_stmt (fcall);
8029 finish_compound_stmt (compound_stmt);
8030 end_cleanup_fn ();
8031 }
8032
8033 /* Call atexit with the cleanup function. */
8034 mark_used (cleanup);
8035 cleanup = build_address (cleanup);
8036
8037 if (CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (decl))
8038 atex_node = get_thread_atexit_node ();
8039 else
8040 atex_node = get_atexit_node ();
8041
8042 if (use_dtor)
8043 {
8044 /* We must convert CLEANUP to the type that "__cxa_atexit"
8045 expects. */
8046 cleanup = build_nop (get_atexit_fn_ptr_type (), cleanup);
8047 /* "__cxa_atexit" will pass the address of DECL to the
8048 cleanup function. */
8049 mark_used (decl);
8050 addr = build_address (decl);
8051 /* The declared type of the parameter to "__cxa_atexit" is
8052 "void *". For plain "T*", we could just let the
8053 machinery in cp_build_function_call convert it -- but if the
8054 type is "cv-qualified T *", then we need to convert it
8055 before passing it in, to avoid spurious errors. */
8056 addr = build_nop (ptr_type_node, addr);
8057 }
8058 else
8059 /* Since the cleanup functions we build ignore the address
8060 they're given, there's no reason to pass the actual address
8061 in, and, in general, it's cheaper to pass NULL than any
8062 other value. */
8063 addr = null_pointer_node;
8064
8065 if (dso_parm)
8066 arg2 = cp_build_addr_expr (get_dso_handle_node (),
8067 tf_warning_or_error);
8068 else if (ob_parm)
8069 /* Just pass NULL to the dso handle parm if we don't actually
8070 have a DSO handle on this target. */
8071 arg2 = null_pointer_node;
8072 else
8073 arg2 = NULL_TREE;
8074
8075 if (ob_parm)
8076 {
8077 if (!CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (decl)
8078 && targetm.cxx.use_aeabi_atexit ())
8079 {
8080 arg1 = cleanup;
8081 arg0 = addr;
8082 }
8083 else
8084 {
8085 arg1 = addr;
8086 arg0 = cleanup;
8087 }
8088 }
8089 else
8090 {
8091 arg0 = cleanup;
8092 arg1 = NULL_TREE;
8093 }
8094 return cp_build_function_call_nary (atex_node, tf_warning_or_error,
8095 arg0, arg1, arg2, NULL_TREE);
8096}
8097
8098/* DECL is a VAR_DECL with static storage duration. INIT, if present,
8099 is its initializer. Generate code to handle the construction
8100 and destruction of DECL. */
8101
8102static void
8103expand_static_init (tree decl, tree init)
8104{
8105 gcc_assert (VAR_P (decl));
8106 gcc_assert (TREE_STATIC (decl));
8107
8108 /* Some variables require no dynamic initialization. */
8109 if (TYPE_HAS_TRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
8110 {
8111 /* Make sure the destructor is callable. */
8112 cxx_maybe_build_cleanup (decl, tf_warning_or_error);
8113 if (!init)
8114 return;
8115 }
8116
8117 if (CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (decl) && DECL_GNU_TLS_P (decl)
8118 && !DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (decl))
8119 {
8120 if (init)
8121 error ("non-local variable %qD declared %<__thread%> "
8122 "needs dynamic initialization", decl);
8123 else
8124 error ("non-local variable %qD declared %<__thread%> "
8125 "has a non-trivial destructor", decl);
8126 static bool informed;
8127 if (!informed)
8128 {
8129 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
8130 "C++11 %<thread_local%> allows dynamic initialization "
8131 "and destruction");
8132 informed = true;
8133 }
8134 return;
8135 }
8136
8137 if (DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (decl))
8138 {
8139 /* Emit code to perform this initialization but once. */
8140 tree if_stmt = NULL_TREE, inner_if_stmt = NULL_TREE;
8141 tree then_clause = NULL_TREE, inner_then_clause = NULL_TREE;
8142 tree guard, guard_addr;
8143 tree flag, begin;
8144 /* We don't need thread-safety code for thread-local vars. */
8145 bool thread_guard = (flag_threadsafe_statics
8146 && !CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (decl));
8147
8148 /* Emit code to perform this initialization but once. This code
8149 looks like:
8150
8151 static <type> guard;
8152 if (!__atomic_load (guard.first_byte)) {
8153 if (__cxa_guard_acquire (&guard)) {
8154 bool flag = false;
8155 try {
8156 // Do initialization.
8157 flag = true; __cxa_guard_release (&guard);
8158 // Register variable for destruction at end of program.
8159 } catch {
8160 if (!flag) __cxa_guard_abort (&guard);
8161 }
8162 }
8163 }
8164
8165 Note that the `flag' variable is only set to 1 *after* the
8166 initialization is complete. This ensures that an exception,
8167 thrown during the construction, will cause the variable to
8168 reinitialized when we pass through this code again, as per:
8169
8170 [stmt.dcl]
8171
8172 If the initialization exits by throwing an exception, the
8173 initialization is not complete, so it will be tried again
8174 the next time control enters the declaration.
8175
8176 This process should be thread-safe, too; multiple threads
8177 should not be able to initialize the variable more than
8178 once. */
8179
8180 /* Create the guard variable. */
8181 guard = get_guard (decl);
8182
8183 /* Begin the conditional initialization. */
8184 if_stmt = begin_if_stmt ();
8185
8186 finish_if_stmt_cond (get_guard_cond (guard, thread_guard), if_stmt);
8187 then_clause = begin_compound_stmt (BCS_NO_SCOPE);
8188
8189 if (thread_guard)
8190 {
8191 tree vfntype = NULL_TREE;
8192 tree acquire_name, release_name, abort_name;
8193 tree acquire_fn, release_fn, abort_fn;
8194 guard_addr = build_address (guard);
8195
8196 acquire_name = get_identifier ("__cxa_guard_acquire");
8197 release_name = get_identifier ("__cxa_guard_release");
8198 abort_name = get_identifier ("__cxa_guard_abort");
8199 acquire_fn = identifier_global_value (acquire_name);
8200 release_fn = identifier_global_value (release_name);
8201 abort_fn = identifier_global_value (abort_name);
8202 if (!acquire_fn)
8203 acquire_fn = push_library_fn
8204 (acquire_name, build_function_type_list (integer_type_node,
8205 TREE_TYPE (guard_addr),
8206 NULL_TREE),
8207 NULL_TREE, ECF_NOTHROW | ECF_LEAF);
8208 if (!release_fn || !abort_fn)
8209 vfntype = build_function_type_list (void_type_node,
8210 TREE_TYPE (guard_addr),
8211 NULL_TREE);
8212 if (!release_fn)
8213 release_fn = push_library_fn (release_name, vfntype, NULL_TREE,
8214 ECF_NOTHROW | ECF_LEAF);
8215 if (!abort_fn)
8216 abort_fn = push_library_fn (abort_name, vfntype, NULL_TREE,
8217 ECF_NOTHROW | ECF_LEAF);
8218
8219 inner_if_stmt = begin_if_stmt ();
8220 finish_if_stmt_cond (build_call_n (acquire_fn, 1, guard_addr),
8221 inner_if_stmt);
8222
8223 inner_then_clause = begin_compound_stmt (BCS_NO_SCOPE);
8224 begin = get_target_expr (boolean_false_node);
8225 flag = TARGET_EXPR_SLOT (begin);
8226
8227 TARGET_EXPR_CLEANUP (begin)
8228 = build3 (COND_EXPR, void_type_node, flag,
8229 void_node,
8230 build_call_n (abort_fn, 1, guard_addr));
8231 CLEANUP_EH_ONLY (begin) = 1;
8232
8233 /* Do the initialization itself. */
8234 init = add_stmt_to_compound (begin, init);
8235 init = add_stmt_to_compound
8236 (init, build2 (MODIFY_EXPR, void_type_node, flag, boolean_true_node));
8237 init = add_stmt_to_compound
8238 (init, build_call_n (release_fn, 1, guard_addr));
8239 }
8240 else
8241 init = add_stmt_to_compound (init, set_guard (guard));
8242
8243 /* Use atexit to register a function for destroying this static
8244 variable. */
8245 init = add_stmt_to_compound (init, register_dtor_fn (decl));
8246
8247 finish_expr_stmt (init);
8248
8249 if (thread_guard)
8250 {
8251 finish_compound_stmt (inner_then_clause);
8252 finish_then_clause (inner_if_stmt);
8253 finish_if_stmt (inner_if_stmt);
8254 }
8255
8256 finish_compound_stmt (then_clause);
8257 finish_then_clause (if_stmt);
8258 finish_if_stmt (if_stmt);
8259 }
8260 else if (CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (decl))
8261 tls_aggregates = tree_cons (init, decl, tls_aggregates);
8262 else
8263 static_aggregates = tree_cons (init, decl, static_aggregates);
8264}
8265
8266
8267/* Make TYPE a complete type based on INITIAL_VALUE.
8268 Return 0 if successful, 1 if INITIAL_VALUE can't be deciphered,
8269 2 if there was no information (in which case assume 0 if DO_DEFAULT),
8270 3 if the initializer list is empty (in pedantic mode). */
8271
8272int
8273cp_complete_array_type (tree *ptype, tree initial_value, bool do_default)
8274{
8275 int failure;
8276 tree type, elt_type;
8277
8278 /* Don't get confused by a CONSTRUCTOR for some other type. */
8279 if (initial_value && TREE_CODE (initial_value) == CONSTRUCTOR
8280 && !BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (initial_value)
8281 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (initial_value)) != ARRAY_TYPE)
8282 return 1;
8283
8284 if (initial_value)
8285 {
8286 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT i;
8287 tree value;
8288
8289 /* An array of character type can be initialized from a
8290 brace-enclosed string constant.
8291
8292 FIXME: this code is duplicated from reshape_init. Probably
8293 we should just call reshape_init here? */
8294 if (char_type_p (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (*ptype)))
8295 && TREE_CODE (initial_value) == CONSTRUCTOR
8296 && !vec_safe_is_empty (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (initial_value)))
8297 {
8298 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *v = CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (initial_value);
8299 tree value = (*v)[0].value;
8300
8301 if (TREE_CODE (value) == STRING_CST
8302 && v->length () == 1)
8303 initial_value = value;
8304 }
8305
8306 /* If any of the elements are parameter packs, we can't actually
8307 complete this type now because the array size is dependent. */
8308 if (TREE_CODE (initial_value) == CONSTRUCTOR)
8309 {
8310 FOR_EACH_CONSTRUCTOR_VALUE (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (initial_value),
8311 i, value)
8312 {
8313 if (PACK_EXPANSION_P (value))
8314 return 0;
8315 }
8316 }
8317 }
8318
8319 failure = complete_array_type (ptype, initial_value, do_default);
8320
8321 /* We can create the array before the element type is complete, which
8322 means that we didn't have these two bits set in the original type
8323 either. In completing the type, we are expected to propagate these
8324 bits. See also complete_type which does the same thing for arrays
8325 of fixed size. */
8326 type = *ptype;
8327 if (TYPE_DOMAIN (type))
8328 {
8329 elt_type = TREE_TYPE (type);
8330 TYPE_NEEDS_CONSTRUCTING (type) = TYPE_NEEDS_CONSTRUCTING (elt_type);
8331 TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (type)
8332 = TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (elt_type);
8333 }
8334
8335 return failure;
8336}
8337
8338/* As above, but either give an error or reject zero-size arrays, depending
8339 on COMPLAIN. */
8340
8341int
8342cp_complete_array_type_or_error (tree *ptype, tree initial_value,
8343 bool do_default, tsubst_flags_t complain)
8344{
8345 int failure;
8346 bool sfinae = !(complain & tf_error);
8347 /* In SFINAE context we can't be lenient about zero-size arrays. */
8348 if (sfinae)
8349 ++pedantic;
8350 failure = cp_complete_array_type (ptype, initial_value, do_default);
8351 if (sfinae)
8352 --pedantic;
8353 if (failure)
8354 {
8355 if (sfinae)
8356 /* Not an error. */;
8357 else if (failure == 1)
8358 error ("initializer fails to determine size of %qT", *ptype);
8359 else if (failure == 2)
8360 {
8361 if (do_default)
8362 error ("array size missing in %qT", *ptype);
8363 }
8364 else if (failure == 3)
8365 error ("zero-size array %qT", *ptype);
8366 *ptype = error_mark_node;
8367 }
8368 return failure;
8369}
8370
8371/* Return zero if something is declared to be a member of type
8372 CTYPE when in the context of CUR_TYPE. STRING is the error
8373 message to print in that case. Otherwise, quietly return 1. */
8374
8375static int
8376member_function_or_else (tree ctype, tree cur_type, enum overload_flags flags)
8377{
8378 if (ctype && ctype != cur_type)
8379 {
8380 if (flags == DTOR_FLAG)
8381 error ("destructor for alien class %qT cannot be a member", ctype);
8382 else
8383 error ("constructor for alien class %qT cannot be a member", ctype);
8384 return 0;
8385 }
8386 return 1;
8387}
8388
8389/* Subroutine of `grokdeclarator'. */
8390
8391/* Generate errors possibly applicable for a given set of specifiers.
8392 This is for ARM $7.1.2. */
8393
8394static void
8395bad_specifiers (tree object,
8396 enum bad_spec_place type,
8397 int virtualp,
8398 int quals,
8399 int inlinep,
8400 int friendp,
8401 int raises)
8402{
8403 switch (type)
8404 {
8405 case BSP_VAR:
8406 if (virtualp)
8407 error ("%qD declared as a %<virtual%> variable", object);
8408 if (quals)
8409 error ("%<const%> and %<volatile%> function specifiers on "
8410 "%qD invalid in variable declaration", object);
8411 break;
8412 case BSP_PARM:
8413 if (virtualp)
8414 error ("%qD declared as a %<virtual%> parameter", object);
8415 if (inlinep)
8416 error ("%qD declared as an %<inline%> parameter", object);
8417 if (quals)
8418 error ("%<const%> and %<volatile%> function specifiers on "
8419 "%qD invalid in parameter declaration", object);
8420 break;
8421 case BSP_TYPE:
8422 if (virtualp)
8423 error ("%qD declared as a %<virtual%> type", object);
8424 if (inlinep)
8425 error ("%qD declared as an %<inline%> type", object);
8426 if (quals)
8427 error ("%<const%> and %<volatile%> function specifiers on "
8428 "%qD invalid in type declaration", object);
8429 break;
8430 case BSP_FIELD:
8431 if (virtualp)
8432 error ("%qD declared as a %<virtual%> field", object);
8433 if (inlinep)
8434 error ("%qD declared as an %<inline%> field", object);
8435 if (quals)
8436 error ("%<const%> and %<volatile%> function specifiers on "
8437 "%qD invalid in field declaration", object);
8438 break;
8439 default:
8440 gcc_unreachable();
8441 }
8442 if (friendp)
8443 error ("%q+D declared as a friend", object);
8444 if (raises
8445 && !flag_noexcept_type
8446 && (TREE_CODE (object) == TYPE_DECL
8447 || (!TYPE_PTRFN_P (TREE_TYPE (object))
8448 && !TYPE_REFFN_P (TREE_TYPE (object))
8449 && !TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (TREE_TYPE (object)))))
8450 error ("%q+D declared with an exception specification", object);
8451}
8452
8453/* DECL is a member function or static data member and is presently
8454 being defined. Check that the definition is taking place in a
8455 valid namespace. */
8456
8457static void
8458check_class_member_definition_namespace (tree decl)
8459{
8460 /* These checks only apply to member functions and static data
8461 members. */
8462 gcc_assert (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (decl));
8463 /* We check for problems with specializations in pt.c in
8464 check_specialization_namespace, where we can issue better
8465 diagnostics. */
8466 if (processing_specialization)
8467 return;
8468 /* We check this in check_explicit_instantiation_namespace. */
8469 if (processing_explicit_instantiation)
8470 return;
8471 /* [class.mfct]
8472
8473 A member function definition that appears outside of the
8474 class definition shall appear in a namespace scope enclosing
8475 the class definition.
8476
8477 [class.static.data]
8478
8479 The definition for a static data member shall appear in a
8480 namespace scope enclosing the member's class definition. */
8481 if (!is_ancestor (current_namespace, DECL_CONTEXT (decl)))
8482 permerror (input_location, "definition of %qD is not in namespace enclosing %qT",
8483 decl, DECL_CONTEXT (decl));
8484}
8485
8486/* Build a PARM_DECL for the "this" parameter. TYPE is the
8487 METHOD_TYPE for a non-static member function; QUALS are the
8488 cv-qualifiers that apply to the function. */
8489
8490tree
8491build_this_parm (tree type, cp_cv_quals quals)
8492{
8493 tree this_type;
8494 tree qual_type;
8495 tree parm;
8496 cp_cv_quals this_quals;
8497
8498 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
8499 {
8500 this_type
8501 = cp_build_qualified_type (type, quals & ~TYPE_QUAL_RESTRICT);
8502 this_type = build_pointer_type (this_type);
8503 }
8504 else
8505 this_type = type_of_this_parm (type);
8506 /* The `this' parameter is implicitly `const'; it cannot be
8507 assigned to. */
8508 this_quals = (quals & TYPE_QUAL_RESTRICT) | TYPE_QUAL_CONST;
8509 qual_type = cp_build_qualified_type (this_type, this_quals);
8510 parm = build_artificial_parm (this_identifier, qual_type);
8511 cp_apply_type_quals_to_decl (this_quals, parm);
8512 return parm;
8513}
8514
8515/* DECL is a static member function. Complain if it was declared
8516 with function-cv-quals. */
8517
8518static void
8519check_static_quals (tree decl, cp_cv_quals quals)
8520{
8521 if (quals != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED)
8522 error ("static member function %q#D declared with type qualifiers",
8523 decl);
8524}
8525
8526// Check that FN takes no arguments and returns bool.
8527static void
8528check_concept_fn (tree fn)
8529{
8530 // A constraint is nullary.
8531 if (DECL_ARGUMENTS (fn))
8532 error ("concept %q#D declared with function parameters", fn);
8533
8534 // The declared return type of the concept shall be bool, and
8535 // it shall not be deduced from it definition.
8536 tree type = TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (fn));
8537 if (is_auto (type))
8538 error ("concept %q#D declared with a deduced return type", fn);
8539 else if (type != boolean_type_node)
8540 error ("concept %q#D with non-%<bool%> return type %qT", fn, type);
8541}
8542
8543/* Helper function. Replace the temporary this parameter injected
8544 during cp_finish_omp_declare_simd with the real this parameter. */
8545
8546static tree
8547declare_simd_adjust_this (tree *tp, int *walk_subtrees, void *data)
8548{
8549 tree this_parm = (tree) data;
8550 if (TREE_CODE (*tp) == PARM_DECL
8551 && DECL_NAME (*tp) == this_identifier
8552 && *tp != this_parm)
8553 *tp = this_parm;
8554 else if (TYPE_P (*tp))
8555 *walk_subtrees = 0;
8556 return NULL_TREE;
8557}
8558
8559/* CTYPE is class type, or null if non-class.
8560 TYPE is type this FUNCTION_DECL should have, either FUNCTION_TYPE
8561 or METHOD_TYPE.
8562 DECLARATOR is the function's name.
8563 PARMS is a chain of PARM_DECLs for the function.
8564 VIRTUALP is truthvalue of whether the function is virtual or not.
8565 FLAGS are to be passed through to `grokclassfn'.
8566 QUALS are qualifiers indicating whether the function is `const'
8567 or `volatile'.
8568 RAISES is a list of exceptions that this function can raise.
8569 CHECK is 1 if we must find this method in CTYPE, 0 if we should
8570 not look, and -1 if we should not call `grokclassfn' at all.
8571
8572 SFK is the kind of special function (if any) for the new function.
8573
8574 Returns `NULL_TREE' if something goes wrong, after issuing
8575 applicable error messages. */
8576
8577static tree
8578grokfndecl (tree ctype,
8579 tree type,
8580 tree declarator,
8581 tree parms,
8582 tree orig_declarator,
8583 tree decl_reqs,
8584 int virtualp,
8585 enum overload_flags flags,
8586 cp_cv_quals quals,
8587 cp_ref_qualifier rqual,
8588 tree raises,
8589 int check,
8590 int friendp,
8591 int publicp,
8592 int inlinep,
8593 bool deletedp,
8594 special_function_kind sfk,
8595 bool funcdef_flag,
8596 int template_count,
8597 tree in_namespace,
8598 tree* attrlist,
8599 location_t location)
8600{
8601 tree decl;
8602 int staticp = ctype && TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE;
8603 tree t;
8604
8605 // Was the concept specifier present?
8606 bool concept_p = inlinep & 4;
8607
8608 // Concept declarations must have a corresponding definition.
8609 if (concept_p && !funcdef_flag)
8610 {
8611 error ("concept %qD has no definition", declarator);
8612 return NULL_TREE;
8613 }
8614
8615 if (rqual)
8616 type = build_ref_qualified_type (type, rqual);
8617 if (raises)
8618 type = build_exception_variant (type, raises);
8619
8620 decl = build_lang_decl (FUNCTION_DECL, declarator, type);
8621
8622 /* Set the constraints on the declaration. */
8623 if (flag_concepts)
8624 {
8625 tree tmpl_reqs = NULL_TREE;
8626 if (processing_template_decl > template_class_depth (ctype))
8627 tmpl_reqs = TEMPLATE_PARMS_CONSTRAINTS (current_template_parms);
8628
8629 /* Adjust the required expression into a constraint. */
8630 if (decl_reqs)
8631 decl_reqs = normalize_expression (decl_reqs);
8632
8633 tree ci = build_constraints (tmpl_reqs, decl_reqs);
8634 set_constraints (decl, ci);
8635 }
8636
8637 /* If we have an explicit location, use it, otherwise use whatever
8638 build_lang_decl used (probably input_location). */
8639 if (location != UNKNOWN_LOCATION)
8640 DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl) = location;
8641
8642 if (TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
8643 {
8644 tree parm;
8645 parm = build_this_parm (type, quals);
8646 DECL_CHAIN (parm) = parms;
8647 parms = parm;
8648
8649 /* Allocate space to hold the vptr bit if needed. */
8650 SET_DECL_ALIGN (decl, MINIMUM_METHOD_BOUNDARY);
8651 }
8652 DECL_ARGUMENTS (decl) = parms;
8653 for (t = parms; t; t = DECL_CHAIN (t))
8654 DECL_CONTEXT (t) = decl;
8655 /* Propagate volatile out from type to decl. */
8656 if (TYPE_VOLATILE (type))
8657 TREE_THIS_VOLATILE (decl) = 1;
8658
8659 /* Setup decl according to sfk. */
8660 switch (sfk)
8661 {
8662 case sfk_constructor:
8663 case sfk_copy_constructor:
8664 case sfk_move_constructor:
8665 DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (decl) = 1;
8666 break;
8667 case sfk_destructor:
8668 DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (decl) = 1;
8669 break;
8670 default:
8671 break;
8672 }
8673
8674 if (friendp
8675 && TREE_CODE (orig_declarator) == TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR)
8676 {
8677 if (funcdef_flag)
8678 error
8679 ("defining explicit specialization %qD in friend declaration",
8680 orig_declarator);
8681 else
8682 {
8683 tree fns = TREE_OPERAND (orig_declarator, 0);
8684 tree args = TREE_OPERAND (orig_declarator, 1);
8685
8686 if (PROCESSING_REAL_TEMPLATE_DECL_P ())
8687 {
8688 /* Something like `template <class T> friend void f<T>()'. */
8689 error ("invalid use of template-id %qD in declaration "
8690 "of primary template",
8691 orig_declarator);
8692 return NULL_TREE;
8693 }
8694
8695
8696 /* A friend declaration of the form friend void f<>(). Record
8697 the information in the TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR. */
8698 SET_DECL_IMPLICIT_INSTANTIATION (decl);
8699
8700 gcc_assert (identifier_p (fns) || TREE_CODE (fns) == OVERLOAD);
8701 DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (decl) = build_template_info (fns, args);
8702
8703 for (t = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (decl)); t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
8704 if (TREE_PURPOSE (t)
8705 && TREE_CODE (TREE_PURPOSE (t)) == DEFAULT_ARG)
8706 {
8707 error ("default arguments are not allowed in declaration "
8708 "of friend template specialization %qD",
8709 decl);
8710 return NULL_TREE;
8711 }
8712
8713 if (inlinep & 1)
8714 {
8715 error ("%<inline%> is not allowed in declaration of friend "
8716 "template specialization %qD",
8717 decl);
8718 return NULL_TREE;
8719 }
8720 }
8721 }
8722
8723 /* If this decl has namespace scope, set that up. */
8724 if (in_namespace)
8725 set_decl_namespace (decl, in_namespace, friendp);
8726 else if (!ctype)
8727 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = FROB_CONTEXT (current_decl_namespace ());
8728
8729 /* `main' and builtins have implicit 'C' linkage. */
8730 if ((MAIN_NAME_P (declarator)
8731 || (IDENTIFIER_LENGTH (declarator) > 10
8732 && IDENTIFIER_POINTER (declarator)[0] == '_'
8733 && IDENTIFIER_POINTER (declarator)[1] == '_'
8734 && strncmp (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (declarator)+2, "builtin_", 8) == 0)
8735 || (targetcm.cxx_implicit_extern_c
8736 && targetcm.cxx_implicit_extern_c(IDENTIFIER_POINTER (declarator))))
8737 && current_lang_name == lang_name_cplusplus
8738 && ctype == NULL_TREE
8739 && DECL_FILE_SCOPE_P (decl))
8740 SET_DECL_LANGUAGE (decl, lang_c);
8741
8742 /* Should probably propagate const out from type to decl I bet (mrs). */
8743 if (staticp)
8744 {
8745 DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (decl) = 1;
8746 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = ctype;
8747 }
8748
8749 if (deletedp)
8750 DECL_DELETED_FN (decl) = 1;
8751
8752 if (ctype)
8753 {
8754 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = ctype;
8755 if (funcdef_flag)
8756 check_class_member_definition_namespace (decl);
8757 }
8758
8759 if (ctype == NULL_TREE && DECL_MAIN_P (decl))
8760 {
8761 if (PROCESSING_REAL_TEMPLATE_DECL_P())
8762 error ("cannot declare %<::main%> to be a template");
8763 if (inlinep & 1)
8764 error ("cannot declare %<::main%> to be inline");
8765 if (inlinep & 2)
8766 error ("cannot declare %<::main%> to be constexpr");
8767 if (!publicp)
8768 error ("cannot declare %<::main%> to be static");
8769 inlinep = 0;
8770 publicp = 1;
8771 }
8772
8773 /* Members of anonymous types and local classes have no linkage; make
8774 them internal. If a typedef is made later, this will be changed. */
8775 if (ctype && (!TREE_PUBLIC (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (ctype))
8776 || decl_function_context (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (ctype))))
8777 publicp = 0;
8778
8779 if (publicp && cxx_dialect == cxx98)
8780 {
8781 /* [basic.link]: A name with no linkage (notably, the name of a class
8782 or enumeration declared in a local scope) shall not be used to
8783 declare an entity with linkage.
8784
8785 DR 757 relaxes this restriction for C++0x. */
8786 no_linkage_error (decl);
8787 }
8788
8789 TREE_PUBLIC (decl) = publicp;
8790 if (! publicp)
8791 {
8792 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl) = 1;
8793 DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (decl) = 1;
8794 }
8795
8796 /* If the declaration was declared inline, mark it as such. */
8797 if (inlinep)
8798 {
8799 DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl) = 1;
8800 if (publicp)
8801 DECL_COMDAT (decl) = 1;
8802 }
8803 if (inlinep & 2)
8804 DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (decl) = true;
8805
8806 // If the concept declaration specifier was found, check
8807 // that the declaration satisfies the necessary requirements.
8808 if (concept_p)
8809 {
8810 DECL_DECLARED_CONCEPT_P (decl) = true;
8811 check_concept_fn (decl);
8812 }
8813
8814 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 1;
8815 if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
8816 {
8817 if (quals || rqual)
8818 TREE_TYPE (decl) = apply_memfn_quals (TREE_TYPE (decl),
8819 TYPE_UNQUALIFIED,
8820 REF_QUAL_NONE);
8821
8822 if (quals)
8823 {
8824 error (ctype
8825 ? G_("static member function %qD cannot have cv-qualifier")
8826 : G_("non-member function %qD cannot have cv-qualifier"),
8827 decl);
8828 quals = TYPE_UNQUALIFIED;
8829 }
8830
8831 if (rqual)
8832 {
8833 error (ctype
8834 ? G_("static member function %qD cannot have ref-qualifier")
8835 : G_("non-member function %qD cannot have ref-qualifier"),
8836 decl);
8837 rqual = REF_QUAL_NONE;
8838 }
8839 }
8840
8841 if (deduction_guide_p (decl))
8842 {
8843 if (!DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (decl))
8844 {
8845 error_at (location, "deduction guide %qD must be declared at "
8846 "namespace scope", decl);
8847 return NULL_TREE;
8848 }
8849 if (funcdef_flag)
8850 error_at (location,
8851 "deduction guide %qD must not have a function body", decl);
8852 }
8853 else if (IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P (DECL_NAME (decl))
8854 && !grok_op_properties (decl, /*complain=*/true))
8855 return NULL_TREE;
8856 else if (UDLIT_OPER_P (DECL_NAME (decl)))
8857 {
8858 bool long_long_unsigned_p;
8859 bool long_double_p;
8860 const char *suffix = NULL;
8861 /* [over.literal]/6: Literal operators shall not have C linkage. */
8862 if (DECL_LANGUAGE (decl) == lang_c)
8863 {
8864 error ("literal operator with C linkage");
8865 return NULL_TREE;
8866 }
8867
8868 if (DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (decl))
8869 {
8870 if (!check_literal_operator_args (decl, &long_long_unsigned_p,
8871 &long_double_p))
8872 {
8873 error ("%qD has invalid argument list", decl);
8874 return NULL_TREE;
8875 }
8876
8877 suffix = UDLIT_OP_SUFFIX (DECL_NAME (decl));
8878 if (long_long_unsigned_p)
8879 {
8880 if (cpp_interpret_int_suffix (parse_in, suffix, strlen (suffix)))
8881 warning (0, "integer suffix %qs"
8882 " shadowed by implementation", suffix);
8883 }
8884 else if (long_double_p)
8885 {
8886 if (cpp_interpret_float_suffix (parse_in, suffix, strlen (suffix)))
8887 warning (0, "floating point suffix %qs"
8888 " shadowed by implementation", suffix);
8889 }
8890 }
8891 else
8892 {
8893 error ("%qD must be a non-member function", decl);
8894 return NULL_TREE;
8895 }
8896 }
8897
8898 if (funcdef_flag)
8899 /* Make the init_value nonzero so pushdecl knows this is not
8900 tentative. error_mark_node is replaced later with the BLOCK. */
8901 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = error_mark_node;
8902
8903 if (TYPE_NOTHROW_P (type) || nothrow_libfn_p (decl))
8904 TREE_NOTHROW (decl) = 1;
8905
8906 if (flag_openmp || flag_openmp_simd || flag_cilkplus)
8907 {
8908 /* Adjust "omp declare simd" attributes. */
8909 tree ods = lookup_attribute ("omp declare simd", *attrlist);
8910 if (ods)
8911 {
8912 tree attr;
8913 for (attr = ods; attr;
8914 attr = lookup_attribute ("omp declare simd", TREE_CHAIN (attr)))
8915 {
8916 if (TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
8917 walk_tree (&TREE_VALUE (attr), declare_simd_adjust_this,
8918 DECL_ARGUMENTS (decl), NULL);
8919 if (TREE_VALUE (attr) != NULL_TREE)
8920 {
8921 tree cl = TREE_VALUE (TREE_VALUE (attr));
8922 cl = c_omp_declare_simd_clauses_to_numbers
8923 (DECL_ARGUMENTS (decl), cl);
8924 if (cl)
8925 TREE_VALUE (TREE_VALUE (attr)) = cl;
8926 else
8927 TREE_VALUE (attr) = NULL_TREE;
8928 }
8929 }
8930 }
8931 }
8932
8933 /* Caller will do the rest of this. */
8934 if (check < 0)
8935 return decl;
8936
8937 if (ctype != NULL_TREE)
8938 grokclassfn (ctype, decl, flags);
8939
8940 /* 12.4/3 */
8941 if (cxx_dialect >= cxx11
8942 && DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (decl)
8943 && !TYPE_BEING_DEFINED (DECL_CONTEXT (decl))
8944 && !processing_template_decl)
8945 deduce_noexcept_on_destructor (decl);
8946
8947 decl = check_explicit_specialization (orig_declarator, decl,
8948 template_count,
8949 2 * funcdef_flag +
8950 4 * (friendp != 0) +
8951 8 * concept_p);
8952 if (decl == error_mark_node)
8953 return NULL_TREE;
8954
8955 if (DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (decl))
8956 check_static_quals (decl, quals);
8957
8958 if (attrlist)
8959 {
8960 cplus_decl_attributes (&decl, *attrlist, 0);
8961 *attrlist = NULL_TREE;
8962 }
8963
8964 /* Check main's type after attributes have been applied. */
8965 if (ctype == NULL_TREE && DECL_MAIN_P (decl))
8966 {
8967 if (!same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (decl)),
8968 integer_type_node))
8969 {
8970 tree oldtypeargs = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (decl));
8971 tree newtype;
8972 error ("%<::main%> must return %<int%>");
8973 newtype = build_function_type (integer_type_node, oldtypeargs);
8974 TREE_TYPE (decl) = newtype;
8975 }
8976 if (warn_main)
8977 check_main_parameter_types (decl);
8978 }
8979
8980 if (ctype != NULL_TREE && check)
8981 {
8982 tree old_decl = check_classfn (ctype, decl,
8983 (processing_template_decl
8984 > template_class_depth (ctype))
8985 ? current_template_parms
8986 : NULL_TREE);
8987
8988 if (old_decl == error_mark_node)
8989 return NULL_TREE;
8990
8991 if (old_decl)
8992 {
8993 tree ok;
8994 tree pushed_scope;
8995
8996 if (TREE_CODE (old_decl) == TEMPLATE_DECL)
8997 /* Because grokfndecl is always supposed to return a
8998 FUNCTION_DECL, we pull out the DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT
8999 here. We depend on our callers to figure out that its
9000 really a template that's being returned. */
9001 old_decl = DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (old_decl);
9002
9003 if (DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (old_decl)
9004 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (decl)) == METHOD_TYPE)
9005 {
9006 /* Remove the `this' parm added by grokclassfn. */
9007 revert_static_member_fn (decl);
9008 check_static_quals (decl, quals);
9009 }
9010 if (DECL_ARTIFICIAL (old_decl))
9011 {
9012 error ("definition of implicitly-declared %qD", old_decl);
9013 return NULL_TREE;
9014 }
9015 else if (DECL_DEFAULTED_FN (old_decl))
9016 {
9017 error ("definition of explicitly-defaulted %q+D", decl);
9018 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (old_decl),
9019 "%q#D explicitly defaulted here", old_decl);
9020 return NULL_TREE;
9021 }
9022
9023 /* Since we've smashed OLD_DECL to its
9024 DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT, we must do the same to DECL. */
9025 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TEMPLATE_DECL)
9026 decl = DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (decl);
9027
9028 /* Attempt to merge the declarations. This can fail, in
9029 the case of some invalid specialization declarations. */
9030 pushed_scope = push_scope (ctype);
9031 ok = duplicate_decls (decl, old_decl, friendp);
9032 if (pushed_scope)
9033 pop_scope (pushed_scope);
9034 if (!ok)
9035 {
9036 error ("no %q#D member function declared in class %qT",
9037 decl, ctype);
9038 return NULL_TREE;
9039 }
9040 if (ok == error_mark_node)
9041 return NULL_TREE;
9042 return old_decl;
9043 }
9044 }
9045
9046 if (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (decl) && !grok_ctor_properties (ctype, decl))
9047 return NULL_TREE;
9048
9049 if (ctype == NULL_TREE || check)
9050 return decl;
9051
9052 if (virtualp)
9053 DECL_VIRTUAL_P (decl) = 1;
9054
9055 return decl;
9056}
9057
9058/* decl is a FUNCTION_DECL.
9059 specifiers are the parsed virt-specifiers.
9060
9061 Set flags to reflect the virt-specifiers.
9062
9063 Returns decl. */
9064
9065static tree
9066set_virt_specifiers (tree decl, cp_virt_specifiers specifiers)
9067{
9068 if (decl == NULL_TREE)
9069 return decl;
9070 if (specifiers & VIRT_SPEC_OVERRIDE)
9071 DECL_OVERRIDE_P (decl) = 1;
9072 if (specifiers & VIRT_SPEC_FINAL)
9073 DECL_FINAL_P (decl) = 1;
9074 return decl;
9075}
9076
9077/* DECL is a VAR_DECL for a static data member. Set flags to reflect
9078 the linkage that DECL will receive in the object file. */
9079
9080static void
9081set_linkage_for_static_data_member (tree decl)
9082{
9083 /* A static data member always has static storage duration and
9084 external linkage. Note that static data members are forbidden in
9085 local classes -- the only situation in which a class has
9086 non-external linkage. */
9087 TREE_PUBLIC (decl) = 1;
9088 TREE_STATIC (decl) = 1;
9089 /* For non-template classes, static data members are always put
9090 out in exactly those files where they are defined, just as
9091 with ordinary namespace-scope variables. */
9092 if (!processing_template_decl)
9093 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl) = 1;
9094}
9095
9096/* Create a VAR_DECL named NAME with the indicated TYPE.
9097
9098 If SCOPE is non-NULL, it is the class type or namespace containing
9099 the variable. If SCOPE is NULL, the variable should is created in
9100 the innermost enclosing scope. */
9101
9102static tree
9103grokvardecl (tree type,
9104 tree name,
9105 tree orig_declarator,
9106 const cp_decl_specifier_seq *declspecs,
9107 int initialized,
9108 int type_quals,
9109 int inlinep,
9110 bool conceptp,
9111 int template_count,
9112 tree scope)
9113{
9114 tree decl;
9115 tree explicit_scope;
9116
9117 gcc_assert (!name || identifier_p (name));
9118
9119 bool constp = (type_quals & TYPE_QUAL_CONST) != 0;
9120 bool volatilep = (type_quals & TYPE_QUAL_VOLATILE) != 0;
9121
9122 /* Compute the scope in which to place the variable, but remember
9123 whether or not that scope was explicitly specified by the user. */
9124 explicit_scope = scope;
9125 if (!scope)
9126 {
9127 /* An explicit "extern" specifier indicates a namespace-scope
9128 variable. */
9129 if (declspecs->storage_class == sc_extern)
9130 scope = current_decl_namespace ();
9131 else if (!at_function_scope_p ())
9132 scope = current_scope ();
9133 }
9134
9135 if (scope
9136 && (/* If the variable is a namespace-scope variable declared in a
9137 template, we need DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC. */
9138 (TREE_CODE (scope) == NAMESPACE_DECL && processing_template_decl)
9139 /* Similarly for namespace-scope variables with language linkage
9140 other than C++. */
9141 || (TREE_CODE (scope) == NAMESPACE_DECL
9142 && current_lang_name != lang_name_cplusplus)
9143 /* Similarly for static data members. */
9144 || TYPE_P (scope)
9145 /* Similarly for explicit specializations. */
9146 || (orig_declarator
9147 && TREE_CODE (orig_declarator) == TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR)))
9148 decl = build_lang_decl (VAR_DECL, name, type);
9149 else
9150 decl = build_decl (input_location, VAR_DECL, name, type);
9151
9152 if (explicit_scope && TREE_CODE (explicit_scope) == NAMESPACE_DECL)
9153 set_decl_namespace (decl, explicit_scope, 0);
9154 else
9155 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = FROB_CONTEXT (scope);
9156
9157 if (declspecs->storage_class == sc_extern)
9158 {
9159 DECL_THIS_EXTERN (decl) = 1;
9160 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = !initialized;
9161 }
9162
9163 if (DECL_CLASS_SCOPE_P (decl))
9164 {
9165 set_linkage_for_static_data_member (decl);
9166 /* This function is only called with out-of-class definitions. */
9167 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 0;
9168 check_class_member_definition_namespace (decl);
9169 }
9170 /* At top level, either `static' or no s.c. makes a definition
9171 (perhaps tentative), and absence of `static' makes it public. */
9172 else if (toplevel_bindings_p ())
9173 {
9174 TREE_PUBLIC (decl) = (declspecs->storage_class != sc_static
9175 && (DECL_THIS_EXTERN (decl)
9176 || ! constp
9177 || volatilep
9178 || inlinep));
9179 TREE_STATIC (decl) = ! DECL_EXTERNAL (decl);
9180 }
9181 /* Not at top level, only `static' makes a static definition. */
9182 else
9183 {
9184 TREE_STATIC (decl) = declspecs->storage_class == sc_static;
9185 TREE_PUBLIC (decl) = DECL_EXTERNAL (decl);
9186 }
9187
9188 if (decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_thread))
9189 {
9190 if (DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) || TREE_STATIC (decl))
9191 {
9192 CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (decl) = true;
9193 if (!processing_template_decl)
9194 set_decl_tls_model (decl, decl_default_tls_model (decl));
9195 }
9196 if (declspecs->gnu_thread_keyword_p)
9197 SET_DECL_GNU_TLS_P (decl);
9198 }
9199
9200 /* If the type of the decl has no linkage, make sure that we'll
9201 notice that in mark_used. */
9202 if (cxx_dialect > cxx98
9203 && decl_linkage (decl) != lk_none
9204 && DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl) == NULL
9205 && !DECL_EXTERN_C_P (decl)
9206 && no_linkage_check (TREE_TYPE (decl), /*relaxed_p=*/false))
9207 retrofit_lang_decl (decl);
9208
9209 if (TREE_PUBLIC (decl))
9210 {
9211 /* [basic.link]: A name with no linkage (notably, the name of a class
9212 or enumeration declared in a local scope) shall not be used to
9213 declare an entity with linkage.
9214
9215 DR 757 relaxes this restriction for C++0x. */
9216 if (cxx_dialect < cxx11)
9217 no_linkage_error (decl);
9218 }
9219 else
9220 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl) = 1;
9221
9222 if (DECL_NAME (decl)
9223 && MAIN_NAME_P (DECL_NAME (decl))
9224 && scope == global_namespace)
9225 error ("cannot declare %<::main%> to be a global variable");
9226
9227 /* Check that the variable can be safely declared as a concept.
9228 Note that this also forbids explicit specializations. */
9229 if (conceptp)
9230 {
9231 if (!processing_template_decl)
9232 {
9233 error ("a non-template variable cannot be %<concept%>");
9234 return NULL_TREE;
9235 }
9236 else
9237 DECL_DECLARED_CONCEPT_P (decl) = true;
9238 if (!same_type_ignoring_top_level_qualifiers_p (type, boolean_type_node))
9239 error_at (declspecs->locations[ds_type_spec],
9240 "concept must have type %<bool%>");
9241 }
9242 else if (flag_concepts
9243 && processing_template_decl > template_class_depth (scope))
9244 {
9245 tree reqs = TEMPLATE_PARMS_CONSTRAINTS (current_template_parms);
9246 tree ci = build_constraints (reqs, NULL_TREE);
9247 set_constraints (decl, ci);
9248 }
9249
9250 // Handle explicit specializations and instantiations of variable templates.
9251 if (orig_declarator)
9252 decl = check_explicit_specialization (orig_declarator, decl,
9253 template_count, conceptp * 8);
9254
9255 return decl != error_mark_node ? decl : NULL_TREE;
9256}
9257
9258/* Create and return a canonical pointer to member function type, for
9259 TYPE, which is a POINTER_TYPE to a METHOD_TYPE. */
9260
9261tree
9262build_ptrmemfunc_type (tree type)
9263{
9264 tree field, fields;
9265 tree t;
9266
9267 if (type == error_mark_node)
9268 return type;
9269
9270 /* Make sure that we always have the unqualified pointer-to-member
9271 type first. */
9272 if (cp_cv_quals quals = cp_type_quals (type))
9273 {
9274 tree unqual = build_ptrmemfunc_type (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type));
9275 return cp_build_qualified_type (unqual, quals);
9276 }
9277
9278 /* If a canonical type already exists for this type, use it. We use
9279 this method instead of type_hash_canon, because it only does a
9280 simple equality check on the list of field members. */
9281
9282 if ((t = TYPE_GET_PTRMEMFUNC_TYPE (type)))
9283 return t;
9284
9285 t = make_node (RECORD_TYPE);
9286
9287 /* Let the front end know this is a pointer to member function. */
9288 TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FLAG (t) = 1;
9289
9290 field = build_decl (input_location, FIELD_DECL, pfn_identifier, type);
9291 fields = field;
9292
9293 field = build_decl (input_location, FIELD_DECL, delta_identifier,
9294 delta_type_node);
9295 DECL_CHAIN (field) = fields;
9296 fields = field;
9297
9298 finish_builtin_struct (t, "__ptrmemfunc_type", fields, ptr_type_node);
9299
9300 /* Zap out the name so that the back end will give us the debugging
9301 information for this anonymous RECORD_TYPE. */
9302 TYPE_NAME (t) = NULL_TREE;
9303
9304 /* Cache this pointer-to-member type so that we can find it again
9305 later. */
9306 TYPE_SET_PTRMEMFUNC_TYPE (type, t);
9307
9308 if (TYPE_STRUCTURAL_EQUALITY_P (type))
9309 SET_TYPE_STRUCTURAL_EQUALITY (t);
9310 else if (TYPE_CANONICAL (type) != type)
9311 TYPE_CANONICAL (t) = build_ptrmemfunc_type (TYPE_CANONICAL (type));
9312
9313 return t;
9314}
9315
9316/* Create and return a pointer to data member type. */
9317
9318tree
9319build_ptrmem_type (tree class_type, tree member_type)
9320{
9321 if (TREE_CODE (member_type) == METHOD_TYPE)
9322 {
9323 cp_cv_quals quals = type_memfn_quals (member_type);
9324 cp_ref_qualifier rqual = type_memfn_rqual (member_type);
9325 member_type = build_memfn_type (member_type, class_type, quals, rqual);
9326 return build_ptrmemfunc_type (build_pointer_type (member_type));
9327 }
9328 else
9329 {
9330 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (member_type) != FUNCTION_TYPE);
9331 return build_offset_type (class_type, member_type);
9332 }
9333}
9334
9335/* DECL is a VAR_DECL defined in-class, whose TYPE is also given.
9336 Check to see that the definition is valid. Issue appropriate error
9337 messages. Return 1 if the definition is particularly bad, or 0
9338 otherwise. */
9339
9340static int
9341check_static_variable_definition (tree decl, tree type)
9342{
9343 /* Avoid redundant diagnostics on out-of-class definitions. */
9344 if (!current_class_type || !TYPE_BEING_DEFINED (current_class_type))
9345 return 0;
9346 /* Can't check yet if we don't know the type. */
9347 if (dependent_type_p (type))
9348 return 0;
9349 /* If DECL is declared constexpr, we'll do the appropriate checks
9350 in check_initializer. Similarly for inline static data members. */
9351 if (DECL_P (decl)
9352 && (DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (decl)
9353 || DECL_VAR_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl)))
9354 return 0;
9355 else if (cxx_dialect >= cxx11 && !INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (type))
9356 {
9357 if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type))
9358 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
9359 "in-class initialization of static data member %q#D of "
9360 "incomplete type", decl);
9361 else if (literal_type_p (type))
9362 permerror (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
9363 "%<constexpr%> needed for in-class initialization of "
9364 "static data member %q#D of non-integral type", decl);
9365 else
9366 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
9367 "in-class initialization of static data member %q#D of "
9368 "non-literal type", decl);
9369 return 1;
9370 }
9371
9372 /* Motion 10 at San Diego: If a static const integral data member is
9373 initialized with an integral constant expression, the initializer
9374 may appear either in the declaration (within the class), or in
9375 the definition, but not both. If it appears in the class, the
9376 member is a member constant. The file-scope definition is always
9377 required. */
9378 if (!ARITHMETIC_TYPE_P (type) && TREE_CODE (type) != ENUMERAL_TYPE)
9379 {
9380 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
9381 "invalid in-class initialization of static data member "
9382 "of non-integral type %qT",
9383 type);
9384 return 1;
9385 }
9386 else if (!CP_TYPE_CONST_P (type))
9387 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
9388 "ISO C++ forbids in-class initialization of non-const "
9389 "static member %qD",
9390 decl);
9391 else if (!INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (type))
9392 pedwarn (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), OPT_Wpedantic,
9393 "ISO C++ forbids initialization of member constant "
9394 "%qD of non-integral type %qT", decl, type);
9395
9396 return 0;
9397}
9398
9399/* *expr_p is part of the TYPE_SIZE of a variably-sized array. If any
9400 SAVE_EXPRs in *expr_p wrap expressions with side-effects, break those
9401 expressions out into temporary variables so that walk_tree doesn't
9402 step into them (c++/15764). */
9403
9404static tree
9405stabilize_save_expr_r (tree *expr_p, int *walk_subtrees, void *data)
9406{
9407 hash_set<tree> *pset = (hash_set<tree> *)data;
9408 tree expr = *expr_p;
9409 if (TREE_CODE (expr) == SAVE_EXPR)
9410 {
9411 tree op = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
9412 cp_walk_tree (&op, stabilize_save_expr_r, data, pset);
9413 if (TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (op))
9414 TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0) = get_temp_regvar (TREE_TYPE (op), op);
9415 *walk_subtrees = 0;
9416 }
9417 else if (!EXPR_P (expr) || !TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (expr))
9418 *walk_subtrees = 0;
9419 return NULL;
9420}
9421
9422/* Entry point for the above. */
9423
9424static void
9425stabilize_vla_size (tree size)
9426{
9427 hash_set<tree> pset;
9428 /* Break out any function calls into temporary variables. */
9429 cp_walk_tree (&size, stabilize_save_expr_r, &pset, &pset);
9430}
9431
9432/* Reduce a SIZEOF_EXPR to its value. */
9433
9434tree
9435fold_sizeof_expr (tree t)
9436{
9437 tree r;
9438 if (SIZEOF_EXPR_TYPE_P (t))
9439 r = cxx_sizeof_or_alignof_type (TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (t, 0)),
9440 SIZEOF_EXPR, false);
9441 else if (TYPE_P (TREE_OPERAND (t, 0)))
9442 r = cxx_sizeof_or_alignof_type (TREE_OPERAND (t, 0), SIZEOF_EXPR,
9443 false);
9444 else
9445 r = cxx_sizeof_or_alignof_expr (TREE_OPERAND (t, 0), SIZEOF_EXPR,
9446 false);
9447 if (r == error_mark_node)
9448 r = size_one_node;
9449 return r;
9450}
9451
9452/* Given the SIZE (i.e., number of elements) in an array, compute
9453 an appropriate index type for the array. If non-NULL, NAME is
9454 the name of the entity being declared. */
9455
9456tree
9457compute_array_index_type (tree name, tree size, tsubst_flags_t complain)
9458{
9459 tree itype;
9460 tree osize = size;
9461
9462 if (error_operand_p (size))
9463 return error_mark_node;
9464
9465 if (!type_dependent_expression_p (size))
9466 {
9467 tree type = TREE_TYPE (size);
9468
9469 mark_rvalue_use (size);
9470
9471 if (cxx_dialect < cxx11 && TREE_CODE (size) == NOP_EXPR
9472 && TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (size))
9473 /* In C++98, we mark a non-constant array bound with a magic
9474 NOP_EXPR with TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS; don't fold in that case. */;
9475 else
9476 {
9477 size = instantiate_non_dependent_expr_sfinae (size, complain);
9478
9479 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type)
9480 && CLASSTYPE_LITERAL_P (type))
9481 {
9482 size = build_expr_type_conversion (WANT_INT, size, true);
9483 if (!size)
9484 {
9485 if (!(complain & tf_error))
9486 return error_mark_node;
9487 if (name)
9488 error ("size of array %qD has non-integral type %qT",
9489 name, type);
9490 else
9491 error ("size of array has non-integral type %qT", type);
9492 size = integer_one_node;
9493 }
9494 if (size == error_mark_node)
9495 return error_mark_node;
9496 type = TREE_TYPE (size);
9497 }
9498
9499 if (INTEGRAL_OR_UNSCOPED_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (type))
9500 size = maybe_constant_value (size);
9501
9502 if (!TREE_CONSTANT (size))
9503 size = osize;
9504 }
9505
9506 if (error_operand_p (size))
9507 return error_mark_node;
9508
9509 /* The array bound must be an integer type. */
9510 if (!INTEGRAL_OR_UNSCOPED_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (type))
9511 {
9512 if (!(complain & tf_error))
9513 return error_mark_node;
9514 if (name)
9515 error ("size of array %qD has non-integral type %qT", name, type);
9516 else
9517 error ("size of array has non-integral type %qT", type);
9518 size = integer_one_node;
9519 type = TREE_TYPE (size);
9520 }
9521 }
9522
9523 /* A type is dependent if it is...an array type constructed from any
9524 dependent type or whose size is specified by a constant expression
9525 that is value-dependent. */
9526 /* We can only call value_dependent_expression_p on integral constant
9527 expressions; treat non-constant expressions as dependent, too. */
9528 if (processing_template_decl
9529 && (type_dependent_expression_p (size)
9530 || !TREE_CONSTANT (size) || value_dependent_expression_p (size)))
9531 {
9532 /* We cannot do any checking for a SIZE that isn't known to be
9533 constant. Just build the index type and mark that it requires
9534 structural equality checks. */
9535 itype = build_index_type (build_min (MINUS_EXPR, sizetype,
9536 size, size_one_node));
9537 TYPE_DEPENDENT_P (itype) = 1;
9538 TYPE_DEPENDENT_P_VALID (itype) = 1;
9539 SET_TYPE_STRUCTURAL_EQUALITY (itype);
9540 return itype;
9541 }
9542
9543 if (TREE_CODE (size) != INTEGER_CST)
9544 {
9545 tree folded = cp_fully_fold (size);
9546 if (TREE_CODE (folded) == INTEGER_CST)
9547 pedwarn (location_of (size), OPT_Wpedantic,
9548 "size of array is not an integral constant-expression");
9549 /* Use the folded result for VLAs, too; it will have resolved
9550 SIZEOF_EXPR. */
9551 size = folded;
9552 }
9553
9554 /* Normally, the array-bound will be a constant. */
9555 if (TREE_CODE (size) == INTEGER_CST)
9556 {
9557 /* Check to see if the array bound overflowed. Make that an
9558 error, no matter how generous we're being. */
9559 constant_expression_error (size);
9560
9561 /* An array must have a positive number of elements. */
9562 tree signed_size = fold_convert (ssizetype, size);
9563 if (tree_int_cst_lt (signed_size, integer_zero_node))
9564 {
9565 if (!(complain & tf_error))
9566 return error_mark_node;
9567 if (name)
9568 error ("size of array %qD is negative", name);
9569 else
9570 error ("size of array is negative");
9571 size = integer_one_node;
9572 }
9573 /* As an extension we allow zero-sized arrays. */
9574 else if (integer_zerop (size))
9575 {
9576 if (!(complain & tf_error))
9577 /* We must fail if performing argument deduction (as
9578 indicated by the state of complain), so that
9579 another substitution can be found. */
9580 return error_mark_node;
9581 else if (in_system_header_at (input_location))
9582 /* Allow them in system headers because glibc uses them. */;
9583 else if (name)
9584 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpedantic, "ISO C++ forbids zero-size array %qD", name);
9585 else
9586 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpedantic, "ISO C++ forbids zero-size array");
9587 }
9588 }
9589 else if (TREE_CONSTANT (size)
9590 /* We don't allow VLAs at non-function scopes, or during
9591 tentative template substitution. */
9592 || !at_function_scope_p ()
9593 || !(complain & tf_error))
9594 {
9595 if (!(complain & tf_error))
9596 return error_mark_node;
9597 /* `(int) &fn' is not a valid array bound. */
9598 if (name)
9599 error ("size of array %qD is not an integral constant-expression",
9600 name);
9601 else
9602 error ("size of array is not an integral constant-expression");
9603 size = integer_one_node;
9604 }
9605 else if (pedantic && warn_vla != 0)
9606 {
9607 if (name)
9608 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wvla, "ISO C++ forbids variable length array %qD", name);
9609 else
9610 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wvla, "ISO C++ forbids variable length array");
9611 }
9612 else if (warn_vla > 0)
9613 {
9614 if (name)
9615 warning (OPT_Wvla,
9616 "variable length array %qD is used", name);
9617 else
9618 warning (OPT_Wvla,
9619 "variable length array is used");
9620 }
9621
9622 if (processing_template_decl && !TREE_CONSTANT (size))
9623 /* A variable sized array. */
9624 itype = build_min (MINUS_EXPR, sizetype, size, integer_one_node);
9625 else
9626 {
9627 HOST_WIDE_INT saved_processing_template_decl;
9628
9629 /* Compute the index of the largest element in the array. It is
9630 one less than the number of elements in the array. We save
9631 and restore PROCESSING_TEMPLATE_DECL so that computations in
9632 cp_build_binary_op will be appropriately folded. */
9633 saved_processing_template_decl = processing_template_decl;
9634 processing_template_decl = 0;
9635 itype = cp_build_binary_op (input_location,
9636 MINUS_EXPR,
9637 cp_convert (ssizetype, size, complain),
9638 cp_convert (ssizetype, integer_one_node,
9639 complain),
9640 complain);
9641 itype = maybe_constant_value (itype);
9642 processing_template_decl = saved_processing_template_decl;
9643
9644 if (!TREE_CONSTANT (itype))
9645 {
9646 /* A variable sized array. */
9647 itype = variable_size (itype);
9648
9649 stabilize_vla_size (itype);
9650
9651 if (flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_VLA
9652 && do_ubsan_in_current_function ())
9653 {
9654 /* We have to add 1 -- in the ubsan routine we generate
9655 LE_EXPR rather than LT_EXPR. */
9656 tree t = fold_build2 (PLUS_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (itype), itype,
9657 build_one_cst (TREE_TYPE (itype)));
9658 t = ubsan_instrument_vla (input_location, t);
9659 finish_expr_stmt (t);
9660 }
9661 }
9662 /* Make sure that there was no overflow when creating to a signed
9663 index type. (For example, on a 32-bit machine, an array with
9664 size 2^32 - 1 is too big.) */
9665 else if (TREE_CODE (itype) == INTEGER_CST
9666 && TREE_OVERFLOW (itype))
9667 {
9668 if (!(complain & tf_error))
9669 return error_mark_node;
9670 error ("overflow in array dimension");
9671 TREE_OVERFLOW (itype) = 0;
9672 }
9673 }
9674
9675 /* Create and return the appropriate index type. */
9676 itype = build_index_type (itype);
9677
9678 /* If the index type were dependent, we would have returned early, so
9679 remember that it isn't. */
9680 TYPE_DEPENDENT_P (itype) = 0;
9681 TYPE_DEPENDENT_P_VALID (itype) = 1;
9682 return itype;
9683}
9684
9685/* Returns the scope (if any) in which the entity declared by
9686 DECLARATOR will be located. If the entity was declared with an
9687 unqualified name, NULL_TREE is returned. */
9688
9689tree
9690get_scope_of_declarator (const cp_declarator *declarator)
9691{
9692 while (declarator && declarator->kind != cdk_id)
9693 declarator = declarator->declarator;
9694
9695 /* If the declarator-id is a SCOPE_REF, the scope in which the
9696 declaration occurs is the first operand. */
9697 if (declarator
9698 && declarator->u.id.qualifying_scope)
9699 return declarator->u.id.qualifying_scope;
9700
9701 /* Otherwise, the declarator is not a qualified name; the entity will
9702 be declared in the current scope. */
9703 return NULL_TREE;
9704}
9705
9706/* Returns an ARRAY_TYPE for an array with SIZE elements of the
9707 indicated TYPE. If non-NULL, NAME is the NAME of the declaration
9708 with this type. */
9709
9710static tree
9711create_array_type_for_decl (tree name, tree type, tree size)
9712{
9713 tree itype = NULL_TREE;
9714
9715 /* If things have already gone awry, bail now. */
9716 if (type == error_mark_node || size == error_mark_node)
9717 return error_mark_node;
9718
9719 /* 8.3.4/1: If the type of the identifier of D contains the auto
9720 type-specifier, the program is ill-formed. */
9721 if (type_uses_auto (type))
9722 {
9723 error ("%qD declared as array of %qT", name, type);
9724 return error_mark_node;
9725 }
9726
9727 /* If there are some types which cannot be array elements,
9728 issue an error-message and return. */
9729 switch (TREE_CODE (type))
9730 {
9731 case VOID_TYPE:
9732 if (name)
9733 error ("declaration of %qD as array of void", name);
9734 else
9735 error ("creating array of void");
9736 return error_mark_node;
9737
9738 case FUNCTION_TYPE:
9739 if (name)
9740 error ("declaration of %qD as array of functions", name);
9741 else
9742 error ("creating array of functions");
9743 return error_mark_node;
9744
9745 case REFERENCE_TYPE:
9746 if (name)
9747 error ("declaration of %qD as array of references", name);
9748 else
9749 error ("creating array of references");
9750 return error_mark_node;
9751
9752 case METHOD_TYPE:
9753 if (name)
9754 error ("declaration of %qD as array of function members", name);
9755 else
9756 error ("creating array of function members");
9757 return error_mark_node;
9758
9759 default:
9760 break;
9761 }
9762
9763 /* [dcl.array]
9764
