9765 The constant expressions that specify the bounds of the arrays
9766 can be omitted only for the first member of the sequence. */
9767 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE && !TYPE_DOMAIN (type))
9768 {
9769 if (name)
9770 error ("declaration of %qD as multidimensional array must "
9771 "have bounds for all dimensions except the first",
9772 name);
9773 else
9774 error ("multidimensional array must have bounds for all "
9775 "dimensions except the first");
9776
9777 return error_mark_node;
9778 }
9779
9780 /* Figure out the index type for the array. */
9781 if (size)
9782 itype = compute_array_index_type (name, size, tf_warning_or_error);
9783
9784 /* [dcl.array]
9785 T is called the array element type; this type shall not be [...] an
9786 abstract class type. */
9787 abstract_virtuals_error (name, type);
9788
9789 return build_cplus_array_type (type, itype);
9790}
9791
9792/* Returns the smallest location != UNKNOWN_LOCATION among the
9793 three stored in LOCATIONS[ds_const], LOCATIONS[ds_volatile],
9794 and LOCATIONS[ds_restrict]. */
9795
9796static location_t
9797smallest_type_quals_location (int type_quals, const location_t* locations)
9798{
9799 location_t loc = UNKNOWN_LOCATION;
9800
9801 if (type_quals & TYPE_QUAL_CONST)
9802 loc = locations[ds_const];
9803
9804 if ((type_quals & TYPE_QUAL_VOLATILE)
9805 && (loc == UNKNOWN_LOCATION || locations[ds_volatile] < loc))
9806 loc = locations[ds_volatile];
9807
9808 if ((type_quals & TYPE_QUAL_RESTRICT)
9809 && (loc == UNKNOWN_LOCATION || locations[ds_restrict] < loc))
9810 loc = locations[ds_restrict];
9811
9812 return loc;
9813}
9814
9815/* Check that it's OK to declare a function with the indicated TYPE
9816 and TYPE_QUALS. SFK indicates the kind of special function (if any)
9817 that this function is. OPTYPE is the type given in a conversion
9818 operator declaration, or the class type for a constructor/destructor.
9819 Returns the actual return type of the function; that may be different
9820 than TYPE if an error occurs, or for certain special functions. */
9821
9822static tree
9823check_special_function_return_type (special_function_kind sfk,
9824 tree type,
9825 tree optype,
9826 int type_quals,
9827 const location_t* locations)
9828{
9829 switch (sfk)
9830 {
9831 case sfk_constructor:
9832 if (type)
9833 error ("return type specification for constructor invalid");
9834 else if (type_quals != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED)
9835 error_at (smallest_type_quals_location (type_quals, locations),
9836 "qualifiers are not allowed on constructor declaration");
9837
9838 if (targetm.cxx.cdtor_returns_this ())
9839 type = build_pointer_type (optype);
9840 else
9841 type = void_type_node;
9842 break;
9843
9844 case sfk_destructor:
9845 if (type)
9846 error ("return type specification for destructor invalid");
9847 else if (type_quals != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED)
9848 error_at (smallest_type_quals_location (type_quals, locations),
9849 "qualifiers are not allowed on destructor declaration");
9850
9851 /* We can't use the proper return type here because we run into
9852 problems with ambiguous bases and covariant returns. */
9853 if (targetm.cxx.cdtor_returns_this ())
9854 type = build_pointer_type (void_type_node);
9855 else
9856 type = void_type_node;
9857 break;
9858
9859 case sfk_conversion:
9860 if (type)
9861 error ("return type specified for %<operator %T%>", optype);
9862 else if (type_quals != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED)
9863 error_at (smallest_type_quals_location (type_quals, locations),
9864 "qualifiers are not allowed on declaration of "
9865 "%<operator %T%>", optype);
9866
9867 type = optype;
9868 break;
9869
9870 case sfk_deduction_guide:
9871 if (type)
9872 error ("return type specified for deduction guide");
9873 else if (type_quals != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED)
9874 error_at (smallest_type_quals_location (type_quals, locations),
9875 "qualifiers are not allowed on declaration of "
9876 "deduction guide");
9877 type = make_template_placeholder (CLASSTYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (optype));
9878 for (int i = 0; i < ds_last; ++i)
9879 if (i != ds_explicit && locations[i])
9880 error_at (locations[i],
9881 "decl-specifier in declaration of deduction guide");
9882 break;
9883
9884 default:
9885 gcc_unreachable ();
9886 }
9887
9888 return type;
9889}
9890
9891/* A variable or data member (whose unqualified name is IDENTIFIER)
9892 has been declared with the indicated TYPE. If the TYPE is not
9893 acceptable, issue an error message and return a type to use for
9894 error-recovery purposes. */
9895
9896tree
9897check_var_type (tree identifier, tree type)
9898{
9899 if (VOID_TYPE_P (type))
9900 {
9901 if (!identifier)
9902 error ("unnamed variable or field declared void");
9903 else if (identifier_p (identifier))
9904 {
9905 gcc_assert (!IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P (identifier));
9906 error ("variable or field %qE declared void", identifier);
9907 }
9908 else
9909 error ("variable or field declared void");
9910 type = error_mark_node;
9911 }
9912
9913 return type;
9914}
9915
9916/* Handle declaring DECL as an inline variable. */
9917
9918static void
9919mark_inline_variable (tree decl)
9920{
9921 bool inlinep = true;
9922 if (! toplevel_bindings_p ())
9923 {
9924 error ("%<inline%> specifier invalid for variable "
9925 "%qD declared at block scope", decl);
9926 inlinep = false;
9927 }
9928 else if (cxx_dialect < cxx1z)
9929 pedwarn (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), 0,
9930 "inline variables are only available "
9931 "with -std=c++1z or -std=gnu++1z");
9932 if (inlinep)
9933 {
9934 retrofit_lang_decl (decl);
9935 SET_DECL_VAR_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl);
9936 }
9937}
9938
9939
9940/* Assign a typedef-given name to a class or enumeration type declared
9941 as anonymous at first. This was split out of grokdeclarator
9942 because it is also used in libcc1. */
9943
9944void
9945name_unnamed_type (tree type, tree decl)
9946{
9947 gcc_assert (TYPE_UNNAMED_P (type));
9948
9949 /* Replace the anonymous name with the real name everywhere. */
9950 for (tree t = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type); t; t = TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT (t))
9951 {
9952 if (anon_aggrname_p (TYPE_IDENTIFIER (t)))
9953 /* We do not rename the debug info representing the
9954 unnamed tagged type because the standard says in
9955 [dcl.typedef] that the naming applies only for
9956 linkage purposes. */
9957 /*debug_hooks->set_name (t, decl);*/
9958 TYPE_NAME (t) = decl;
9959 }
9960
9961 if (TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (type))
9962 TYPE_WAS_UNNAMED (type) = 1;
9963
9964 /* If this is a typedef within a template class, the nested
9965 type is a (non-primary) template. The name for the
9966 template needs updating as well. */
9967 if (TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (type) && CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (type))
9968 DECL_NAME (CLASSTYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (type))
9969 = TYPE_IDENTIFIER (type);
9970
9971 /* Adjust linkage now that we aren't unnamed anymore. */
9972 reset_type_linkage (type);
9973
9974 /* FIXME remangle member functions; member functions of a
9975 type with external linkage have external linkage. */
9976
9977 /* Check that our job is done, and that it would fail if we
9978 attempted to do it again. */
9979 gcc_assert (!TYPE_UNNAMED_P (type));
9980}
9981
9982/* Given declspecs and a declarator (abstract or otherwise), determine
9983 the name and type of the object declared and construct a DECL node
9984 for it.
9985
9986 DECLSPECS points to the representation of declaration-specifier
9987 sequence that precedes declarator.
9988
9989 DECL_CONTEXT says which syntactic context this declaration is in:
9990 NORMAL for most contexts. Make a VAR_DECL or FUNCTION_DECL or TYPE_DECL.
9991 FUNCDEF for a function definition. Like NORMAL but a few different
9992 error messages in each case. Return value may be zero meaning
9993 this definition is too screwy to try to parse.
9994 MEMFUNCDEF for a function definition. Like FUNCDEF but prepares to
9995 handle member functions (which have FIELD context).
9996 Return value may be zero meaning this definition is too screwy to
9997 try to parse.
9998 PARM for a parameter declaration (either within a function prototype
9999 or before a function body). Make a PARM_DECL, or return void_type_node.
10000 TPARM for a template parameter declaration.
10001 CATCHPARM for a parameter declaration before a catch clause.
10002 TYPENAME if for a typename (in a cast or sizeof).
10003 Don't make a DECL node; just return the ..._TYPE node.
10004 FIELD for a struct or union field; make a FIELD_DECL.
10005 BITFIELD for a field with specified width.
10006
10007 INITIALIZED is as for start_decl.
10008
10009 ATTRLIST is a pointer to the list of attributes, which may be NULL
10010 if there are none; *ATTRLIST may be modified if attributes from inside
10011 the declarator should be applied to the declaration.
10012
10013 When this function is called, scoping variables (such as
10014 CURRENT_CLASS_TYPE) should reflect the scope in which the
10015 declaration occurs, not the scope in which the new declaration will
10016 be placed. For example, on:
10017
10018 void S::f() { ... }
10019
10020 when grokdeclarator is called for `S::f', the CURRENT_CLASS_TYPE
10021 should not be `S'.
10022
10023 Returns a DECL (if a declarator is present), a TYPE (if there is no
10024 declarator, in cases like "struct S;"), or the ERROR_MARK_NODE if an
10025 error occurs. */
10026
10027tree
10028grokdeclarator (const cp_declarator *declarator,
10029 cp_decl_specifier_seq *declspecs,
10030 enum decl_context decl_context,
10031 int initialized,
10032 tree* attrlist)
10033{
10034 tree type = NULL_TREE;
10035 int longlong = 0;
10036 int explicit_intN = 0;
10037 int virtualp, explicitp, friendp, inlinep, staticp;
10038 int explicit_int = 0;
10039 int explicit_char = 0;
10040 int defaulted_int = 0;
10041
10042 tree typedef_decl = NULL_TREE;
10043 const char *name = NULL;
10044 tree typedef_type = NULL_TREE;
10045 /* True if this declarator is a function definition. */
10046 bool funcdef_flag = false;
10047 cp_declarator_kind innermost_code = cdk_error;
10048 int bitfield = 0;
10049#if 0
10050 /* See the code below that used this. */
10051 tree decl_attr = NULL_TREE;
10052#endif
10053
10054 /* Keep track of what sort of function is being processed
10055 so that we can warn about default return values, or explicit
10056 return values which do not match prescribed defaults. */
10057 special_function_kind sfk = sfk_none;
10058
10059 tree dname = NULL_TREE;
10060 tree ctor_return_type = NULL_TREE;
10061 enum overload_flags flags = NO_SPECIAL;
10062 /* cv-qualifiers that apply to the declarator, for a declaration of
10063 a member function. */
10064 cp_cv_quals memfn_quals = TYPE_UNQUALIFIED;
10065 /* virt-specifiers that apply to the declarator, for a declaration of
10066 a member function. */
10067 cp_virt_specifiers virt_specifiers = VIRT_SPEC_UNSPECIFIED;
10068 /* ref-qualifier that applies to the declarator, for a declaration of
10069 a member function. */
10070 cp_ref_qualifier rqual = REF_QUAL_NONE;
10071 /* cv-qualifiers that apply to the type specified by the DECLSPECS. */
10072 int type_quals = TYPE_UNQUALIFIED;
10073 tree raises = NULL_TREE;
10074 int template_count = 0;
10075 tree returned_attrs = NULL_TREE;
10076 tree parms = NULL_TREE;
10077 const cp_declarator *id_declarator;
10078 /* The unqualified name of the declarator; either an
10079 IDENTIFIER_NODE, BIT_NOT_EXPR, or TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR. */
10080 tree unqualified_id;
10081 /* The class type, if any, in which this entity is located,
10082 or NULL_TREE if none. Note that this value may be different from
10083 the current class type; for example if an attempt is made to declare
10084 "A::f" inside "B", this value will be "A". */
10085 tree ctype = current_class_type;
10086 /* The NAMESPACE_DECL for the namespace in which this entity is
10087 located. If an unqualified name is used to declare the entity,
10088 this value will be NULL_TREE, even if the entity is located at
10089 namespace scope. */
10090 tree in_namespace = NULL_TREE;
10091 cp_storage_class storage_class;
10092 bool unsigned_p, signed_p, short_p, long_p, thread_p;
10093 bool type_was_error_mark_node = false;
10094 bool parameter_pack_p = declarator ? declarator->parameter_pack_p : false;
10095 bool template_type_arg = false;
10096 bool template_parm_flag = false;
10097 bool typedef_p = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_typedef);
10098 bool constexpr_p = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_constexpr);
10099 bool late_return_type_p = false;
10100 bool array_parameter_p = false;
10101 source_location saved_loc = input_location;
10102 tree reqs = NULL_TREE;
10103
10104 signed_p = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_signed);
10105 unsigned_p = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_unsigned);
10106 short_p = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_short);
10107 long_p = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_long);
10108 longlong = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_long_long);
10109 explicit_intN = declspecs->explicit_intN_p;
10110 thread_p = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_thread);
10111
10112 // Was concept_p specified? Note that ds_concept
10113 // implies ds_constexpr!
10114 bool concept_p = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_concept);
10115 if (concept_p)
10116 constexpr_p = true;
10117
10118 if (decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_const))
10119 type_quals |= TYPE_QUAL_CONST;
10120 if (decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_volatile))
10121 type_quals |= TYPE_QUAL_VOLATILE;
10122 if (decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_restrict))
10123 type_quals |= TYPE_QUAL_RESTRICT;
10124
10125 if (decl_context == FUNCDEF)
10126 funcdef_flag = true, decl_context = NORMAL;
10127 else if (decl_context == MEMFUNCDEF)
10128 funcdef_flag = true, decl_context = FIELD;
10129 else if (decl_context == BITFIELD)
10130 bitfield = 1, decl_context = FIELD;
10131 else if (decl_context == TEMPLATE_TYPE_ARG)
10132 template_type_arg = true, decl_context = TYPENAME;
10133 else if (decl_context == TPARM)
10134 template_parm_flag = true, decl_context = PARM;
10135
10136 if (initialized > 1)
10137 funcdef_flag = true;
10138
10139 location_t typespec_loc = smallest_type_quals_location (type_quals,
10140 declspecs->locations);
10141 if (typespec_loc == UNKNOWN_LOCATION)
10142 typespec_loc = declspecs->locations[ds_type_spec];
10143 if (typespec_loc == UNKNOWN_LOCATION)
10144 typespec_loc = input_location;
10145
10146 /* Look inside a declarator for the name being declared
10147 and get it as a string, for an error message. */
10148 for (id_declarator = declarator;
10149 id_declarator;
10150 id_declarator = id_declarator->declarator)
10151 {
10152 if (id_declarator->kind != cdk_id)
10153 innermost_code = id_declarator->kind;
10154
10155 switch (id_declarator->kind)
10156 {
10157 case cdk_function:
10158 if (id_declarator->declarator
10159 && id_declarator->declarator->kind == cdk_id)
10160 {
10161 sfk = id_declarator->declarator->u.id.sfk;
10162 if (sfk == sfk_destructor)
10163 flags = DTOR_FLAG;
10164 }
10165 break;
10166
10167 case cdk_id:
10168 {
10169 tree qualifying_scope = id_declarator->u.id.qualifying_scope;
10170 tree decl = id_declarator->u.id.unqualified_name;
10171 if (!decl)
10172 break;
10173 if (qualifying_scope)
10174 {
10175 if (at_function_scope_p ())
10176 {
10177 /* [dcl.meaning]
10178
10179 A declarator-id shall not be qualified except
10180 for ...
10181
10182 None of the cases are permitted in block
10183 scope. */
10184 if (qualifying_scope == global_namespace)
10185 error ("invalid use of qualified-name %<::%D%>",
10186 decl);
10187 else if (TYPE_P (qualifying_scope))
10188 error ("invalid use of qualified-name %<%T::%D%>",
10189 qualifying_scope, decl);
10190 else
10191 error ("invalid use of qualified-name %<%D::%D%>",
10192 qualifying_scope, decl);
10193 return error_mark_node;
10194 }
10195 else if (TYPE_P (qualifying_scope))
10196 {
10197 ctype = qualifying_scope;
10198 if (!MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (ctype))
10199 {
10200 error ("%q#T is not a class or a namespace", ctype);
10201 ctype = NULL_TREE;
10202 }
10203 else if (innermost_code != cdk_function
10204 && current_class_type
10205 && !uniquely_derived_from_p (ctype,
10206 current_class_type))
10207 {
10208 error ("invalid use of qualified-name %<%T::%D%>",
10209 qualifying_scope, decl);
10210 return error_mark_node;
10211 }
10212 }
10213 else if (TREE_CODE (qualifying_scope) == NAMESPACE_DECL)
10214 in_namespace = qualifying_scope;
10215 }
10216 switch (TREE_CODE (decl))
10217 {
10218 case BIT_NOT_EXPR:
10219 {
10220 tree type;
10221
10222 if (innermost_code != cdk_function)
10223 {
10224 error ("declaration of %qD as non-function", decl);
10225 return error_mark_node;
10226 }
10227 else if (!qualifying_scope
10228 && !(current_class_type && at_class_scope_p ()))
10229 {
10230 error ("declaration of %qD as non-member", decl);
10231 return error_mark_node;
10232 }
10233
10234 type = TREE_OPERAND (decl, 0);
10235 if (TYPE_P (type))
10236 type = constructor_name (type);
10237 name = identifier_to_locale (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (type));
10238 dname = decl;
10239 }
10240 break;
10241
10242 case TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR:
10243 {
10244 tree fns = TREE_OPERAND (decl, 0);
10245
10246 dname = fns;
10247 if (!identifier_p (dname))
10248 {
10249 if (variable_template_p (dname))
10250 dname = DECL_NAME (dname);
10251 else
10252 {
10253 gcc_assert (is_overloaded_fn (dname));
10254 dname = DECL_NAME (get_first_fn (dname));
10255 }
10256 }
10257 }
10258 /* Fall through. */
10259
10260 case IDENTIFIER_NODE:
10261 if (identifier_p (decl))
10262 dname = decl;
10263
10264 if (C_IS_RESERVED_WORD (dname))
10265 {
10266 error ("declarator-id missing; using reserved word %qD",
10267 dname);
10268 name = identifier_to_locale (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (dname));
10269 }
10270 else if (!IDENTIFIER_TYPENAME_P (dname))
10271 name = identifier_to_locale (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (dname));
10272 else
10273 {
10274 gcc_assert (flags == NO_SPECIAL);
10275 flags = TYPENAME_FLAG;
10276 sfk = sfk_conversion;
10277 if (is_typename_at_global_scope (dname))
10278 name = identifier_to_locale (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (dname));
10279 else
10280 name = "<invalid operator>";
10281 }
10282 break;
10283
10284 default:
10285 gcc_unreachable ();
10286 }
10287 break;
10288 }
10289
10290 case cdk_array:
10291 case cdk_pointer:
10292 case cdk_reference:
10293 case cdk_ptrmem:
10294 break;
10295
10296 case cdk_decomp:
10297 name = "decomposition";
10298 break;
10299
10300 case cdk_error:
10301 return error_mark_node;
10302
10303 default:
10304 gcc_unreachable ();
10305 }
10306 if (id_declarator->kind == cdk_id)
10307 break;
10308 }
10309
10310 /* [dcl.fct.edf]
10311
10312 The declarator in a function-definition shall have the form
10313 D1 ( parameter-declaration-clause) ... */
10314 if (funcdef_flag && innermost_code != cdk_function)
10315 {
10316 error ("function definition does not declare parameters");
10317 return error_mark_node;
10318 }
10319
10320 if (flags == TYPENAME_FLAG
10321 && innermost_code != cdk_function
10322 && ! (ctype && !declspecs->any_specifiers_p))
10323 {
10324 error ("declaration of %qD as non-function", dname);
10325 return error_mark_node;
10326 }
10327
10328 if (dname
10329 && identifier_p (dname)
10330 && UDLIT_OPER_P (dname)
10331 && innermost_code != cdk_function)
10332 {
10333 error ("declaration of %qD as non-function", dname);
10334 return error_mark_node;
10335 }
10336
10337 if (dname && IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P (dname))
10338 {
10339 if (typedef_p)
10340 {
10341 error ("declaration of %qD as %<typedef%>", dname);
10342 return error_mark_node;
10343 }
10344 else if (decl_context == PARM || decl_context == CATCHPARM)
10345 {
10346 error ("declaration of %qD as parameter", dname);
10347 return error_mark_node;
10348 }
10349 }
10350
10351 /* Anything declared one level down from the top level
10352 must be one of the parameters of a function
10353 (because the body is at least two levels down). */
10354
10355 /* This heuristic cannot be applied to C++ nodes! Fixed, however,
10356 by not allowing C++ class definitions to specify their parameters
10357 with xdecls (must be spec.d in the parmlist).
10358
10359 Since we now wait to push a class scope until we are sure that
10360 we are in a legitimate method context, we must set oldcname
10361 explicitly (since current_class_name is not yet alive).
10362
10363 We also want to avoid calling this a PARM if it is in a namespace. */
10364
10365 if (decl_context == NORMAL && !toplevel_bindings_p ())
10366 {
10367 cp_binding_level *b = current_binding_level;
10368 current_binding_level = b->level_chain;
10369 if (current_binding_level != 0 && toplevel_bindings_p ())
10370 decl_context = PARM;
10371 current_binding_level = b;
10372 }
10373
10374 if (name == NULL)
10375 name = decl_context == PARM ? "parameter" : "type name";
10376
10377 if (concept_p && typedef_p)
10378 {
10379 error ("%<concept%> cannot appear in a typedef declaration");
10380 return error_mark_node;
10381 }
10382
10383 if (constexpr_p && typedef_p)
10384 {
10385 error ("%<constexpr%> cannot appear in a typedef declaration");
10386 return error_mark_node;
10387 }
10388
10389 /* If there were multiple types specified in the decl-specifier-seq,
10390 issue an error message. */
10391 if (declspecs->multiple_types_p)
10392 {
10393 error ("two or more data types in declaration of %qs", name);
10394 return error_mark_node;
10395 }
10396
10397 if (declspecs->conflicting_specifiers_p)
10398 {
10399 error ("conflicting specifiers in declaration of %qs", name);
10400 return error_mark_node;
10401 }
10402
10403 /* Extract the basic type from the decl-specifier-seq. */
10404 type = declspecs->type;
10405 if (type == error_mark_node)
10406 {
10407 type = NULL_TREE;
10408 type_was_error_mark_node = true;
10409 }
10410 /* If the entire declaration is itself tagged as deprecated then
10411 suppress reports of deprecated items. */
10412 if (type && TREE_DEPRECATED (type)
10413 && deprecated_state != DEPRECATED_SUPPRESS)
10414 cp_warn_deprecated_use (type);
10415 if (type && TREE_CODE (type) == TYPE_DECL)
10416 {
10417 typedef_decl = type;
10418 type = TREE_TYPE (typedef_decl);
10419 if (TREE_DEPRECATED (type)
10420 && DECL_ARTIFICIAL (typedef_decl)
10421 && deprecated_state != DEPRECATED_SUPPRESS)
10422 cp_warn_deprecated_use (type);
10423 }
10424 /* No type at all: default to `int', and set DEFAULTED_INT
10425 because it was not a user-defined typedef. */
10426 if (type == NULL_TREE)
10427 {
10428 if (signed_p || unsigned_p || long_p || short_p)
10429 {
10430 /* These imply 'int'. */
10431 type = integer_type_node;
10432 defaulted_int = 1;
10433 }
10434 /* If we just have "complex", it is equivalent to "complex double". */
10435 else if (!longlong && !explicit_intN
10436 && decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_complex))
10437 {
10438 type = double_type_node;
10439 pedwarn (declspecs->locations[ds_complex], OPT_Wpedantic,
10440 "ISO C++ does not support plain %<complex%> meaning "
10441 "%<double complex%>");
10442 }
10443 }
10444 /* Gather flags. */
10445 explicit_int = declspecs->explicit_int_p;
10446 explicit_char = declspecs->explicit_char_p;
10447
10448#if 0
10449 /* See the code below that used this. */
10450 if (typedef_decl)
10451 decl_attr = DECL_ATTRIBUTES (typedef_decl);
10452#endif
10453 typedef_type = type;
10454
10455 if (sfk == sfk_conversion || sfk == sfk_deduction_guide)
10456 ctor_return_type = TREE_TYPE (dname);
10457 else
10458 ctor_return_type = ctype;
10459
10460 if (sfk != sfk_none)
10461 {
10462 type = check_special_function_return_type (sfk, type,
10463 ctor_return_type,
10464 type_quals,
10465 declspecs->locations);
10466 type_quals = TYPE_UNQUALIFIED;
10467 }
10468 else if (type == NULL_TREE)
10469 {
10470 int is_main;
10471
10472 explicit_int = -1;
10473
10474 /* We handle `main' specially here, because 'main () { }' is so
10475 common. With no options, it is allowed. With -Wreturn-type,
10476 it is a warning. It is only an error with -pedantic-errors. */
10477 is_main = (funcdef_flag
10478 && dname && identifier_p (dname)
10479 && MAIN_NAME_P (dname)
10480 && ctype == NULL_TREE
10481 && in_namespace == NULL_TREE
10482 && current_namespace == global_namespace);
10483
10484 if (type_was_error_mark_node)
10485 /* We've already issued an error, don't complain more. */;
10486 else if (in_system_header_at (input_location) || flag_ms_extensions)
10487 /* Allow it, sigh. */;
10488 else if (! is_main)
10489 permerror (input_location, "ISO C++ forbids declaration of %qs with no type", name);
10490 else if (pedantic)
10491 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpedantic,
10492 "ISO C++ forbids declaration of %qs with no type", name);
10493 else
10494 warning (OPT_Wreturn_type,
10495 "ISO C++ forbids declaration of %qs with no type", name);
10496
10497 if (type_was_error_mark_node && template_parm_flag)
10498 /* FIXME we should be able to propagate the error_mark_node as is
10499 for other contexts too. */
10500 type = error_mark_node;
10501 else
10502 type = integer_type_node;
10503 }
10504
10505 ctype = NULL_TREE;
10506
10507 if (explicit_intN)
10508 {
10509 if (! int_n_enabled_p[declspecs->int_n_idx])
10510 {
10511 error ("%<__int%d%> is not supported by this target",
10512 int_n_data[declspecs->int_n_idx].bitsize);
10513 explicit_intN = false;
10514 }
10515 else if (pedantic && ! in_system_header_at (input_location))
10516 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpedantic,
10517 "ISO C++ does not support %<__int%d%> for %qs",
10518 int_n_data[declspecs->int_n_idx].bitsize, name);
10519 }
10520
10521 /* Now process the modifiers that were specified
10522 and check for invalid combinations. */
10523
10524 /* Long double is a special combination. */
10525 if (long_p && !longlong && TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type) == double_type_node)
10526 {
10527 long_p = false;
10528 type = cp_build_qualified_type (long_double_type_node,
10529 cp_type_quals (type));
10530 }
10531
10532 /* Check all other uses of type modifiers. */
10533
10534 if (unsigned_p || signed_p || long_p || short_p)
10535 {
10536 int ok = 0;
10537
10538 if ((signed_p || unsigned_p) && TREE_CODE (type) != INTEGER_TYPE)
10539 error ("%<signed%> or %<unsigned%> invalid for %qs", name);
10540 else if (signed_p && unsigned_p)
10541 error ("%<signed%> and %<unsigned%> specified together for %qs", name);
10542 else if (longlong && TREE_CODE (type) != INTEGER_TYPE)
10543 error ("%<long long%> invalid for %qs", name);
10544 else if (long_p && TREE_CODE (type) == REAL_TYPE)
10545 error ("%<long%> invalid for %qs", name);
10546 else if (short_p && TREE_CODE (type) == REAL_TYPE)
10547 error ("%<short%> invalid for %qs", name);
10548 else if ((long_p || short_p) && TREE_CODE (type) != INTEGER_TYPE)
10549 error ("%<long%> or %<short%> invalid for %qs", name);
10550 else if ((long_p || short_p || explicit_char || explicit_int) && explicit_intN)
10551 error ("%<long%>, %<int%>, %<short%>, or %<char%> invalid for %qs", name);
10552 else if ((long_p || short_p) && explicit_char)
10553 error ("%<long%> or %<short%> specified with char for %qs", name);
10554 else if (long_p && short_p)
10555 error ("%<long%> and %<short%> specified together for %qs", name);
10556 else if (type == char16_type_node || type == char32_type_node)
10557 {
10558 if (signed_p || unsigned_p)
10559 error ("%<signed%> or %<unsigned%> invalid for %qs", name);
10560 else if (short_p || long_p)
10561 error ("%<short%> or %<long%> invalid for %qs", name);
10562 }
10563 else
10564 {
10565 ok = 1;
10566 if (!explicit_int && !defaulted_int && !explicit_char && !explicit_intN && pedantic)
10567 {
10568 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpedantic,
10569 "long, short, signed or unsigned used invalidly for %qs",
10570 name);
10571 if (flag_pedantic_errors)
10572 ok = 0;
10573 }
10574 }
10575
10576 /* Discard the type modifiers if they are invalid. */
10577 if (! ok)
10578 {
10579 unsigned_p = false;
10580 signed_p = false;
10581 long_p = false;
10582 short_p = false;
10583 longlong = 0;
10584 }
10585 }
10586
10587 /* Decide whether an integer type is signed or not.
10588 Optionally treat bitfields as signed by default. */
10589 if (unsigned_p
10590 /* [class.bit]
10591
10592 It is implementation-defined whether a plain (neither
10593 explicitly signed or unsigned) char, short, int, or long
10594 bit-field is signed or unsigned.
10595
10596 Naturally, we extend this to long long as well. Note that
10597 this does not include wchar_t. */
10598 || (bitfield && !flag_signed_bitfields
10599 && !signed_p
10600 /* A typedef for plain `int' without `signed' can be
10601 controlled just like plain `int', but a typedef for
10602 `signed int' cannot be so controlled. */
10603 && !(typedef_decl
10604 && C_TYPEDEF_EXPLICITLY_SIGNED (typedef_decl))
10605 && TREE_CODE (type) == INTEGER_TYPE
10606 && !same_type_p (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type), wchar_type_node)))
10607 {
10608 if (explicit_intN)
10609 type = int_n_trees[declspecs->int_n_idx].unsigned_type;
10610 else if (longlong)
10611 type = long_long_unsigned_type_node;
10612 else if (long_p)
10613 type = long_unsigned_type_node;
10614 else if (short_p)
10615 type = short_unsigned_type_node;
10616 else if (type == char_type_node)
10617 type = unsigned_char_type_node;
10618 else if (typedef_decl)
10619 type = unsigned_type_for (type);
10620 else
10621 type = unsigned_type_node;
10622 }
10623 else if (signed_p && type == char_type_node)
10624 type = signed_char_type_node;
10625 else if (explicit_intN)
10626 type = int_n_trees[declspecs->int_n_idx].signed_type;
10627 else if (longlong)
10628 type = long_long_integer_type_node;
10629 else if (long_p)
10630 type = long_integer_type_node;
10631 else if (short_p)
10632 type = short_integer_type_node;
10633
10634 if (decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_complex))
10635 {
10636 if (TREE_CODE (type) != INTEGER_TYPE && TREE_CODE (type) != REAL_TYPE)
10637 error ("complex invalid for %qs", name);
10638 /* If a modifier is specified, the resulting complex is the complex
10639 form of TYPE. E.g, "complex short" is "complex short int". */
10640 else if (type == integer_type_node)
10641 type = complex_integer_type_node;
10642 else if (type == float_type_node)
10643 type = complex_float_type_node;
10644 else if (type == double_type_node)
10645 type = complex_double_type_node;
10646 else if (type == long_double_type_node)
10647 type = complex_long_double_type_node;
10648 else
10649 type = build_complex_type (type);
10650 }
10651
10652 /* If we're using the injected-class-name to form a compound type or a
10653 declaration, replace it with the underlying class so we don't get
10654 redundant typedefs in the debug output. But if we are returning the
10655 type unchanged, leave it alone so that it's available to
10656 maybe_get_template_decl_from_type_decl. */
10657 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type)
10658 && DECL_SELF_REFERENCE_P (TYPE_NAME (type))
10659 && type == TREE_TYPE (TYPE_NAME (type))
10660 && (declarator || type_quals))
10661 type = DECL_ORIGINAL_TYPE (TYPE_NAME (type));
10662
10663 type_quals |= cp_type_quals (type);
10664 type = cp_build_qualified_type_real
10665 (type, type_quals, ((((typedef_decl && !DECL_ARTIFICIAL (typedef_decl))
10666 || declspecs->decltype_p)
10667 ? tf_ignore_bad_quals : 0) | tf_warning_or_error));
10668 /* We might have ignored or rejected some of the qualifiers. */
10669 type_quals = cp_type_quals (type);
10670
10671 if (cxx_dialect >= cxx1z && type && is_auto (type)
10672 && innermost_code != cdk_function
10673 && id_declarator && declarator != id_declarator)
10674 if (tree tmpl = CLASS_PLACEHOLDER_TEMPLATE (type))
10675 {
10676 error_at (typespec_loc, "template placeholder type %qT must be followed "
10677 "by a simple declarator-id", type);
10678 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (tmpl), "%qD declared here", tmpl);
10679 }
10680
10681 staticp = 0;
10682 inlinep = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_inline);
10683 virtualp = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_virtual);
10684 explicitp = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_explicit);
10685
10686 storage_class = declspecs->storage_class;
10687 if (storage_class == sc_static)
10688 staticp = 1 + (decl_context == FIELD);
10689
10690 if (virtualp)
10691 {
10692 if (staticp == 2)
10693 {
10694 error ("member %qD cannot be declared both %<virtual%> "
10695 "and %<static%>", dname);
10696 storage_class = sc_none;
10697 staticp = 0;
10698 }
10699 if (constexpr_p)
10700 error ("member %qD cannot be declared both %<virtual%> "
10701 "and %<constexpr%>", dname);
10702 }
10703 friendp = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_friend);
10704
10705 /* Issue errors about use of storage classes for parameters. */
10706 if (decl_context == PARM)
10707 {
10708 if (typedef_p)
10709 {
10710 error ("typedef declaration invalid in parameter declaration");
10711 return error_mark_node;
10712 }
10713 else if (template_parm_flag && storage_class != sc_none)
10714 {
10715 error ("storage class specified for template parameter %qs", name);
10716 return error_mark_node;
10717 }
10718 else if (storage_class == sc_static
10719 || storage_class == sc_extern
10720 || thread_p)
10721 error ("storage class specifiers invalid in parameter declarations");
10722
10723 /* Function parameters cannot be concept. */
10724 if (concept_p)
10725 error ("a parameter cannot be declared %<concept%>");
10726 /* Function parameters cannot be constexpr. If we saw one, moan
10727 and pretend it wasn't there. */
10728 else if (constexpr_p)
10729 {
10730 error ("a parameter cannot be declared %<constexpr%>");
10731 constexpr_p = 0;
10732 }
10733 }
10734
10735 /* Give error if `virtual' is used outside of class declaration. */
10736 if (virtualp
10737 && (current_class_name == NULL_TREE || decl_context != FIELD))
10738 {
10739 error_at (declspecs->locations[ds_virtual],
10740 "%<virtual%> outside class declaration");
10741 virtualp = 0;
10742 }
10743
10744 if (innermost_code == cdk_decomp)
10745 {
10746 location_t loc = (declarator->kind == cdk_reference
10747 ? declarator->declarator->id_loc : declarator->id_loc);
10748 if (inlinep)
10749 error_at (declspecs->locations[ds_inline],
10750 "decomposition declaration cannot be declared %<inline%>");
10751 if (typedef_p)
10752 error_at (declspecs->locations[ds_typedef],
10753 "decomposition declaration cannot be declared %<typedef%>");
10754 if (constexpr_p)
10755 error_at (declspecs->locations[ds_constexpr], "decomposition "
10756 "declaration cannot be declared %<constexpr%>");
10757 if (thread_p)
10758 error_at (declspecs->locations[ds_thread],
10759 "decomposition declaration cannot be declared %qs",
10760 declspecs->gnu_thread_keyword_p
10761 ? "__thread" : "thread_local");
10762 if (concept_p)
10763 error_at (declspecs->locations[ds_concept],
10764 "decomposition declaration cannot be declared %<concept%>");
10765 switch (storage_class)
10766 {
10767 case sc_none:
10768 break;
10769 case sc_register:
10770 error_at (loc, "decomposition declaration cannot be declared "
10771 "%<register%>");
10772 break;
10773 case sc_static:
10774 error_at (loc, "decomposition declaration cannot be declared "
10775 "%<static%>");
10776 break;
10777 case sc_extern:
10778 error_at (loc, "decomposition declaration cannot be declared "
10779 "%<extern%>");
10780 break;
10781 case sc_mutable:
10782 error_at (loc, "decomposition declaration cannot be declared "
10783 "%<mutable%>");
10784 break;
10785 case sc_auto:
10786 error_at (loc, "decomposition declaration cannot be declared "
10787 "C++98 %<auto%>");
10788 break;
10789 default:
10790 gcc_unreachable ();
10791 }
10792 if (TREE_CODE (type) != TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM
10793 || TYPE_IDENTIFIER (type) != auto_identifier)
10794 {
10795 if (type != error_mark_node)
10796 {
10797 error_at (loc, "decomposition declaration cannot be declared "
10798 "with type %qT", type);
10799 inform (loc,
10800 "type must be cv-qualified %<auto%> or reference to "
10801 "cv-qualified %<auto%>");
10802 }
10803 type = build_qualified_type (make_auto (), type_quals);
10804 declspecs->type = type;
10805 }
10806 inlinep = 0;
10807 typedef_p = 0;
10808 constexpr_p = 0;
10809 thread_p = 0;
10810 concept_p = 0;
10811 storage_class = sc_none;
10812 staticp = 0;
10813 declspecs->storage_class = sc_none;
10814 declspecs->locations[ds_thread] = UNKNOWN_LOCATION;
10815 }
10816
10817 /* Static anonymous unions are dealt with here. */
10818 if (staticp && decl_context == TYPENAME
10819 && declspecs->type
10820 && ANON_AGGR_TYPE_P (declspecs->type))
10821 decl_context = FIELD;
10822
10823 /* Warn about storage classes that are invalid for certain
10824 kinds of declarations (parameters, typenames, etc.). */
10825 if (thread_p
10826 && ((storage_class
10827 && storage_class != sc_extern
10828 && storage_class != sc_static)
10829 || typedef_p))
10830 {
10831 error ("multiple storage classes in declaration of %qs", name);
10832 thread_p = false;
10833 }
10834 if (decl_context != NORMAL
10835 && ((storage_class != sc_none
10836 && storage_class != sc_mutable)
10837 || thread_p))
10838 {
10839 if ((decl_context == PARM || decl_context == CATCHPARM)
10840 && (storage_class == sc_register
10841 || storage_class == sc_auto))
10842 ;
10843 else if (typedef_p)
10844 ;
10845 else if (decl_context == FIELD
10846 /* C++ allows static class elements. */
10847 && storage_class == sc_static)
10848 /* C++ also allows inlines and signed and unsigned elements,
10849 but in those cases we don't come in here. */
10850 ;
10851 else
10852 {
10853 if (decl_context == FIELD)
10854 error ("storage class specified for %qs", name);
10855 else
10856 {
10857 if (decl_context == PARM || decl_context == CATCHPARM)
10858 error ("storage class specified for parameter %qs", name);
10859 else
10860 error ("storage class specified for typename");
10861 }
10862 if (storage_class == sc_register
10863 || storage_class == sc_auto
10864 || storage_class == sc_extern
10865 || thread_p)
10866 storage_class = sc_none;
10867 }
10868 }
10869 else if (storage_class == sc_extern && funcdef_flag
10870 && ! toplevel_bindings_p ())
10871 error ("nested function %qs declared %<extern%>", name);
10872 else if (toplevel_bindings_p ())
10873 {
10874 if (storage_class == sc_auto)
10875 error ("top-level declaration of %qs specifies %<auto%>", name);
10876 }
10877 else if (thread_p
10878 && storage_class != sc_extern
10879 && storage_class != sc_static)
10880 {
10881 if (declspecs->gnu_thread_keyword_p)
10882 pedwarn (input_location, 0, "function-scope %qs implicitly auto and "
10883 "declared %<__thread%>", name);
10884
10885 /* When thread_local is applied to a variable of block scope the
10886 storage-class-specifier static is implied if it does not appear
10887 explicitly. */
10888 storage_class = declspecs->storage_class = sc_static;
10889 staticp = 1;
10890 }
10891
10892 if (storage_class && friendp)
10893 {
10894 error ("storage class specifiers invalid in friend function declarations");
10895 storage_class = sc_none;
10896 staticp = 0;
10897 }
10898
10899 if (!id_declarator)
10900 unqualified_id = NULL_TREE;
10901 else
10902 {
10903 unqualified_id = id_declarator->u.id.unqualified_name;
10904 switch (TREE_CODE (unqualified_id))
10905 {
10906 case BIT_NOT_EXPR:
10907 unqualified_id = TREE_OPERAND (unqualified_id, 0);
10908 if (TYPE_P (unqualified_id))
10909 unqualified_id = constructor_name (unqualified_id);
10910 break;
10911
10912 case IDENTIFIER_NODE:
10913 case TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR:
10914 break;
10915
10916 default:
10917 gcc_unreachable ();
10918 }
10919 }
10920
10921 if (declspecs->std_attributes)
10922 {
10923 /* Apply the c++11 attributes to the type preceding them. */
10924 input_location = declspecs->locations[ds_std_attribute];
10925 decl_attributes (&type, declspecs->std_attributes, 0);
10926 input_location = saved_loc;
10927 }
10928
10929 /* Determine the type of the entity declared by recurring on the
10930 declarator. */
10931 for (; declarator; declarator = declarator->declarator)
10932 {
10933 const cp_declarator *inner_declarator;
10934 tree attrs;
10935
10936 if (type == error_mark_node)
10937 return error_mark_node;
10938
10939 attrs = declarator->attributes;
10940 if (attrs)
10941 {
10942 int attr_flags;
10943
10944 attr_flags = 0;
10945 if (declarator == NULL || declarator->kind == cdk_id)
10946 attr_flags |= (int) ATTR_FLAG_DECL_NEXT;
10947 if (declarator->kind == cdk_function)
10948 attr_flags |= (int) ATTR_FLAG_FUNCTION_NEXT;
10949 if (declarator->kind == cdk_array)
10950 attr_flags |= (int) ATTR_FLAG_ARRAY_NEXT;
10951 returned_attrs = decl_attributes (&type,
10952 chainon (returned_attrs, attrs),
10953 attr_flags);
10954 }
10955
10956 if (declarator->kind == cdk_id || declarator->kind == cdk_decomp)
10957 break;
10958
10959 inner_declarator = declarator->declarator;
10960
10961 switch (declarator->kind)
10962 {
10963 case cdk_array:
10964 type = create_array_type_for_decl (dname, type,
10965 declarator->u.array.bounds);
10966 if (!valid_array_size_p (input_location, type, dname))
10967 type = error_mark_node;
10968
10969 if (declarator->std_attributes)
10970 /* [dcl.array]/1:
10971
10972 The optional attribute-specifier-seq appertains to the
10973 array. */
10974 returned_attrs = chainon (returned_attrs,
10975 declarator->std_attributes);
10976 break;
10977
10978 case cdk_function:
10979 {
10980 tree arg_types;
10981 int funcdecl_p;
10982
10983 /* Declaring a function type.
10984 Make sure we have a valid type for the function to return. */
10985
10986 if (type_quals != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED)
10987 {
10988 if (SCALAR_TYPE_P (type) || VOID_TYPE_P (type))
10989 {
10990 warning_at (typespec_loc, OPT_Wignored_qualifiers, "type "
10991 "qualifiers ignored on function return type");
10992 }
10993 /* We now know that the TYPE_QUALS don't apply to the
10994 decl, but to its return type. */
10995 type_quals = TYPE_UNQUALIFIED;
10996 }
10997
10998 /* Error about some types functions can't return. */
10999
11000 if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
11001 {
11002 error ("%qs declared as function returning a function", name);
11003 return error_mark_node;
11004 }
11005 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
11006 {
11007 error ("%qs declared as function returning an array", name);
11008 return error_mark_node;
11009 }
11010
11011 input_location = declspecs->locations[ds_type_spec];
11012 abstract_virtuals_error (ACU_RETURN, type);
11013 input_location = saved_loc;
11014
11015 /* Pick up type qualifiers which should be applied to `this'. */
11016 memfn_quals = declarator->u.function.qualifiers;
11017 /* Pick up virt-specifiers. */
11018 virt_specifiers = declarator->u.function.virt_specifiers;
11019 /* And ref-qualifier, too */
11020 rqual = declarator->u.function.ref_qualifier;
11021 /* And tx-qualifier. */
11022 tree tx_qual = declarator->u.function.tx_qualifier;
11023 /* Pick up the exception specifications. */
11024 raises = declarator->u.function.exception_specification;
11025 /* If the exception-specification is ill-formed, let's pretend
11026 there wasn't one. */
11027 if (raises == error_mark_node)
11028 raises = NULL_TREE;
11029
11030 if (reqs)
11031 error_at (location_of (reqs), "requires-clause on return type");
11032 reqs = declarator->u.function.requires_clause;
11033
11034 /* Say it's a definition only for the CALL_EXPR
11035 closest to the identifier. */
11036 funcdecl_p = inner_declarator && inner_declarator->kind == cdk_id;
11037
11038 /* Handle a late-specified return type. */
11039 tree late_return_type = declarator->u.function.late_return_type;
11040 if (funcdecl_p)
11041 {
11042 if (tree auto_node = type_uses_auto (type))
11043 {
11044 if (!late_return_type)
11045 {
11046 if (current_class_type
11047 && LAMBDA_TYPE_P (current_class_type))
11048 /* OK for C++11 lambdas. */;
11049 else if (cxx_dialect < cxx14)
11050 {
11051 error ("%qs function uses "
11052 "%<auto%> type specifier without trailing "
11053 "return type", name);
11054 inform (input_location, "deduced return type "
11055 "only available with -std=c++14 or "
11056 "-std=gnu++14");
11057 }
11058 else if (virtualp)
11059 {
11060 error ("virtual function cannot "
11061 "have deduced return type");
11062 virtualp = false;
11063 }
11064 }
11065 else if (!is_auto (type) && sfk != sfk_conversion)
11066 {
11067 error ("%qs function with trailing return type has"
11068 " %qT as its type rather than plain %<auto%>",
11069 name, type);
11070 return error_mark_node;
11071 }
11072 if (tree tmpl = CLASS_PLACEHOLDER_TEMPLATE (auto_node))
11073 {
11074 if (!late_return_type)
11075 {
11076 if (dguide_name_p (unqualified_id))
11077 error_at (declarator->id_loc, "deduction guide "
11078 "for %qT must have trailing return "
11079 "type", TREE_TYPE (tmpl));
11080 else
11081 error_at (declarator->id_loc, "deduced class "
11082 "type %qT in function return type",
11083 type);
11084 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (tmpl),
11085 "%qD declared here", tmpl);
11086 }
11087 else if (CLASS_TYPE_P (late_return_type)
11088 && CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (late_return_type)
11089 && (CLASSTYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (late_return_type)
11090 == tmpl))
11091 /* OK */;
11092 else
11093 error ("trailing return type %qT of deduction guide "
11094 "is not a specialization of %qT",
11095 late_return_type, TREE_TYPE (tmpl));
11096 }
11097 }
11098 else if (late_return_type
11099 && sfk != sfk_conversion)
11100 {
11101 if (cxx_dialect < cxx11)
11102 /* Not using maybe_warn_cpp0x because this should
11103 always be an error. */
11104 error ("trailing return type only available with "
11105 "-std=c++11 or -std=gnu++11");
11106 else
11107 error ("%qs function with trailing return type not "
11108 "declared with %<auto%> type specifier", name);
11109 return error_mark_node;
11110 }
11111 }
11112 type = splice_late_return_type (type, late_return_type);
11113 if (type == error_mark_node)
11114 return error_mark_node;
11115
11116 if (late_return_type)
11117 late_return_type_p = true;
11118
11119 if (ctype == NULL_TREE
11120 && decl_context == FIELD
11121 && funcdecl_p
11122 && friendp == 0)
11123 ctype = current_class_type;
11124
11125 if (ctype && (sfk == sfk_constructor
11126 || sfk == sfk_destructor))
11127 {
11128 /* We are within a class's scope. If our declarator name
11129 is the same as the class name, and we are defining
11130 a function, then it is a constructor/destructor, and
11131 therefore returns a void type. */
11132
11133 /* ISO C++ 12.4/2. A destructor may not be declared
11134 const or volatile. A destructor may not be static.
11135 A destructor may not be declared with ref-qualifier.
11136
11137 ISO C++ 12.1. A constructor may not be declared
11138 const or volatile. A constructor may not be
11139 virtual. A constructor may not be static.
11140 A constructor may not be declared with ref-qualifier. */
11141 if (staticp == 2)
11142 error ((flags == DTOR_FLAG)
11143 ? G_("destructor cannot be static member function")
11144 : G_("constructor cannot be static member function"));
11145 if (memfn_quals)
11146 {
11147 error ((flags == DTOR_FLAG)
11148 ? G_("destructors may not be cv-qualified")
11149 : G_("constructors may not be cv-qualified"));
11150 memfn_quals = TYPE_UNQUALIFIED;
11151 }
11152
11153 if (rqual)
11154 {
11155 maybe_warn_cpp0x (CPP0X_REF_QUALIFIER);
11156 error ((flags == DTOR_FLAG)
11157 ? G_("destructors may not be ref-qualified")
11158 : G_("constructors may not be ref-qualified"));
11159 rqual = REF_QUAL_NONE;
11160 }
11161
11162 if (decl_context == FIELD
11163 && !member_function_or_else (ctype,
11164 current_class_type,
11165 flags))
11166 return error_mark_node;
11167
11168 if (flags != DTOR_FLAG)
11169 {
11170 /* It's a constructor. */
11171 if (explicitp == 1)
11172 explicitp = 2;
11173 if (virtualp)
11174 {
11175 permerror (input_location,
11176 "constructors cannot be declared %<virtual%>");
11177 virtualp = 0;
11178 }
11179 if (decl_context == FIELD
11180 && sfk != sfk_constructor)
11181 return error_mark_node;
11182 }
11183 if (decl_context == FIELD)
11184 staticp = 0;
11185 }
11186 else if (friendp)
11187 {
11188 if (virtualp)
11189 {
11190 /* Cannot be both friend and virtual. */
11191 error ("virtual functions cannot be friends");
11192 friendp = 0;
11193 }
11194 if (decl_context == NORMAL)
11195 error ("friend declaration not in class definition");
11196 if (current_function_decl && funcdef_flag)
11197 error ("can%'t define friend function %qs in a local "
11198 "class definition",
11199 name);
11200 }
11201 else if (ctype && sfk == sfk_conversion)
11202 {
11203 if (explicitp == 1)
11204 {
11205 maybe_warn_cpp0x (CPP0X_EXPLICIT_CONVERSION);
11206 explicitp = 2;
11207 }
11208 if (late_return_type_p)
11209 error ("a conversion function cannot have a trailing return type");
11210 }
11211 else if (sfk == sfk_deduction_guide)
11212 {
11213 if (explicitp == 1)
11214 explicitp = 2;
11215 }
11216
11217 tree pushed_scope = NULL_TREE;
11218 if (funcdecl_p
11219 && decl_context != FIELD
11220 && inner_declarator->u.id.qualifying_scope
11221 && CLASS_TYPE_P (inner_declarator->u.id.qualifying_scope))
11222 pushed_scope
11223 = push_scope (inner_declarator->u.id.qualifying_scope);
11224
11225 arg_types = grokparms (declarator->u.function.parameters, &parms);
11226
11227 if (pushed_scope)
11228 pop_scope (pushed_scope);
11229
11230 if (inner_declarator
11231 && inner_declarator->kind == cdk_id
11232 && inner_declarator->u.id.sfk == sfk_destructor
11233 && arg_types != void_list_node)
11234 {
11235 error ("destructors may not have parameters");
11236 arg_types = void_list_node;
11237 parms = NULL_TREE;
11238 }
11239
11240 type = build_function_type (type, arg_types);
11241
11242 tree attrs = declarator->std_attributes;
11243 if (tx_qual)
11244 {
11245 tree att = build_tree_list (tx_qual, NULL_TREE);
11246 /* transaction_safe applies to the type, but
11247 transaction_safe_dynamic applies to the function. */
11248 if (is_attribute_p ("transaction_safe", tx_qual))
11249 attrs = chainon (attrs, att);
11250 else
11251 returned_attrs = chainon (returned_attrs, att);
11252 }
11253 if (attrs)
11254 /* [dcl.fct]/2:
11255
11256 The optional attribute-specifier-seq appertains to
11257 the function type. */
11258 decl_attributes (&type, attrs, 0);
11259
11260 if (raises)
11261 type = build_exception_variant (type, raises);
11262 }
11263 break;
11264
11265 case cdk_pointer:
11266 case cdk_reference:
11267 case cdk_ptrmem:
11268 /* Filter out pointers-to-references and references-to-references.
11269 We can get these if a TYPE_DECL is used. */
11270
11271 if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
11272 {
11273 if (declarator->kind != cdk_reference)
11274 {
11275 error ("cannot declare pointer to %q#T", type);
11276 type = TREE_TYPE (type);
11277 }
11278
11279 /* In C++0x, we allow reference to reference declarations
11280 that occur indirectly through typedefs [7.1.3/8 dcl.typedef]
11281 and template type arguments [14.3.1/4 temp.arg.type]. The
11282 check for direct reference to reference declarations, which
11283 are still forbidden, occurs below. Reasoning behind the change
11284 can be found in DR106, DR540, and the rvalue reference
11285 proposals. */
11286 else if (cxx_dialect == cxx98)
11287 {
11288 error ("cannot declare reference to %q#T", type);
11289 type = TREE_TYPE (type);
11290 }
11291 }
11292 else if (VOID_TYPE_P (type))
11293 {
11294 if (declarator->kind == cdk_reference)
11295 error ("cannot declare reference to %q#T", type);
11296 else if (declarator->kind == cdk_ptrmem)
11297 error ("cannot declare pointer to %q#T member", type);
11298 }
11299
11300 /* We now know that the TYPE_QUALS don't apply to the decl,
11301 but to the target of the pointer. */
11302 type_quals = TYPE_UNQUALIFIED;
11303
11304 /* This code used to handle METHOD_TYPE, but I don't think it's
11305 possible to get it here anymore. */
11306 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (type) != METHOD_TYPE);
11307 if (declarator->kind == cdk_ptrmem
11308 && TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
11309 {
11310 memfn_quals |= type_memfn_quals (type);
11311 type = build_memfn_type (type,
11312 declarator->u.pointer.class_type,
11313 memfn_quals,
11314 rqual);
11315 if (type == error_mark_node)
11316 return error_mark_node;
11317
11318 rqual = REF_QUAL_NONE;
11319 memfn_quals = TYPE_UNQUALIFIED;
11320 }
11321
11322 if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE
11323 && (type_memfn_quals (type) != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED
11324 || type_memfn_rqual (type) != REF_QUAL_NONE))
11325 error (declarator->kind == cdk_reference
11326 ? G_("cannot declare reference to qualified function type %qT")
11327 : G_("cannot declare pointer to qualified function type %qT"),
11328 type);
11329
11330 /* When the pointed-to type involves components of variable size,
11331 care must be taken to ensure that the size evaluation code is
11332 emitted early enough to dominate all the possible later uses
11333 and late enough for the variables on which it depends to have
11334 been assigned.
11335
11336 This is expected to happen automatically when the pointed-to
11337 type has a name/declaration of it's own, but special attention
11338 is required if the type is anonymous.
11339
11340 We handle the NORMAL and FIELD contexts here by inserting a
11341 dummy statement that just evaluates the size at a safe point
11342 and ensures it is not deferred until e.g. within a deeper
11343 conditional context (c++/43555).
11344
11345 We expect nothing to be needed here for PARM or TYPENAME.
11346 Evaluating the size at this point for TYPENAME would
11347 actually be incorrect, as we might be in the middle of an
11348 expression with side effects on the pointed-to type size
11349 "arguments" prior to the pointer declaration point and the
11350 size evaluation could end up prior to the side effects. */
11351
11352 if (!TYPE_NAME (type)
11353 && (decl_context == NORMAL || decl_context == FIELD)
11354 && at_function_scope_p ()
11355 && variably_modified_type_p (type, NULL_TREE))
11356 {
11357 TYPE_NAME (type) = build_decl (UNKNOWN_LOCATION, TYPE_DECL,
11358 NULL_TREE, type);
11359 add_decl_expr (TYPE_NAME (type));
11360 }
11361
11362 if (declarator->kind == cdk_reference)
11363 {
11364 /* In C++0x, the type we are creating a reference to might be
11365 a typedef which is itself a reference type. In that case,
11366 we follow the reference collapsing rules in
11367 [7.1.3/8 dcl.typedef] to create the final reference type:
11368
11369 "If a typedef TD names a type that is a reference to a type
11370 T, an attempt to create the type 'lvalue reference to cv TD'
11371 creates the type 'lvalue reference to T,' while an attempt
11372 to create the type "rvalue reference to cv TD' creates the
11373 type TD."
11374 */
11375 if (VOID_TYPE_P (type))
11376 /* We already gave an error. */;
11377 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
11378 {
11379 if (declarator->u.reference.rvalue_ref)
11380 /* Leave type alone. */;
11381 else
11382 type = cp_build_reference_type (TREE_TYPE (type), false);
11383 }
11384 else
11385 type = cp_build_reference_type
11386 (type, declarator->u.reference.rvalue_ref);
11387
11388 /* In C++0x, we need this check for direct reference to
11389 reference declarations, which are forbidden by
11390 [8.3.2/5 dcl.ref]. Reference to reference declarations
11391 are only allowed indirectly through typedefs and template
11392 type arguments. Example:
11393
11394 void foo(int & &); // invalid ref-to-ref decl
11395
11396 typedef int & int_ref;
11397 void foo(int_ref &); // valid ref-to-ref decl
11398 */
11399 if (inner_declarator && inner_declarator->kind == cdk_reference)
11400 error ("cannot declare reference to %q#T, which is not "
11401 "a typedef or a template type argument", type);
11402 }
11403 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
11404 type = build_ptrmemfunc_type (build_pointer_type (type));
11405 else if (declarator->kind == cdk_ptrmem)
11406 {
11407 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (declarator->u.pointer.class_type)
11408 != NAMESPACE_DECL);
11409 if (declarator->u.pointer.class_type == error_mark_node)
11410 /* We will already have complained. */
11411 type = error_mark_node;
11412 else
11413 type = build_ptrmem_type (declarator->u.pointer.class_type,
11414 type);
11415 }
11416 else
11417 type = build_pointer_type (type);
11418
11419 /* Process a list of type modifier keywords (such as
11420 const or volatile) that were given inside the `*' or `&'. */
11421
11422 if (declarator->u.pointer.qualifiers)
11423 {
11424 type
11425 = cp_build_qualified_type (type,
11426 declarator->u.pointer.qualifiers);
11427 type_quals = cp_type_quals (type);
11428 }
11429
11430 /* Apply C++11 attributes to the pointer, and not to the
11431 type pointed to. This is unlike what is done for GNU
11432 attributes above. It is to comply with [dcl.ptr]/1:
11433
11434 [the optional attribute-specifier-seq (7.6.1) appertains
11435 to the pointer and not to the object pointed to]. */
11436 if (declarator->std_attributes)
11437 decl_attributes (&type, declarator->std_attributes,
11438 0);
11439
11440 ctype = NULL_TREE;
11441 break;
11442
11443 case cdk_error:
11444 break;
11445
11446 default:
11447 gcc_unreachable ();
11448 }
11449 }
11450
11451 /* A `constexpr' specifier used in an object declaration declares
11452 the object as `const'. */
11453 if (constexpr_p && innermost_code != cdk_function)
11454 {
11455 /* DR1688 says that a `constexpr' specifier in combination with
11456 `volatile' is valid. */
11457
11458 if (TREE_CODE (type) != REFERENCE_TYPE)
11459 {
11460 type_quals |= TYPE_QUAL_CONST;
11461 type = cp_build_qualified_type (type, type_quals);
11462 }
11463 }
11464
11465 if (unqualified_id && TREE_CODE (unqualified_id) == TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR
11466 && TREE_CODE (type) != FUNCTION_TYPE
11467 && TREE_CODE (type) != METHOD_TYPE
11468 && !variable_template_p (TREE_OPERAND (unqualified_id, 0)))
11469 {
11470 error ("template-id %qD used as a declarator",
11471 unqualified_id);
11472 unqualified_id = dname;
11473 }
11474
11475 /* If TYPE is a FUNCTION_TYPE, but the function name was explicitly
11476 qualified with a class-name, turn it into a METHOD_TYPE, unless
11477 we know that the function is static. We take advantage of this
11478 opportunity to do other processing that pertains to entities
11479 explicitly declared to be class members. Note that if DECLARATOR
11480 is non-NULL, we know it is a cdk_id declarator; otherwise, we
11481 would not have exited the loop above. */
11482 if (declarator
11483 && declarator->kind == cdk_id
11484 && declarator->u.id.qualifying_scope
11485 && MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (declarator->u.id.qualifying_scope))
11486 {
11487 ctype = declarator->u.id.qualifying_scope;
11488 ctype = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (ctype);
11489 template_count = num_template_headers_for_class (ctype);
11490
11491 if (ctype == current_class_type)
11492 {
11493 if (friendp)
11494 {
11495 permerror (input_location, "member functions are implicitly "
11496 "friends of their class");
11497 friendp = 0;
11498 }
11499 else
11500 permerror (declarator->id_loc,
11501 "extra qualification %<%T::%> on member %qs",
11502 ctype, name);
11503 }
11504 else if (/* If the qualifying type is already complete, then we
11505 can skip the following checks. */
11506 !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (ctype)
11507 && (/* If the function is being defined, then
11508 qualifying type must certainly be complete. */
11509 funcdef_flag
11510 /* A friend declaration of "T::f" is OK, even if
11511 "T" is a template parameter. But, if this
11512 function is not a friend, the qualifying type
11513 must be a class. */
11514 || (!friendp && !CLASS_TYPE_P (ctype))
11515 /* For a declaration, the type need not be
11516 complete, if either it is dependent (since there
11517 is no meaningful definition of complete in that
11518 case) or the qualifying class is currently being
11519 defined. */
11520 || !(dependent_type_p (ctype)
11521 || currently_open_class (ctype)))
11522 /* Check that the qualifying type is complete. */
11523 && !complete_type_or_else (ctype, NULL_TREE))
11524 return error_mark_node;
11525 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
11526 {
11527 if (current_class_type
11528 && (!friendp || funcdef_flag || initialized))
11529 {
11530 error (funcdef_flag || initialized
11531 ? G_("cannot define member function %<%T::%s%> "
11532 "within %<%T%>")
11533 : G_("cannot declare member function %<%T::%s%> "
11534 "within %<%T%>"),
11535 ctype, name, current_class_type);
11536 return error_mark_node;
11537 }
11538 }
11539 else if (typedef_p && current_class_type)
11540 {
11541 error ("cannot declare member %<%T::%s%> within %qT",
11542 ctype, name, current_class_type);
11543 return error_mark_node;
11544 }
11545 }
11546
11547 if (ctype == NULL_TREE && decl_context == FIELD && friendp == 0)
11548 ctype = current_class_type;
11549
11550 /* Now TYPE has the actual type. */
11551
11552 if (returned_attrs)
11553 {
11554 if (attrlist)
11555 *attrlist = chainon (returned_attrs, *attrlist);
11556 else
11557 attrlist = &returned_attrs;
11558 }
11559
11560 if (declarator
11561 && declarator->kind == cdk_id
11562 && declarator->std_attributes
11563 && attrlist != NULL)
11564 /* [dcl.meaning]/1: The optional attribute-specifier-seq following
11565 a declarator-id appertains to the entity that is declared. */
11566 *attrlist = chainon (*attrlist, declarator->std_attributes);
11567
11568 /* Handle parameter packs. */
11569 if (parameter_pack_p)
11570 {
11571 if (decl_context == PARM)
11572 /* Turn the type into a pack expansion.*/
11573 type = make_pack_expansion (type);
11574 else
11575 error ("non-parameter %qs cannot be a parameter pack", name);
11576 }
11577
11578 if ((decl_context == FIELD || decl_context == PARM)
11579 && !processing_template_decl
11580 && variably_modified_type_p (type, NULL_TREE))
11581 {
11582 if (decl_context == FIELD)
11583 error ("data member may not have variably modified type %qT", type);
11584 else
11585 error ("parameter may not have variably modified type %qT", type);
11586 type = error_mark_node;
11587 }
11588
11589 if (explicitp == 1 || (explicitp && friendp))
11590 {
11591 /* [dcl.fct.spec] (C++11) The explicit specifier shall be used only
11592 in the declaration of a constructor or conversion function within
11593 a class definition. */
11594 if (!current_class_type)
11595 error_at (declspecs->locations[ds_explicit],
11596 "%<explicit%> outside class declaration");
11597 else if (friendp)
11598 error_at (declspecs->locations[ds_explicit],
11599 "%<explicit%> in friend declaration");
11600 else
11601 error_at (declspecs->locations[ds_explicit],
11602 "only declarations of constructors and conversion operators "
11603 "can be %<explicit%>");
11604 explicitp = 0;
11605 }
11606
11607 if (storage_class == sc_mutable)
11608 {
11609 if (decl_context != FIELD || friendp)
11610 {
11611 error ("non-member %qs cannot be declared %<mutable%>", name);
11612 storage_class = sc_none;
11613 }
11614 else if (decl_context == TYPENAME || typedef_p)
11615 {
11616 error ("non-object member %qs cannot be declared %<mutable%>", name);
11617 storage_class = sc_none;
11618 }
11619 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE
11620 || TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
11621 {
11622 error ("function %qs cannot be declared %<mutable%>", name);
11623 storage_class = sc_none;
11624 }
11625 else if (staticp)
11626 {
11627 error ("static %qs cannot be declared %<mutable%>", name);
11628 storage_class = sc_none;
11629 }
11630 else if (type_quals & TYPE_QUAL_CONST)
11631 {
11632 error ("const %qs cannot be declared %<mutable%>", name);
11633 storage_class = sc_none;
11634 }
11635 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
11636 {
11637 permerror (input_location, "reference %qs cannot be declared "
11638 "%<mutable%>", name);
11639 storage_class = sc_none;
11640 }
11641 }
11642
11643 /* If this is declaring a typedef name, return a TYPE_DECL. */
11644 if (typedef_p && decl_context != TYPENAME)
11645 {
11646 tree decl;
11647
11648 /* This declaration:
11649
11650 typedef void f(int) const;
11651
11652 declares a function type which is not a member of any
11653 particular class, but which is cv-qualified; for
11654 example "f S::*" declares a pointer to a const-qualified
11655 member function of S. We record the cv-qualification in the
11656 function type. */
11657 if ((rqual || memfn_quals) && TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
11658 {
11659 type = apply_memfn_quals (type, memfn_quals, rqual);
11660
11661 /* We have now dealt with these qualifiers. */
11662 memfn_quals = TYPE_UNQUALIFIED;
11663 rqual = REF_QUAL_NONE;
11664 }
11665
11666 if (type_uses_auto (type))
11667 {
11668 error ("typedef declared %<auto%>");
11669 type = error_mark_node;
11670 }
11671
11672 if (reqs)
11673 error_at (location_of (reqs), "requires-clause on typedef");
11674
11675 if (decl_context == FIELD)
11676 decl = build_lang_decl (TYPE_DECL, unqualified_id, type);
11677 else
11678 decl = build_decl (input_location, TYPE_DECL, unqualified_id, type);
11679 if (id_declarator && declarator->u.id.qualifying_scope) {
11680 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
11681 "typedef name may not be a nested-name-specifier");
11682 TREE_TYPE (decl) = error_mark_node;
11683 }
11684
11685 if (decl_context != FIELD)
11686 {
11687 if (!current_function_decl)
11688 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = FROB_CONTEXT (current_namespace);
11689 else if (DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_CONSTRUCTOR_P (current_function_decl)
11690 || (DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_DESTRUCTOR_P
11691 (current_function_decl)))
11692 /* The TYPE_DECL is "abstract" because there will be
11693 clones of this constructor/destructor, and there will
11694 be copies of this TYPE_DECL generated in those
11695 clones. The decloning optimization (for space) may
11696 revert this subsequently if it determines that
11697 the clones should share a common implementation. */
11698 DECL_ABSTRACT_P (decl) = true;
11699 }
11700 else if (current_class_type
11701 && constructor_name_p (unqualified_id, current_class_type))
11702 permerror (input_location, "ISO C++ forbids nested type %qD with same name "
11703 "as enclosing class",
11704 unqualified_id);
11705
11706 /* If the user declares "typedef struct {...} foo" then the
11707 struct will have an anonymous name. Fill that name in now.
11708 Nothing can refer to it, so nothing needs know about the name
11709 change. */
11710 if (type != error_mark_node
11711 && unqualified_id
11712 && TYPE_NAME (type)
11713 && TREE_CODE (TYPE_NAME (type)) == TYPE_DECL
11714 && TYPE_UNNAMED_P (type)
11715 && declspecs->type_definition_p
11716 && attributes_naming_typedef_ok (*attrlist)
11717 && cp_type_quals (type) == TYPE_UNQUALIFIED)
11718 name_unnamed_type (type, decl);
11719
11720 if (signed_p
11721 || (typedef_decl && C_TYPEDEF_EXPLICITLY_SIGNED (typedef_decl)))
11722 C_TYPEDEF_EXPLICITLY_SIGNED (decl) = 1;
11723
11724 bad_specifiers (decl, BSP_TYPE, virtualp,
11725 memfn_quals != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED,
11726 inlinep, friendp, raises != NULL_TREE);
11727
11728 if (decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_alias))
11729 /* Acknowledge that this was written:
11730 `using analias = atype;'. */
11731 TYPE_DECL_ALIAS_P (decl) = 1;
11732
11733 return decl;
11734 }
11735
11736 /* Detect the case of an array type of unspecified size
11737 which came, as such, direct from a typedef name.
11738 We must copy the type, so that the array's domain can be
11739 individually set by the object's initializer. */
11740
11741 if (type && typedef_type
11742 && TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE && !TYPE_DOMAIN (type)
11743 && TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type) == TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (typedef_type))
11744 type = build_cplus_array_type (TREE_TYPE (type), NULL_TREE);
11745
11746 /* Detect where we're using a typedef of function type to declare a
11747 function. PARMS will not be set, so we must create it now. */
11748
11749 if (type == typedef_type && TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
11750 {
11751 tree decls = NULL_TREE;
11752 tree args;
11753
11754 for (args = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type);
11755 args && args != void_list_node;
11756 args = TREE_CHAIN (args))
11757 {
11758 tree decl = cp_build_parm_decl (NULL_TREE, TREE_VALUE (args));
11759
11760 DECL_CHAIN (decl) = decls;
11761 decls = decl;
11762 }
11763
11764 parms = nreverse (decls);
11765
11766 if (decl_context != TYPENAME)
11767 {
11768 /* The qualifiers on the function type become the qualifiers on
11769 the non-static member function. */
11770 memfn_quals |= type_memfn_quals (type);
11771 rqual = type_memfn_rqual (type);
11772 type_quals = TYPE_UNQUALIFIED;
11773 }
11774 }
11775
11776 /* If this is a type name (such as, in a cast or sizeof),
11777 compute the type and return it now. */
11778
11779 if (decl_context == TYPENAME)
11780 {
11781 /* Note that here we don't care about type_quals. */
11782
11783 /* Special case: "friend class foo" looks like a TYPENAME context. */
11784 if (friendp)
11785 {
11786 if (inlinep)
11787 {
11788 error ("%<inline%> specified for friend class declaration");
11789 inlinep = 0;
11790 }
11791
11792 if (!current_aggr)
11793 {
11794 /* Don't allow friend declaration without a class-key. */
11795 if (TREE_CODE (type) == TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM)
11796 permerror (input_location, "template parameters cannot be friends");
11797 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == TYPENAME_TYPE)
11798 permerror (input_location, "friend declaration requires class-key, "
11799 "i.e. %<friend class %T::%D%>",
11800 TYPE_CONTEXT (type), TYPENAME_TYPE_FULLNAME (type));
11801 else
11802 permerror (input_location, "friend declaration requires class-key, "
11803 "i.e. %<friend %#T%>",
11804 type);
11805 }
11806
11807 /* Only try to do this stuff if we didn't already give up. */
11808 if (type != integer_type_node)
11809 {
11810 /* A friendly class? */
11811 if (current_class_type)
11812 make_friend_class (current_class_type, TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type),
11813 /*complain=*/true);
11814 else
11815 error ("trying to make class %qT a friend of global scope",
11816 type);
11817
11818 type = void_type_node;
11819 }
11820 }
11821 else if (memfn_quals || rqual)
11822 {
11823 if (ctype == NULL_TREE
11824 && TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
11825 ctype = TYPE_METHOD_BASETYPE (type);
11826
11827 if (ctype)
11828 type = build_memfn_type (type, ctype, memfn_quals, rqual);
11829 /* Core issue #547: need to allow this in template type args.
11830 Allow it in general in C++11 for alias-declarations. */
11831 else if ((template_type_arg || cxx_dialect >= cxx11)
11832 && TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
11833 type = apply_memfn_quals (type, memfn_quals, rqual);
11834 else
11835 error ("invalid qualifiers on non-member function type");
11836 }
11837
11838 if (reqs)
11839 error_at (location_of (reqs), "requires-clause on type-id");
11840
11841 return type;
11842 }
11843 else if (unqualified_id == NULL_TREE && decl_context != PARM
11844 && decl_context != CATCHPARM
11845 && TREE_CODE (type) != UNION_TYPE
11846 && ! bitfield
11847 && innermost_code != cdk_decomp)
11848 {
11849 error ("abstract declarator %qT used as declaration", type);
11850 return error_mark_node;
11851 }
11852
11853 /* Only functions may be declared using an operator-function-id. */
11854 if (unqualified_id
11855 && IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P (unqualified_id)
11856 && TREE_CODE (type) != FUNCTION_TYPE
11857 && TREE_CODE (type) != METHOD_TYPE)
11858 {
11859 error ("declaration of %qD as non-function", unqualified_id);
11860 return error_mark_node;
11861 }
11862
11863 if (reqs
11864 && TREE_CODE (type) != FUNCTION_TYPE
11865 && TREE_CODE (type) != METHOD_TYPE)
11866 error_at (location_of (reqs),
11867 "requires-clause on declaration of non-function type %qT",
11868 type);
11869
11870 /* We don't check parameter types here because we can emit a better
11871 error message later. */
11872 if (decl_context != PARM)
11873 {
11874 type = check_var_type (unqualified_id, type);
11875 if (type == error_mark_node)
11876 return error_mark_node;
11877 }
11878
11879 /* Now create the decl, which may be a VAR_DECL, a PARM_DECL
11880 or a FUNCTION_DECL, depending on DECL_CONTEXT and TYPE. */
11881
11882 if (decl_context == PARM || decl_context == CATCHPARM)
11883 {
11884 if (ctype || in_namespace)
11885 error ("cannot use %<::%> in parameter declaration");
11886
11887 if (type_uses_auto (type)
11888 && !(cxx_dialect >= cxx1z && template_parm_flag))
11889 {
11890 if (cxx_dialect >= cxx14)
11891 error ("%<auto%> parameter not permitted in this context");
11892 else
11893 error ("parameter declared %<auto%>");
11894 type = error_mark_node;
11895 }
11896
11897 /* A parameter declared as an array of T is really a pointer to T.
11898 One declared as a function is really a pointer to a function.
11899 One declared as a member is really a pointer to member. */
11900
11901 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
11902 {
11903 /* Transfer const-ness of array into that of type pointed to. */
11904 type = build_pointer_type (TREE_TYPE (type));
11905 type_quals = TYPE_UNQUALIFIED;
11906 array_parameter_p = true;
11907 }
11908 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
11909 type = build_pointer_type (type);
11910 }
11911
11912 if (ctype && TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE && staticp < 2
11913 && !NEW_DELETE_OPNAME_P (unqualified_id))
11914 {
11915 cp_cv_quals real_quals = memfn_quals;
11916 if (cxx_dialect < cxx14 && constexpr_p
11917 && sfk != sfk_constructor && sfk != sfk_destructor)
11918 real_quals |= TYPE_QUAL_CONST;
11919 type = build_memfn_type (type, ctype, real_quals, rqual);
11920 }
11921
11922 {
11923 tree decl = NULL_TREE;
11924
11925 if (decl_context == PARM)
11926 {
11927 decl = cp_build_parm_decl (unqualified_id, type);
11928 DECL_ARRAY_PARAMETER_P (decl) = array_parameter_p;
11929
11930 bad_specifiers (decl, BSP_PARM, virtualp,
11931 memfn_quals != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED,
11932 inlinep, friendp, raises != NULL_TREE);
11933 }
11934 else if (decl_context == FIELD)
11935 {
11936 if (!staticp && !friendp && TREE_CODE (type) != METHOD_TYPE)
11937 if (tree auto_node = type_uses_auto (type))
11938 {
11939 location_t loc = declspecs->locations[ds_type_spec];
11940 if (CLASS_PLACEHOLDER_TEMPLATE (auto_node))
11941 error_at (loc, "invalid use of template-name %qE without an "
11942 "argument list",
11943 CLASS_PLACEHOLDER_TEMPLATE (auto_node));
11944 else
11945 error_at (loc, "non-static data member declared with "
11946 "placeholder %qT", auto_node);
11947 type = error_mark_node;
11948 }
11949
11950 /* The C99 flexible array extension. */
11951 if (!staticp && TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE
11952 && TYPE_DOMAIN (type) == NULL_TREE)
11953 {
11954 if (ctype
11955 && (TREE_CODE (ctype) == UNION_TYPE
11956 || TREE_CODE (ctype) == QUAL_UNION_TYPE))
11957 {
11958 error ("flexible array member in union");
11959 type = error_mark_node;
11960 }
11961 else
11962 {
11963 /* Array is a flexible member. */
11964 if (in_system_header_at (input_location))
11965 /* Do not warn on flexible array members in system
11966 headers because glibc uses them. */;
11967 else if (name)
11968 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpedantic,
11969 "ISO C++ forbids flexible array member %qs", name);
11970 else
11971 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpedantic,
11972 "ISO C++ forbids flexible array members");
11973
11974 /* Flexible array member has a null domain. */
11975 type = build_cplus_array_type (TREE_TYPE (type), NULL_TREE);
11976 }
11977 }
11978
11979 if (type == error_mark_node)
11980 {
11981 /* Happens when declaring arrays of sizes which
11982 are error_mark_node, for example. */
11983 decl = NULL_TREE;
11984 }
11985 else if (in_namespace && !friendp)
11986 {
11987 /* Something like struct S { int N::j; }; */
11988 error ("invalid use of %<::%>");
11989 return error_mark_node;
11990 }
11991 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE
11992 || TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
11993 {
11994 int publicp = 0;
11995 tree function_context;
11996
11997 if (friendp == 0)
11998 {
11999 /* This should never happen in pure C++ (the check
12000 could be an assert). It could happen in
12001 Objective-C++ if someone writes invalid code that
12002 uses a function declaration for an instance
12003 variable or property (instance variables and
12004 properties are parsed as FIELD_DECLs, but they are
12005 part of an Objective-C class, not a C++ class).
12006 That code is invalid and is caught by this
12007 check. */
12008 if (!ctype)
12009 {
12010 error ("declaration of function %qD in invalid context",
12011 unqualified_id);
12012 return error_mark_node;
12013 }
12014
12015 /* ``A union may [ ... ] not [ have ] virtual functions.''
12016 ARM 9.5 */
12017 if (virtualp && TREE_CODE (ctype) == UNION_TYPE)
12018 {
12019 error ("function %qD declared %<virtual%> inside a union",
12020 unqualified_id);
12021 return error_mark_node;
12022 }
12023
12024 if (NEW_DELETE_OPNAME_P (unqualified_id))
12025 {
12026 if (virtualp)
12027 {
12028 error ("%qD cannot be declared %<virtual%>, since it "
12029 "is always static",
12030 unqualified_id);
12031 virtualp = 0;
12032 }
12033 }
12034 }
12035
12036 /* Check that the name used for a destructor makes sense. */
12037 if (sfk == sfk_destructor)
12038 {
12039 tree uqname = id_declarator->u.id.unqualified_name;
12040
12041 if (!ctype)
12042 {
12043 gcc_assert (friendp);
12044 error ("expected qualified name in friend declaration "
12045 "for destructor %qD", uqname);
12046 return error_mark_node;
12047 }
12048
12049 if (!check_dtor_name (ctype, TREE_OPERAND (uqname, 0)))
12050 {
12051 error ("declaration of %qD as member of %qT",
12052 uqname, ctype);
12053 return error_mark_node;
12054 }
12055 if (concept_p)
12056 {
12057 error ("a destructor cannot be %<concept%>");
12058 return error_mark_node;
12059 }
12060 if (constexpr_p)
12061 {
12062 error ("a destructor cannot be %<constexpr%>");
12063 return error_mark_node;
12064 }
12065 }
12066 else if (sfk == sfk_constructor && friendp && !ctype)
12067 {
12068 error ("expected qualified name in friend declaration "
12069 "for constructor %qD",
12070 id_declarator->u.id.unqualified_name);
12071 return error_mark_node;
12072 }
12073 if (sfk == sfk_constructor)
12074 if (concept_p)
12075 {
12076 error ("a constructor cannot be %<concept%>");
12077 return error_mark_node;
12078 }
12079 if (concept_p)
12080 {
12081 error ("a concept cannot be a member function");
12082 concept_p = false;
12083 }
12084
12085 if (TREE_CODE (unqualified_id) == TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR)
12086 {
12087 tree tmpl = TREE_OPERAND (unqualified_id, 0);
12088 if (variable_template_p (tmpl))
12089 {
12090 error ("specialization of variable template %qD "
12091 "declared as function", tmpl);
12092 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (tmpl),
12093 "variable template declared here");
12094 return error_mark_node;
12095 }
12096 }
12097
12098 /* Tell grokfndecl if it needs to set TREE_PUBLIC on the node. */
12099 function_context = (ctype != NULL_TREE) ?
12100 decl_function_context (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (ctype)) : NULL_TREE;
12101 publicp = (! friendp || ! staticp)
12102 && function_context == NULL_TREE;
12103
12104 if (late_return_type_p)
12105 TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE (type) = 1;
12106
12107 decl = grokfndecl (ctype, type,
12108 TREE_CODE (unqualified_id) != TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR
12109 ? unqualified_id : dname,
12110 parms,
12111 unqualified_id,
12112 reqs,
12113 virtualp, flags, memfn_quals, rqual, raises,
12114 friendp ? -1 : 0, friendp, publicp,
12115 inlinep | (2 * constexpr_p) | (4 * concept_p),
12116 initialized == SD_DELETED, sfk,
12117 funcdef_flag, template_count, in_namespace,
12118 attrlist, declarator->id_loc);
12119 decl = set_virt_specifiers (decl, virt_specifiers);
12120 if (decl == NULL_TREE)
12121 return error_mark_node;
12122#if 0
12123 /* This clobbers the attrs stored in `decl' from `attrlist'. */
12124 /* The decl and setting of decl_attr is also turned off. */
12125 decl = build_decl_attribute_variant (decl, decl_attr);
12126#endif
12127
12128 /* [class.conv.ctor]
12129
12130 A constructor declared without the function-specifier
12131 explicit that can be called with a single parameter
12132 specifies a conversion from the type of its first
12133 parameter to the type of its class. Such a constructor
12134 is called a converting constructor. */
12135 if (explicitp == 2)
12136 DECL_NONCONVERTING_P (decl) = 1;
12137 }
12138 else if (!staticp && !dependent_type_p (type)
12139 && !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (complete_type (type))
12140 && (!complete_or_array_type_p (type)
