12141 || initialized == 0))
12142 {
12143 if (TREE_CODE (type) != ARRAY_TYPE
12144 || !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (type)))
12145 {
12146 if (unqualified_id)
12147 {
12148 error ("field %qD has incomplete type %qT",
12149 unqualified_id, type);
12150 cxx_incomplete_type_inform (strip_array_types (type));
12151 }
12152 else
12153 error ("name %qT has incomplete type", type);
12154
12155 type = error_mark_node;
12156 decl = NULL_TREE;
12157 }
12158 }
12159 else
12160 {
12161 if (friendp)
12162 {
12163 error ("%qE is neither function nor member function; "
12164 "cannot be declared friend", unqualified_id);
12165 friendp = 0;
12166 }
12167 decl = NULL_TREE;
12168 }
12169
12170 if (friendp)
12171 {
12172 /* Friends are treated specially. */
12173 if (ctype == current_class_type)
12174 ; /* We already issued a permerror. */
12175 else if (decl && DECL_NAME (decl))
12176 {
12177 if (template_class_depth (current_class_type) == 0)
12178 {
12179 decl = check_explicit_specialization
12180 (unqualified_id, decl, template_count,
12181 2 * funcdef_flag + 4);
12182 if (decl == error_mark_node)
12183 return error_mark_node;
12184 }
12185
12186 decl = do_friend (ctype, unqualified_id, decl,
12187 *attrlist, flags,
12188 funcdef_flag);
12189 return decl;
12190 }
12191 else
12192 return error_mark_node;
12193 }
12194
12195 /* Structure field. It may not be a function, except for C++. */
12196
12197 if (decl == NULL_TREE)
12198 {
12199 if (staticp)
12200 {
12201 /* C++ allows static class members. All other work
12202 for this is done by grokfield. */
12203 decl = build_lang_decl_loc (declarator
12204 ? declarator->id_loc
12205 : input_location,
12206 VAR_DECL, unqualified_id, type);
12207 set_linkage_for_static_data_member (decl);
12208 if (concept_p)
12209 error ("static data member %qE declared %<concept%>",
12210 unqualified_id);
12211 else if (constexpr_p && !initialized)
12212 {
12213 error ("constexpr static data member %qD must have an "
12214 "initializer", decl);
12215 constexpr_p = false;
12216 }
12217
12218 if (inlinep)
12219 mark_inline_variable (decl);
12220
12221 if (!DECL_VAR_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl)
12222 && !(cxx_dialect >= cxx1z && constexpr_p))
12223 /* Even if there is an in-class initialization, DECL
12224 is considered undefined until an out-of-class
12225 definition is provided, unless this is an inline
12226 variable. */
12227 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 1;
12228
12229 if (thread_p)
12230 {
12231 CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (decl) = true;
12232 if (!processing_template_decl)
12233 set_decl_tls_model (decl, decl_default_tls_model (decl));
12234 if (declspecs->gnu_thread_keyword_p)
12235 SET_DECL_GNU_TLS_P (decl);
12236 }
12237 }
12238 else
12239 {
12240 if (concept_p)
12241 error ("non-static data member %qE declared %<concept%>",
12242 unqualified_id);
12243 else if (constexpr_p)
12244 {
12245 error ("non-static data member %qE declared %<constexpr%>",
12246 unqualified_id);
12247 constexpr_p = false;
12248 }
12249 decl = build_decl (input_location,
12250 FIELD_DECL, unqualified_id, type);
12251 DECL_NONADDRESSABLE_P (decl) = bitfield;
12252 if (bitfield && !unqualified_id)
12253 TREE_NO_WARNING (decl) = 1;
12254
12255 if (storage_class == sc_mutable)
12256 {
12257 DECL_MUTABLE_P (decl) = 1;
12258 storage_class = sc_none;
12259 }
12260
12261 if (initialized)
12262 {
12263 /* An attempt is being made to initialize a non-static
12264 member. This is new in C++11. */
12265 maybe_warn_cpp0x (CPP0X_NSDMI);
12266
12267 /* If this has been parsed with static storage class, but
12268 errors forced staticp to be cleared, ensure NSDMI is
12269 not present. */
12270 if (declspecs->storage_class == sc_static)
12271 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = error_mark_node;
12272 }
12273 }
12274
12275 bad_specifiers (decl, BSP_FIELD, virtualp,
12276 memfn_quals != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED,
12277 staticp ? false : inlinep, friendp,
12278 raises != NULL_TREE);
12279 }
12280 }
12281 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE
12282 || TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
12283 {
12284 tree original_name;
12285 int publicp = 0;
12286
12287 if (!unqualified_id)
12288 return error_mark_node;
12289
12290 if (TREE_CODE (unqualified_id) == TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR)
12291 original_name = dname;
12292 else
12293 original_name = unqualified_id;
12294
12295 if (storage_class == sc_auto)
12296 error ("storage class %<auto%> invalid for function %qs", name);
12297 else if (storage_class == sc_register)
12298 error ("storage class %<register%> invalid for function %qs", name);
12299 else if (thread_p)
12300 {
12301 if (declspecs->gnu_thread_keyword_p)
12302 error ("storage class %<__thread%> invalid for function %qs",
12303 name);
12304 else
12305 error ("storage class %<thread_local%> invalid for function %qs",
12306 name);
12307 }
12308
12309 if (virt_specifiers)
12310 error ("virt-specifiers in %qs not allowed outside a class definition", name);
12311 /* Function declaration not at top level.
12312 Storage classes other than `extern' are not allowed
12313 and `extern' makes no difference. */
12314 if (! toplevel_bindings_p ()
12315 && (storage_class == sc_static
12316 || decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_inline))
12317 && pedantic)
12318 {
12319 if (storage_class == sc_static)
12320 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpedantic,
12321 "%<static%> specifier invalid for function %qs "
12322 "declared out of global scope", name);
12323 else
12324 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpedantic,
12325 "%<inline%> specifier invalid for function %qs "
12326 "declared out of global scope", name);
12327 }
12328
12329 if (ctype == NULL_TREE)
12330 {
12331 if (virtualp)
12332 {
12333 error ("virtual non-class function %qs", name);
12334 virtualp = 0;
12335 }
12336 else if (sfk == sfk_constructor
12337 || sfk == sfk_destructor)
12338 {
12339 error (funcdef_flag
12340 ? G_("%qs defined in a non-class scope")
12341 : G_("%qs declared in a non-class scope"), name);
12342 sfk = sfk_none;
12343 }
12344 }
12345
12346 /* Record whether the function is public. */
12347 publicp = (ctype != NULL_TREE
12348 || storage_class != sc_static);
12349
12350 if (late_return_type_p)
12351 TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE (type) = 1;
12352
12353 decl = grokfndecl (ctype, type, original_name, parms, unqualified_id,
12354 reqs, virtualp, flags, memfn_quals, rqual, raises,
12355 1, friendp,
12356 publicp,
12357 inlinep | (2 * constexpr_p) | (4 * concept_p),
12358 initialized == SD_DELETED,
12359 sfk,
12360 funcdef_flag,
12361 template_count, in_namespace, attrlist,
12362 declarator->id_loc);
12363 if (decl == NULL_TREE)
12364 return error_mark_node;
12365
12366 if (explicitp == 2)
12367 DECL_NONCONVERTING_P (decl) = 1;
12368 if (staticp == 1)
12369 {
12370 int invalid_static = 0;
12371
12372 /* Don't allow a static member function in a class, and forbid
12373 declaring main to be static. */
12374 if (TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
12375 {
12376 permerror (input_location, "cannot declare member function %qD to have "
12377 "static linkage", decl);
12378 invalid_static = 1;
12379 }
12380 else if (current_function_decl)
12381 {
12382 /* 7.1.1: There can be no static function declarations within a
12383 block. */
12384 error ("cannot declare static function inside another function");
12385 invalid_static = 1;
12386 }
12387
12388 if (invalid_static)
12389 {
12390 staticp = 0;
12391 storage_class = sc_none;
12392 }
12393 }
12394 }
12395 else
12396 {
12397 /* It's a variable. */
12398
12399 /* An uninitialized decl with `extern' is a reference. */
12400 decl = grokvardecl (type, dname, unqualified_id,
12401 declspecs,
12402 initialized,
12403 type_quals,
12404 inlinep,
12405 concept_p,
12406 template_count,
12407 ctype ? ctype : in_namespace);
12408 if (decl == NULL_TREE)
12409 return error_mark_node;
12410
12411 bad_specifiers (decl, BSP_VAR, virtualp,
12412 memfn_quals != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED,
12413 inlinep, friendp, raises != NULL_TREE);
12414
12415 if (ctype)
12416 {
12417 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = ctype;
12418 if (staticp == 1)
12419 {
12420 permerror (input_location, "%<static%> may not be used when defining "
12421 "(as opposed to declaring) a static data member");
12422 staticp = 0;
12423 storage_class = sc_none;
12424 }
12425 if (storage_class == sc_register && TREE_STATIC (decl))
12426 {
12427 error ("static member %qD declared %<register%>", decl);
12428 storage_class = sc_none;
12429 }
12430 if (storage_class == sc_extern && pedantic)
12431 {
12432 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpedantic,
12433 "cannot explicitly declare member %q#D to have "
12434 "extern linkage", decl);
12435 storage_class = sc_none;
12436 }
12437 }
12438 else if (constexpr_p && DECL_EXTERNAL (decl))
12439 {
12440 error ("declaration of constexpr variable %qD is not a definition",
12441 decl);
12442 constexpr_p = false;
12443 }
12444
12445 if (inlinep)
12446 mark_inline_variable (decl);
12447 if (innermost_code == cdk_decomp)
12448 {
12449 gcc_assert (declarator && declarator->kind == cdk_decomp);
12450 DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl) = declarator->id_loc;
12451 retrofit_lang_decl (decl);
12452 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl) = 1;
12453 SET_DECL_DECOMPOSITION_P (decl);
12454 }
12455 }
12456
12457 if (VAR_P (decl) && !initialized)
12458 if (tree auto_node = type_uses_auto (type))
12459 if (!CLASS_PLACEHOLDER_TEMPLATE (auto_node))
12460 {
12461 location_t loc = declspecs->locations[ds_type_spec];
12462 error_at (loc, "declaration of %q#D has no initializer", decl);
12463 TREE_TYPE (decl) = error_mark_node;
12464 }
12465
12466 if (storage_class == sc_extern && initialized && !funcdef_flag)
12467 {
12468 if (toplevel_bindings_p ())
12469 {
12470 /* It's common practice (and completely valid) to have a const
12471 be initialized and declared extern. */
12472 if (!(type_quals & TYPE_QUAL_CONST))
12473 warning (0, "%qs initialized and declared %<extern%>", name);
12474 }
12475 else
12476 {
12477 error ("%qs has both %<extern%> and initializer", name);
12478 return error_mark_node;
12479 }
12480 }
12481
12482 /* Record `register' declaration for warnings on &
12483 and in case doing stupid register allocation. */
12484
12485 if (storage_class == sc_register)
12486 {
12487 DECL_REGISTER (decl) = 1;
12488 /* Warn about register storage specifiers on PARM_DECLs. */
12489 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == PARM_DECL)
12490 {
12491 if (cxx_dialect >= cxx1z)
12492 pedwarn (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), OPT_Wregister,
12493 "ISO C++1z does not allow %<register%> storage "
12494 "class specifier");
12495 else
12496 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), OPT_Wregister,
12497 "%<register%> storage class specifier used");
12498 }
12499 }
12500 else if (storage_class == sc_extern)
12501 DECL_THIS_EXTERN (decl) = 1;
12502 else if (storage_class == sc_static)
12503 DECL_THIS_STATIC (decl) = 1;
12504
12505 /* Set constexpr flag on vars (functions got it in grokfndecl). */
12506 if (constexpr_p && VAR_P (decl))
12507 DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (decl) = true;
12508
12509 /* Record constancy and volatility on the DECL itself . There's
12510 no need to do this when processing a template; we'll do this
12511 for the instantiated declaration based on the type of DECL. */
12512 if (!processing_template_decl)
12513 cp_apply_type_quals_to_decl (type_quals, decl);
12514
12515 return decl;
12516 }
12517}
12518
12519/* Subroutine of start_function. Ensure that each of the parameter
12520 types (as listed in PARMS) is complete, as is required for a
12521 function definition. */
12522
12523static void
12524require_complete_types_for_parms (tree parms)
12525{
12526 for (; parms; parms = DECL_CHAIN (parms))
12527 {
12528 if (dependent_type_p (TREE_TYPE (parms)))
12529 continue;
12530 if (!VOID_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (parms))
12531 && complete_type_or_else (TREE_TYPE (parms), parms))
12532 {
12533 relayout_decl (parms);
12534 DECL_ARG_TYPE (parms) = type_passed_as (TREE_TYPE (parms));
12535 }
12536 else
12537 /* grokparms or complete_type_or_else will have already issued
12538 an error. */
12539 TREE_TYPE (parms) = error_mark_node;
12540 }
12541}
12542
12543/* Returns nonzero if T is a local variable. */
12544
12545int
12546local_variable_p (const_tree t)
12547{
12548 if ((VAR_P (t)
12549 /* A VAR_DECL with a context that is a _TYPE is a static data
12550 member. */
12551 && !TYPE_P (CP_DECL_CONTEXT (t))
12552 /* Any other non-local variable must be at namespace scope. */
12553 && !DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (t))
12554 || (TREE_CODE (t) == PARM_DECL))
12555 return 1;
12556
12557 return 0;
12558}
12559
12560/* Like local_variable_p, but suitable for use as a tree-walking
12561 function. */
12562
12563static tree
12564local_variable_p_walkfn (tree *tp, int *walk_subtrees,
12565 void * /*data*/)
12566{
12567 if (local_variable_p (*tp)
12568 && (!DECL_ARTIFICIAL (*tp) || DECL_NAME (*tp) == this_identifier))
12569 return *tp;
12570 else if (TYPE_P (*tp))
12571 *walk_subtrees = 0;
12572
12573 return NULL_TREE;
12574}
12575
12576/* Check that ARG, which is a default-argument expression for a
12577 parameter DECL, is valid. Returns ARG, or ERROR_MARK_NODE, if
12578 something goes wrong. DECL may also be a _TYPE node, rather than a
12579 DECL, if there is no DECL available. */
12580
12581tree
12582check_default_argument (tree decl, tree arg, tsubst_flags_t complain)
12583{
12584 tree var;
12585 tree decl_type;
12586
12587 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == DEFAULT_ARG)
12588 /* We get a DEFAULT_ARG when looking at an in-class declaration
12589 with a default argument. Ignore the argument for now; we'll
12590 deal with it after the class is complete. */
12591 return arg;
12592
12593 if (TYPE_P (decl))
12594 {
12595 decl_type = decl;
12596 decl = NULL_TREE;
12597 }
12598 else
12599 decl_type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
12600
12601 if (arg == error_mark_node
12602 || decl == error_mark_node
12603 || TREE_TYPE (arg) == error_mark_node
12604 || decl_type == error_mark_node)
12605 /* Something already went wrong. There's no need to check
12606 further. */
12607 return error_mark_node;
12608
12609 /* [dcl.fct.default]
12610
12611 A default argument expression is implicitly converted to the
12612 parameter type. */
12613 ++cp_unevaluated_operand;
12614 /* Avoid digest_init clobbering the initializer. */
12615 tree carg = BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (arg) ? unshare_expr (arg): arg;
12616 perform_implicit_conversion_flags (decl_type, carg, complain,
12617 LOOKUP_IMPLICIT);
12618 --cp_unevaluated_operand;
12619
12620 /* Avoid redundant -Wzero-as-null-pointer-constant warnings at
12621 the call sites. */
12622 if (TYPE_PTR_OR_PTRMEM_P (decl_type)
12623 && null_ptr_cst_p (arg))
12624 return nullptr_node;
12625
12626 /* [dcl.fct.default]
12627
12628 Local variables shall not be used in default argument
12629 expressions.
12630
12631 The keyword `this' shall not be used in a default argument of a
12632 member function. */
12633 var = cp_walk_tree_without_duplicates (&arg, local_variable_p_walkfn, NULL);
12634 if (var)
12635 {
12636 if (complain & tf_warning_or_error)
12637 {
12638 if (DECL_NAME (var) == this_identifier)
12639 permerror (input_location, "default argument %qE uses %qD",
12640 arg, var);
12641 else
12642 error ("default argument %qE uses local variable %qD", arg, var);
12643 }
12644 return error_mark_node;
12645 }
12646
12647 /* All is well. */
12648 return arg;
12649}
12650
12651/* Returns a deprecated type used within TYPE, or NULL_TREE if none. */
12652
12653static tree
12654type_is_deprecated (tree type)
12655{
12656 enum tree_code code;
12657 if (TREE_DEPRECATED (type))
12658 return type;
12659 if (TYPE_NAME (type))
12660 {
12661 if (TREE_DEPRECATED (TYPE_NAME (type)))
12662 return type;
12663 else
12664 return NULL_TREE;
12665 }
12666
12667 /* Do warn about using typedefs to a deprecated class. */
12668 if (OVERLOAD_TYPE_P (type) && type != TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type))
12669 return type_is_deprecated (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type));
12670
12671 code = TREE_CODE (type);
12672
12673 if (code == POINTER_TYPE || code == REFERENCE_TYPE
12674 || code == OFFSET_TYPE || code == FUNCTION_TYPE
12675 || code == METHOD_TYPE || code == ARRAY_TYPE)
12676 return type_is_deprecated (TREE_TYPE (type));
12677
12678 if (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (type))
12679 return type_is_deprecated
12680 (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FN_TYPE (type))));
12681
12682 return NULL_TREE;
12683}
12684
12685/* Decode the list of parameter types for a function type.
12686 Given the list of things declared inside the parens,
12687 return a list of types.
12688
12689 If this parameter does not end with an ellipsis, we append
12690 void_list_node.
12691
12692 *PARMS is set to the chain of PARM_DECLs created. */
12693
12694tree
12695grokparms (tree parmlist, tree *parms)
12696{
12697 tree result = NULL_TREE;
12698 tree decls = NULL_TREE;
12699 tree parm;
12700 int any_error = 0;
12701
12702 for (parm = parmlist; parm != NULL_TREE; parm = TREE_CHAIN (parm))
12703 {
12704 tree type = NULL_TREE;
12705 tree init = TREE_PURPOSE (parm);
12706 tree decl = TREE_VALUE (parm);
12707
12708 if (parm == void_list_node)
12709 break;
12710
12711 if (! decl || TREE_TYPE (decl) == error_mark_node)
12712 continue;
12713
12714 type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
12715 if (VOID_TYPE_P (type))
12716 {
12717 if (same_type_p (type, void_type_node)
12718 && !init
12719 && !DECL_NAME (decl) && !result
12720 && TREE_CHAIN (parm) == void_list_node)
12721 /* DR 577: A parameter list consisting of a single
12722 unnamed parameter of non-dependent type 'void'. */
12723 break;
12724 else if (cv_qualified_p (type))
12725 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
12726 "invalid use of cv-qualified type %qT in "
12727 "parameter declaration", type);
12728 else
12729 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
12730 "invalid use of type %<void%> in parameter "
12731 "declaration");
12732 /* It's not a good idea to actually create parameters of
12733 type `void'; other parts of the compiler assume that a
12734 void type terminates the parameter list. */
12735 type = error_mark_node;
12736 TREE_TYPE (decl) = error_mark_node;
12737 }
12738
12739 if (type != error_mark_node)
12740 {
12741 if (deprecated_state != DEPRECATED_SUPPRESS)
12742 {
12743 tree deptype = type_is_deprecated (type);
12744 if (deptype)
12745 cp_warn_deprecated_use (deptype);
12746 }
12747
12748 /* Top-level qualifiers on the parameters are
12749 ignored for function types. */
12750 type = cp_build_qualified_type (type, 0);
12751 if (TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
12752 {
12753 error ("parameter %qD invalidly declared method type", decl);
12754 type = build_pointer_type (type);
12755 TREE_TYPE (decl) = type;
12756 }
12757 else if (abstract_virtuals_error (decl, type))
12758 any_error = 1; /* Seems like a good idea. */
12759 else if (POINTER_TYPE_P (type))
12760 {
12761 /* [dcl.fct]/6, parameter types cannot contain pointers
12762 (references) to arrays of unknown bound. */
12763 tree t = TREE_TYPE (type);
12764 int ptr = TYPE_PTR_P (type);
12765
12766 while (1)
12767 {
12768 if (TYPE_PTR_P (t))
12769 ptr = 1;
12770 else if (TREE_CODE (t) != ARRAY_TYPE)
12771 break;
12772 else if (!TYPE_DOMAIN (t))
12773 break;
12774 t = TREE_TYPE (t);
12775 }
12776 if (TREE_CODE (t) == ARRAY_TYPE)
12777 error (ptr
12778 ? G_("parameter %qD includes pointer to array of "
12779 "unknown bound %qT")
12780 : G_("parameter %qD includes reference to array of "
12781 "unknown bound %qT"),
12782 decl, t);
12783 }
12784
12785 if (any_error)
12786 init = NULL_TREE;
12787 else if (init && !processing_template_decl)
12788 init = check_default_argument (decl, init, tf_warning_or_error);
12789 }
12790
12791 DECL_CHAIN (decl) = decls;
12792 decls = decl;
12793 result = tree_cons (init, type, result);
12794 }
12795 decls = nreverse (decls);
12796 result = nreverse (result);
12797 if (parm)
12798 result = chainon (result, void_list_node);
12799 *parms = decls;
12800
12801 return result;
12802}
12803
12804
12805/* D is a constructor or overloaded `operator='.
12806
12807 Let T be the class in which D is declared. Then, this function
12808 returns:
12809
12810 -1 if D's is an ill-formed constructor or copy assignment operator
12811 whose first parameter is of type `T'.
12812 0 if D is not a copy constructor or copy assignment
12813 operator.
12814 1 if D is a copy constructor or copy assignment operator whose
12815 first parameter is a reference to non-const qualified T.
12816 2 if D is a copy constructor or copy assignment operator whose
12817 first parameter is a reference to const qualified T.
12818
12819 This function can be used as a predicate. Positive values indicate
12820 a copy constructor and nonzero values indicate a copy assignment
12821 operator. */
12822
12823int
12824copy_fn_p (const_tree d)
12825{
12826 tree args;
12827 tree arg_type;
12828 int result = 1;
12829
12830 gcc_assert (DECL_FUNCTION_MEMBER_P (d));
12831
12832 if (TREE_CODE (d) == TEMPLATE_DECL
12833 || (DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (d)
12834 && DECL_MEMBER_TEMPLATE_P (DECL_TI_TEMPLATE (d))))
12835 /* Instantiations of template member functions are never copy
12836 functions. Note that member functions of templated classes are
12837 represented as template functions internally, and we must
12838 accept those as copy functions. */
12839 return 0;
12840
12841 args = FUNCTION_FIRST_USER_PARMTYPE (d);
12842 if (!args)
12843 return 0;
12844
12845 arg_type = TREE_VALUE (args);
12846 if (arg_type == error_mark_node)
12847 return 0;
12848
12849 if (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (arg_type) == DECL_CONTEXT (d))
12850 {
12851 /* Pass by value copy assignment operator. */
12852 result = -1;
12853 }
12854 else if (TREE_CODE (arg_type) == REFERENCE_TYPE
12855 && !TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (arg_type)
12856 && TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (arg_type)) == DECL_CONTEXT (d))
12857 {
12858 if (CP_TYPE_CONST_P (TREE_TYPE (arg_type)))
12859 result = 2;
12860 }
12861 else
12862 return 0;
12863
12864 args = TREE_CHAIN (args);
12865
12866 if (args && args != void_list_node && !TREE_PURPOSE (args))
12867 /* There are more non-optional args. */
12868 return 0;
12869
12870 return result;
12871}
12872
12873/* D is a constructor or overloaded `operator='.
12874
12875 Let T be the class in which D is declared. Then, this function
12876 returns true when D is a move constructor or move assignment
12877 operator, false otherwise. */
12878
12879bool
12880move_fn_p (const_tree d)
12881{
12882 gcc_assert (DECL_FUNCTION_MEMBER_P (d));
12883
12884 if (cxx_dialect == cxx98)
12885 /* There are no move constructors if we are in C++98 mode. */
12886 return false;
12887
12888 if (TREE_CODE (d) == TEMPLATE_DECL
12889 || (DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (d)
12890 && DECL_MEMBER_TEMPLATE_P (DECL_TI_TEMPLATE (d))))
12891 /* Instantiations of template member functions are never move
12892 functions. Note that member functions of templated classes are
12893 represented as template functions internally, and we must
12894 accept those as move functions. */
12895 return 0;
12896
12897 return move_signature_fn_p (d);
12898}
12899
12900/* D is a constructor or overloaded `operator='.
12901
12902 Then, this function returns true when D has the same signature as a move
12903 constructor or move assignment operator (because either it is such a
12904 ctor/op= or it is a template specialization with the same signature),
12905 false otherwise. */
12906
12907bool
12908move_signature_fn_p (const_tree d)
12909{
12910 tree args;
12911 tree arg_type;
12912 bool result = false;
12913
12914 args = FUNCTION_FIRST_USER_PARMTYPE (d);
12915 if (!args)
12916 return 0;
12917
12918 arg_type = TREE_VALUE (args);
12919 if (arg_type == error_mark_node)
12920 return 0;
12921
12922 if (TREE_CODE (arg_type) == REFERENCE_TYPE
12923 && TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (arg_type)
12924 && same_type_p (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (arg_type)),
12925 DECL_CONTEXT (d)))
12926 result = true;
12927
12928 args = TREE_CHAIN (args);
12929
12930 if (args && args != void_list_node && !TREE_PURPOSE (args))
12931 /* There are more non-optional args. */
12932 return false;
12933
12934 return result;
12935}
12936
12937/* Remember any special properties of member function DECL. */
12938
12939void
12940grok_special_member_properties (tree decl)
12941{
12942 tree class_type;
12943
12944 if (!DECL_NONSTATIC_MEMBER_FUNCTION_P (decl))
12945 return;
12946
12947 class_type = DECL_CONTEXT (decl);
12948 if (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (decl))
12949 {
12950 int ctor = copy_fn_p (decl);
12951
12952 if (!DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl))
12953 TYPE_HAS_USER_CONSTRUCTOR (class_type) = 1;
12954
12955 if (ctor > 0)
12956 {
12957 /* [class.copy]
12958
12959 A non-template constructor for class X is a copy
12960 constructor if its first parameter is of type X&, const
12961 X&, volatile X& or const volatile X&, and either there
12962 are no other parameters or else all other parameters have
12963 default arguments. */
12964 TYPE_HAS_COPY_CTOR (class_type) = 1;
12965 if (user_provided_p (decl))
12966 TYPE_HAS_COMPLEX_COPY_CTOR (class_type) = 1;
12967 if (ctor > 1)
12968 TYPE_HAS_CONST_COPY_CTOR (class_type) = 1;
12969 }
12970 else if (sufficient_parms_p (FUNCTION_FIRST_USER_PARMTYPE (decl)))
12971 TYPE_HAS_DEFAULT_CONSTRUCTOR (class_type) = 1;
12972 else if (move_fn_p (decl) && user_provided_p (decl))
12973 TYPE_HAS_COMPLEX_MOVE_CTOR (class_type) = 1;
12974 else if (is_list_ctor (decl))
12975 TYPE_HAS_LIST_CTOR (class_type) = 1;
12976
12977 if (DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (decl)
12978 && !copy_fn_p (decl) && !move_fn_p (decl))
12979 TYPE_HAS_CONSTEXPR_CTOR (class_type) = 1;
12980 }
12981 else if (DECL_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_P (decl) == NOP_EXPR)
12982 {
12983 /* [class.copy]
12984
12985 A non-template assignment operator for class X is a copy
12986 assignment operator if its parameter is of type X, X&, const
12987 X&, volatile X& or const volatile X&. */
12988
12989 int assop = copy_fn_p (decl);
12990
12991 if (assop)
12992 {
12993 TYPE_HAS_COPY_ASSIGN (class_type) = 1;
12994 if (user_provided_p (decl))
12995 TYPE_HAS_COMPLEX_COPY_ASSIGN (class_type) = 1;
12996 if (assop != 1)
12997 TYPE_HAS_CONST_COPY_ASSIGN (class_type) = 1;
12998 }
12999 else if (move_fn_p (decl) && user_provided_p (decl))
13000 TYPE_HAS_COMPLEX_MOVE_ASSIGN (class_type) = 1;
13001 }
13002 /* Destructors are handled in check_methods. */
13003}
13004
13005/* Check a constructor DECL has the correct form. Complains
13006 if the class has a constructor of the form X(X). */
13007
13008int
13009grok_ctor_properties (const_tree ctype, const_tree decl)
13010{
13011 int ctor_parm = copy_fn_p (decl);
13012
13013 if (ctor_parm < 0)
13014 {
13015 /* [class.copy]
13016
13017 A declaration of a constructor for a class X is ill-formed if
13018 its first parameter is of type (optionally cv-qualified) X
13019 and either there are no other parameters or else all other
13020 parameters have default arguments.
13021
13022 We *don't* complain about member template instantiations that
13023 have this form, though; they can occur as we try to decide
13024 what constructor to use during overload resolution. Since
13025 overload resolution will never prefer such a constructor to
13026 the non-template copy constructor (which is either explicitly
13027 or implicitly defined), there's no need to worry about their
13028 existence. Theoretically, they should never even be
13029 instantiated, but that's hard to forestall. */
13030 error ("invalid constructor; you probably meant %<%T (const %T&)%>",
13031 ctype, ctype);
13032 return 0;
13033 }
13034
13035 return 1;
13036}
13037
13038/* An operator with this code is unary, but can also be binary. */
13039
13040static int
13041ambi_op_p (enum tree_code code)
13042{
13043 return (code == INDIRECT_REF
13044 || code == ADDR_EXPR
13045 || code == UNARY_PLUS_EXPR
13046 || code == NEGATE_EXPR
13047 || code == PREINCREMENT_EXPR
13048 || code == PREDECREMENT_EXPR);
13049}
13050
13051/* An operator with this name can only be unary. */
13052
13053static int
13054unary_op_p (enum tree_code code)
13055{
13056 return (code == TRUTH_NOT_EXPR
13057 || code == BIT_NOT_EXPR
13058 || code == COMPONENT_REF
13059 || code == TYPE_EXPR);
13060}
13061
13062/* DECL is a declaration for an overloaded operator. If COMPLAIN is true,
13063 errors are issued for invalid declarations. */
13064
13065bool
13066grok_op_properties (tree decl, bool complain)
13067{
13068 tree argtypes = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (decl));
13069 tree argtype;
13070 int methodp = (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (decl)) == METHOD_TYPE);
13071 tree name = DECL_NAME (decl);
13072 enum tree_code operator_code;
13073 int arity;
13074 bool ellipsis_p;
13075 tree class_type;
13076
13077 /* Count the number of arguments and check for ellipsis. */
13078 for (argtype = argtypes, arity = 0;
13079 argtype && argtype != void_list_node;
13080 argtype = TREE_CHAIN (argtype))
13081 ++arity;
13082 ellipsis_p = !argtype;
13083
13084 class_type = DECL_CONTEXT (decl);
13085 if (class_type && !CLASS_TYPE_P (class_type))
13086 class_type = NULL_TREE;
13087
13088 if (DECL_CONV_FN_P (decl))
13089 operator_code = TYPE_EXPR;
13090 else
13091 do
13092 {
13093#define DEF_OPERATOR(NAME, CODE, MANGLING, ARITY, ASSN_P) \
13094 if (cp_operator_id (CODE) == name) \
13095 { \
13096 operator_code = (CODE); \
13097 break; \
13098 } \
13099 else if (cp_assignment_operator_id (CODE) == name) \
13100 { \
13101 operator_code = (CODE); \
13102 DECL_ASSIGNMENT_OPERATOR_P (decl) = 1; \
13103 break; \
13104 }
13105
13106#include "operators.def"
13107#undef DEF_OPERATOR
13108
13109 gcc_unreachable ();
13110 }
13111 while (0);
13112 gcc_assert (operator_code != MAX_TREE_CODES);
13113 SET_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_CODE (decl, operator_code);
13114
13115 if (class_type)
13116 switch (operator_code)
13117 {
13118 case NEW_EXPR:
13119 TYPE_HAS_NEW_OPERATOR (class_type) = 1;
13120 break;
13121
13122 case DELETE_EXPR:
13123 TYPE_GETS_DELETE (class_type) |= 1;
13124 break;
13125
13126 case VEC_NEW_EXPR:
13127 TYPE_HAS_ARRAY_NEW_OPERATOR (class_type) = 1;
13128 break;
13129
13130 case VEC_DELETE_EXPR:
13131 TYPE_GETS_DELETE (class_type) |= 2;
13132 break;
13133
13134 default:
13135 break;
13136 }
13137
13138 /* [basic.std.dynamic.allocation]/1:
13139
13140 A program is ill-formed if an allocation function is declared
13141 in a namespace scope other than global scope or declared static
13142 in global scope.
13143
13144 The same also holds true for deallocation functions. */
13145 if (operator_code == NEW_EXPR || operator_code == VEC_NEW_EXPR
13146 || operator_code == DELETE_EXPR || operator_code == VEC_DELETE_EXPR)
13147 {
13148 if (DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (decl))
13149 {
13150 if (CP_DECL_CONTEXT (decl) != global_namespace)
13151 {
13152 error ("%qD may not be declared within a namespace", decl);
13153 return false;
13154 }
13155 else if (!TREE_PUBLIC (decl))
13156 {
13157 error ("%qD may not be declared as static", decl);
13158 return false;
13159 }
13160 }
13161 }
13162
13163 if (operator_code == NEW_EXPR || operator_code == VEC_NEW_EXPR)
13164 {
13165 TREE_TYPE (decl) = coerce_new_type (TREE_TYPE (decl));
13166 DECL_IS_OPERATOR_NEW (decl) = 1;
13167 }
13168 else if (operator_code == DELETE_EXPR || operator_code == VEC_DELETE_EXPR)
13169 TREE_TYPE (decl) = coerce_delete_type (TREE_TYPE (decl));
13170 else
13171 {
13172 /* An operator function must either be a non-static member function
13173 or have at least one parameter of a class, a reference to a class,
13174 an enumeration, or a reference to an enumeration. 13.4.0.6 */
13175 if (! methodp || DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (decl))
13176 {
13177 if (operator_code == TYPE_EXPR
13178 || operator_code == CALL_EXPR
13179 || operator_code == COMPONENT_REF
13180 || operator_code == ARRAY_REF
13181 || operator_code == NOP_EXPR)
13182 {
13183 error ("%qD must be a nonstatic member function", decl);
13184 return false;
13185 }
13186 else
13187 {
13188 tree p;
13189
13190 if (DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (decl))
13191 {
13192 error ("%qD must be either a non-static member "
13193 "function or a non-member function", decl);
13194 return false;
13195 }
13196
13197 for (p = argtypes; p && p != void_list_node; p = TREE_CHAIN (p))
13198 {
13199 tree arg = non_reference (TREE_VALUE (p));
13200 if (arg == error_mark_node)
13201 return false;
13202
13203 /* MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P, rather than CLASS_TYPE_P, is used
13204 because these checks are performed even on
13205 template functions. */
13206 if (MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (arg)
13207 || TREE_CODE (arg) == ENUMERAL_TYPE)
13208 break;
13209 }
13210
13211 if (!p || p == void_list_node)
13212 {
13213 if (complain)
13214 error ("%qD must have an argument of class or "
13215 "enumerated type", decl);
13216 return false;
13217 }
13218 }
13219 }
13220
13221 /* There are no restrictions on the arguments to an overloaded
13222 "operator ()". */
13223 if (operator_code == CALL_EXPR)
13224 return true;
13225
13226 /* Warn about conversion operators that will never be used. */
13227 if (IDENTIFIER_TYPENAME_P (name)
13228 && ! DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (decl)
13229 && warn_conversion
13230 /* Warn only declaring the function; there is no need to
13231 warn again about out-of-class definitions. */
13232 && class_type == current_class_type)
13233 {
13234 tree t = TREE_TYPE (name);
13235 int ref = (TREE_CODE (t) == REFERENCE_TYPE);
13236
13237 if (ref)
13238 t = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (t));
13239
13240 if (VOID_TYPE_P (t))
13241 warning (OPT_Wconversion,
13242 ref
13243 ? G_("conversion to a reference to void "
13244 "will never use a type conversion operator")
13245 : G_("conversion to void "
13246 "will never use a type conversion operator"));
13247 else if (class_type)
13248 {
13249 if (t == class_type)
13250 warning (OPT_Wconversion,
13251 ref
13252 ? G_("conversion to a reference to the same type "
13253 "will never use a type conversion operator")
13254 : G_("conversion to the same type "
13255 "will never use a type conversion operator"));
13256 /* Don't force t to be complete here. */
13257 else if (MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (t)
13258 && COMPLETE_TYPE_P (t)
13259 && DERIVED_FROM_P (t, class_type))
13260 warning (OPT_Wconversion,
13261 ref
13262 ? G_("conversion to a reference to a base class "
13263 "will never use a type conversion operator")
13264 : G_("conversion to a base class "
13265 "will never use a type conversion operator"));
13266 }
13267
13268 }
13269
13270 if (operator_code == COND_EXPR)
13271 {
13272 /* 13.4.0.3 */
13273 error ("ISO C++ prohibits overloading operator ?:");
13274 return false;
13275 }
13276 else if (ellipsis_p)
13277 {
13278 error ("%qD must not have variable number of arguments", decl);
13279 return false;
13280 }
13281 else if (ambi_op_p (operator_code))
13282 {
13283 if (arity == 1)
13284 /* We pick the one-argument operator codes by default, so
13285 we don't have to change anything. */
13286 ;
13287 else if (arity == 2)
13288 {
13289 /* If we thought this was a unary operator, we now know
13290 it to be a binary operator. */
13291 switch (operator_code)
13292 {
13293 case INDIRECT_REF:
13294 operator_code = MULT_EXPR;
13295 break;
13296
13297 case ADDR_EXPR:
13298 operator_code = BIT_AND_EXPR;
13299 break;
13300
13301 case UNARY_PLUS_EXPR:
13302 operator_code = PLUS_EXPR;
13303 break;
13304
13305 case NEGATE_EXPR:
13306 operator_code = MINUS_EXPR;
13307 break;
13308
13309 case PREINCREMENT_EXPR:
13310 operator_code = POSTINCREMENT_EXPR;
13311 break;
13312
13313 case PREDECREMENT_EXPR:
13314 operator_code = POSTDECREMENT_EXPR;
13315 break;
13316
13317 default:
13318 gcc_unreachable ();
13319 }
13320
13321 SET_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_CODE (decl, operator_code);
13322
13323 if ((operator_code == POSTINCREMENT_EXPR
13324 || operator_code == POSTDECREMENT_EXPR)
13325 && ! processing_template_decl
13326 && ! same_type_p (TREE_VALUE (TREE_CHAIN (argtypes)), integer_type_node))
13327 {
13328 if (methodp)
13329 error ("postfix %qD must take %<int%> as its argument",
13330 decl);
13331 else
13332 error ("postfix %qD must take %<int%> as its second "
13333 "argument", decl);
13334 return false;
13335 }
13336 }
13337 else
13338 {
13339 if (methodp)
13340 error ("%qD must take either zero or one argument", decl);
13341 else
13342 error ("%qD must take either one or two arguments", decl);
13343 return false;
13344 }
13345
13346 /* More Effective C++ rule 6. */
13347 if (warn_ecpp
13348 && (operator_code == POSTINCREMENT_EXPR
13349 || operator_code == POSTDECREMENT_EXPR
13350 || operator_code == PREINCREMENT_EXPR
13351 || operator_code == PREDECREMENT_EXPR))
13352 {
13353 tree arg = TREE_VALUE (argtypes);
13354 tree ret = TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (decl));
13355 if (methodp || TREE_CODE (arg) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
13356 arg = TREE_TYPE (arg);
13357 arg = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (arg);
13358 if (operator_code == PREINCREMENT_EXPR
13359 || operator_code == PREDECREMENT_EXPR)
13360 {
13361 if (TREE_CODE (ret) != REFERENCE_TYPE
13362 || !same_type_p (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (ret)),
13363 arg))
13364 warning (OPT_Weffc__, "prefix %qD should return %qT", decl,
13365 build_reference_type (arg));
13366 }
13367 else
13368 {
13369 if (!same_type_p (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (ret), arg))
13370 warning (OPT_Weffc__, "postfix %qD should return %qT", decl, arg);
13371 }
13372 }
13373 }
13374 else if (unary_op_p (operator_code))
13375 {
13376 if (arity != 1)
13377 {
13378 if (methodp)
13379 error ("%qD must take %<void%>", decl);
13380 else
13381 error ("%qD must take exactly one argument", decl);
13382 return false;
13383 }
13384 }
13385 else /* if (binary_op_p (operator_code)) */
13386 {
13387 if (arity != 2)
13388 {
13389 if (methodp)
13390 error ("%qD must take exactly one argument", decl);
13391 else
13392 error ("%qD must take exactly two arguments", decl);
13393 return false;
13394 }
13395
13396 /* More Effective C++ rule 7. */
13397 if (warn_ecpp
13398 && (operator_code == TRUTH_ANDIF_EXPR
13399 || operator_code == TRUTH_ORIF_EXPR
13400 || operator_code == COMPOUND_EXPR))
13401 warning (OPT_Weffc__, "user-defined %qD always evaluates both arguments",
13402 decl);
13403 }
13404
13405 /* Effective C++ rule 23. */
13406 if (warn_ecpp
13407 && arity == 2
13408 && !DECL_ASSIGNMENT_OPERATOR_P (decl)
13409 && (operator_code == PLUS_EXPR
13410 || operator_code == MINUS_EXPR
13411 || operator_code == TRUNC_DIV_EXPR
13412 || operator_code == MULT_EXPR
13413 || operator_code == TRUNC_MOD_EXPR)
13414 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (decl))) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
13415 warning (OPT_Weffc__, "%qD should return by value", decl);
13416
13417 /* [over.oper]/8 */
13418 for (; argtypes && argtypes != void_list_node;
13419 argtypes = TREE_CHAIN (argtypes))
13420 if (TREE_PURPOSE (argtypes))
13421 {
13422 TREE_PURPOSE (argtypes) = NULL_TREE;
13423 if (operator_code == POSTINCREMENT_EXPR
13424 || operator_code == POSTDECREMENT_EXPR)
13425 {
13426 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpedantic, "%qD cannot have default arguments",
13427 decl);
13428 }
13429 else
13430 {
13431 error ("%qD cannot have default arguments", decl);
13432 return false;
13433 }
13434 }
13435 }
13436 return true;
13437}
13438
13439/* Return a string giving the keyword associate with CODE. */
13440
13441static const char *
13442tag_name (enum tag_types code)
13443{
13444 switch (code)
13445 {
13446 case record_type:
13447 return "struct";
13448 case class_type:
13449 return "class";
13450 case union_type:
13451 return "union";
13452 case enum_type:
13453 return "enum";
13454 case typename_type:
13455 return "typename";
13456 default:
13457 gcc_unreachable ();
13458 }
13459}
13460
13461/* Name lookup in an elaborated-type-specifier (after the keyword
13462 indicated by TAG_CODE) has found the TYPE_DECL DECL. If the
13463 elaborated-type-specifier is invalid, issue a diagnostic and return
13464 error_mark_node; otherwise, return the *_TYPE to which it referred.
13465 If ALLOW_TEMPLATE_P is true, TYPE may be a class template. */
13466
13467tree
13468check_elaborated_type_specifier (enum tag_types tag_code,
13469 tree decl,
13470 bool allow_template_p)
13471{
13472 tree type;
13473
13474 /* In the case of:
13475
13476 struct S { struct S *p; };
13477
13478 name lookup will find the TYPE_DECL for the implicit "S::S"
13479 typedef. Adjust for that here. */
13480 if (DECL_SELF_REFERENCE_P (decl))
13481 decl = TYPE_NAME (TREE_TYPE (decl));
13482
13483 type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
13484
13485 /* Check TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM first because DECL_IMPLICIT_TYPEDEF_P
13486 is false for this case as well. */
13487 if (TREE_CODE (type) == TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM)
13488 {
13489 error ("using template type parameter %qT after %qs",
13490 type, tag_name (tag_code));
13491 return error_mark_node;
13492 }
13493 /* Accept template template parameters. */
13494 else if (allow_template_p
13495 && (TREE_CODE (type) == BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM
13496 || TREE_CODE (type) == TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM))
13497 ;
13498 /* [dcl.type.elab]
13499
13500 If the identifier resolves to a typedef-name or the
13501 simple-template-id resolves to an alias template
13502 specialization, the elaborated-type-specifier is ill-formed.
13503
13504 In other words, the only legitimate declaration to use in the
13505 elaborated type specifier is the implicit typedef created when
13506 the type is declared. */
13507 else if (!DECL_IMPLICIT_TYPEDEF_P (decl)
13508 && !DECL_SELF_REFERENCE_P (decl)
13509 && tag_code != typename_type)
13510 {
13511 if (alias_template_specialization_p (type))
13512 error ("using alias template specialization %qT after %qs",
13513 type, tag_name (tag_code));
13514 else
13515 error ("using typedef-name %qD after %qs", decl, tag_name (tag_code));
13516 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
13517 "%qD has a previous declaration here", decl);
13518 return error_mark_node;
13519 }
13520 else if (TREE_CODE (type) != RECORD_TYPE
13521 && TREE_CODE (type) != UNION_TYPE
13522 && tag_code != enum_type
13523 && tag_code != typename_type)
13524 {
13525 error ("%qT referred to as %qs", type, tag_name (tag_code));
13526 inform (location_of (type), "%qT has a previous declaration here", type);
13527 return error_mark_node;
13528 }
13529 else if (TREE_CODE (type) != ENUMERAL_TYPE
13530 && tag_code == enum_type)
13531 {
13532 error ("%qT referred to as enum", type);
13533 inform (location_of (type), "%qT has a previous declaration here", type);
13534 return error_mark_node;
13535 }
13536 else if (!allow_template_p
13537 && TREE_CODE (type) == RECORD_TYPE
13538 && CLASSTYPE_IS_TEMPLATE (type))
13539 {
13540 /* If a class template appears as elaborated type specifier
13541 without a template header such as:
13542
13543 template <class T> class C {};
13544 void f(class C); // No template header here
13545
13546 then the required template argument is missing. */
13547 error ("template argument required for %<%s %T%>",
13548 tag_name (tag_code),
13549 DECL_NAME (CLASSTYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (type)));
13550 return error_mark_node;
13551 }
13552
13553 return type;
13554}
13555
13556/* Lookup NAME in elaborate type specifier in scope according to
13557 SCOPE and issue diagnostics if necessary.
13558 Return *_TYPE node upon success, NULL_TREE when the NAME is not
13559 found, and ERROR_MARK_NODE for type error. */
13560
13561static tree
13562lookup_and_check_tag (enum tag_types tag_code, tree name,
13563 tag_scope scope, bool template_header_p)
13564{
13565 tree t;
13566 tree decl;
13567 if (scope == ts_global)
13568 {
13569 /* First try ordinary name lookup, ignoring hidden class name
13570 injected via friend declaration. */
13571 decl = lookup_name_prefer_type (name, 2);
13572 decl = strip_using_decl (decl);
13573 /* If that fails, the name will be placed in the smallest
13574 non-class, non-function-prototype scope according to 3.3.1/5.
13575 We may already have a hidden name declared as friend in this
13576 scope. So lookup again but not ignoring hidden names.
13577 If we find one, that name will be made visible rather than
13578 creating a new tag. */
13579 if (!decl)
13580 decl = lookup_type_scope (name, ts_within_enclosing_non_class);
13581 }
13582 else
13583 decl = lookup_type_scope (name, scope);
13584
13585 if (decl
13586 && (DECL_CLASS_TEMPLATE_P (decl)
13587 /* If scope is ts_current we're defining a class, so ignore a
13588 template template parameter. */
13589 || (scope != ts_current
13590 && DECL_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM_P (decl))))
13591 decl = DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (decl);
13592
13593 if (decl && TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL)
13594 {
13595 /* Look for invalid nested type:
13596 class C {
13597 class C {};
13598 }; */
13599 if (scope == ts_current && DECL_SELF_REFERENCE_P (decl))
13600 {
13601 error ("%qD has the same name as the class in which it is "
13602 "declared",
13603 decl);
13604 return error_mark_node;
13605 }
13606
13607 /* Two cases we need to consider when deciding if a class
13608 template is allowed as an elaborated type specifier:
13609 1. It is a self reference to its own class.
13610 2. It comes with a template header.
13611
13612 For example:
13613
13614 template <class T> class C {
13615 class C *c1; // DECL_SELF_REFERENCE_P is true
13616 class D;
13617 };
13618 template <class U> class C; // template_header_p is true
13619 template <class T> class C<T>::D {
13620 class C *c2; // DECL_SELF_REFERENCE_P is true
13621 }; */
13622
13623 t = check_elaborated_type_specifier (tag_code,
13624 decl,
13625 template_header_p
13626 | DECL_SELF_REFERENCE_P (decl));
13627 if (template_header_p && t && CLASS_TYPE_P (t)
13628 && (!CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (t)
13629 || (!PRIMARY_TEMPLATE_P (CLASSTYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (t)))))
13630 {
13631 error ("%qT is not a template", t);
13632 inform (location_of (t), "previous declaration here");
13633 if (TYPE_CLASS_SCOPE_P (t)
13634 && CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (TYPE_CONTEXT (t)))
13635 inform (input_location,
13636 "perhaps you want to explicitly add %<%T::%>",
13637 TYPE_CONTEXT (t));
13638 t = error_mark_node;
13639 }
13640
13641 return t;
13642 }
13643 else if (decl && TREE_CODE (decl) == TREE_LIST)
13644 {
13645 error ("reference to %qD is ambiguous", name);
13646 print_candidates (decl);
13647 return error_mark_node;
13648 }
13649 else
13650 return NULL_TREE;
13651}
13652
13653/* Get the struct, enum or union (TAG_CODE says which) with tag NAME.
13654 Define the tag as a forward-reference if it is not defined.
13655
13656 If a declaration is given, process it here, and report an error if
13657 multiple declarations are not identical.
13658
13659 SCOPE is TS_CURRENT when this is also a definition. Only look in
13660 the current frame for the name (since C++ allows new names in any
13661 scope.) It is TS_WITHIN_ENCLOSING_NON_CLASS if this is a friend
13662 declaration. Only look beginning from the current scope outward up
13663 till the nearest non-class scope. Otherwise it is TS_GLOBAL.
13664
13665 TEMPLATE_HEADER_P is true when this declaration is preceded by
13666 a set of template parameters. */
13667
13668static tree
13669xref_tag_1 (enum tag_types tag_code, tree name,
13670 tag_scope orig_scope, bool template_header_p)
13671{
13672 enum tree_code code;
13673 tree t;
13674 tree context = NULL_TREE;
13675 tag_scope scope;
13676
13677 gcc_assert (identifier_p (name));
13678
13679 switch (tag_code)
13680 {
13681 case record_type:
13682 case class_type:
13683 code = RECORD_TYPE;
13684 break;
13685 case union_type:
13686 code = UNION_TYPE;
13687 break;
13688 case enum_type:
13689 code = ENUMERAL_TYPE;
13690 break;
13691 default:
13692 gcc_unreachable ();
13693 }
13694
13695 if (orig_scope == ts_lambda)
13696 scope = ts_current;
13697 else
13698 scope = orig_scope;
13699
13700 /* In case of anonymous name, xref_tag is only called to
13701 make type node and push name. Name lookup is not required. */
13702 if (anon_aggrname_p (name))
13703 t = NULL_TREE;
13704 else
13705 t = lookup_and_check_tag (tag_code, name,
13706 scope, template_header_p);
13707
13708 if (t == error_mark_node)
13709 return error_mark_node;
13710
13711 if (scope != ts_current && t && current_class_type
13712 && template_class_depth (current_class_type)
13713 && template_header_p)
13714 {
13715 if (TREE_CODE (t) == TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM)
13716 return t;
13717
13718 /* Since SCOPE is not TS_CURRENT, we are not looking at a
13719 definition of this tag. Since, in addition, we are currently
13720 processing a (member) template declaration of a template
13721 class, we must be very careful; consider:
13722
13723 template <class X>
13724 struct S1
13725
13726 template <class U>
13727 struct S2
13728 { template <class V>
13729 friend struct S1; };
13730
13731 Here, the S2::S1 declaration should not be confused with the
13732 outer declaration. In particular, the inner version should
13733 have a template parameter of level 2, not level 1. This
13734 would be particularly important if the member declaration
13735 were instead:
13736
13737 template <class V = U> friend struct S1;
13738
13739 say, when we should tsubst into `U' when instantiating
13740 S2. On the other hand, when presented with:
13741
13742 template <class T>
13743 struct S1 {
13744 template <class U>
13745 struct S2 {};
13746 template <class U>
13747 friend struct S2;
13748 };
13749
13750 we must find the inner binding eventually. We
13751 accomplish this by making sure that the new type we
13752 create to represent this declaration has the right
13753 TYPE_CONTEXT. */
13754 context = TYPE_CONTEXT (t);
13755 t = NULL_TREE;
13756 }
13757
13758 if (! t)
13759 {
13760 /* If no such tag is yet defined, create a forward-reference node
13761 and record it as the "definition".
13762 When a real declaration of this type is found,
13763 the forward-reference will be altered into a real type. */
13764 if (code == ENUMERAL_TYPE)
13765 {
13766 error ("use of enum %q#D without previous declaration", name);
13767 return error_mark_node;
13768 }
13769 else
13770 {
13771 t = make_class_type (code);
13772 TYPE_CONTEXT (t) = context;
13773 if (orig_scope == ts_lambda)
13774 /* Remember that we're declaring a lambda to avoid bogus errors
13775 in push_template_decl. */
13776 CLASSTYPE_LAMBDA_EXPR (t) = error_mark_node;
13777 t = pushtag (name, t, scope);
13778 }
13779 }
13780 else
13781 {
13782 if (template_header_p && MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (t))
13783 {
13784 /* Check that we aren't trying to overload a class with different
13785 constraints. */
13786 tree constr = NULL_TREE;
13787 if (current_template_parms)
13788 {
13789 tree reqs = TEMPLATE_PARMS_CONSTRAINTS (current_template_parms);
13790 constr = build_constraints (reqs, NULL_TREE);
13791 }
13792 if (!redeclare_class_template (t, current_template_parms, constr))
13793 return error_mark_node;
13794 }
13795 else if (!processing_template_decl
13796 && CLASS_TYPE_P (t)
13797 && CLASSTYPE_IS_TEMPLATE (t))
13798 {
13799 error ("redeclaration of %qT as a non-template", t);
13800 inform (location_of (t), "previous declaration %qD", t);
13801 return error_mark_node;
13802 }
13803
13804 /* Make injected friend class visible. */
13805 if (scope != ts_within_enclosing_non_class
13806 && hidden_name_p (TYPE_NAME (t)))
13807 {
13808 DECL_ANTICIPATED (TYPE_NAME (t)) = 0;
13809 DECL_FRIEND_P (TYPE_NAME (t)) = 0;
13810
13811 if (TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (t))
13812 {
13813 DECL_ANTICIPATED (TYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (t)) = 0;
13814 DECL_FRIEND_P (TYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (t)) = 0;
13815 }
13816 }
13817 }
13818
13819 return t;
13820}
13821
13822/* Wrapper for xref_tag_1. */
13823
13824tree
13825xref_tag (enum tag_types tag_code, tree name,
13826 tag_scope scope, bool template_header_p)
13827{
13828 tree ret;
13829 bool subtime;
13830 subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
13831 ret = xref_tag_1 (tag_code, name, scope, template_header_p);
13832 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
13833 return ret;
13834}
13835
13836
13837tree
13838xref_tag_from_type (tree old, tree id, tag_scope scope)
13839{
13840 enum tag_types tag_kind;
13841
13842 if (TREE_CODE (old) == RECORD_TYPE)
13843 tag_kind = (CLASSTYPE_DECLARED_CLASS (old) ? class_type : record_type);
13844 else
13845 tag_kind = union_type;
13846
13847 if (id == NULL_TREE)
13848 id = TYPE_IDENTIFIER (old);
13849
13850 return xref_tag (tag_kind, id, scope, false);
13851}
13852
13853/* Create the binfo hierarchy for REF with (possibly NULL) base list
13854 BASE_LIST. For each element on BASE_LIST the TREE_PURPOSE is an
13855 access_* node, and the TREE_VALUE is the type of the base-class.
13856 Non-NULL TREE_TYPE indicates virtual inheritance. */
13857
13858void
13859xref_basetypes (tree ref, tree base_list)
13860{
13861 tree *basep;
13862 tree binfo, base_binfo;
13863 unsigned max_vbases = 0; /* Maximum direct & indirect virtual bases. */
13864 unsigned max_bases = 0; /* Maximum direct bases. */
13865 unsigned max_dvbases = 0; /* Maximum direct virtual bases. */
13866 int i;
13867 tree default_access;
13868 tree igo_prev; /* Track Inheritance Graph Order. */
13869
13870 if (ref == error_mark_node)
13871 return;
13872
13873 /* The base of a derived class is private by default, all others are
13874 public. */
13875 default_access = (TREE_CODE (ref) == RECORD_TYPE
13876 && CLASSTYPE_DECLARED_CLASS (ref)
13877 ? access_private_node : access_public_node);
13878
13879 /* First, make sure that any templates in base-classes are
13880 instantiated. This ensures that if we call ourselves recursively
13881 we do not get confused about which classes are marked and which
13882 are not. */
13883 basep = &base_list;
13884 while (*basep)
13885 {
13886 tree basetype = TREE_VALUE (*basep);
13887
13888 /* The dependent_type_p call below should really be dependent_scope_p
13889 so that we give a hard error about using an incomplete type as a
13890 base, but we allow it with a pedwarn for backward
13891 compatibility. */
13892 if (processing_template_decl
13893 && CLASS_TYPE_P (basetype) && TYPE_BEING_DEFINED (basetype))
13894 cxx_incomplete_type_diagnostic (NULL_TREE, basetype, DK_PEDWARN);
13895 if (!dependent_type_p (basetype)
13896 && !complete_type_or_else (basetype, NULL))
13897 /* An incomplete type. Remove it from the list. */
13898 *basep = TREE_CHAIN (*basep);
13899 else
13900 {
13901 max_bases++;
13902 if (TREE_TYPE (*basep))
13903 max_dvbases++;
13904 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (basetype))
13905 max_vbases += vec_safe_length (CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES (basetype));
13906 basep = &TREE_CHAIN (*basep);
13907 }
13908 }
13909 max_vbases += max_dvbases;
13910
13911 TYPE_MARKED_P (ref) = 1;
13912
13913 /* The binfo slot should be empty, unless this is an (ill-formed)
13914 redefinition. */
13915 gcc_assert (!TYPE_BINFO (ref) || TYPE_SIZE (ref));
13916
13917 gcc_assert (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (ref) == ref);
13918
13919 binfo = make_tree_binfo (max_bases);
13920
13921 TYPE_BINFO (ref) = binfo;
13922 BINFO_OFFSET (binfo) = size_zero_node;
13923 BINFO_TYPE (binfo) = ref;
13924
13925 /* Apply base-class info set up to the variants of this type. */
13926 fixup_type_variants (ref);
13927
13928 if (max_bases)
13929 {
13930 vec_alloc (BINFO_BASE_ACCESSES (binfo), max_bases);
13931 /* A C++98 POD cannot have base classes. */
13932 CLASSTYPE_NON_LAYOUT_POD_P (ref) = true;
13933
13934 if (TREE_CODE (ref) == UNION_TYPE)
13935 error ("derived union %qT invalid", ref);
13936 }
13937
13938 if (max_bases > 1)
13939 warning (OPT_Wmultiple_inheritance,
13940 "%qT defined with multiple direct bases", ref);
13941
13942 if (max_vbases)
13943 {
13944 /* An aggregate can't have virtual base classes. */
13945 CLASSTYPE_NON_AGGREGATE (ref) = true;
13946
13947 vec_alloc (CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES (ref), max_vbases);
13948
13949 if (max_dvbases)
13950 warning (OPT_Wvirtual_inheritance,
13951 "%qT defined with direct virtual base", ref);
13952 }
13953
13954 for (igo_prev = binfo; base_list; base_list = TREE_CHAIN (base_list))
13955 {
13956 tree access = TREE_PURPOSE (base_list);
13957 int via_virtual = TREE_TYPE (base_list) != NULL_TREE;
13958 tree basetype = TREE_VALUE (base_list);
13959
13960 if (access == access_default_node)
13961 access = default_access;
13962
13963 /* Before C++17, an aggregate cannot have base classes. In C++17, an
13964 aggregate can't have virtual, private, or protected base classes. */
13965 if (cxx_dialect < cxx1z
13966 || access != access_public_node
13967 || via_virtual)
13968 CLASSTYPE_NON_AGGREGATE (ref) = true;
13969
13970 if (PACK_EXPANSION_P (basetype))
13971 basetype = PACK_EXPANSION_PATTERN (basetype);
13972 if (TREE_CODE (basetype) == TYPE_DECL)
13973 basetype = TREE_TYPE (basetype);
13974 if (!MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (basetype) || TREE_CODE (basetype) == UNION_TYPE)
13975 {
13976 error ("base type %qT fails to be a struct or class type",
13977 basetype);
13978 goto dropped_base;
13979 }
13980
13981 base_binfo = NULL_TREE;
13982 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (basetype) && !dependent_scope_p (basetype))
13983 {
13984 base_binfo = TYPE_BINFO (basetype);
13985 /* The original basetype could have been a typedef'd type. */
13986 basetype = BINFO_TYPE (base_binfo);
13987
13988 /* Inherit flags from the base. */
13989 TYPE_HAS_NEW_OPERATOR (ref)
13990 |= TYPE_HAS_NEW_OPERATOR (basetype);
13991 TYPE_HAS_ARRAY_NEW_OPERATOR (ref)
13992 |= TYPE_HAS_ARRAY_NEW_OPERATOR (basetype);
13993 TYPE_GETS_DELETE (ref) |= TYPE_GETS_DELETE (basetype);
13994 TYPE_HAS_CONVERSION (ref) |= TYPE_HAS_CONVERSION (basetype);
13995 CLASSTYPE_DIAMOND_SHAPED_P (ref)
13996 |= CLASSTYPE_DIAMOND_SHAPED_P (basetype);
13997 CLASSTYPE_REPEATED_BASE_P (ref)
13998 |= CLASSTYPE_REPEATED_BASE_P (basetype);
13999 }
14000
14001 /* We must do this test after we've seen through a typedef
14002 type. */
14003 if (TYPE_MARKED_P (basetype))
14004 {
14005 if (basetype == ref)
14006 error ("recursive type %qT undefined", basetype);
14007 else
14008 error ("duplicate base type %qT invalid", basetype);
14009 goto dropped_base;
14010 }
14011
14012 if (PACK_EXPANSION_P (TREE_VALUE (base_list)))
14013 /* Regenerate the pack expansion for the bases. */
14014 basetype = make_pack_expansion (basetype);
14015
14016 TYPE_MARKED_P (basetype) = 1;
14017
14018 base_binfo = copy_binfo (base_binfo, basetype, ref,
14019 &igo_prev, via_virtual);
14020 if (!BINFO_INHERITANCE_CHAIN (base_binfo))
14021 BINFO_INHERITANCE_CHAIN (base_binfo) = binfo;
14022
14023 BINFO_BASE_APPEND (binfo, base_binfo);
14024 BINFO_BASE_ACCESS_APPEND (binfo, access);
14025 continue;
14026
14027 dropped_base:
14028 /* Update max_vbases to reflect the reality that we are dropping
14029 this base: if it reaches zero we want to undo the vec_alloc
14030 above to avoid inconsistencies during error-recovery: eg, in
14031 build_special_member_call, CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES non null
14032 and vtt null (c++/27952). */
14033 if (via_virtual)
14034 max_vbases--;
14035 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (basetype))
14036 max_vbases
14037 -= vec_safe_length (CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES (basetype));
14038 }
14039
14040 if (CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES (ref)
14041 && max_vbases == 0)
14042 vec_free (CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES (ref));
14043
14044 if (vec_safe_length (CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES (ref)) < max_vbases)
14045 /* If we didn't get max_vbases vbases, we must have shared at
14046 least one of them, and are therefore diamond shaped. */
14047 CLASSTYPE_DIAMOND_SHAPED_P (ref) = 1;
14048
14049 /* Unmark all the types. */
14050 for (i = 0; BINFO_BASE_ITERATE (binfo, i, base_binfo); i++)
14051 TYPE_MARKED_P (BINFO_TYPE (base_binfo)) = 0;
14052 TYPE_MARKED_P (ref) = 0;
14053
14054 /* Now see if we have a repeated base type. */
14055 if (!CLASSTYPE_REPEATED_BASE_P (ref))
14056 {
14057 for (base_binfo = binfo; base_binfo;
14058 base_binfo = TREE_CHAIN (base_binfo))
14059 {
14060 if (TYPE_MARKED_P (BINFO_TYPE (base_binfo)))
14061 {
14062 CLASSTYPE_REPEATED_BASE_P (ref) = 1;
14063 break;
14064 }
14065 TYPE_MARKED_P (BINFO_TYPE (base_binfo)) = 1;
14066 }
14067 for (base_binfo = binfo; base_binfo;
14068 base_binfo = TREE_CHAIN (base_binfo))
14069 if (TYPE_MARKED_P (BINFO_TYPE (base_binfo)))
14070 TYPE_MARKED_P (BINFO_TYPE (base_binfo)) = 0;
14071 else
14072 break;
14073 }
14074}
14075
14076
14077/* Copies the enum-related properties from type SRC to type DST.
14078 Used with the underlying type of an enum and the enum itself. */
14079static void
14080copy_type_enum (tree dst, tree src)
14081{
14082 tree t;
14083 for (t = dst; t; t = TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT (t))
14084 {
14085 TYPE_MIN_VALUE (t) = TYPE_MIN_VALUE (src);
14086 TYPE_MAX_VALUE (t) = TYPE_MAX_VALUE (src);
14087 TYPE_SIZE (t) = TYPE_SIZE (src);
14088 TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (t) = TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (src);
14089 SET_TYPE_MODE (dst, TYPE_MODE (src));
14090 TYPE_PRECISION (t) = TYPE_PRECISION (src);
14091 unsigned valign = TYPE_ALIGN (src);
14092 if (TYPE_USER_ALIGN (t))
14093 valign = MAX (valign, TYPE_ALIGN (t));
14094 else
14095 TYPE_USER_ALIGN (t) = TYPE_USER_ALIGN (src);
14096 SET_TYPE_ALIGN (t, valign);
14097 TYPE_UNSIGNED (t) = TYPE_UNSIGNED (src);
14098 }
14099}
14100
14101/* Begin compiling the definition of an enumeration type.
14102 NAME is its name,
14103
14104 if ENUMTYPE is not NULL_TREE then the type has alredy been found.
14105
14106 UNDERLYING_TYPE is the type that will be used as the storage for
14107 the enumeration type. This should be NULL_TREE if no storage type
14108 was specified.
14109
14110 ATTRIBUTES are any attributes specified after the enum-key.
14111
14112 SCOPED_ENUM_P is true if this is a scoped enumeration type.
14113
14114 if IS_NEW is not NULL, gets TRUE iff a new type is created.
14115
14116 Returns the type object, as yet incomplete.
14117 Also records info about it so that build_enumerator
14118 may be used to declare the individual values as they are read. */
14119
14120tree
14121start_enum (tree name, tree enumtype, tree underlying_type,
14122 tree attributes, bool scoped_enum_p, bool *is_new)
14123{
14124 tree prevtype = NULL_TREE;
14125 gcc_assert (identifier_p (name));
14126
14127 if (is_new)
14128 *is_new = false;
14129 /* [C++0x dcl.enum]p5:
14130
14131 If not explicitly specified, the underlying type of a scoped
14132 enumeration type is int. */
14133 if (!underlying_type && scoped_enum_p)
14134 underlying_type = integer_type_node;
14135
14136 if (underlying_type)
14137 underlying_type = cv_unqualified (underlying_type);
14138
14139 /* If this is the real definition for a previous forward reference,
14140 fill in the contents in the same object that used to be the
14141 forward reference. */
14142 if (!enumtype)
14143 enumtype = lookup_and_check_tag (enum_type, name,
14144 /*tag_scope=*/ts_current,
14145 /*template_header_p=*/false);
14146
14147 /* In case of a template_decl, the only check that should be deferred
14148 to instantiation time is the comparison of underlying types. */
14149 if (enumtype && TREE_CODE (enumtype) == ENUMERAL_TYPE)
14150 {
14151 if (scoped_enum_p != SCOPED_ENUM_P (enumtype))
14152 {
14153 error_at (input_location, "scoped/unscoped mismatch "
14154 "in enum %q#T", enumtype);
14155 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (enumtype)),
14156 "previous definition here");
14157 enumtype = error_mark_node;
14158 }
14159 else if (ENUM_FIXED_UNDERLYING_TYPE_P (enumtype) != !! underlying_type)
14160 {
14161 error_at (input_location, "underlying type mismatch "
14162 "in enum %q#T", enumtype);
14163 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (enumtype)),
14164 "previous definition here");
14165 enumtype = error_mark_node;
14166 }
14167 else if (underlying_type && ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype)
14168 && !dependent_type_p (underlying_type)
14169 && !dependent_type_p (ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype))
14170 && !same_type_p (underlying_type,
14171 ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype)))
14172 {
14173 error_at (input_location, "different underlying type "
14174 "in enum %q#T", enumtype);
14175 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (enumtype)),
14176 "previous definition here");
14177 underlying_type = NULL_TREE;
14178 }
14179 }
14180
14181 if (!enumtype || TREE_CODE (enumtype) != ENUMERAL_TYPE
14182 || processing_template_decl)
14183 {
14184 /* In case of error, make a dummy enum to allow parsing to
14185 continue. */
14186 if (enumtype == error_mark_node)
14187 {
14188 name = make_anon_name ();
14189 enumtype = NULL_TREE;
14190 }
14191
14192 /* enumtype may be an ENUMERAL_TYPE if this is a redefinition
14193 of an opaque enum, or an opaque enum of an already defined
14194 enumeration (C++0x only).
14195 In any other case, it'll be NULL_TREE. */
14196 if (!enumtype)
14197 {
14198 if (is_new)
14199 *is_new = true;
14200 }
14201 prevtype = enumtype;
14202
14203 /* Do not push the decl more than once, unless we need to
14204 compare underlying types at instantiation time */
14205 if (!enumtype
14206 || TREE_CODE (enumtype) != ENUMERAL_TYPE
14207 || (underlying_type
14208 && dependent_type_p (underlying_type))
14209 || (ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype)
14210 && dependent_type_p (ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype))))
14211 {
14212 enumtype = cxx_make_type (ENUMERAL_TYPE);
14213 enumtype = pushtag (name, enumtype, /*tag_scope=*/ts_current);
14214
14215 /* std::byte aliases anything. */
14216 if (enumtype != error_mark_node
14217 && TYPE_CONTEXT (enumtype) == std_node
14218 && !strcmp ("byte", TYPE_NAME_STRING (enumtype)))
14219 TYPE_ALIAS_SET (enumtype) = 0;
14220 }
14221 else
14222 enumtype = xref_tag (enum_type, name, /*tag_scope=*/ts_current,
14223 false);
14224
14225 if (enumtype == error_mark_node)
14226 return error_mark_node;
14227
14228 /* The enum is considered opaque until the opening '{' of the
14229 enumerator list. */
14230 SET_OPAQUE_ENUM_P (enumtype, true);
14231 ENUM_FIXED_UNDERLYING_TYPE_P (enumtype) = !! underlying_type;
14232 }
14233
14234 SET_SCOPED_ENUM_P (enumtype, scoped_enum_p);
14235
14236 cplus_decl_attributes (&enumtype, attributes, (int)ATTR_FLAG_TYPE_IN_PLACE);
14237
14238 if (underlying_type)
14239 {
14240 if (ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype))
14241 /* We already checked that it matches, don't change it to a different
14242 typedef variant. */;
14243 else if (CP_INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (underlying_type))
14244 {
14245 copy_type_enum (enumtype, underlying_type);
14246 ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype) = underlying_type;
14247 }
14248 else if (dependent_type_p (underlying_type))
14249 ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype) = underlying_type;
14250 else
14251 error ("underlying type %<%T%> of %<%T%> must be an integral type",
14252 underlying_type, enumtype);
14253 }
14254
14255 /* If into a template class, the returned enum is always the first
14256 declaration (opaque or not) seen. This way all the references to
14257 this type will be to the same declaration. The following ones are used
14258 only to check for definition errors. */
14259 if (prevtype && processing_template_decl)
14260 return prevtype;
14261 else
14262 return enumtype;
14263}
14264
14265/* After processing and defining all the values of an enumeration type,
14266 install their decls in the enumeration type.
14267 ENUMTYPE is the type object. */
14268
14269void
14270finish_enum_value_list (tree enumtype)
14271{
14272 tree values;
14273 tree underlying_type;
14274 tree decl;
14275 tree value;
14276 tree minnode, maxnode;
14277 tree t;
14278
14279 bool fixed_underlying_type_p
14280 = ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype) != NULL_TREE;
14281
14282 /* We built up the VALUES in reverse order. */
14283 TYPE_VALUES (enumtype) = nreverse (TYPE_VALUES (enumtype));
14284
14285 /* For an enum defined in a template, just set the type of the values;
14286 all further processing is postponed until the template is
14287 instantiated. We need to set the type so that tsubst of a CONST_DECL
14288 works. */
14289 if (processing_template_decl)
14290 {
14291 for (values = TYPE_VALUES (enumtype);
14292 values;
14293 values = TREE_CHAIN (values))
14294 TREE_TYPE (TREE_VALUE (values)) = enumtype;
14295 return;
14296 }
14297
14298 /* Determine the minimum and maximum values of the enumerators. */
14299 if (TYPE_VALUES (enumtype))
14300 {
14301 minnode = maxnode = NULL_TREE;
14302
14303 for (values = TYPE_VALUES (enumtype);
14304 values;
14305 values = TREE_CHAIN (values))
14306 {
14307 decl = TREE_VALUE (values);
14308
14309 /* [dcl.enum]: Following the closing brace of an enum-specifier,
14310 each enumerator has the type of its enumeration. Prior to the
14311 closing brace, the type of each enumerator is the type of its
14312 initializing value. */
14313 TREE_TYPE (decl) = enumtype;
14314
14315 /* Update the minimum and maximum values, if appropriate. */
14316 value = DECL_INITIAL (decl);
14317 if (value == error_mark_node)
14318 value = integer_zero_node;
14319 /* Figure out what the minimum and maximum values of the
14320 enumerators are. */
14321 if (!minnode)
14322 minnode = maxnode = value;
14323 else if (tree_int_cst_lt (maxnode, value))
14324 maxnode = value;
14325 else if (tree_int_cst_lt (value, minnode))
14326 minnode = value;
14327 }
14328 }
14329 else
14330 /* [dcl.enum]
14331
14332 If the enumerator-list is empty, the underlying type is as if
14333 the enumeration had a single enumerator with value 0. */
14334 minnode = maxnode = integer_zero_node;
14335
14336 if (!fixed_underlying_type_p)
14337 {
14338 /* Compute the number of bits require to represent all values of the
14339 enumeration. We must do this before the type of MINNODE and
14340 MAXNODE are transformed, since tree_int_cst_min_precision relies
14341 on the TREE_TYPE of the value it is passed. */
14342 signop sgn = tree_int_cst_sgn (minnode) >= 0 ? UNSIGNED : SIGNED;
14343 int lowprec = tree_int_cst_min_precision (minnode, sgn);
14344 int highprec = tree_int_cst_min_precision (maxnode, sgn);
14345 int precision = MAX (lowprec, highprec);
14346 unsigned int itk;
14347 bool use_short_enum;
14348
14349 /* Determine the underlying type of the enumeration.
14350
14351 [dcl.enum]
14352
14353 The underlying type of an enumeration is an integral type that
14354 can represent all the enumerator values defined in the
14355 enumeration. It is implementation-defined which integral type is
14356 used as the underlying type for an enumeration except that the
14357 underlying type shall not be larger than int unless the value of
14358 an enumerator cannot fit in an int or unsigned int.
14359
14360 We use "int" or an "unsigned int" as the underlying type, even if
14361 a smaller integral type would work, unless the user has
14362 explicitly requested that we use the smallest possible type. The
14363 user can request that for all enumerations with a command line
14364 flag, or for just one enumeration with an attribute. */
14365
14366 use_short_enum = flag_short_enums
14367 || lookup_attribute ("packed", TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (enumtype));
14368
14369 /* If the precision of the type was specified with an attribute and it
14370 was too small, give an error. Otherwise, use it. */
14371 if (TYPE_PRECISION (enumtype))
14372 {
14373 if (precision > TYPE_PRECISION (enumtype))
14374 error ("specified mode too small for enumeral values");
14375 else
14376 {
14377 use_short_enum = true;
14378 precision = TYPE_PRECISION (enumtype);
14379 }
14380 }
14381
14382 for (itk = (use_short_enum ? itk_char : itk_int);
14383 itk != itk_none;
14384 itk++)
14385 {
14386 underlying_type = integer_types[itk];
14387 if (underlying_type != NULL_TREE
14388 && TYPE_PRECISION (underlying_type) >= precision
14389 && TYPE_SIGN (underlying_type) == sgn)
14390 break;
14391 }
14392 if (itk == itk_none)
14393 {
14394 /* DR 377
14395
14396 IF no integral type can represent all the enumerator values, the
14397 enumeration is ill-formed. */
14398 error ("no integral type can represent all of the enumerator values "
14399 "for %qT", enumtype);
14400 precision = TYPE_PRECISION (long_long_integer_type_node);
14401 underlying_type = integer_types[itk_unsigned_long_long];
14402 }
14403
14404 /* [dcl.enum]
14405
14406 The value of sizeof() applied to an enumeration type, an object
14407 of an enumeration type, or an enumerator, is the value of sizeof()
14408 applied to the underlying type. */
14409 copy_type_enum (enumtype, underlying_type);
14410
14411 /* Compute the minimum and maximum values for the type.
14412
14413 [dcl.enum]
14414
14415 For an enumeration where emin is the smallest enumerator and emax
14416 is the largest, the values of the enumeration are the values of the
14417 underlying type in the range bmin to bmax, where bmin and bmax are,
14418 respectively, the smallest and largest values of the smallest bit-
14419 field that can store emin and emax. */
14420
14421 /* The middle-end currently assumes that types with TYPE_PRECISION
14422 narrower than their underlying type are suitably zero or sign
14423 extended to fill their mode. Similarly, it assumes that the front
14424 end assures that a value of a particular type must be within
14425 TYPE_MIN_VALUE and TYPE_MAX_VALUE.
14426
14427 We used to set these fields based on bmin and bmax, but that led
14428 to invalid assumptions like optimizing away bounds checking. So
14429 now we just set the TYPE_PRECISION, TYPE_MIN_VALUE, and
14430 TYPE_MAX_VALUE to the values for the mode above and only restrict
14431 the ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE for the benefit of diagnostics. */
14432 ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype)
14433 = build_distinct_type_copy (underlying_type);
14434 TYPE_PRECISION (ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype)) = precision;
14435 set_min_and_max_values_for_integral_type
14436 (ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype), precision, sgn);
14437
14438 /* If -fstrict-enums, still constrain TYPE_MIN/MAX_VALUE. */
14439 if (flag_strict_enums)
14440 set_min_and_max_values_for_integral_type (enumtype, precision, sgn);
14441 }
14442 else
14443 underlying_type = ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype);
14444
14445 /* Convert each of the enumerators to the type of the underlying
14446 type of the enumeration. */
14447 for (values = TYPE_VALUES (enumtype); values; values = TREE_CHAIN (values))
14448 {
14449 location_t saved_location;
14450
14451 decl = TREE_VALUE (values);
14452 saved_location = input_location;
14453 input_location = DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl);
14454 if (fixed_underlying_type_p)
14455 /* If the enumeration type has a fixed underlying type, we
14456 already checked all of the enumerator values. */
14457 value = DECL_INITIAL (decl);
14458 else
14459 value = perform_implicit_conversion (underlying_type,
14460 DECL_INITIAL (decl),
14461 tf_warning_or_error);
14462 input_location = saved_location;
14463
14464 /* Do not clobber shared ints. */
14465 if (value != error_mark_node)
14466 {
14467 value = copy_node (value);
14468
14469 TREE_TYPE (value) = enumtype;
14470 }
14471 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = value;
14472 }
14473
14474 /* Fix up all variant types of this enum type. */
14475 for (t = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (enumtype); t; t = TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT (t))
14476 TYPE_VALUES (t) = TYPE_VALUES (enumtype);
14477
14478 if (at_class_scope_p ()
14479 && COMPLETE_TYPE_P (current_class_type)
14480 && UNSCOPED_ENUM_P (enumtype))
14481 {
14482 insert_late_enum_def_into_classtype_sorted_fields (enumtype,
14483 current_class_type);
14484 fixup_type_variants (current_class_type);
14485 }
14486
14487 /* Finish debugging output for this type. */
14488 rest_of_type_compilation (enumtype, namespace_bindings_p ());
14489
14490 /* Each enumerator now has the type of its enumeration. Clear the cache
14491 so that this change in types doesn't confuse us later on. */
14492 clear_cv_and_fold_caches ();
14493}
14494
14495/* Finishes the enum type. This is called only the first time an
14496 enumeration is seen, be it opaque or odinary.
14497 ENUMTYPE is the type object. */
14498
14499void
14500finish_enum (tree enumtype)
14501{
14502 if (processing_template_decl)
14503 {
14504 if (at_function_scope_p ())
14505 add_stmt (build_min (TAG_DEFN, enumtype));
14506 return;
14507 }
14508
14509 /* If this is a forward declaration, there should not be any variants,
14510 though we can get a variant in the middle of an enum-specifier with
14511 wacky code like 'enum E { e = sizeof(const E*) };' */
14512 gcc_assert (enumtype == TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (enumtype)
14513 && (TYPE_VALUES (enumtype)
14514 || !TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT (enumtype)));
14515}
14516
14517/* Build and install a CONST_DECL for an enumeration constant of the
14518 enumeration type ENUMTYPE whose NAME and VALUE (if any) are provided.
14519 Apply ATTRIBUTES if available. LOC is the location of NAME.
14520 Assignment of sequential values by default is handled here. */
14521
14522void
14523build_enumerator (tree name, tree value, tree enumtype, tree attributes,
14524 location_t loc)
14525{
14526 tree decl;
14527 tree context;
14528 tree type;
14529
14530 /* scalar_constant_value will pull out this expression, so make sure
14531 it's folded as appropriate. */
14532 if (processing_template_decl)
14533 value = fold_non_dependent_expr (value);
14534
14535 /* If the VALUE was erroneous, pretend it wasn't there; that will
14536 result in the enum being assigned the next value in sequence. */
14537 if (value == error_mark_node)
14538 value = NULL_TREE;
14539
14540 /* Remove no-op casts from the value. */
14541 if (value)
14542 STRIP_TYPE_NOPS (value);
14543
14544 if (! processing_template_decl)
14545 {
14546 /* Validate and default VALUE. */
14547 if (value != NULL_TREE)
14548 {
14549 if (!ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype))
14550 {
14551 tree tmp_value = build_expr_type_conversion (WANT_INT | WANT_ENUM,
14552 value, true);
14553 if (tmp_value)
14554 value = tmp_value;
14555 }
14556 else if (! INTEGRAL_OR_UNSCOPED_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P
14557 (TREE_TYPE (value)))
14558 value = perform_implicit_conversion_flags
14559 (ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype), value, tf_warning_or_error,
14560 LOOKUP_IMPLICIT | LOOKUP_NO_NARROWING);
14561
14562 if (value == error_mark_node)
14563 value = NULL_TREE;
14564
14565 if (value != NULL_TREE)
14566 {
14567 if (! INTEGRAL_OR_UNSCOPED_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P
14568 (TREE_TYPE (value)))
14569 {
14570 error ("enumerator value for %qD must have integral or "
14571 "unscoped enumeration type", name);
14572 value = NULL_TREE;
14573 }
14574 else
14575 {
14576 value = cxx_constant_value (value);
14577
14578 if (TREE_CODE (value) != INTEGER_CST)
14579 {
14580 error ("enumerator value for %qD is not an integer "
14581 "constant", name);
14582 value = NULL_TREE;
14583 }
14584 }
14585 }
14586 }
14587
14588 /* Default based on previous value. */
14589 if (value == NULL_TREE)
14590 {
14591 if (TYPE_VALUES (enumtype))
14592 {
14593 tree prev_value;
14594 bool overflowed;
14595
14596 /* C++03 7.2/4: If no initializer is specified for the first
14597 enumerator, the type is an unspecified integral
14598 type. Otherwise the type is the same as the type of the
14599 initializing value of the preceding enumerator unless the
14600 incremented value is not representable in that type, in
14601 which case the type is an unspecified integral type
14602 sufficient to contain the incremented value. */
14603 prev_value = DECL_INITIAL (TREE_VALUE (TYPE_VALUES (enumtype)));
14604 if (error_operand_p (prev_value))
14605 value = error_mark_node;
14606 else
14607 {
14608 tree type = TREE_TYPE (prev_value);
14609 signop sgn = TYPE_SIGN (type);
14610 widest_int wi = wi::add (wi::to_widest (prev_value), 1, sgn,
14611 &overflowed);
14612 if (!overflowed)
14613 {
14614 bool pos = !wi::neg_p (wi, sgn);
14615 if (!wi::fits_to_tree_p (wi, type))
14616 {
14617 unsigned int itk;
14618 for (itk = itk_int; itk != itk_none; itk++)
14619 {
14620 type = integer_types[itk];
14621 if (type != NULL_TREE
14622 && (pos || !TYPE_UNSIGNED (type))
14623 && wi::fits_to_tree_p (wi, type))
14624 break;
14625 }
14626 if (type && cxx_dialect < cxx11
14627 && itk > itk_unsigned_long)
14628 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wlong_long,
14629 pos ? G_("\
14630incremented enumerator value is too large for %<unsigned long%>") : G_("\
14631incremented enumerator value is too large for %<long%>"));
14632 }
14633 if (type == NULL_TREE)
14634 overflowed = true;
14635 else
14636 value = wide_int_to_tree (type, wi);
14637 }
14638
14639 if (overflowed)
14640 {
14641 error ("overflow in enumeration values at %qD", name);
14642 value = error_mark_node;
14643 }
14644 }
14645 }
14646 else
14647 value = integer_zero_node;
14648 }
14649
14650 /* Remove no-op casts from the value. */
14651 STRIP_TYPE_NOPS (value);
14652
14653 /* If the underlying type of the enum is fixed, check whether
14654 the enumerator values fits in the underlying type. If it
14655 does not fit, the program is ill-formed [C++0x dcl.enum]. */
