14656 if (ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype)
14657 && value
14658 && TREE_CODE (value) == INTEGER_CST)
14659 {
14660 if (!int_fits_type_p (value, ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype)))
14661 error ("enumerator value %E is outside the range of underlying "
14662 "type %<%T%>", value, ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype));
14663
14664 /* Convert the value to the appropriate type. */
14665 value = fold_convert (ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (enumtype), value);
14666 }
14667 }
14668
14669 /* C++ associates enums with global, function, or class declarations. */
14670 context = current_scope ();
14671
14672 /* Build the actual enumeration constant. Note that the enumeration
14673 constants have the underlying type of the enum (if it is fixed)
14674 or the type of their initializer (if the underlying type of the
14675 enum is not fixed):
14676
14677 [ C++0x dcl.enum ]
14678
14679 If the underlying type is fixed, the type of each enumerator
14680 prior to the closing brace is the underlying type; if the
14681 initializing value of an enumerator cannot be represented by
14682 the underlying type, the program is ill-formed. If the
14683 underlying type is not fixed, the type of each enumerator is
14684 the type of its initializing value.
14685
14686 If the underlying type is not fixed, it will be computed by
14687 finish_enum and we will reset the type of this enumerator. Of
14688 course, if we're processing a template, there may be no value. */
14689 type = value ? TREE_TYPE (value) : NULL_TREE;
14690
14691 decl = build_decl (loc, CONST_DECL, name, type);
14692
14693 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = enumtype;
14694 TREE_CONSTANT (decl) = 1;
14695 TREE_READONLY (decl) = 1;
14696 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = value;
14697
14698 if (attributes)
14699 cplus_decl_attributes (&decl, attributes, 0);
14700
14701 if (context && context == current_class_type && !SCOPED_ENUM_P (enumtype))
14702 {
14703 /* In something like `struct S { enum E { i = 7 }; };' we put `i'
14704 on the TYPE_FIELDS list for `S'. (That's so that you can say
14705 things like `S::i' later.) */
14706
14707 /* The enumerator may be getting declared outside of its enclosing
14708 class, like so:
14709
14710 class S { public: enum E : int; }; enum S::E : int { i = 7; };
14711
14712 For which case we need to make sure that the access of `S::i'
14713 matches the access of `S::E'. */
14714 tree saved_cas = current_access_specifier;
14715 if (TREE_PRIVATE (TYPE_NAME (enumtype)))
14716 current_access_specifier = access_private_node;
14717 else if (TREE_PROTECTED (TYPE_NAME (enumtype)))
14718 current_access_specifier = access_protected_node;
14719 else
14720 current_access_specifier = access_public_node;
14721
14722 finish_member_declaration (decl);
14723
14724 current_access_specifier = saved_cas;
14725 }
14726 else
14727 pushdecl (decl);
14728
14729 /* Add this enumeration constant to the list for this type. */
14730 TYPE_VALUES (enumtype) = tree_cons (name, decl, TYPE_VALUES (enumtype));
14731}
14732
14733/* Look for an enumerator with the given NAME within the enumeration
14734 type ENUMTYPE. This routine is used primarily for qualified name
14735 lookup into an enumerator in C++0x, e.g.,
14736
14737 enum class Color { Red, Green, Blue };
14738
14739 Color color = Color::Red;
14740
14741 Returns the value corresponding to the enumerator, or
14742 NULL_TREE if no such enumerator was found. */
14743tree
14744lookup_enumerator (tree enumtype, tree name)
14745{
14746 tree e;
14747 gcc_assert (enumtype && TREE_CODE (enumtype) == ENUMERAL_TYPE);
14748
14749 e = purpose_member (name, TYPE_VALUES (enumtype));
14750 return e? TREE_VALUE (e) : NULL_TREE;
14751}
14752
14753
14754/* We're defining DECL. Make sure that its type is OK. */
14755
14756static void
14757check_function_type (tree decl, tree current_function_parms)
14758{
14759 tree fntype = TREE_TYPE (decl);
14760 tree return_type = complete_type (TREE_TYPE (fntype));
14761
14762 /* In a function definition, arg types must be complete. */
14763 require_complete_types_for_parms (current_function_parms);
14764
14765 if (dependent_type_p (return_type)
14766 || type_uses_auto (return_type))
14767 return;
14768 if (!COMPLETE_OR_VOID_TYPE_P (return_type))
14769 {
14770 tree args = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (fntype);
14771
14772 error ("return type %q#T is incomplete", return_type);
14773
14774 /* Make it return void instead. */
14775 if (TREE_CODE (fntype) == METHOD_TYPE)
14776 fntype = build_method_type_directly (TREE_TYPE (TREE_VALUE (args)),
14777 void_type_node,
14778 TREE_CHAIN (args));
14779 else
14780 fntype = build_function_type (void_type_node, args);
14781 fntype
14782 = build_exception_variant (fntype,
14783 TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (TREE_TYPE (decl)));
14784 fntype = (cp_build_type_attribute_variant
14785 (fntype, TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (TREE_TYPE (decl))));
14786 TREE_TYPE (decl) = fntype;
14787 }
14788 else
14789 abstract_virtuals_error (decl, TREE_TYPE (fntype));
14790}
14791
14792/* True iff FN is an implicitly-defined default constructor. */
14793
14794static bool
14795implicit_default_ctor_p (tree fn)
14796{
14797 return (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (fn)
14798 && !user_provided_p (fn)
14799 && sufficient_parms_p (FUNCTION_FIRST_USER_PARMTYPE (fn)));
14800}
14801
14802/* Clobber the contents of *this to let the back end know that the object
14803 storage is dead when we enter the constructor or leave the destructor. */
14804
14805static tree
14806build_clobber_this ()
14807{
14808 /* Clobbering an empty base is pointless, and harmful if its one byte
14809 TYPE_SIZE overlays real data. */
14810 if (is_empty_class (current_class_type))
14811 return void_node;
14812
14813 /* If we have virtual bases, clobber the whole object, but only if we're in
14814 charge. If we don't have virtual bases, clobber the as-base type so we
14815 don't mess with tail padding. */
14816 bool vbases = CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES (current_class_type);
14817
14818 tree ctype = current_class_type;
14819 if (!vbases)
14820 ctype = CLASSTYPE_AS_BASE (ctype);
14821
14822 tree clobber = build_constructor (ctype, NULL);
14823 TREE_THIS_VOLATILE (clobber) = true;
14824
14825 tree thisref = current_class_ref;
14826 if (ctype != current_class_type)
14827 {
14828 thisref = build_nop (build_reference_type (ctype), current_class_ptr);
14829 thisref = convert_from_reference (thisref);
14830 }
14831
14832 tree exprstmt = build2 (MODIFY_EXPR, void_type_node, thisref, clobber);
14833 if (vbases)
14834 exprstmt = build_if_in_charge (exprstmt);
14835
14836 return exprstmt;
14837}
14838
14839/* Create the FUNCTION_DECL for a function definition.
14840 DECLSPECS and DECLARATOR are the parts of the declaration;
14841 they describe the function's name and the type it returns,
14842 but twisted together in a fashion that parallels the syntax of C.
14843
14844 FLAGS is a bitwise or of SF_PRE_PARSED (indicating that the
14845 DECLARATOR is really the DECL for the function we are about to
14846 process and that DECLSPECS should be ignored), SF_INCLASS_INLINE
14847 indicating that the function is an inline defined in-class.
14848
14849 This function creates a binding context for the function body
14850 as well as setting up the FUNCTION_DECL in current_function_decl.
14851
14852 For C++, we must first check whether that datum makes any sense.
14853 For example, "class A local_a(1,2);" means that variable local_a
14854 is an aggregate of type A, which should have a constructor
14855 applied to it with the argument list [1, 2].
14856
14857 On entry, DECL_INITIAL (decl1) should be NULL_TREE or error_mark_node,
14858 or may be a BLOCK if the function has been defined previously
14859 in this translation unit. On exit, DECL_INITIAL (decl1) will be
14860 error_mark_node if the function has never been defined, or
14861 a BLOCK if the function has been defined somewhere. */
14862
14863bool
14864start_preparsed_function (tree decl1, tree attrs, int flags)
14865{
14866 tree ctype = NULL_TREE;
14867 tree fntype;
14868 tree restype;
14869 int doing_friend = 0;
14870 cp_binding_level *bl;
14871 tree current_function_parms;
14872 struct c_fileinfo *finfo
14873 = get_fileinfo (LOCATION_FILE (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl1)));
14874 bool honor_interface;
14875
14876 /* Sanity check. */
14877 gcc_assert (VOID_TYPE_P (TREE_VALUE (void_list_node)));
14878 gcc_assert (TREE_CHAIN (void_list_node) == NULL_TREE);
14879
14880 fntype = TREE_TYPE (decl1);
14881 if (TREE_CODE (fntype) == METHOD_TYPE)
14882 ctype = TYPE_METHOD_BASETYPE (fntype);
14883
14884 /* ISO C++ 11.4/5. A friend function defined in a class is in
14885 the (lexical) scope of the class in which it is defined. */
14886 if (!ctype && DECL_FRIEND_P (decl1))
14887 {
14888 ctype = DECL_FRIEND_CONTEXT (decl1);
14889
14890 /* CTYPE could be null here if we're dealing with a template;
14891 for example, `inline friend float foo()' inside a template
14892 will have no CTYPE set. */
14893 if (ctype && TREE_CODE (ctype) != RECORD_TYPE)
14894 ctype = NULL_TREE;
14895 else
14896 doing_friend = 1;
14897 }
14898
14899 if (DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl1)
14900 && lookup_attribute ("noinline", attrs))
14901 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl1), 0,
14902 "inline function %qD given attribute noinline", decl1);
14903
14904 /* Handle gnu_inline attribute. */
14905 if (GNU_INLINE_P (decl1))
14906 {
14907 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl1) = 1;
14908 DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (decl1) = 0;
14909 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl1) = 1;
14910 DECL_DISREGARD_INLINE_LIMITS (decl1) = 1;
14911 }
14912
14913 if (DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_CONSTRUCTOR_P (decl1))
14914 /* This is a constructor, we must ensure that any default args
14915 introduced by this definition are propagated to the clones
14916 now. The clones are used directly in overload resolution. */
14917 adjust_clone_args (decl1);
14918
14919 /* Sometimes we don't notice that a function is a static member, and
14920 build a METHOD_TYPE for it. Fix that up now. */
14921 gcc_assert (!(ctype != NULL_TREE && DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (decl1)
14922 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (decl1)) == METHOD_TYPE));
14923
14924 /* Set up current_class_type, and enter the scope of the class, if
14925 appropriate. */
14926 if (ctype)
14927 push_nested_class (ctype);
14928 else if (DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (decl1))
14929 push_nested_class (DECL_CONTEXT (decl1));
14930
14931 /* Now that we have entered the scope of the class, we must restore
14932 the bindings for any template parameters surrounding DECL1, if it
14933 is an inline member template. (Order is important; consider the
14934 case where a template parameter has the same name as a field of
14935 the class.) It is not until after this point that
14936 PROCESSING_TEMPLATE_DECL is guaranteed to be set up correctly. */
14937 if (flags & SF_INCLASS_INLINE)
14938 maybe_begin_member_template_processing (decl1);
14939
14940 /* Effective C++ rule 15. */
14941 if (warn_ecpp
14942 && DECL_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_P (decl1) == NOP_EXPR
14943 && VOID_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (fntype)))
14944 warning (OPT_Weffc__, "%<operator=%> should return a reference to %<*this%>");
14945
14946 /* Make the init_value nonzero so pushdecl knows this is not tentative.
14947 error_mark_node is replaced below (in poplevel) with the BLOCK. */
14948 if (!DECL_INITIAL (decl1))
14949 DECL_INITIAL (decl1) = error_mark_node;
14950
14951 /* This function exists in static storage.
14952 (This does not mean `static' in the C sense!) */
14953 TREE_STATIC (decl1) = 1;
14954
14955 /* We must call push_template_decl after current_class_type is set
14956 up. (If we are processing inline definitions after exiting a
14957 class scope, current_class_type will be NULL_TREE until set above
14958 by push_nested_class.) */
14959 if (processing_template_decl)
14960 {
14961 tree newdecl1 = push_template_decl (decl1);
14962 if (newdecl1 == error_mark_node)
14963 {
14964 if (ctype || DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (decl1))
14965 pop_nested_class ();
14966 return false;
14967 }
14968 decl1 = newdecl1;
14969 }
14970
14971 /* We are now in the scope of the function being defined. */
14972 current_function_decl = decl1;
14973
14974 /* Save the parm names or decls from this function's declarator
14975 where store_parm_decls will find them. */
14976 current_function_parms = DECL_ARGUMENTS (decl1);
14977
14978 /* Make sure the parameter and return types are reasonable. When
14979 you declare a function, these types can be incomplete, but they
14980 must be complete when you define the function. */
14981 check_function_type (decl1, current_function_parms);
14982
14983 /* Build the return declaration for the function. */
14984 restype = TREE_TYPE (fntype);
14985
14986 if (DECL_RESULT (decl1) == NULL_TREE)
14987 {
14988 tree resdecl;
14989
14990 resdecl = build_decl (input_location, RESULT_DECL, 0, restype);
14991 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (resdecl) = 1;
14992 DECL_IGNORED_P (resdecl) = 1;
14993 DECL_RESULT (decl1) = resdecl;
14994
14995 cp_apply_type_quals_to_decl (cp_type_quals (restype), resdecl);
14996 }
14997
14998 /* Let the user know we're compiling this function. */
14999 announce_function (decl1);
15000
15001 /* Record the decl so that the function name is defined.
15002 If we already have a decl for this name, and it is a FUNCTION_DECL,
15003 use the old decl. */
15004 if (!processing_template_decl && !(flags & SF_PRE_PARSED))
15005 {
15006 /* A specialization is not used to guide overload resolution. */
15007 if (!DECL_FUNCTION_MEMBER_P (decl1)
15008 && !(DECL_USE_TEMPLATE (decl1) &&
15009 PRIMARY_TEMPLATE_P (DECL_TI_TEMPLATE (decl1))))
15010 {
15011 tree olddecl = pushdecl (decl1);
15012
15013 if (olddecl == error_mark_node)
15014 /* If something went wrong when registering the declaration,
15015 use DECL1; we have to have a FUNCTION_DECL to use when
15016 parsing the body of the function. */
15017 ;
15018 else
15019 {
15020 /* Otherwise, OLDDECL is either a previous declaration
15021 of the same function or DECL1 itself. */
15022
15023 if (warn_missing_declarations
15024 && olddecl == decl1
15025 && !DECL_MAIN_P (decl1)
15026 && TREE_PUBLIC (decl1)
15027 && !DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl1))
15028 {
15029 tree context;
15030
15031 /* Check whether DECL1 is in an anonymous
15032 namespace. */
15033 for (context = DECL_CONTEXT (decl1);
15034 context;
15035 context = DECL_CONTEXT (context))
15036 {
15037 if (TREE_CODE (context) == NAMESPACE_DECL
15038 && DECL_NAME (context) == NULL_TREE)
15039 break;
15040 }
15041
15042 if (context == NULL)
15043 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl1),
15044 OPT_Wmissing_declarations,
15045 "no previous declaration for %qD", decl1);
15046 }
15047
15048 decl1 = olddecl;
15049 }
15050 }
15051 else
15052 {
15053 /* We need to set the DECL_CONTEXT. */
15054 if (!DECL_CONTEXT (decl1) && DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (decl1))
15055 DECL_CONTEXT (decl1) = DECL_CONTEXT (DECL_TI_TEMPLATE (decl1));
15056 }
15057 fntype = TREE_TYPE (decl1);
15058 restype = TREE_TYPE (fntype);
15059
15060 /* If #pragma weak applies, mark the decl appropriately now.
15061 The pragma only applies to global functions. Because
15062 determining whether or not the #pragma applies involves
15063 computing the mangled name for the declaration, we cannot
15064 apply the pragma until after we have merged this declaration
15065 with any previous declarations; if the original declaration
15066 has a linkage specification, that specification applies to
15067 the definition as well, and may affect the mangled name. */
15068 if (DECL_FILE_SCOPE_P (decl1))
15069 maybe_apply_pragma_weak (decl1);
15070 }
15071
15072 /* Reset this in case the call to pushdecl changed it. */
15073 current_function_decl = decl1;
15074
15075 gcc_assert (DECL_INITIAL (decl1));
15076
15077 /* This function may already have been parsed, in which case just
15078 return; our caller will skip over the body without parsing. */
15079 if (DECL_INITIAL (decl1) != error_mark_node)
15080 return true;
15081
15082 /* Initialize RTL machinery. We cannot do this until
15083 CURRENT_FUNCTION_DECL and DECL_RESULT are set up. We do this
15084 even when processing a template; this is how we get
15085 CFUN set up, and our per-function variables initialized.
15086 FIXME factor out the non-RTL stuff. */
15087 bl = current_binding_level;
15088 allocate_struct_function (decl1, processing_template_decl);
15089
15090 /* Initialize the language data structures. Whenever we start
15091 a new function, we destroy temporaries in the usual way. */
15092 cfun->language = ggc_cleared_alloc<language_function> ();
15093 current_stmt_tree ()->stmts_are_full_exprs_p = 1;
15094 current_binding_level = bl;
15095
15096 if (!processing_template_decl && type_uses_auto (restype))
15097 {
15098 FNDECL_USED_AUTO (decl1) = true;
15099 current_function_auto_return_pattern = restype;
15100 }
15101
15102 /* Start the statement-tree, start the tree now. */
15103 DECL_SAVED_TREE (decl1) = push_stmt_list ();
15104
15105 /* If we are (erroneously) defining a function that we have already
15106 defined before, wipe out what we knew before. */
15107 if (!DECL_PENDING_INLINE_P (decl1))
15108 DECL_SAVED_FUNCTION_DATA (decl1) = NULL;
15109
15110 if (ctype && !doing_friend && !DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (decl1))
15111 {
15112 /* We know that this was set up by `grokclassfn'. We do not
15113 wait until `store_parm_decls', since evil parse errors may
15114 never get us to that point. Here we keep the consistency
15115 between `current_class_type' and `current_class_ptr'. */
15116 tree t = DECL_ARGUMENTS (decl1);
15117
15118 gcc_assert (t != NULL_TREE && TREE_CODE (t) == PARM_DECL);
15119 gcc_assert (TYPE_PTR_P (TREE_TYPE (t)));
15120
15121 cp_function_chain->x_current_class_ref
15122 = cp_build_indirect_ref (t, RO_NULL, tf_warning_or_error);
15123 /* Set this second to avoid shortcut in cp_build_indirect_ref. */
15124 cp_function_chain->x_current_class_ptr = t;
15125
15126 /* Constructors and destructors need to know whether they're "in
15127 charge" of initializing virtual base classes. */
15128 t = DECL_CHAIN (t);
15129 if (DECL_HAS_IN_CHARGE_PARM_P (decl1))
15130 {
15131 current_in_charge_parm = t;
15132 t = DECL_CHAIN (t);
15133 }
15134 if (DECL_HAS_VTT_PARM_P (decl1))
15135 {
15136 gcc_assert (DECL_NAME (t) == vtt_parm_identifier);
15137 current_vtt_parm = t;
15138 }
15139 }
15140
15141 honor_interface = (!DECL_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATION (decl1)
15142 /* Implicitly-defined methods (like the
15143 destructor for a class in which no destructor
15144 is explicitly declared) must not be defined
15145 until their definition is needed. So, we
15146 ignore interface specifications for
15147 compiler-generated functions. */
15148 && !DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl1));
15149
15150 if (processing_template_decl)
15151 /* Don't mess with interface flags. */;
15152 else if (DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl1))
15153 {
15154 tree ctx = decl_function_context (decl1);
15155
15156 if (DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (decl1))
15157 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl1) = 0;
15158
15159 if (ctx != NULL_TREE && vague_linkage_p (ctx))
15160 /* This is a function in a local class in an extern inline
15161 or template function. */
15162 comdat_linkage (decl1);
15163 }
15164 /* If this function belongs to an interface, it is public.
15165 If it belongs to someone else's interface, it is also external.
15166 This only affects inlines and template instantiations. */
15167 else if (!finfo->interface_unknown && honor_interface)
15168 {
15169 if (DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl1)
15170 || DECL_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATION (decl1))
15171 {
15172 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl1)
15173 = (finfo->interface_only
15174 || (DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl1)
15175 && ! flag_implement_inlines
15176 && !DECL_VINDEX (decl1)));
15177
15178 /* For WIN32 we also want to put these in linkonce sections. */
15179 maybe_make_one_only (decl1);
15180 }
15181 else
15182 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl1) = 0;
15183 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl1) = 1;
15184 /* If this function is in an interface implemented in this file,
15185 make sure that the back end knows to emit this function
15186 here. */
15187 if (!DECL_EXTERNAL (decl1))
15188 mark_needed (decl1);
15189 }
15190 else if (finfo->interface_unknown && finfo->interface_only
15191 && honor_interface)
15192 {
15193 /* If MULTIPLE_SYMBOL_SPACES is defined and we saw a #pragma
15194 interface, we will have both finfo->interface_unknown and
15195 finfo->interface_only set. In that case, we don't want to
15196 use the normal heuristics because someone will supply a
15197 #pragma implementation elsewhere, and deducing it here would
15198 produce a conflict. */
15199 comdat_linkage (decl1);
15200 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl1) = 0;
15201 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl1) = 1;
15202 DECL_DEFER_OUTPUT (decl1) = 1;
15203 }
15204 else
15205 {
15206 /* This is a definition, not a reference.
15207 So clear DECL_EXTERNAL, unless this is a GNU extern inline. */
15208 if (!GNU_INLINE_P (decl1))
15209 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl1) = 0;
15210
15211 if ((DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl1)
15212 || DECL_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATION (decl1))
15213 && ! DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl1))
15214 DECL_DEFER_OUTPUT (decl1) = 1;
15215 else
15216 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl1) = 1;
15217 }
15218
15219 /* Determine the ELF visibility attribute for the function. We must not
15220 do this before calling "pushdecl", as we must allow "duplicate_decls"
15221 to merge any attributes appropriately. We also need to wait until
15222 linkage is set. */
15223 if (!DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (decl1))
15224 determine_visibility (decl1);
15225
15226 if (!processing_template_decl)
15227 maybe_instantiate_noexcept (decl1);
15228
15229 begin_scope (sk_function_parms, decl1);
15230
15231 ++function_depth;
15232
15233 if (DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (decl1)
15234 || (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (decl1)
15235 && targetm.cxx.cdtor_returns_this ()))
15236 cdtor_label = create_artificial_label (input_location);
15237
15238 start_fname_decls ();
15239
15240 store_parm_decls (current_function_parms);
15241
15242 if (!processing_template_decl
15243 && (flag_lifetime_dse > 1)
15244 && DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (decl1)
15245 && !DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (decl1)
15246 /* Clobbering an empty base is harmful if it overlays real data. */
15247 && !is_empty_class (current_class_type)
15248 /* We can't clobber safely for an implicitly-defined default constructor
15249 because part of the initialization might happen before we enter the
15250 constructor, via AGGR_INIT_ZERO_FIRST (c++/68006). */
15251 && !implicit_default_ctor_p (decl1))
15252 finish_expr_stmt (build_clobber_this ());
15253
15254 if (!processing_template_decl
15255 && DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (decl1)
15256 && (flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_VPTR)
15257 && !DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (decl1)
15258 && !implicit_default_ctor_p (decl1))
15259 cp_ubsan_maybe_initialize_vtbl_ptrs (current_class_ptr);
15260
15261 return true;
15262}
15263
15264
15265/* Like start_preparsed_function, except that instead of a
15266 FUNCTION_DECL, this function takes DECLSPECS and DECLARATOR.
15267
15268 Returns true on success. If the DECLARATOR is not suitable
15269 for a function, we return false, which tells the parser to
15270 skip the entire function. */
15271
15272bool
15273start_function (cp_decl_specifier_seq *declspecs,
15274 const cp_declarator *declarator,
15275 tree attrs)
15276{
15277 tree decl1;
15278
15279 decl1 = grokdeclarator (declarator, declspecs, FUNCDEF, 1, &attrs);
15280 invoke_plugin_callbacks (PLUGIN_START_PARSE_FUNCTION, decl1);
15281 if (decl1 == error_mark_node)
15282 return false;
15283 /* If the declarator is not suitable for a function definition,
15284 cause a syntax error. */
15285 if (decl1 == NULL_TREE || TREE_CODE (decl1) != FUNCTION_DECL)
15286 {
15287 error ("invalid function declaration");
15288 return false;
15289 }
15290
15291 if (DECL_MAIN_P (decl1))
15292 /* main must return int. grokfndecl should have corrected it
15293 (and issued a diagnostic) if the user got it wrong. */
15294 gcc_assert (same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (decl1)),
15295 integer_type_node));
15296
15297 return start_preparsed_function (decl1, attrs, /*flags=*/SF_DEFAULT);
15298}
15299
15300/* Returns true iff an EH_SPEC_BLOCK should be created in the body of
15301 FN. */
15302
15303static bool
15304use_eh_spec_block (tree fn)
15305{
15306 return (flag_exceptions && flag_enforce_eh_specs
15307 && !processing_template_decl
15308 && !type_throw_all_p (TREE_TYPE (fn))
15309 /* We insert the EH_SPEC_BLOCK only in the original
15310 function; then, it is copied automatically to the
15311 clones. */
15312 && !DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (fn)
15313 /* Implicitly-generated constructors and destructors have
15314 exception specifications. However, those specifications
15315 are the union of the possible exceptions specified by the
15316 constructors/destructors for bases and members, so no
15317 unallowed exception will ever reach this function. By
15318 not creating the EH_SPEC_BLOCK we save a little memory,
15319 and we avoid spurious warnings about unreachable
15320 code. */
15321 && !DECL_DEFAULTED_FN (fn));
15322}
15323
15324/* Store the parameter declarations into the current function declaration.
15325 This is called after parsing the parameter declarations, before
15326 digesting the body of the function.
15327
15328 Also install to binding contour return value identifier, if any. */
15329
15330static void
15331store_parm_decls (tree current_function_parms)
15332{
15333 tree fndecl = current_function_decl;
15334 tree parm;
15335
15336 /* This is a chain of any other decls that came in among the parm
15337 declarations. If a parm is declared with enum {foo, bar} x;
15338 then CONST_DECLs for foo and bar are put here. */
15339 tree nonparms = NULL_TREE;
15340
15341 if (current_function_parms)
15342 {
15343 /* This case is when the function was defined with an ANSI prototype.
15344 The parms already have decls, so we need not do anything here
15345 except record them as in effect
15346 and complain if any redundant old-style parm decls were written. */
15347
15348 tree specparms = current_function_parms;
15349 tree next;
15350
15351 /* Must clear this because it might contain TYPE_DECLs declared
15352 at class level. */
15353 current_binding_level->names = NULL;
15354
15355 /* If we're doing semantic analysis, then we'll call pushdecl
15356 for each of these. We must do them in reverse order so that
15357 they end in the correct forward order. */
15358 specparms = nreverse (specparms);
15359
15360 for (parm = specparms; parm; parm = next)
15361 {
15362 next = DECL_CHAIN (parm);
15363 if (TREE_CODE (parm) == PARM_DECL)
15364 pushdecl (parm);
15365 else
15366 {
15367 /* If we find an enum constant or a type tag,
15368 put it aside for the moment. */
15369 TREE_CHAIN (parm) = NULL_TREE;
15370 nonparms = chainon (nonparms, parm);
15371 }
15372 }
15373
15374 /* Get the decls in their original chain order and record in the
15375 function. This is all and only the PARM_DECLs that were
15376 pushed into scope by the loop above. */
15377 DECL_ARGUMENTS (fndecl) = getdecls ();
15378 }
15379 else
15380 DECL_ARGUMENTS (fndecl) = NULL_TREE;
15381
15382 /* Now store the final chain of decls for the arguments
15383 as the decl-chain of the current lexical scope.
15384 Put the enumerators in as well, at the front so that
15385 DECL_ARGUMENTS is not modified. */
15386 current_binding_level->names = chainon (nonparms, DECL_ARGUMENTS (fndecl));
15387
15388 if (use_eh_spec_block (current_function_decl))
15389 current_eh_spec_block = begin_eh_spec_block ();
15390}
15391
15392
15393/* We have finished doing semantic analysis on DECL, but have not yet
15394 generated RTL for its body. Save away our current state, so that
15395 when we want to generate RTL later we know what to do. */
15396
15397static void
15398save_function_data (tree decl)
15399{
15400 struct language_function *f;
15401
15402 /* Save the language-specific per-function data so that we can
15403 get it back when we really expand this function. */
15404 gcc_assert (!DECL_PENDING_INLINE_P (decl));
15405
15406 /* Make a copy. */
15407 f = ggc_alloc<language_function> ();
15408 memcpy (f, cp_function_chain, sizeof (struct language_function));
15409 DECL_SAVED_FUNCTION_DATA (decl) = f;
15410
15411 /* Clear out the bits we don't need. */
15412 f->base.x_stmt_tree.x_cur_stmt_list = NULL;
15413 f->bindings = NULL;
15414 f->x_local_names = NULL;
15415 f->base.local_typedefs = NULL;
15416}
15417
15418
15419/* Set the return value of the constructor (if present). */
15420
15421static void
15422finish_constructor_body (void)
15423{
15424 tree val;
15425 tree exprstmt;
15426
15427 if (targetm.cxx.cdtor_returns_this ())
15428 {
15429 /* Any return from a constructor will end up here. */
15430 add_stmt (build_stmt (input_location, LABEL_EXPR, cdtor_label));
15431
15432 val = DECL_ARGUMENTS (current_function_decl);
15433 val = build2 (MODIFY_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (val),
15434 DECL_RESULT (current_function_decl), val);
15435 /* Return the address of the object. */
15436 exprstmt = build_stmt (input_location, RETURN_EXPR, val);
15437 add_stmt (exprstmt);
15438 }
15439}
15440
15441/* Do all the processing for the beginning of a destructor; set up the
15442 vtable pointers and cleanups for bases and members. */
15443
15444static void
15445begin_destructor_body (void)
15446{
15447 tree compound_stmt;
15448
15449 /* If the CURRENT_CLASS_TYPE is incomplete, we will have already
15450 issued an error message. We still want to try to process the
15451 body of the function, but initialize_vtbl_ptrs will crash if
15452 TYPE_BINFO is NULL. */
15453 if (COMPLETE_TYPE_P (current_class_type))
15454 {
15455 compound_stmt = begin_compound_stmt (0);
15456 /* Make all virtual function table pointers in non-virtual base
15457 classes point to CURRENT_CLASS_TYPE's virtual function
15458 tables. */
15459 initialize_vtbl_ptrs (current_class_ptr);
15460 finish_compound_stmt (compound_stmt);
15461
15462 if (flag_lifetime_dse
15463 /* Clobbering an empty base is harmful if it overlays real data. */
15464 && !is_empty_class (current_class_type))
15465 finish_decl_cleanup (NULL_TREE, build_clobber_this ());
15466
15467 /* And insert cleanups for our bases and members so that they
15468 will be properly destroyed if we throw. */
15469 push_base_cleanups ();
15470 }
15471}
15472
15473/* At the end of every destructor we generate code to delete the object if
15474 necessary. Do that now. */
15475
15476static void
15477finish_destructor_body (void)
15478{
15479 tree exprstmt;
15480
15481 /* Any return from a destructor will end up here; that way all base
15482 and member cleanups will be run when the function returns. */
15483 add_stmt (build_stmt (input_location, LABEL_EXPR, cdtor_label));
15484
15485 if (targetm.cxx.cdtor_returns_this ())
15486 {
15487 tree val;
15488
15489 val = DECL_ARGUMENTS (current_function_decl);
15490 val = build2 (MODIFY_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (val),
15491 DECL_RESULT (current_function_decl), val);
15492 /* Return the address of the object. */
15493 exprstmt = build_stmt (input_location, RETURN_EXPR, val);
15494 add_stmt (exprstmt);
15495 }
15496}
15497
15498/* Do the necessary processing for the beginning of a function body, which
15499 in this case includes member-initializers, but not the catch clauses of
15500 a function-try-block. Currently, this means opening a binding level
15501 for the member-initializers (in a ctor), member cleanups (in a dtor),
15502 and capture proxies (in a lambda operator()). */
15503
15504tree
15505begin_function_body (void)
15506{
15507 tree stmt;
15508
15509 if (! FUNCTION_NEEDS_BODY_BLOCK (current_function_decl))
15510 return NULL_TREE;
15511
15512 if (processing_template_decl)
15513 /* Do nothing now. */;
15514 else
15515 /* Always keep the BLOCK node associated with the outermost pair of
15516 curly braces of a function. These are needed for correct
15517 operation of dwarfout.c. */
15518 keep_next_level (true);
15519
15520 stmt = begin_compound_stmt (BCS_FN_BODY);
15521
15522 if (processing_template_decl)
15523 /* Do nothing now. */;
15524 else if (DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (current_function_decl))
15525 begin_destructor_body ();
15526
15527 return stmt;
15528}
15529
15530/* Do the processing for the end of a function body. Currently, this means
15531 closing out the cleanups for fully-constructed bases and members, and in
15532 the case of the destructor, deleting the object if desired. Again, this
15533 is only meaningful for [cd]tors, since they are the only functions where
15534 there is a significant distinction between the main body and any
15535 function catch clauses. Handling, say, main() return semantics here
15536 would be wrong, as flowing off the end of a function catch clause for
15537 main() would also need to return 0. */
15538
15539void
15540finish_function_body (tree compstmt)
15541{
15542 if (compstmt == NULL_TREE)
15543 return;
15544
15545 /* Close the block. */
15546 finish_compound_stmt (compstmt);
15547
15548 if (processing_template_decl)
15549 /* Do nothing now. */;
15550 else if (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (current_function_decl))
15551 finish_constructor_body ();
15552 else if (DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (current_function_decl))
15553 finish_destructor_body ();
15554}
15555
15556/* Given a function, returns the BLOCK corresponding to the outermost level
15557 of curly braces, skipping the artificial block created for constructor
15558 initializers. */
15559
15560tree
15561outer_curly_brace_block (tree fndecl)
15562{
15563 tree block = DECL_INITIAL (fndecl);
15564 if (BLOCK_OUTER_CURLY_BRACE_P (block))
15565 return block;
15566 block = BLOCK_SUBBLOCKS (block);
15567 if (BLOCK_OUTER_CURLY_BRACE_P (block))
15568 return block;
15569 block = BLOCK_SUBBLOCKS (block);
15570 gcc_assert (BLOCK_OUTER_CURLY_BRACE_P (block));
15571 return block;
15572}
15573
15574/* If FNDECL is a class's key method, add the class to the list of
15575 keyed classes that should be emitted. */
15576
15577static void
15578record_key_method_defined (tree fndecl)
15579{
15580 if (DECL_NONSTATIC_MEMBER_FUNCTION_P (fndecl)
15581 && DECL_VIRTUAL_P (fndecl)
15582 && !processing_template_decl)
15583 {
15584 tree fnclass = DECL_CONTEXT (fndecl);
15585 if (fndecl == CLASSTYPE_KEY_METHOD (fnclass))
15586 keyed_classes = tree_cons (NULL_TREE, fnclass, keyed_classes);
15587 }
15588}
15589
15590/* Subroutine of finish_function.
15591 Save the body of constexpr functions for possible
15592 future compile time evaluation. */
15593
15594static void
15595maybe_save_function_definition (tree fun)
15596{
15597 if (!processing_template_decl
15598 && DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (fun)
15599 && !cp_function_chain->invalid_constexpr
15600 && !DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (fun))
15601 register_constexpr_fundef (fun, DECL_SAVED_TREE (fun));
15602}
15603
15604/* Finish up a function declaration and compile that function
15605 all the way to assembler language output. The free the storage
15606 for the function definition.
15607
15608 FLAGS is a bitwise or of the following values:
15609 2 - INCLASS_INLINE
15610 We just finished processing the body of an in-class inline
15611 function definition. (This processing will have taken place
15612 after the class definition is complete.) */
15613
15614tree
15615finish_function (int flags)
15616{
15617 tree fndecl = current_function_decl;
15618 tree fntype, ctype = NULL_TREE;
15619 int inclass_inline = (flags & 2) != 0;
15620
15621 /* When we get some parse errors, we can end up without a
15622 current_function_decl, so cope. */
15623 if (fndecl == NULL_TREE)
15624 return error_mark_node;
15625
15626 if (c_dialect_objc ())
15627 objc_finish_function ();
15628
15629 record_key_method_defined (fndecl);
15630
15631 fntype = TREE_TYPE (fndecl);
15632
15633 /* TREE_READONLY (fndecl) = 1;
15634 This caused &foo to be of type ptr-to-const-function
15635 which then got a warning when stored in a ptr-to-function variable. */
15636
15637 gcc_assert (building_stmt_list_p ());
15638 /* The current function is being defined, so its DECL_INITIAL should
15639 be set, and unless there's a multiple definition, it should be
15640 error_mark_node. */
15641 gcc_assert (DECL_INITIAL (fndecl) == error_mark_node);
15642
15643 /* For a cloned function, we've already got all the code we need;
15644 there's no need to add any extra bits. */
15645 if (!DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (fndecl))
15646 {
15647 /* Make it so that `main' always returns 0 by default. */
15648 if (DECL_MAIN_P (current_function_decl))
15649 finish_return_stmt (integer_zero_node);
15650
15651 if (use_eh_spec_block (current_function_decl))
15652 finish_eh_spec_block (TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS
15653 (TREE_TYPE (current_function_decl)),
15654 current_eh_spec_block);
15655 }
15656
15657 /* If we're saving up tree structure, tie off the function now. */
15658 DECL_SAVED_TREE (fndecl) = pop_stmt_list (DECL_SAVED_TREE (fndecl));
15659
15660 if (fn_contains_cilk_spawn_p (cfun) && !processing_template_decl)
15661 cfun->cilk_frame_decl = insert_cilk_frame (fndecl);
15662
15663 finish_fname_decls ();
15664
15665 /* If this function can't throw any exceptions, remember that. */
15666 if (!processing_template_decl
15667 && !cp_function_chain->can_throw
15668 && !flag_non_call_exceptions
15669 && !decl_replaceable_p (fndecl))
15670 TREE_NOTHROW (fndecl) = 1;
15671
15672 /* This must come after expand_function_end because cleanups might
15673 have declarations (from inline functions) that need to go into
15674 this function's blocks. */
15675
15676 /* If the current binding level isn't the outermost binding level
15677 for this function, either there is a bug, or we have experienced
15678 syntax errors and the statement tree is malformed. */
15679 if (current_binding_level->kind != sk_function_parms)
15680 {
15681 /* Make sure we have already experienced errors. */
15682 gcc_assert (errorcount);
15683
15684 /* Throw away the broken statement tree and extra binding
15685 levels. */
15686 DECL_SAVED_TREE (fndecl) = alloc_stmt_list ();
15687
15688 while (current_binding_level->kind != sk_function_parms)
15689 {
15690 if (current_binding_level->kind == sk_class)
15691 pop_nested_class ();
15692 else
15693 poplevel (0, 0, 0);
15694 }
15695 }
15696 poplevel (1, 0, 1);
15697
15698 /* Statements should always be full-expressions at the outermost set
15699 of curly braces for a function. */
15700 gcc_assert (stmts_are_full_exprs_p ());
15701
15702 /* If there are no return statements in a function with auto return type,
15703 the return type is void. But if the declared type is something like
15704 auto*, this is an error. */
15705 if (!processing_template_decl && FNDECL_USED_AUTO (fndecl)
15706 && TREE_TYPE (fntype) == current_function_auto_return_pattern)
15707 {
15708 if (!is_auto (current_function_auto_return_pattern)
15709 && !current_function_returns_value && !current_function_returns_null)
15710 {
15711 error ("no return statements in function returning %qT",
15712 current_function_auto_return_pattern);
15713 inform (input_location, "only plain %<auto%> return type can be "
15714 "deduced to %<void%>");
15715 }
15716 apply_deduced_return_type (fndecl, void_type_node);
15717 fntype = TREE_TYPE (fndecl);
15718 }
15719
15720 // If this is a concept, check that the definition is reasonable.
15721 if (DECL_DECLARED_CONCEPT_P (fndecl))
15722 check_function_concept (fndecl);
15723
15724 /* Lambda closure members are implicitly constexpr if possible. */
15725 if (cxx_dialect >= cxx1z
15726 && LAMBDA_TYPE_P (CP_DECL_CONTEXT (fndecl))
15727 && (processing_template_decl
15728 || is_valid_constexpr_fn (fndecl, /*complain*/false))
15729 && potential_constant_expression (DECL_SAVED_TREE (fndecl)))
15730 DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (fndecl) = true;
15731
15732 /* Save constexpr function body before it gets munged by
15733 the NRV transformation. */
15734 maybe_save_function_definition (fndecl);
15735
15736 /* Invoke the pre-genericize plugin before we start munging things. */
15737 if (!processing_template_decl)
15738 invoke_plugin_callbacks (PLUGIN_PRE_GENERICIZE, fndecl);
15739
15740 /* Perform delayed folding before NRV transformation. */
15741 if (!processing_template_decl)
15742 cp_fold_function (fndecl);
15743
15744 /* Set up the named return value optimization, if we can. Candidate
15745 variables are selected in check_return_expr. */
15746 if (current_function_return_value)
15747 {
15748 tree r = current_function_return_value;
15749 tree outer;
15750
15751 if (r != error_mark_node
15752 /* This is only worth doing for fns that return in memory--and
15753 simpler, since we don't have to worry about promoted modes. */
15754 && aggregate_value_p (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (fndecl)), fndecl)
15755 /* Only allow this for variables declared in the outer scope of
15756 the function so we know that their lifetime always ends with a
15757 return; see g++.dg/opt/nrv6.C. We could be more flexible if
15758 we were to do this optimization in tree-ssa. */
15759 && (outer = outer_curly_brace_block (fndecl))
15760 && chain_member (r, BLOCK_VARS (outer)))
15761 finalize_nrv (&DECL_SAVED_TREE (fndecl), r, DECL_RESULT (fndecl));
15762
15763 current_function_return_value = NULL_TREE;
15764 }
15765
15766 /* Remember that we were in class scope. */
15767 if (current_class_name)
15768 ctype = current_class_type;
15769
15770 /* Must mark the RESULT_DECL as being in this function. */
15771 DECL_CONTEXT (DECL_RESULT (fndecl)) = fndecl;
15772
15773 /* Set the BLOCK_SUPERCONTEXT of the outermost function scope to point
15774 to the FUNCTION_DECL node itself. */
15775 BLOCK_SUPERCONTEXT (DECL_INITIAL (fndecl)) = fndecl;
15776
15777 /* Save away current state, if appropriate. */
15778 if (!processing_template_decl)
15779 save_function_data (fndecl);
15780
15781 /* Complain if there's just no return statement. */
15782 if (warn_return_type
15783 && !VOID_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (fntype))
15784 && !dependent_type_p (TREE_TYPE (fntype))
15785 && !current_function_returns_value && !current_function_returns_null
15786 /* Don't complain if we abort or throw. */
15787 && !current_function_returns_abnormally
15788 /* Don't complain if there's an infinite loop. */
15789 && !current_function_infinite_loop
15790 /* Don't complain if we are declared noreturn. */
15791 && !TREE_THIS_VOLATILE (fndecl)
15792 && !DECL_NAME (DECL_RESULT (fndecl))
15793 && !TREE_NO_WARNING (fndecl)
15794 /* Structor return values (if any) are set by the compiler. */
15795 && !DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (fndecl)
15796 && !DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (fndecl)
15797 && targetm.warn_func_return (fndecl))
15798 {
15799 warning (OPT_Wreturn_type,
15800 "no return statement in function returning non-void");
15801 TREE_NO_WARNING (fndecl) = 1;
15802 }
15803
15804 /* Store the end of the function, so that we get good line number
15805 info for the epilogue. */
15806 cfun->function_end_locus = input_location;
15807
15808 /* Complain about parameters that are only set, but never otherwise used. */
15809 if (warn_unused_but_set_parameter
15810 && !processing_template_decl
15811 && errorcount == unused_but_set_errorcount
15812 && !DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (fndecl))
15813 {
15814 tree decl;
15815
15816 for (decl = DECL_ARGUMENTS (fndecl);
15817 decl;
15818 decl = DECL_CHAIN (decl))
15819 if (TREE_USED (decl)
15820 && TREE_CODE (decl) == PARM_DECL
15821 && !DECL_READ_P (decl)
15822 && DECL_NAME (decl)
15823 && !DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl)
15824 && !TREE_NO_WARNING (decl)
15825 && !DECL_IN_SYSTEM_HEADER (decl)
15826 && TREE_TYPE (decl) != error_mark_node
15827 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (decl)) != REFERENCE_TYPE
15828 && (!CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (decl))
15829 || !TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (TREE_TYPE (decl))))
15830 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
15831 OPT_Wunused_but_set_parameter,
15832 "parameter %qD set but not used", decl);
15833 unused_but_set_errorcount = errorcount;
15834 }
15835
15836 /* Complain about locally defined typedefs that are not used in this
15837 function. */
15838 maybe_warn_unused_local_typedefs ();
15839
15840 /* Possibly warn about unused parameters. */
15841 if (warn_unused_parameter
15842 && !processing_template_decl
15843 && !DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (fndecl))
15844 do_warn_unused_parameter (fndecl);
15845
15846 /* Genericize before inlining. */
15847 if (!processing_template_decl)
15848 {
15849 struct language_function *f = DECL_SAVED_FUNCTION_DATA (fndecl);
15850 cp_genericize (fndecl);
15851 /* Clear out the bits we don't need. */
15852 f->x_current_class_ptr = NULL;
15853 f->x_current_class_ref = NULL;
15854 f->x_eh_spec_block = NULL;
15855 f->x_in_charge_parm = NULL;
15856 f->x_vtt_parm = NULL;
15857 f->x_return_value = NULL;
15858 f->bindings = NULL;
15859 f->extern_decl_map = NULL;
15860 f->infinite_loops = NULL;
15861 }
15862 /* Clear out the bits we don't need. */
15863 local_names = NULL;
15864
15865 /* We're leaving the context of this function, so zap cfun. It's still in
15866 DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION, and we'll restore it in tree_rest_of_compilation. */
15867 set_cfun (NULL);
15868 current_function_decl = NULL;
15869
15870 /* If this is an in-class inline definition, we may have to pop the
15871 bindings for the template parameters that we added in
15872 maybe_begin_member_template_processing when start_function was
15873 called. */
15874 if (inclass_inline)
15875 maybe_end_member_template_processing ();
15876
15877 /* Leave the scope of the class. */
15878 if (ctype)
15879 pop_nested_class ();
15880
15881 --function_depth;
15882
15883 /* Clean up. */
15884 current_function_decl = NULL_TREE;
15885
15886 invoke_plugin_callbacks (PLUGIN_FINISH_PARSE_FUNCTION, fndecl);
15887 return fndecl;
15888}
15889
15890/* Create the FUNCTION_DECL for a function definition.
15891 DECLSPECS and DECLARATOR are the parts of the declaration;
15892 they describe the return type and the name of the function,
15893 but twisted together in a fashion that parallels the syntax of C.
15894
15895 This function creates a binding context for the function body
15896 as well as setting up the FUNCTION_DECL in current_function_decl.
15897
15898 Returns a FUNCTION_DECL on success.
15899
15900 If the DECLARATOR is not suitable for a function (it defines a datum
15901 instead), we return 0, which tells yyparse to report a parse error.
15902
15903 May return void_type_node indicating that this method is actually
15904 a friend. See grokfield for more details.
15905
15906 Came here with a `.pushlevel' .
15907
15908 DO NOT MAKE ANY CHANGES TO THIS CODE WITHOUT MAKING CORRESPONDING
15909 CHANGES TO CODE IN `grokfield'. */
15910
15911tree
15912grokmethod (cp_decl_specifier_seq *declspecs,
15913 const cp_declarator *declarator, tree attrlist)
15914{
15915 tree fndecl = grokdeclarator (declarator, declspecs, MEMFUNCDEF, 0,
15916 &attrlist);
15917
15918 if (fndecl == error_mark_node)
15919 return error_mark_node;
15920
15921 if (fndecl == NULL || TREE_CODE (fndecl) != FUNCTION_DECL)
15922 {
15923 error ("invalid member function declaration");
15924 return error_mark_node;
15925 }
15926
15927 if (attrlist)
15928 cplus_decl_attributes (&fndecl, attrlist, 0);
15929
15930 /* Pass friends other than inline friend functions back. */
15931 if (fndecl == void_type_node)
15932 return fndecl;
15933
15934 if (DECL_IN_AGGR_P (fndecl))
15935 {
15936 if (DECL_CLASS_SCOPE_P (fndecl))
15937 error ("%qD is already defined in class %qT", fndecl,
15938 DECL_CONTEXT (fndecl));
15939 return error_mark_node;
15940 }
15941
15942 check_template_shadow (fndecl);
15943
15944 if (TREE_PUBLIC (fndecl))
15945 DECL_COMDAT (fndecl) = 1;
15946 DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (fndecl) = 1;
15947 DECL_NO_INLINE_WARNING_P (fndecl) = 1;
15948
15949 /* We process method specializations in finish_struct_1. */
15950 if (processing_template_decl && !DECL_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION (fndecl))
15951 {
15952 fndecl = push_template_decl (fndecl);
15953 if (fndecl == error_mark_node)
15954 return fndecl;
15955 }
15956
15957 if (! DECL_FRIEND_P (fndecl))
15958 {
15959 if (DECL_CHAIN (fndecl))
15960 {
15961 fndecl = copy_node (fndecl);
15962 TREE_CHAIN (fndecl) = NULL_TREE;
15963 }
15964 }
15965
15966 cp_finish_decl (fndecl, NULL_TREE, false, NULL_TREE, 0);
15967
15968 DECL_IN_AGGR_P (fndecl) = 1;
15969 return fndecl;
15970}
15971
15972
15973/* VAR is a VAR_DECL. If its type is incomplete, remember VAR so that
15974 we can lay it out later, when and if its type becomes complete.
15975
15976 Also handle constexpr variables where the initializer involves
15977 an unlowered PTRMEM_CST because the class isn't complete yet. */
15978
15979void
15980maybe_register_incomplete_var (tree var)
15981{
15982 gcc_assert (VAR_P (var));
15983
15984 /* Keep track of variables with incomplete types. */
15985 if (!processing_template_decl && TREE_TYPE (var) != error_mark_node
15986 && DECL_EXTERNAL (var))
15987 {
15988 tree inner_type = TREE_TYPE (var);
15989
15990 while (TREE_CODE (inner_type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
15991 inner_type = TREE_TYPE (inner_type);
15992 inner_type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (inner_type);
15993
15994 if ((!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (inner_type) && CLASS_TYPE_P (inner_type))
15995 /* RTTI TD entries are created while defining the type_info. */
15996 || (TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (inner_type)
15997 && TYPE_BEING_DEFINED (inner_type)))
15998 {
15999 incomplete_var iv = {var, inner_type};
16000 vec_safe_push (incomplete_vars, iv);
16001 }
16002 else if (!(DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (var) && DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (var))
16003 && decl_constant_var_p (var)
16004 && (TYPE_PTRMEM_P (inner_type) || CLASS_TYPE_P (inner_type)))
16005 {
16006 /* When the outermost open class is complete we can resolve any
16007 pointers-to-members. */
16008 tree context = outermost_open_class ();
16009 incomplete_var iv = {var, context};
16010 vec_safe_push (incomplete_vars, iv);
16011 }
16012 }
16013}
16014
16015/* Called when a class type (given by TYPE) is defined. If there are
16016 any existing VAR_DECLs whose type has been completed by this
16017 declaration, update them now. */
16018
16019void
16020complete_vars (tree type)
16021{
16022 unsigned ix;
16023 incomplete_var *iv;
16024
16025 for (ix = 0; vec_safe_iterate (incomplete_vars, ix, &iv); )
16026 {
16027 if (same_type_p (type, iv->incomplete_type))
16028 {
16029 tree var = iv->decl;
16030 tree type = TREE_TYPE (var);
16031
16032 if (type != error_mark_node
16033 && (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (strip_array_types (type))
16034 == iv->incomplete_type))
16035 {
16036 /* Complete the type of the variable. The VAR_DECL itself
16037 will be laid out in expand_expr. */
16038 complete_type (type);
16039 cp_apply_type_quals_to_decl (cp_type_quals (type), var);
16040 }
16041
16042 /* Remove this entry from the list. */
16043 incomplete_vars->unordered_remove (ix);
16044 }
16045 else
16046 ix++;
16047 }
16048
16049 /* Check for pending declarations which may have abstract type. */
16050 complete_type_check_abstract (type);
16051}
16052
16053/* If DECL is of a type which needs a cleanup, build and return an
16054 expression to perform that cleanup here. Return NULL_TREE if no
16055 cleanup need be done. DECL can also be a _REF when called from
16056 split_nonconstant_init_1. */
16057
16058tree
16059cxx_maybe_build_cleanup (tree decl, tsubst_flags_t complain)
16060{
16061 tree type;
16062 tree attr;
16063 tree cleanup;
16064
16065 /* Assume no cleanup is required. */
16066 cleanup = NULL_TREE;
16067
16068 if (error_operand_p (decl))
16069 return cleanup;
16070
16071 /* Handle "__attribute__((cleanup))". We run the cleanup function
16072 before the destructor since the destructor is what actually
16073 terminates the lifetime of the object. */
16074 if (DECL_P (decl))
16075 attr = lookup_attribute ("cleanup", DECL_ATTRIBUTES (decl));
16076 else
16077 attr = NULL_TREE;
16078 if (attr)
16079 {
16080 tree id;
16081 tree fn;
16082 tree arg;
16083
16084 /* Get the name specified by the user for the cleanup function. */
16085 id = TREE_VALUE (TREE_VALUE (attr));
16086 /* Look up the name to find the cleanup function to call. It is
16087 important to use lookup_name here because that is what is
16088 used in c-common.c:handle_cleanup_attribute when performing
16089 initial checks on the attribute. Note that those checks
16090 include ensuring that the function found is not an overloaded
16091 function, or an object with an overloaded call operator,
16092 etc.; we can rely on the fact that the function found is an
16093 ordinary FUNCTION_DECL. */
16094 fn = lookup_name (id);
16095 arg = build_address (decl);
16096 if (!mark_used (decl, complain) && !(complain & tf_error))
16097 return error_mark_node;
16098 cleanup = cp_build_function_call_nary (fn, complain, arg, NULL_TREE);
16099 if (cleanup == error_mark_node)
16100 return error_mark_node;
16101 }
16102 /* Handle ordinary C++ destructors. */
16103 type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
16104 if (type_build_dtor_call (type))
16105 {
16106 int flags = LOOKUP_NORMAL|LOOKUP_NONVIRTUAL|LOOKUP_DESTRUCTOR;
16107 tree addr;
16108 tree call;
16109
16110 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
16111 addr = decl;
16112 else
16113 addr = build_address (decl);
16114
16115 call = build_delete (TREE_TYPE (addr), addr,
16116 sfk_complete_destructor, flags, 0, complain);
16117 if (call == error_mark_node)
16118 cleanup = error_mark_node;
16119 else if (TYPE_HAS_TRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (type))
16120 /* Discard the call. */;
16121 else if (cleanup)
16122 cleanup = cp_build_compound_expr (cleanup, call, complain);
16123 else
16124 cleanup = call;
16125 }
16126
16127 /* build_delete sets the location of the destructor call to the
16128 current location, even though the destructor is going to be
16129 called later, at the end of the current scope. This can lead to
16130 a "jumpy" behavior for users of debuggers when they step around
16131 the end of the block. So let's unset the location of the
16132 destructor call instead. */
16133 protected_set_expr_location (cleanup, UNKNOWN_LOCATION);
16134
16135 if (cleanup
16136 && DECL_P (decl)
16137 && !lookup_attribute ("warn_unused", TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
16138 /* Treat objects with destructors as used; the destructor may do
16139 something substantive. */
16140 && !mark_used (decl, complain) && !(complain & tf_error))
16141 return error_mark_node;
16142
16143 return cleanup;
16144}
16145
16146
16147/* Return the FUNCTION_TYPE that corresponds to MEMFNTYPE, which can be a
16148 FUNCTION_DECL, METHOD_TYPE, FUNCTION_TYPE, pointer or reference to
16149 METHOD_TYPE or FUNCTION_TYPE, or pointer to member function. */
16150
16151tree
16152static_fn_type (tree memfntype)
16153{
16154 tree fntype;
16155 tree args;
16156
16157 if (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (memfntype))
16158 memfntype = TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FN_TYPE (memfntype);
16159 if (POINTER_TYPE_P (memfntype)
16160 || TREE_CODE (memfntype) == FUNCTION_DECL)
16161 memfntype = TREE_TYPE (memfntype);
16162 if (TREE_CODE (memfntype) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
16163 return memfntype;
16164 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (memfntype) == METHOD_TYPE);
16165 args = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (memfntype);
16166 cp_ref_qualifier rqual = type_memfn_rqual (memfntype);
16167 fntype = build_function_type (TREE_TYPE (memfntype), TREE_CHAIN (args));
16168 fntype = apply_memfn_quals (fntype, type_memfn_quals (memfntype), rqual);
16169 fntype = (cp_build_type_attribute_variant
16170 (fntype, TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (memfntype)));
16171 fntype = (build_exception_variant
16172 (fntype, TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (memfntype)));
16173 if (TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE (memfntype))
16174 TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE (fntype) = 1;
16175 return fntype;
16176}
16177
16178/* DECL was originally constructed as a non-static member function,
16179 but turned out to be static. Update it accordingly. */
16180
16181void
16182revert_static_member_fn (tree decl)
16183{
16184 tree stype = static_fn_type (decl);
16185 cp_cv_quals quals = type_memfn_quals (stype);
16186 cp_ref_qualifier rqual = type_memfn_rqual (stype);
16187
16188 if (quals != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED || rqual != REF_QUAL_NONE)
16189 stype = apply_memfn_quals (stype, TYPE_UNQUALIFIED, REF_QUAL_NONE);
16190
16191 TREE_TYPE (decl) = stype;
16192
16193 if (DECL_ARGUMENTS (decl))
16194 DECL_ARGUMENTS (decl) = DECL_CHAIN (DECL_ARGUMENTS (decl));
16195 DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (decl) = 1;
16196}
16197
16198/* Return which tree structure is used by T, or TS_CP_GENERIC if T is
16199 one of the language-independent trees. */
16200
16201enum cp_tree_node_structure_enum
16202cp_tree_node_structure (union lang_tree_node * t)
16203{
16204 switch (TREE_CODE (&t->generic))
16205 {
16206 case DEFAULT_ARG: return TS_CP_DEFAULT_ARG;
16207 case DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT: return TS_CP_DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT;
16208 case IDENTIFIER_NODE: return TS_CP_IDENTIFIER;
16209 case OVERLOAD: return TS_CP_OVERLOAD;
16210 case TEMPLATE_PARM_INDEX: return TS_CP_TPI;
16211 case PTRMEM_CST: return TS_CP_PTRMEM;
16212 case BASELINK: return TS_CP_BASELINK;
16213 case TEMPLATE_DECL: return TS_CP_TEMPLATE_DECL;
16214 case STATIC_ASSERT: return TS_CP_STATIC_ASSERT;
16215 case ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT: return TS_CP_ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT;
16216 case TRAIT_EXPR: return TS_CP_TRAIT_EXPR;
16217 case LAMBDA_EXPR: return TS_CP_LAMBDA_EXPR;
16218 case TEMPLATE_INFO: return TS_CP_TEMPLATE_INFO;
16219 case CONSTRAINT_INFO: return TS_CP_CONSTRAINT_INFO;
16220 case USERDEF_LITERAL: return TS_CP_USERDEF_LITERAL;
16221 default: return TS_CP_GENERIC;
16222 }
16223}
16224
16225/* Build the void_list_node (void_type_node having been created). */
16226tree
16227build_void_list_node (void)
16228{
16229 tree t = build_tree_list (NULL_TREE, void_type_node);
16230 return t;
16231}
16232
16233bool
16234cp_missing_noreturn_ok_p (tree decl)
16235{
16236 /* A missing noreturn is ok for the `main' function. */
16237 return DECL_MAIN_P (decl);
16238}
16239
16240/* Return the decl used to identify the COMDAT group into which DECL should
16241 be placed. */
16242
16243tree
16244cxx_comdat_group (tree decl)
16245{
16246 /* Virtual tables, construction virtual tables, and virtual table
16247 tables all go in a single COMDAT group, named after the primary
16248 virtual table. */
16249 if (VAR_P (decl) && DECL_VTABLE_OR_VTT_P (decl))
16250 decl = CLASSTYPE_VTABLES (DECL_CONTEXT (decl));
16251 /* For all other DECLs, the COMDAT group is the mangled name of the
16252 declaration itself. */
16253 else
16254 {
16255 while (DECL_THUNK_P (decl))
16256 {
16257 /* If TARGET_USE_LOCAL_THUNK_ALIAS_P, use_thunk puts the thunk
16258 into the same section as the target function. In that case
16259 we must return target's name. */
16260 tree target = THUNK_TARGET (decl);
16261 if (TARGET_USE_LOCAL_THUNK_ALIAS_P (target)
16262 && DECL_SECTION_NAME (target) != NULL
16263 && DECL_ONE_ONLY (target))
16264 decl = target;
16265 else
16266 break;
16267 }
16268 }
16269
16270 return decl;
16271}
16272
16273/* Returns the return type for FN as written by the user, which may include
16274 a placeholder for a deduced return type. */
16275
16276tree
16277fndecl_declared_return_type (tree fn)
16278{
16279 fn = STRIP_TEMPLATE (fn);
16280 if (FNDECL_USED_AUTO (fn))
16281 {
16282 struct language_function *f = NULL;
16283 if (DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (fn))
16284 f = DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (fn)->language;
16285 if (f == NULL)
16286 f = DECL_SAVED_FUNCTION_DATA (fn);
16287 return f->x_auto_return_pattern;
16288 }
16289 return TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (fn));
16290}
16291
16292/* Returns true iff DECL was declared with an auto type and it has
16293 not yet been deduced to a real type. */
16294
16295bool
16296undeduced_auto_decl (tree decl)
16297{
16298 if (cxx_dialect < cxx11)
16299 return false;
16300 return type_uses_auto (TREE_TYPE (decl));
16301}
16302
16303/* Complain if DECL has an undeduced return type. */
16304
16305bool
16306require_deduced_type (tree decl, tsubst_flags_t complain)
16307{
16308 if (undeduced_auto_decl (decl))
16309 {
16310 if (complain & tf_error)
16311 error ("use of %qD before deduction of %<auto%>", decl);
16312 return false;
16313 }
16314 return true;
16315}
